Content: Do you like eating your burgers in the dark If so DMK is the place for you Kidding set aside I had an absolutely enjoyable time at DMK on my visit to Chicago The service was spectacular we were seated right away and the food came out so quickly and accurately The seating was very cozymeaning getting in and out of your seat was a little awkward as you were basically on top of the people next to you So maybe if you have personal space issues you might want to request a table away from the perimeter of the restaurant The 1000 reviews earning this a solid 4star restaurant is not a glitch my friends It is well deserved Their menu is simple and approachable I went with the 4 it included green chile fried farm egg and bacon K ordered the 3 which included pastrami french gruyere sauerkraut and remoulade Holy crap those burgers were delish We split an order of sweet potato fries and a chocolatevanilla shake and we were definitely satisfied DMK has an upscalefeel to it without the pretentiousness youd expect from a place with lowlighting sorry to keep mentioning it but it was so dark in there not a bad thing The service as topnotch and they got us in and out of there in under 45 minutes without feeling like we were getting brushed off I prefer my cheeseburgers full and unsmashed but I didnt have a problem with DMKs style It was just a very very good meal Im glad my research lead me to DMK it was definitely worth itDMK is great It involved all my favorite things burgers and wonderful design Props to the people responsible for the branding and merchandising Great experience overall

Author: Jeremy B.
Content: Amazing burgers  Best in the city possibly  Great beer selection and craft cocktails  The service here is always top notch as well  Be prepared to wait  Im not a big fan of long waits for places so a tip is to go during off hours such as early or mid afternoon on a weekend

Author: Michelle K.
Content: Im always on the hunt for a great burger and I am so glad that I finally got to come to DMK to get one The service was greatour server was attentive and friendly but not overbearing The atmosphere was relaxed definitely a place I would come back with my friends for burgers and drinks But probably not one where Id bring my parents obviously Then again I took my parents to The Publican so who knowsAs for the food it was so great My mouth is watering thinking about the burgers I got the 5 burger and my friend got the buffalo burger with blueberry bbq sauce I usually dont like my patties grilled and pressed down diner style but for some reason the burgers were so great that way here The flavors all went together very nicely I especially liked the way the blueberry flavor came outsweet and a little tartinn the buffalo burger I honestly cant even put my finger on what about the 5 burger was so great but it was like a little piece of heaven on a plateWe also got the truffle parmesan fries but I could go without this the next time The cheese wasnt too flavorful and was crusted onto the fries in a not melty way and the truffle mayo was pretty underwhelming BUT the burgers The burgers make up for it

Author: Marcus H.
Content: Came here on a Saturday night There was a bit of a wait but it was well worth it IMO Our server Marie did a great job taking care of us Great beer selection Definitely coming back

Author: Food Junkie S.
Content: Nothing to complain about All their burgers are very good They arent so big that you cant get a good grip or bite of Very flavorful The fries are also very good Their beer selection alone would keep me coming Their service is on target Most importantly their food is always consistent Probably one of my favorite burger joints

Author: Michael H.
Content: Delicious meat freshlybaked bread and creative toppings make for a great burger experience  They also have an excellent beer selection that includes Half Acre and a rotating selection of specialty drafts  Decent cocktails are available 710  Service is fast and friendly  I recommend getting the burger with blue cheese and crispy onion ringsThe place gets packed so you may want to consider going during an off time

Author: Desmond W.
Content: Been here many times before going here later on this beautiful day so I figured it was time to write a review  Not much to say about this lovely burger establishment than what has already been said here  Ill try to add some nice nuggetsThey have days during the week where food is discounted due to being in the industry  This includes medical professionals who show up in scrubs since Illinois Masonic Hospital is just down the road FYI  you do not have to work at Illinois Masonic to get the discount at least dont admit itThey are always running some kind of charity drive changing the benefactor monthtomonth which is pretty awesome that they have such a dedication to philanthropyThe burgers are excellent  They arent huge if you want something like that go wait for 2 hours at Kumas Korner  They are sliderstyle patties with grassfed beef on a delicious housemade potato bun  All the fries are delicious but the sweet potato fries are especially good  Ive tried most of the burgers on the menu and I cant say Ive been disappointed yetTerrific beer and liquor selection  Most importantly  eat at the bar and you will usually walk out with business cards of the bartender who served you inviting you back for a free draft beer with your next meal  So since my wife doesnt drink beer that basically means 2 free beers for me every time we return  Pure awesomeSometimes theres a bit of a wait all the more reason to try to snag seats at the bar  Otherwise the servers are very good and often times bring out some free food for you to sample when the restaurant is a little slower

Author: Anna L.
Content: Terrible disappointment We went after reading the reviews for out of this world delicious bison burger with blueberry BBQ From the second they brought it out and put it on the table I knew it would be terrible The bun was twice the thickness of the meat there was no medium rare about it that thing was very well done I could not really tell how it tasted it was a mess of over peppered over salted something The bun was like a tasteless marshmallow I didnt even eat it After picking at the meat I moved in to try the Parmesan fries They were cold not slightly warmish even cold The cheese just sat on top of them would not melt even a little bit There was so much black pepper in the fries I could taste absolutely nothing but pepper The only reason I am giving two stars is the service which was friendly

Author: Hilary T.
Content: Pretty good burger spot The turkey burger is amazing Best turkey burger Ive had in a while The Wisconsin cheddar fries are good as well A bit pricey though

Author: M Y.
Content: I forgot how good this place is Was there over the weekend and reminded how uberfabulous the food is BURGERS FRIES MILK SHAKES BEER DRINKS SALADS Will please EVERYONE Dreaming of my next visit nowI have to add that this is the place to be for some serious EYE CANDY  the waitersbartenders HOLY SHUCKS Not only that but they are SO NICE explaining every special on the menu with the most adorable smiles and coming to check in with us several timesThe food is amazing but along with the good looking and super nice staff  this place beats any other burger joints in the city

Author: A.J. S.
Content: Zagat One of the BEST BURGERS in Chicagoland Me EhhhFriend BEST BURGER EVARRR Me Ehhh you still enjoy McDoublesYelp AWESOME BURGER NOM NOM BEER GO NOW Me OKAY I rallied the troops here on a Saturday night and was thrilled they had only a 20 minute wait for a table and quick bar service while we waited Smalls Gin was found here cheap and fabulous as usual microdistilled gin makes a great start to any night I would caps lock cheap because it deserves emphasis but Yelp told me my Shouting Quota has been used up early in the review already After our juniper berry enhanced aperitifs at the bar we got a seat and checked out the menu with our server the most patient and friendly woman ever to grace our table at DMK Even after a lovely one in our party demanded to know what each beer on the beer page tasted like she was a troopers and gave great recommendations Bless her heart its these people that makes good tips feel extra wonderfulA word on the beer list I would like to continue the theme of inexpensive Im real jealous of your MidWest booze prices yall On the West Coast we happy give our left nut for a good craft beer on tap DMK offered a page full of awesome selections for great prices Really shockingly low prices alongside their alcohol selection I dont know if its a Chicago thing or a DMK thing but I like it a lot Back to the burger The burger patty was a bit thinner than I expected thinner than Kumas and Butcher and the Burger but a soft baked bun better than I ever thought imaginable You can get your burger with lots of fancy shit like chiles and fried egg and fancinesses yeah clearly after all those cheap beers  I cant remember much else of the menu but whatever you choose it will be delicious The sides are great to split and I had a hard time keeping my hands out of the fried onions and sweet potatoes sides we split Incredible My burger itself was juicy perfectly cooked and flavorful the bun wonderfully soft and the toppings fresh In my Butcher and the Burger review I tried to compare it to DMK and I couldnt I enjoyed DMKs loud scene and great beer list but the burgers themselves were too different BB you make your own a la carte style and Im not as creative as DMK Regardless DMK is a must try on your Chicago burger hunt

Author: Jessica V.
Content: Hello BeautifulI am not a burger girl but if you get some drinks in me I could be that girl Let me rephrase that if you gimme craft beer I could be that girl and they have a ton of craft beer If you come here for a burger great if you come here for beer even betterI am simple when it comes to burger because when you get crazy you might end up with some stranger danger in your mouth I chose to get a regular burger and splurge with okra and pickles and some truffle fries cause THATS HOW I DO All the plates are small reason being they want to ONE make you feel like you are doing some sort of portion control or TWO they want you to eat after you drink Eating sounds legit to me so I am going with the latter I may have not written too many reviews in the past couple weeks but when it comes to eating I am too legit to quit

Author: Ryan E.
Content: Great beer selection Great burgers Cool atmosphere DMK Burger Bar is awesome

Author: Joel G.
Content: I have seen mixed reviews on this place however I think its a really solid hamburger joint  Great beer selection burgers are very good great fries and rings  Im not sure whats not to like about this place  I like the atmosphere as well does get a bit loud but for a burger joint I think its just right  Love the bison and blueberry burger and the BBQ is excellent as well  Id skip the mac and cheese but man it never fails I have to try it every where I go and am constantly let down  I have been here several times and will continue to go thereTip hit this place for dinner and have a few beers then head over to the bar Headquarters for a even better micro brew selection and video game bar thats pretty darn fun but as of late too crowded

Author: Brady M.
Content: We walked in to a 45 min wait for 2 but we sat at the bar quick Two older woman sat at the bar and were not eating and still waiting for a table is only the real complaint Other then that  the bartender was great server as well as amazing burgers They came out fast and fresh The fries were awesome and to top off the meal the shake of the month will def go back again

Author: EL S.
Content: Mediocre burger fries however were very good Not good bang for the buck and you can go elsewhere for a better burger experience Rowdy bar with tons of suburbanites

Author: Andrew P.
Content: Simple menu  burgers fries beer andor milkshakes Burgers are 9 Burgers are OK fries are OK Biggest value here is the ambiance if you want a cool place to hang out music thumping beautiful servers long wait time then go here

Author: Deena H.
Content: The fried okra and dill Pickles were decent The bison burger was ordered by my buddy and he said it was great The Greek lamb burger was really juicy and you could taste the olives The sweet potato fries were average This place is always crowded and service is with a smile

Author: Cj J.
Content: There is hype for a reason Great atmosphere and amazing food There was a few bumps in the road with service and them forgetting things or taking forever bit this time around the food and company made up for it I would come again

Author: Jeff S.
Content: So the food was fantastic service was great so 5 stars for thatBut the loud musicMinus one star  I felt like I was in a nightclub My friend and I couldnt hear anything the other said and my throat was hoarse by the time we left because I was screaming over the music the whole time We also had to use flashlight apps on our phones to read the menu because it was so dark But aside from the loudest music Ive ever heard and the dimmest lighting Ive ever seen I will be back

Author: Alana T.
Content: Look dont fight me on this shit Get the 10 its a turkey burger Dont change shit on it Add a fried egg make sure its nice and runny Eat it Enjoy it Get the sweet potatoe spuds Get extra sauce DIP consume GLUTTONIZE yourselfGet the CHOCOLATE SHAKE INHALE IT Get a damn brain freeze Leave this place Send me a message on Yelp thanking me Youre welcome in advance THIS PLACE IS SWOOONTASTIC

Author: Eric T.
Content: I loved the veggie burger I appreciate when burger places do not just serve a generic boca burger or some other frozen thing Veggie burgers can be amazing The multitude of burger options is just great On my second trip within 4 days of my first I had the crispy portabella which was also really great So fear not vegetarians the DMK has you covered and WITH CHOICES DMK really crushes it with the fries Sweet potato truffle parmesan and the ones with melted cheddar were all amazing The large size portions are HUGE we had two for a group of 4 and it was a lot The second trip we did two small portions for two people and it was probably about right I would say in a group of 4 to get 34 small servings for the varietyI am a lover of fried pickles so I jumped on the chance to eat some here They were good not great and come with fried okra which I am not so much a fan of but generally tasty Finally the beer A great selection of craft beers on tap DMK is the local burger place I wish was in my neighborhood

Author: Justin G.
Content: Been here twice and absolutely no complaints First the atmosphere some decent music not too loud  great selection of beers and cocktails  so if you are waiting for a table you can hang out at the bar Huge selection of burgers and would be really surprised if you couldnt find something to match your taste I went with the number 6  chorizo burger with avocado and some chipotle mayo highly recommend this if you like a little kick The bun is nice and soft as well Their hand cut fries are a big plus good to compliment your burger too Waiterswaitressesbar tenders are all friendly and nice which always make it more enjoyable If you are looking for a good burger place not looking to wait hours and have some good service give this place a shot

Author: Amber S.
Content: My possibly new favorite place for a burger I ordered a number 6 the guacamole and chorizo burger a lemonblueberry pop and our table ordered bacon blue fries and parmesantruffle fries to split I loved my burger I wasnt expecting it to be spicymost places with spicy foods arent spicy I wasnt expecting my pop to be orange since it was blueberry but it was good although I do need to try it again to see how much I truly enjoyed it  I loved the fries The bacon and bleu cheese fries were the best The sauce was creamy but not heavy and the fries were perfect The parmesantruffle fries on the other hand werent the best Only due to the fact that the cheese was hardened together and you couldnt taste the cheese with the truffle dip and the fries I also liked the music and the atmosphere Every song had me dancing in my chair Overall great place and I will make sure to visit again

Author: Dan S.
Content: Trendy Burger Joint where the Fries Steal the ShowThe inside had a very cool vibe with rock music playing over the speakers  Long tables lined the walls with plenty of booth and stool seatingLet me preface this with the fact that the burger was very good and beats many burgers  However what was billed as the star of the meal was fairly underwhelming  The burger itself was tasty but not cooked to my desired preparation and was small for the price  They also go extremely light on the toppings at least on my burger which left me wanting for moreThe true shining star of the menu was the french fries  They have several different types and they are AhMehZang  If you are going to skip the fries you might as well just not even botherThe beer list consisted entirely of craft beer with a wide selection available  They bring a glass and will offer a pairing for the burger you choose if you get the right serverMy MealBison burger with blueberry barbecue sauce and pickled onionsParmesan fries with truffle cream A Must HaveAmish blue cheese and smoked bacon fries A MUST MUST MUST HAVE

Author: Andrew B.
Content: Great Burgers and FriesIve tried most of the burgers including the beef bison lamb veggie and crispy portobello burgers  All were delicious and uniqueThe fries themselves are average but the toppings make them into real junkfoody goodness that fries should beYou wont find heinz or hidden valley here they only serve their inhouse chipotle ketchup and herb ranch  Sometimes I think all a burger and fries need is regular ketchup so sometimes this disappoints meVery often my table is served a free side of onion straws or sweet potato fries  Not sure if this is because they like us or they just had extras but its always a pleasant surpriseAnd the cocktails try them  Never been disappointed

Author: Chelsea E.
Content: Always consistent Always delicious Always great service Always keeps me wanting to come back for more Thank you DMK thank you

Author: Jeff P.
Content: Bison Burger Truffle Fries enough said

Author: Jackie G.
Content: 1079 4 star reviews its gotta be good right  No not at all  I ordered the patty melt and my boyfriend ordered the 1 burger with cheddar bacon and BBQ sauce I was shocked to see how extremely dry the burgers were  The parmesan fries were just ok I didnt finish my burger because I didnt feel it was worth the calories  Smash burger or even sad to say Steak n Shake is betterActually we left and went next door to the Fish Bar which was 100 times better  My recommendation is I would skip DMK and hit up the Fish Bar next door

Author: Jordan M.
Content: First the good the burgers here are juicy and well constructed  Standouts include The Big DMK basically an upscale Big Mac and the Fresh Salmon burger see Diners Driveins and Dives for more on this one  Your best bet for sides are either the chilirubbed onion strings or the sweet potato fries  The staff is friendly the beer list is great and the prices are okayNow the bad if you want to call it that You cant help but compare this place to Kumas especially now that Kumas Too has moved into the neighborhood  Kumas has a much wider and more creative selection larger patties and better sides  The Wisconsin cheddar and scallion fries at DMK are far too heavy and at times the wait here is nearly as long as it is at KumasIf Kumas didnt exist this review would be far more positive than the 5050 treatment I just gave it but the reality of the situation is that Kumas is legendary and DMK is just very good  Hit this place up so that you can say youve been there before but understand theres nothing they do better than Kumas

Author: Cheryl B.
Content: Another 5 star review for this place Been here a dozen times never a bad experience One of my favorite goto burger places in the city I bring all my out of town friends here they all love it I love that their burgers are juicy and thin and the buns are homemade Lots of unique toppings my favorite is anything with cheese  friend onions on it My husband loves the 4 with green chilies pepperjack cheese  fried egg The french fries are awesome all of them really  Wisconsin cheddar blue cheese truffle sweet potato etc They have a great beer selection  the bloody marys are also top notchMy ONLY complaint is sometimes there is a huge wait not their fault My other complaint is usually the music is way too loud So not a place to have a lunch meeting unfortunately

Author: Sean m.
Content: So I saw this place on DDD Diners DriverThrus and Dives a few weeks prior to my trip to Chicago  I was so excited about finding this place  We tried the Turkey Burger and the Bison Burger  Also had the small truffle fries and a Blood Meridian drink  The drink was very good  The fries were okay something they highlighted on DDDthey made them sound much better  If you want to share the fries get the bigger sizethe small serves one  The burgers were okaypatties were VERY thin  The Bison Burger was mediocre in my opinion   Wish I had a better experience  Kudos to the restaurant for their 365 days of giving which supports a different charity every month

Author: Zach O.
Content: My first yelp review You cant go wrong here Fantastic service a smooth old fashioned unreal burger and their fries speak for themselves I always go with a 8

Author: Lafe S.
Content: This is an emotional reviewWe tried to eat here and were unsuccessful  Being a holiday and closed is understandable  What is notnot taking the time to communicate that to their customer they were going to be closedBeing from out of town DMK was a recommendation  We had to plan and make it a point to visit  Under my normal reviewing habits I would not waste my time to review  Since we are from out of town I have to write because we cannot vote with our dollarsThe number one undisputed rule for the service industry is to always have your customer at top of mind  Long story short is they do NOTSo I have ask myself  what else are they doing without the customer on their mind

Author: Cheryl D.
Content: Hubby took me here for date nite on Wednesday  The place was dimly lit with a lively crowd Good selection of beers and an interesting menu comprised of unique burgers can get turkey burgers or portobello as a sub if desired shakes fries sides etc Our server was Jack  he was very good and even sent us an order of fried pickles gratis Food was great and would definitely go back Next time well share small fries instead of large

Author: Dana Z.
Content: My favorite burger place and its because of the buns  The proportion of meat to bread to ingredients is perfect for my liking and the buns are super duper soft Its relatively small but its worth the wait Service was friendly Good beer selection Fun place

Author: Stephanie C.
Content: Guys signature on the wall This Triple D spot is a must try  The fries and burgers are all amazing  We had the lamb burger and truffle fries  Great atmosphere along with craft cocktails and great beer selection  Cant wait to go back

Author: Anna E.
Content: Unfortunately I was a little hungover so I am disappointed that I didnt try something a little more creative  I went with the lamb burger which had feta and tzatziki and it was pretty tasty  The patty was well seasoned and juicy the bun was soft and held up well with the toppings  However if youre expecting a super thick juicy oozy burger like you get at a lot of places these are on the small size which lends itself to being just a tad on the overcooked side  We also tried the truffle fries sweet potato fries and mac n cheese all which were very good  But I think the favorite at the table was the sweet potato fries  Only downside was how loud it was and we were there fairly early 600ish on a Saturday

Author: Johanna G.
Content: These mofos know how to put together a burger  I never ever ever ever ever get a fried egg on my burgers  I dont know why I just dont  I like burgers the way they are but I figured hey youre in a different state why not give it a go and man worth it  I had a burger with jalapeno cheese and a fried egg on top  I cant remember what the name was but it was effn good  Effn good  And their mac and cheese was fantastic  maybe because Im going through withdrawals on the mac and cheese front maybe not but it was good  The fries were good and crunchy and not greasy  I like that they didnt have an overwhelmingly large bun or hunk of meat you could really get into your burgerand you left full but not holy crap i think im going to puke fatthe service however was not that great  I could understand our wait if the place was mobbed but we got there in off hours  I think our waitress was training someone but generally you dont want to train someone to ignore their tablesespecially when they only have two

Author: Jim B.
Content: Great burgers and good beer selectionfries with the different saucestoppings are awesome

Author: Caitie E.
Content: I love DMK I think theyre my favorite burger place in the city mind you I enjoy thinner patties on my burger so the size isnt an issue for me Im a big fan of the quality of ingredients and over all flavor I have a problem making my way down the menu Ive only tried the first 2 and find myself going back to them or trying their 15 They have a lot of other choices that I need to try I havent had trouble sampling each of their fries and you cant really go wrong My favorites are the truffle parmesan and sweet potato Two people can definitely share the small size They have some great sides too like the wasabi coleslaw and deviled eggs Id like to say Ive tried the salads but when I come here I know Im going to be a fatty They have a great beer list and cocktail menu Also their milkshakes are fantastic their monthly flavors are really creativeThe service is good never have had a bad experience They play a good selection of music and they interior fits the concept perfectly I highly recommend

Author: Anne T.
Content: These are the best burgers in Chicago I have hauntingly beautiful dreams of their burgers nod to How I Met Your Mother Even starring at their online menu makes my mouth drool with anticipation of the next time I will go back there Everything is made to perfection The burger bun has an eversoslight chew to it so much better than your normal airy and flavorless burger bun Their burger options are incredible and so much better than anything you could ever imagine I also love that they have options like veggie burgers and portobello burgers as well as salmon burgers Yum Getting fries is a must And dont just settle for normal fries While those are delicious why not try something like parmesan truffle cream fries  Their aioli sauce that goes along with it is so good I cannot go on Such good burgers Nothing has even close in comparison Go now

Author: Laleh A.
Content: A solid burger but nothin amazing about them Just wish that would be more veggies or give the options to add more My boyfriend got the bison burger which was good but lacked flavorI got the number one which was good but again nothing amazing I just really wish theyd give more veggie options or sauce options or somethingBut what was awesome were the fries and the truffle oil Holy moly that truffle oil made up for the whole meal I also got a michelada which was flavorful Definitely a good drink It had a nice vibe and the playlist was good It was a nice place place to start our evening of drinking Service was good from the bar to the waitress If youre in the area is suggest it but nothing to go out of the way for

Author: Emily H.
Content: I want to put together a Best Burgers in Chicago list  DMK would definitely be on the list  I ate here and it was soo good  I was completely stuffed when I left  Like you need to lie down and hug your stomach because you ate so much sick  I had a beef burger with bacon egg jack cheese and a roasted hatch chili  I didnt even put it down  I ate the whole thingI tried the macaroni and cheese with bacon and caramelized onions  It was really good as well  Although I didnt taste any caramelized onionsI have a fried okra addiction so we tried the fried okra and fried pickles   I think I like my fried okra chopped up though  We also had the Parmesan truffle fries  Why are truffles so good  I love truffle flavor  We tried a Cinnamon Toast Crunch milkshake for dessert  It was tasty of course but you could probably make this at home yourself

Author: Chris J.
Content: There are so many good things to say about DMK but first I really have to mention the service I was here again about a week ago on a Thursday night and we had about a 30 min wait normal The server Lauren was awesome the entire time and even gave us free deviled eggs before burgers arrived and milkshakes after our we finished eating When we were nearly finished the GM came over and explained we had waited a few extra minutes beyond our wait time I didnt even notice and thanked us for our patience Very few managers would have taken the time to come over to a table and apologize for that honestly waiting a few extra minutes is nothing but I really appreciated it Now to the food Everything Ive tried here is so freakin good I usually go with the 1 4 or 15 burger The toppings are all great but the grassfed beef is really what sets it apart from other burgers You can really taste the difference All of the fries are great and their homemade ketchup really needs to be bottled and sold Its incredible  DMK is also a great spot to hang out Good beer and craft cocktail selection great tunes and quite an attractive staff as well

Author: Kelly Q.
Content: Stopped in here en route to a flick at the Vic Not what I expected from a burger joint pleasantly surprised It was crowded for a snowy Wednesday night so luckily my hot date had already snagged a few seats at the bar I got the bison burger which comes with pickled onion goat cheese and blueberry BBQ sauce asking the bartender if I should sub a turkey burger for the bison He advised against it for which Im grateful The food arrived quickly and the bison patty was so tender and flavorful and the toppings worked in perfect harmony My date covered all the animal food groups with his beef burger topped with bacon and egg and probably some other ingredients that I missed as I was busy shoving bison into my face We also got a side of cheddar and scallion fries and fried okra and pickles which I thought were okay but my date took the lead on and polished off fairly quickly The beer list is solid and we each washed our meals down with a draft Lagunitas IPA for meAnd if that wasnt enough the bartender surprised us with some sort of chocolateraspberry jam milkshake so yummy and unnecessary Im still full 14 hours later They also gave us cards to come back for two free drafts sold

Author: Megan D.
Content: I loved going here on a Friday night date with my boyfriend The wait was close to 45 minutes but we enjoyed some delicious beers while we were waiting It was a fun place to be Our burgers were both delicious I ordered the 12 and he ordered the 5 Interesting combos Will definitely come back for more burger and fry combos Also I heavily respect their investment in the community with their charity sponsorships each month and their commitment to quality ingredients for their food

Author: maggie m.
Content: Awesome place for a beer and a unique burger This was my first time there before a Hawks game and it hit the spot Lily was our server and she was very friendly and an all around great server She was knowledgable of all the different beer and menu items I had the Mac and cheese 1 simple but very tasty The 3 others I was with had the party melt and 2 different burgers 4 and the special Patrick Kane burger We split the Wisconsin cheddar fries no scallions All the food was amazing For drinks we all had different beers all delicious Last but not least pumpkin milkshakes can you say yum A great place cant wait to go back and try one of the grilled cheeses

Author: Britni W.
Content: There are few places in Chicago that I suggest hands down to go to but this is one of them The place gets packed easy on a weekend night so if you arent willing to wait but still want to have some of the food drop in for lunch The food is still amazing and you dont have to wait forever The burgers are amazing and creative to say the least The fries also come in creative combination There is literally nothing Ive had from here that was bad With all the said its not cheap Youre paying at least ten dollars just for your burger but if Ive got the time and money its worth it If you are looking for a good burger even if you dont eat meat try out this place You wont regret it

Author: Rachel T.
Content: Not bad for a 9 burger I had the Lamb burger very tasty and I love the soft bread they use for the buns Went with my roommate she enjoyed her turkey burger didnt like whatever sauce they used on it though so she dipped her burger in ketchup lol and we shared an order of both the sweet potato fries and the truffle friesI am a sucker for truffle fries but at this particular spot I would sooner order the sweet potato fries Very yummy Maybe a little pricey for the amount of fries you actually get thoughOur server was pleasant and overall we liked the simple decor of the bar Would go back again

Author: Clayton B.
Content: Ive recently moved to Chicago and have become a regular at DMK within weeks I have absolutely loved everything Ive ordered here This place has made me visit all other DMK owned restaurantsThe decor is nicer than youd expect for a burger bar without looking like its trying to hard I always sit at the bar and get great service They play funny classics like Mrs Doubtfire on the TVs A few of the bartenders have given me great suggestions for cocktails They have a great selection of tequilas Which is unique for a burger place DMK also has a large beer selection more bottles than draftRecent obsession blue cheese and bacon fries

Author: Kyle D.
Content: I really wanted to give DMK 5 stars but there were just several flaws that kept it from such First off they have a great beer and alcohol selection If you are looking for craft beers this is a good place Their menu is also pretty good though obviously anything out of the burgerfries realm is probably absent That said the food was great Buffalo burger with bleu cheese and blueberry BBQ sauce was awesome and the sweet potato fries are clutch Their menu has so many great sounding burgers ranging from fried eggs peppers guac fried goodies and even turkeybeansalmonportebello burgersHowever the layout of the place is weirdwaited 45 mins for our table which the bar was handy for But we had to stand the whole time and the place was packed It was also pretty loud hard to hold conversation with all of the people and loud music Then the food took 20ish minutes after we ordered just a long time to waitOverall great burgers and drinks just dont come starving and expect to wait awhileAtmosphere 710Service 710Food 8510

Author: Kristen D.
Content: The service here is always really friendly I ordered the Bison burger with goat cheese omggoatcheese and blueberry bbq sauce I thought there would be a little bit more to this burger though it was basically onion sauce and goat cheese Thats all it needed It was so good and so different Never thought Id be a fan of bison meat but I am Their parmesan truffle fries are SO worth it but the small is pretty small for two people to share Looking forward to going back soon

Author: r.v. s.
Content: Too fucking loud even for a midweek midafternoon burger And Ive been pissed at them since they unceremoniously raised the price of a burger to 9 without even a shrug as if I wouldnt notice Really Nine bones for meat on a bun and no fries They get the stars for good beer selection and the green chili pork stew only during the winter Hintcheck out Indie Burger up the street Kenmore  Belmont At least there you can hear your own thoughts

Author: Justine M.
Content: I wasnt impressed The burgers are super greasy and flat The fries werent as flavorful as the menu makes them out to be The 2nd time I went here I got a cripsy portabello burger no meat and its wasnt flavorful I got a big bite of fried portobello I also dont enjoy the shared tables loud music and how dark it is

Author: Patrick L.
Content: Awesome My first time at a DMK Went with the bf  we split a number 1 with an egg a small order of the Wisconsin Cheese Fries  the Mac  Cheese 2 All were great The egg on the burger was cooked just right  those inhouse potato buns were awesomeOn top of that even at a busy point in the night the food came quick The service was excellent all around too With everything listed above plus two milkshakes our bill was just over 30 which was an awesome  inexpensive dinner I will definitely return as well as check out other of their locations

Author: Natasha C.
Content: Visited DMK tonight and it was PACKED Good sign I was surprised but pleasantly surprised I was also surprised at the number of small children in the place However they were quickly given some French fries and were stilled for a moment We put our name on the list and were told that we can snag a seat at the bar We were also offered some beer samples while we waited AWESOME So we stalked the bar and in about 15 minutes 2 seats cleared and we swooped down We were greeted by Effie who was amazing Effie made our visit amazing She was knowledgeable about all the beers on the menu and very patient with us because it was our first time there She even told us the name of the other bartenders so that we can ask them for service tooThats a first Everyone was really nice and the food was exceptional I really like the fact that you can substitute any of the burgers for turkey or portabella BRILLIANT I was in LOVE I mean in LOVE with Epic Burger but DMK has stolen my heart I even had a beer here and Im not even a beer drinker The next time we visit I will try the shakebelieve me that will be sooner than later I recommend the Wisconsin cheddar fries unbelievable and the burnt onions on your burger amazing Definitely worth the time and money

Author: Bill S.
Content: Perhaps I had unrealistic expectations after reading The Burger Issue of Time Out Chicago and from hearing about the place from my friends but I was not impressed by DMK We ordered three different burgers and shared them None of the selections were remarkable We also tried three different fries Better than the burgers for sure but also not the beall endall of fries Id heard about Great selection of beer although the first two we ordered were on the menu but apparently sold out That seemed a little weird Still a good selection and served nice and coldService was friendly and fast and they were very apologetic about the items they forgot to bring to the table All things considered not a bad place but frankly not in my top 10

Author: Seth F.
Content: Best Burger Bar in Chicago  Now those of you who read my Kumas post may cry a foul at what appears like hypocrisy but I assure you my words have been VERY carefully chosenRoasted Hatch Green Chile is in my humble opinion the best they offer  The Grassfed lamb is amazing too but as far as I can tell in my visits you cant really go wrong even their ketchups are amazing If you can get in without waiting more than 25 mins this is the best there is  Aside I went once with a large group and my friends boyfriend ordered a plain burger  Plain No cheese toppings or condiments Just a beef patty  I severely discounted every dern thing the guy said from that point forward

Author: Jules H.
Content: Im quite happy with the right size blue cheese and crispy onion string burger I had here It was very tasty And my fellow burger gobbler really liked the patty melt he had They serve like 9 different beef burger creations and several turkey burger cousins Fries are creatively concocted as well We had the sweet potato fries with alioli sauce on the side We were teetotaling so I cant vouch for anything other than a diet coke beverage wiseThey do serve the burgers on little plates which at first struck me odd but it was all good because everything I wanted on the burger was on it I dont do lettuce pickles or tomatoes on my burger so it was nice to not have a plate piled with things I dont like on a burgerThis place is on the smallish side you might have to wait for a table when you arrive It also looks like a great place to consume adult bevs Huge bar menu Very loud atmosphere though so its not the place for meaningful chit chat with friends because you can barely hear each other speak But the food makes up for it because it is really good food arrives quickly and when it arrives everyone shuts up and eats Yay

Author: Annie H.
Content: Absolutely the best veggie burger in the city Ive been twice and both times Ive been blown away I looooove their fries but beware if youre a strict vegetarian theyre beef fat fries My one star off for that one is I was warned the SECOND time I ate there and not the first If youre serving veggie friendly food you need to make sure people know on the menu or via server that they arent ordering vegetarian friendly foods Otherwise their buns are out of control and I love the blood orange soda and Ill definitely be back again and again

Author: Christie B.
Content: Ok so I dont like that there really isnt much of a waiting area since you almost always have to wait at least 2030 minutes on a good night Its also really loud and really dark And some of the waitstaff acts a little too cool for school Putting that all aside the food is really good The Big DMK which is their version of the Big Mac is so freaking good I can never eat the whole thing but one of these days I will defeat you Big DMK  I also love their milkshakes that you can get boozed up if you are a big kid who still loves milkshakes with their burgersAnother cool thing about DMK is their Uniform  Industry nights Industry night is every Sunday and gets you 50 off WooHoo for being a bartender And Uniform night is on various Wednesdays so check the website This gives cops firefighters EMTS and nurses 25 off AND they let current military dine free I totally respect DMK for that and that is why I think they deserve 5 stars

Author: Beth M.
Content: I want to love this place more  I really do I love the environment the people the free pickles the beer list love itBut it comes down to Im paying 9 for a burger thats good but is it the best burger in Chicago No Im usually three bites into my burger and its just ehhhh Ill focus on my fries now I want to say Im ordering the wrong thing but Ive tried several different burgers Maybe I am picking the wrong mix for ME but I should have hit that OMG BEST BURGER EVER moment by nowBut things I totally love their Wisconsin fries I will so so happily come back here just for that and everything else minus the burger My biggest complaint is that you cant get it cooked to order How can a burger place only serve it one way I prefer it medium rare and feel like the patties are a little too well cooked and dry Also they super overdo the black pepper there Its not a matter of if you like some kick its picking black pepper out of your teeth later and its all you can taste sometimes Really Id give this place 375 stars I cant give it a 4 just because it is 9 down the drain knowing there are much tastier burgers in Chicago for cheaper But all in all I do enjoy my time there Im sure I will be back ever hopeful with trying a new burger and hoping this is the one

Author: Hillary G.
Content: Came here with my dad on a daddate because burgers and we both really enjoyed it We arrived at opening on a Wednesday which was primetime for us because it wasnt busy and it wasnt noisy two things dads tend to dislike in my experience Our burgers were awesome very flavorful We also ordered the creamy coleslaw and sweet potato fries The coleslaw was nice and fresh not TOO creamy and the sweet potato fries were delicious with their lemontabasco aioli Mmmm An added bonus was that the guy that brought the food to the table was exceptionally good looking and put my plate down in front of me with a for you mlady so THANK YOU YUM Would definitely return to this dadfriendly establishment

Author: K F.
Content: Turkey burger w fried egg sweet potato fries and a 5 thin mint girl scout cookie milkshake Mouthgasm First off that was thee tastiest turkey Ive ever tasted on a burger I dont know what they put in the meat but my taste buds were celebrating Im not a huge fan of sweet potatoes but due to the abundance in recommendations via yelp I decided to give it a try No regrets they were quite amazing Not too greasy and the portion of the small was perfect I just prefer regular ketchup over the sauce it came with The milkshake was a concoction of vanilla and mint chocolate chip icecream complimented by a generous helping of girl scout thin mint cookiesneed I say more I loved the chunks and whole pieces of cookies they included wandering in the minty goodness Returning and dragging all of my yearning to get fat friends with me Service was good too btw Food came out surprisingly quick and our waitress was friendly

Author: A. M.
Content: Drinks  Great selection of beers  I didnt partake in any cocktails but the list looked awesome One had rhubarb jam  so creative  Also there was a huge selection of gin  tonic mixes  ScoreFood  Unbelievably AWESOME  This is probably my second favorite burger of all time  I had the standard one and husband had the bbq one  Both delicious  We also had the mac  cheese with bacon and red onion as well as the fries with salt  vinegar with pepper  All were stellar  Even though we ate a substantial amount of food we left feeling light as feathers  I attribute that to the grassfed beef  Truly top quality and didnt leave you feeling gross and puffy like other burgers  Service  Bartenders were attentive even though it was busy 3pm on St Patricks Day  Our waitress was equally attentive and friendly  Really no complaints here Ambience  Packed but not overflowing  It was a pretty chill crowd but all likes of people  kids and parents to older adults and all in between  No douche bags even on St Patricks DayAnything else worth noting  Ive been wanting to come to this place for a long time because Ive heard so many great things about the burgers and how great you feel after eating them  It really was everything I wanted it to be and more  I will definitely be back

Author: Mark H.
Content: Fast servicenice staff Great beer selections  Young crowd 20ish Low prices Would definitely go back again

Author: Claire P.
Content: Tasty lamb burger Really nice waitress she have us free fried pickles Also best music around

Author: Gigi E.
Content: Hands down best burgers Know that it is loud and you will wait for a bit 3060 mins on Saturday evening but totally worth it Awesome service

Author: Erich S.
Content: DMK versus the other places that weve given 5stars burgers has a nice balance between a straightup burger versus fun variances on the classicTheir selection of burgers is akin to Kumas but I find them tastier and better executed Their fries damn amazing Seriously Its a thinner patty so dont expect a big honkin thick burger but its juicy and average sized Where they go the extra mile IMHO is in the beverages  great beer selection plus shakes I mean if youre doing a burger with bacon and fries with aioli youre already going allout so why not have a shake

Author: Alejandro H.
Content: Ive been here numerous times and I am never disappointed There is really nothing I would change about this place The service is great the prices arent bad and the environment is cool I would recommend the Big DMK its a Big Mac on crack Their sodas are awesome too I try and take all my friends that visit Chicago here the ones that do manage to make it here have had their taste buds changed for life

Author: Jeremy D.
Content: Famous chef Michael Kornick and famous steak family varying siblings of Mortons the Steakhouse as well as family have been doing business together for several years now and mostly in upscale joints Bringing things down to earth in a Burger Bar concept And another warrior enters the Terrordome for Burger SupremacyThis place has been open for a little while they seem to overall be holding their own against those who enterNow You have a choice of 15 burgers and their combos So if you are someone who prefers to build your ownyou may not like this  See you can remove ingredients from the 15 listed but except for additional patty of beef 3 or adding an egg 1 you cant add nutthin Now I liked the idea of the combos and so Im overall ok with itWent with a 4 Burger with Roasted Hatch Chilies Over Easy Egg Smoked Bacon and Sonoma Jack CheeseThe bun here is really good Almost a slightly fluffier lighter English Muffin so it has a bit of density but not as puffed out as a traditional Parker House Roll style Burger BunThe beef is excellent comes out just under medium would like to see a bit more char and VERY juicy The 4 combo is a GOOD one All things I like and I really LIKE Hatch Chilies the burger comes together in a very satisfying package Im also a BIG fan of Sweet Potato Fries The Lemon and Tabasco Aioli is pretty outstanding Not too hot at first but the tang of the chilies AND the aioli suddenly sneaks up on you The fries themselves were good and crispy Properly seasonedExtensive and well priced beer list Would like to see some more interesting choices on their wines Cmon this is BEEFThis place is good Could be a touch more generous with the bacon Id also like to see the burger FILL the circumference of the bun and not come kinda shy of But the flavors are good and the variety shows some creativity Id like to also see some flexibility in adding ingredients Im a BIG fan of a Bleu and Bacon with mushrooms burger

Author: Brian I.
Content: Ive eaten here numerous times and I typically avoid the busiest times of day if you read my reviews youll notice that I dont believe in standing in lines I enjoy the burgers and fries and have been known to make an excuse to end up walking past DMK  Im not a vegetarian but I have many friends who are When 3 people at the table order the veggie burgers  I would like to think the staff might warn us that the fries arent vegetarian  I mean how often does a nonveggie order a veggie burger at a burger place right We had no idea granted we should have asked before we did on our 5 or 6th visit But eventually we did find out that the fries are not vegetarian Now I get the fries to myself  which is cool for me Overall Im a huge fan of the burgers and the beer list is always good Dogfish 120 min on tap what what but  unfortunately Im docking a star  for what I think the quality of the food deserves  due to the somewhat deceptive fries BTW the veggie patties are fried separately and are vegetarian

Author: Allison S.
Content: Boo for the wayyyyyyyyy too loud music Its a shame because it takes away from the awesome burgers and even awesomer fries I would go there all the time but ive been three times and its sort of way over the top too loud Like cant hear the person RIGHT next to you loudIf they fixed that it would be a whole new ballgame and a whole nother star

Author: Karl M.
Content: The service was very spacey I asked the waitress if my beer came in a bomber and she said Yes so naturally I was expecting a nice big session brew and what showed up was a puny 16 oz bottle I thought Ok Now I have room for that awesome peanut butter chocolate malt Ive been hearing about SO fine small beer it is On to the feastOr wait is this IT YepThe burger just isnt that big I ordered the double and it still seemed kinda flimsyThe toppings were great and seemed well put together I had the Bison burger and it was nice juicy and thinThe fried pickles and okra were a bit heavy but they had an interesting taste I am not a deepfry fan anymore The waitress just brought them out They kinda sent my palate off and ruined my stomach The megasuperridiculous IPA rounded that out thoughThe sweet potato fries were fries Something truffle or whatever Thin and crispy OkThe beer selection is alright They have some nice ones in most every common style Not a huge selection but a very nice one Beers change all the time so I wont name namesThe peanut butter chocolate malt was a big let down It had no malty character whatsoever and they hardly blended it at all so it just had a big smear of peanut butter and chocolatewhateverthehelltheyuse marbled on the side of the cheap togo plastic cup pretty and all but tasty as shit too AND SMALLI double checked to make sure they put the malt in and they SAID they did It was pretty much vanilla shakey until the peanut butter clogged my straw halfway through Then I mixed it around and had a peanut butter shake with a crappy chocolate kind of colored substance but no chocolate flavorMaybe my expectations were too high but who can I blame for that It just seems like a shallow joint that serves overpriced clever food but not high quality well thought out foodsThe only reason I wasnt completely throwing this place in the forgetmepile was because my buddy got the bill If I had to pay for this I would have hit  a brick My stars dont come cheap and if youre charging a premium price youd better deliver the goodsThe place wasnt even busy in fact we were the second tableThe staff seem to have such a holy high regard for the place as if it were gods gift to burgers But thats probably due to the location it is an awesome spotMaybe Im just too demanding Go judge for yourself

Author: Sarah S.
Content: This place has really good burgers but its probably not the best choice to come here on a Friday or Saturday night at dinner time Wait times are 2 hours long If you really want to try this place grab your best guy or gal and try to wiggle your way into a bar seat The staff was polite the atmosphere was loud crowded think a bar and probably not the best place to take parents when they are in town Oh yea food is ala carte and you will definitely end up spending 3040 if you get a burger fries and maybe 2 beersEpic burger has similar food without the crowds

Author: Scott K.
Content: Definitely worth the reputation Stopped here several times while in Chicago for work DMK is notable for not only having a great burger and bun but also being a cool joint for unique burger toppings and a full bar that gets lively at night The bartenders were very friendly and service was great Their buns come from a local bakery and are awesome and the cool sides mac and cheese and french fry varieties are a great addition as well I visited a few times during my stay and each burger was excellent but the 4 with a fried egg definitely stood out as one of the best burgers I have had in my life Would recommend this place to any TexanI recommend 4 with sweet potato fries or mac n cheese with bacon

Author: T C M.
Content: Both times burgers have been okay 4 needs more green chile Its barely enough to taste Fries too crispy Very loud

Author: John F.
Content: This place was reviewed over 1000 times  Yelp sure is going strong in ChicagoSolid burger great service and classy yet cool layout made DMK an awesome place to frequent My burger tasted a lot like a big mac only better order it trust me  Im not super familiar with the neighborhood but it seems nice  Burgers were very flavorful and big  The fries pretty much stole the show as they were excellent and generously portioned  If you happen to have room after your through with your meal try their delicious shakesThe service was excellent  Our bartender was a really nice guy and made sure our foodbeers were served promptly  Prices here are also reasonableLooking forward to coming back soon

Author: Lauren S.
Content: Okay burgers are really really good here  MMMM  Sad part  The service kind of stinksWe came here for lunch on a weekday a group of about 6 gals that love their burgers The restaurant was not very crowded and it took forever to get drinks or to make an order or ask for anything  Even though our server was very nice they just werent very attentive  It actually took a long time to even get our check to pay these peeps which was a disappointment  BUT the burger I enjoyed very very much

Author: Anuj S.
Content: DMK knows how to do it rightWhat wait DMK is a popular place and unfortunately they dont take reservations  I guess we were in the mood to wait  Its a Saturday night the wait was 1hr and 45mins when we got there at like 815pm  I didnt know that until later because I went to park or I wouldnt have stayed  We sort of eased our way in to seats at the bar  Eventually the entire group was seated quite comfortably at this table kind of at the end of the bar  We got the last two seats probably an hour in  Well it was still a long wait but we knew that going inThe thing that bothered me more than the wait was how rude the hostess was  Honestly thats probably the main reason for my hesitation to give this place the full 5 stars  With such a long wait I think it was normal to check on the timing after like an hour  I didnt think that was imposing on her or anything  She was quite rude about the followupOn the other hand our server was great  Since we ended up sitting at the bar the bartender was also our waiter  He was awesome  It was one of the best service experiences after that point  He was patient accommodating attentive  He handled special requests without any hint of annoyance and even brought us out some taste portions of fries while we waited  And this was at the bar which was like crazyjampackedbusy  It was an impressive experienceNow for the food and drink  The fries and onion rings were great  The veggie burger I had was also really good  Maybe not the best Ive ever had but I liked it  It was like fried crispy on the outside  Was great with onion rings and blue cheese on top  Others tried the portabella sandwich which they enjoyed  Also other variations of the veggie burger were also enjoyed by all  Lastly the mac  cheese and grilled cheese were all yummy I took a bite of each for tasting  So really foodwise everything was greatEven though the place was packed we noticed that the crowd really thinned out around the same time we sat at the bar  Next time Id definitely go at like 930 even 9pm  Overall great job at DMK  Ill be back

Author: Brittany H.
Content: I am not a huge burger person but I am hooked on DMK If youre looking for a spot for some awesome burgers and brews dmk is the place Not only do they have great burgers they have an extensive list of craft beers and their fries are delicious My girlfriend  I always go and split the truffle fries  wisconsin cheese fries Theyre both so good we can never settle on just one kindI always get the burger with blue cheese and onion straws It is seriously so good I cant even bring myself to try another kind Ive also gotten the same burger with a veggie patty and it was delish Although it is usually crowded around dinner time the place is lively and its not too difficult to grab a beer at the bar while you wait This is one of my fav places to take my out of town guests since its both affordable and delish

Author: Erica K.
Content: I really want to like DMK Seriously Ive gone 3 times always hoping it will really knock my socks off But it never does My issues are as followsIts just too loud in this place Im just not impressed with the food The burgers aretrying too hard The meat is so covered in toppings that you lose the taste of this grass fed beef they play up so much They only have 1 bathroom each for men and women WTH This place is busy on a weekend evening and the bathroom line gets silly long with no where really stand without being in the way of the kitchen That said Sunday we had a very nice waitress and a very handsome like dang gina food runner and the bloody marys were excellent BUT that doesnt make up for the fact that my 11 burger was kind of lame

Author: Brett G.
Content: DMK Burger Bar is really awesome   Ive gone on an actual quest to find the best burgers in Chicago  DMK is one of the frontrunners in this competition   There are so many reason  The burgers are awesome  I really like the friescheese combinations that you can orderI mostly stick to the HolyGuacaioli  Chorizo a bunch of other stuff and a patty  IM IN  Why would I want to try any of the other sandwiches when I already know that this one is so awesomeIm not into beer as much but my craft beer friend was into their selection  They had a nice liquor selection if I recall correctly though  The atmosphere is nice and hip Theres usually a 30 min wait whenever I go   Definitely worth it though

Author: Jen L.
Content: This place is goooood Went there on a Saturday and they were very busy We waited about 30 minutes to be seated but once seated the service was very fast The atmosphere is loud so I wouldnt recommend going here on a first date Okay lets talk about what really mattersthe food I had the 10 which is a turkey burger and oh my goodness was it delicious The buns are perfect and the dijonnaise spread is yummy My husband had the 1 and he too thought his was delicious We split an order of the parmesan fries and those were good too We will definitely be going here again

Author: Diana C.
Content: I love everything about youDMK is one of my favorites and my goto I cant think of anytime someone has suggested and Ive thought I dont feel like going thereMy goto is the Turkey Burger with Arugula served alongside the Wisconsin Cheddar Fries deliciousIt is ridiculous on the craving scale I have hopped the Brown Line to go there from downtown for lunch Bonuses they have delicious milkshakes chocolate vanilla peanut butter and a special milkshake every month Also every month they choose a nonprofit organization to donate all proceeds of their 5 special to Delicious dogooders Im IN

Author: Cameron H.
Content: After seeing this place on DDD I could not resist  Finally I was able to go with a friend last night  Upon our arrival we were asked did we want to sit high or low  Of course we chose high  Then our waitress arrived with the menus  She was very friendly and cute as well  This is truly a burger joint  I love the option of being able to swap any burger with either Turkey or crispy portobello no charge or even bison lamb or veggie for an up charge 2  The only thing I dont like is that there are no substitutions on condiments or cheese  You have the option of leaving it off but not exchanging it for something else  OddWe started off with a bottle of wine red zin  Delicious  For our meal I had the 4 Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack Smoked Bacon but with the crispy portobello  My friend had the 10 Turkey Smoked Swiss Tomato Arugula Dijonnaise  For a side she ordered the sweet potato fries and I ordered the standard cut fries with Parmesan Truffle Cream  Every thing was amazing   Great location Wellington and the brownpurple line great service great food and great priceI will definitely go back

Author: Tabitha W.
Content: I was all set to love this place  I had checked out the menu online and was excited to try their Peanut Butter Shake as well as some of their interesting french fry flavors  oh and a veggie burger of course  We arrived around 1 on a Saturday afternoon and were quoted a 45minute wait This actually ended up being like a 30minute wait  I always appreciate less of a wait time than estimated  So the wait time was fine but there is just nowhere good to wait Especially with the crowd that was there A better designated wait area would work wonders  Finally seated we ordered that Peanut Butter Milkshake which was super yummy  There were 2 veggie burgers on the menu so my husband ordered 11 with the House Veggie and Grain burger and the Wisconsin Cheese Fries and I ordered the Crispy Portobello with the Parmesan and Truffle Cream FriesAnd then the waitress asked are you guys vegetarian She explained that the fries are actually cooked in beef fat so we nixed those Curiously the other appetizers are cooked in canola oil so my husband opted for the the Fried Okra  Dill Pickles Sensing our immense disappointment she also brought us a halforder of the ChiliRubbed Onion Strings on the house  My burger was good  the crispness made it less chewy and soggy than it can be at other places  Oh if only I could have tried those fries    I really appreciate that the waitress volunteered that information  a lot of places arent even knowledgeable about that but I really dont understand why they dont prepare the fries differently

Author: Amy X.
Content: I was amazed They have great burgers and sweet potato fries I came here with a friend on a weekday afternoon Street parking was not too bad They have a mini bar so you can come with a friend or two to chat and chill Burger portions are small so if you are a big eater consider ordering a second or appetizers

Author: Heidi S.
Content: Burgers were really large which helps justify the price and creative  However Ive had more creative burgers where the ingredients worked together a little bit betterI thought the macncheese was fine but nothing special  We also got a side of the fries with cheddar and scallions but the cheddar was more of a sauce than just melted cheese and it had kind of a funky texture and aftertaste that was REALLY strongOverall its a fine meal but it was a little pricey for menu items that were good not amazing

Author: Thamer B.
Content: me my wife and another couple were at a show in the area and it was kinda late so i checked my bookmarks found DMK is nearest open so we decided to give it a shotThe area was kinda dark but did not feel unsafe that much anyways i ordered the turkey burger which i liked my wife had the bison burger with goat cheese and raspberry bbq sauce which she did not like the other couple ordered basic bison burger and they said it was just okaytheir fries is a blast specially the truffle and the sweet potatoes friesit was not a bad experience but it was not an outstanding although the waitress was attentive and helpful pretty muchif i was in the area and i had limited choices to pick from i would consider eating here again

Author: Chris A.
Content: Ive tried to find a better burger in the world but nothing has come close to DMK  The 1 Aged Cheddar Smoked Bacon Charred Balsamic Red Onions Rufus Teagues BBQ Sauce simply cannot be beat  I strayed once from the 1 and got the 5 Bison Burger Fresh Goat Cheese Pickled Red Onions Blueberry BBQ Sauce and although it was delicious it didnt match the 1One of the most difficult things a restaurant can do is deliver a favorite dish to a loyal customer over and over again  DMK nails it in spadesHonestly the food is so good the other pieces of the puzzle dont matter that much but the ambiance is great service is pretty good and the wait is well worth it

Author: Shaina K.
Content: This place is slightly expensive but theyre good Their burgers are the perfect portion and there will probably be no leftovers I love their fries they have some awesome truffle fries This place gets crowded later at night but we went at 6 and were able to get a table with no issues The service was great

Author: Jamie B.
Content: After a few beers at the Kirkwood for the NE game we decided to go get something to eat at DMK  Overall they have pretty good burgers  I like that theyre on a traditional bun and are clearly handmade  They have a couple of veggie burgers too that cater to the vegetarians so thats nice too  The three of us split some onion strings which I was disappointed with  Should have ordered the fries like everyone recommends  We will be back to try some more things off the menu

Author: Justin B.
Content: Lets keep it brief since there are hundreds of reviews for this place alreadyservice was great my 15 burger special was great dont remember exactly what was in it but there was definitely cheese duck and beef all over this thing with the DMK buntasty my milkshake was maybe the best Ive had in Chicago and the french friesboth the Wisconsin cheddar fries and the parmesantrufflewere pretty good  The beer selection was hearty and had something for all four of my team membersI dont think this ranks as high for me as the triumvirate of Kumas Lockdown and Butcher  the Burger but its close

Author: Mandy K.
Content: This place has an awesome ambiance great service and even better burgers  The beer list is pretty great as well  Our bartender Alex was terrific  made perfect suggestions for both beer and food We also really liked the fact that they had charity items where all proceeds of those items went to the charity of the month Great idea

Author: Kelly M.
Content: Wonderful Great food friendly service great atmosphere So good Had the bison burger Parmesan fries and pineapple basil shake Delicious on all counts

Author: Ben B.
Content: DMK has the potential to be greatI kinda hate the layout of the place  Long bench seats are on one side of each table and chairs are on the other  This required our server to jut her entire upper torso over our table to speak to both of usI ordered one of the temporary special burgers  It had duck sausage gruyere cheese and red wine caramelized onions  Tasty for sure  I wish the beef patty were thicker  Perhaps the combo was too richWe also ordered the Parmesan fries  Those were really good  I would have preferred thickercut fries as wellI also drank a Death  Companys Whirling Tiger bourbon fresh apple  lemon ginger syrup  It was blindingly strongI applaud DMKs creativity and Ill be back  I just wish the portions were a little beefier

Author: Meagan H.
Content: Holy cow Although this place was packed it was well worth the wait for a table  It was super dark I didnt like that because I want to see what color my burger comes out But they did a good job cookingI ordered my usual dog fish 90 minute I love my strong beer  To start off we ordered fried pickles Yup It was definitely deep fried to divert me to a diabetes state But good  I then got my burger A chorizo chipotle cilantro and guacamole hunk of heaven I loved it  If I had room for dessert I definitely would have taken advantage because Im sure it would have been amazingWhat can I say The service was just ok but it was better than most places that are that busy  I was surprised the waitress could remember our orders off the top of her head considering all tables were full  So I was impressed by that  She got a hefty tip  This place was great I couldnt have asked for much more except for a little more light

Author: Lenny S.
Content: Great Food delicious burgers and awesome Mac  Cheese They have a great beer and cocktail selection too The reason I didnt give them 5 stars is the beer I ordered for 7 was teeny Shouldve been a pint for 7 bucks

Author: Shawn K.
Content: Parmesan truffle fries are awesome

Author: Ben B.
Content: I had a little sticker shock when I saw the burgers dont even come with sides but I quickly changed my tune once the food came out These burgers are phenomenal and they have Daisy cutter on tap I was in a rush so I sat at the bar I was gone in less then 15 minutes and cant wait to try more of the menu

Author: Anna T.
Content: Truffle fries were a bust Totally not worth the 40 for two burgers and a basket of fries Go to other places They will be better

Author: Bridget K.
Content: Its a Tuesday night in the beginning of February and my family is out and about to celebrate the brotherinlaws birthday  He loves burgers and so does the rest of the family  After trying a few other famous burger places we found out they all had an hour wait on a Tuesday  We were super hungry so we headed off to DMK Burger Bar  We walked in and we seated right away  We ordered our burgers one being vegetarian and two orders of fries to share  The burgers and fries came out fast which was nice considering how hungry we all were  The fries were pretty great  We got one order of the Wisconsin cheddar and scallion which were delish  The other fries were the sea salt and cracked pepper which were also great  After dinner we were getting ready for the check so we could get some desert  When our server came over and gave us free samples of the Raspberry Linzer Shake which happens to be the shake of the month for February 2013  The shake was good and a nice surprise  Thanks DMK for saving the day when it came to the brotherinlaws birthday dinner

Author: Klima K.
Content: Their burger wont let you down I guarantee just the atmosphere take away one star from the rating cuz its too noisy You cant hear others words unless they yell to you

Author: Jess F.
Content: My friends and I came a time when there werent a lot of people I saw good reviews on yelp and decided to give it a try Its a bit far from downtown but very close to the subway This place is literally all about burgers Their menu is very small Fries are separate from the burgers just a FYI I guess its so you can focus all your attention on the burger They have lots of burgers so it was kind of hard to decide which one to eatI ended up getting the special which was Santa something I dont remember But it was salsa egg and tortilla chips It was very unique and very good HUGE burger with very moist meat grilled to perfection THe only thing that was disappointing which I know would be really hard to perfect was the fact my tortilla chips were soggy I know thats just being really picky but the sides that didnt soak up the sauce were very crispy so it left a nice sensation in my mouth My friend ordered the double stack It was HUGE He had a messy time eating it But definitely worth it My other friend ordered the regular Still a very big burger but also grilled to perfection We ordered sweet potato tots to share Those were really good Very sweet potatoes and very crispy Usually sweet potato fries arent as crispy as youd get with regular fries but these tots were super crispy The sauce it came with was also really good My friend ordered the choco banana milkshake SO GOOD If I had more room in my stomach I probably would have gotten one myself Very bananay flavour and good hint of chocolate VERY thick milkshake I used a spoon to take some from my friends drink Hahaha Great place for burgers and milkshakes The only thing is its far from the city so for tourists like me it would be very hard and probably would go unnoticed if I hadnt done some research ahead of time At least we stopped by Lincoln park when we came back from this place Its only a few bus stops away When you go visit be prepared to get messy Not a place to be eating your burger with delicacy and table manners

Author: Taylor O.
Content: Do not expect to have a conversation while dining here SO loud The bison burger with goat cheese and blueberry BBQ is great and worth the chaos The house veggie burger is also decent

Author: Paul F.
Content: Amazing burger Perfect size and no wastage  The taste is just out of this world Hostess and servers were all very attentive 3 thumbs up

Author: Jennie C.
Content: Fiiiiiinally had a chance to try this place at the suggestion of a vegetarian friend Huh what Yep this is a burger place that can sub out the patty of any burger with a fried Portobello I was almost jealousif my own burger werent so good I had burger 1 with the balsamic onions  bbq sauce AND a fried egg Not your steakhouse big patties so no inquiries about doneness But it was still juicy and yummy Friend got the greek burger with Portobello and really loved it too We shared some sweet potato fries and an espresso shake ok I drank most of it which is why this review took so long because Ive been trying to work off all that food Yes its loud but your mouth will be too busy chewing so no need to worry about conversations We walked right in to a mostly empty dining room around 5p on a Sunday but there were tons of people waiting by 630

Author: Jocelyn D.
Content: Delicious yet different burgers amazing fries awesome homemade sodas and consistently pleasant service Totally recommended burger spot

Author: Jack B.
Content: Great BurgersBeef Fries are even better than the burgers  I got the big DMK 5 stars  Wisconsin Cheddar scallion fries 5 stars I am from WI and it might of been the best cheddar ive ever had  Parmesan fries with truffle cream sauce is probably one of the best things Ive ever had  This is not your typical burger joint that has good to great burgers and then some crappy buns and frozen fries  Great beer selection be prepared to wait with one   Any burger can be made with a veggie or turkey patty They make their burgers medium only   Still amazing though

Author: Roland C.
Content: This place is for you if you like   Sweet potatoes Burgers Cheese too many to chose The Chicago Cubs

Author: Jen P.
Content: I had to have CHEESE FRIES  However I didnt know where to go So I prayedyes I did  I read reviews on DMK and decided to also try a burger I ordered 1 and happy I did The hand cut fries wcheddar  scallions was good however it had TOO much salt I dont know if thats the way they serve them or someone got happy with the salt  I understand this Establishment is a bar whereas if your drinking beer you might not notice it  But everyone doesnt like their food drowning in salt Overall I would revisit

Author: Chris C.
Content: I only ever come here on a Sunday night because after 9pm if you work in the industry EVERYTHING IS HALF PRICE Great deal Ive enjoyed the bison burger the big salad and the garlic fries on numerous occasions They also have great american beers I LOVE DMK

Author: Francisco A.
Content: This place is awesome their meat is amazing  definitely on list of best burger meat I ever had I personally tried 11 I believe chorizo guacamole burger AMAZING  Their fries are good as well  Waitress was always checking on us and food was served quickly You wont be disappointed

Author: Renee E.
Content: I really enjoy a good burger and I always prefer mine rare to medium rare I was a bit surprised that I was unable to order mine that way at DMK and that my waitress informed me theyre all done medium Sadness So I got my burger and as it was I was doing this paleochallenge ie no bun so it was a wee little beef patty with pretty much no discernable seasoning and definitely on the other side of medium toward well I dont know if the bun wouldve saved it but I wasnt feeling it Mustard helped salvage the dryness but definitely not what I was looking forDMK however gets an extra star for the sweet potato fries accompanied by a delicious aioli YUM

Author: Christie K.
Content: I came here because I wanted to try a very good burger in Chicago And this burger was definitely delicious I have never had beef from grassfed cows before Maybe its because I just assumed it tastes all the same But its reallllllllly different The beef is less dense and more porous Its just as good as other beef patties Ive had its just different I tried the 1 Beef Burger w Cheddar Smoked Bacon  Charred Balsamic Red Onions Rufus Teaguqs BBQ Sauce and the 4 Beef Burger with Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack Smoked Bacon I LOVED both burgers but I liked the 4 because I love eating peppers and jack cheese I love their beers on tap too It complements the burger very well Now Im on the prowl for places that use grassfed beef

Author: Bethany B.
