Content: I just dont get it I love hamburgers and had DMK on my musttry list for ages Glowing reviews on yelp Friends raved this is the best burger in the cityFinally had the chance to try a DMK burger last weekend and I was left disappointed and confused The burger was very meh Thin bun Thin patty Burger patty was cooked well done and tasted slightly burnt in places We werent asked how we wanted the burgers cooked I understand some places dont do this but Ive come to expect it at places where the burger is the star of the show and high quality meat is used French fries were fine but also over done I had McDonalds fries this weekend too and they were way better The service was great friendly timely Beer list had a decent selection With so many amazing juicy wellbunned and properly cooked burgers to be had in this city I just dont understand the hype around DMK What am I missing

Author: Stephanie W.
Content: Is this real lifeThese burgers are incredible As always I went with a fairly classic plain choice by ordering 8 I said it once and Ill say it again delicious burgers do not need a million flavors to make my taste buds water Although the condiments were minimal the taste was notAnd what SIX different kinds of fries Its almost like they created this restaurant with me in mind Im partial to Wisconsin cheddar  scallionAs Arnold Schwarzenegger once said Ill be back

Author: Damian S.
Content: The waitstaff is super nice the beer selection is awesome the burger list is short but there were at least 6 of the 14 that I really wanted to try I also couldnt believe that they will let you sample from the bottles or cans of beer that they have availablethats unheard ofbut great I would definitely go back againThe atmosphere is really laid back and the space is very open I could imagine that this place gets a little crowded at night but probably with standing patrons for the bar as the tables are spaced nicely far apart You shouldnt hear too much of the adjacent tables conversation

Author: Casie S.
Content: DMK does not disappoint and the Chicago and Oak Brook locations are consistently delish Ive tried just about every burger on the menu and loved them all I would say the bison burger is my favorite and the party melt an close runner up but you cant go wrong on any of the burger items The Parmesan truffle fries the blue cheese bacon fries and sweet potato fries are incredible  For drinks the blood orange soda was refreshing and the espresso shake was probably the best coffee flavored shake Ive ever had I do wish they had some chicken options on the menu Every now and then they do have a special turkey burger but chances are Id still get a beef burger  Keep up the great work and I will definitely be back

Author: Brett D.
Content: I didnt love it I didnt hate it If I were Erin P Id nothing it Either way I think its plain to see I did not find the love affair I was so hungrily seeking with the newly opened DMK Burger Bar While the modernrustic décor inventive concept and friendly staff appear to be a smashing success the burgers are not Le Exhale Noisily er Sigh You cant have Burger Bar in your name without really being able to produce big time on burger fabulosity I mean even our beloved beef Forefathers knew to keep it ambiguous think about it Kumas Corner Apple Pan Blackies hell even Flub A Dub Chubs they all manage to keep expectations in check by promising nothing  but um floppy appendages  in their moniker But to tout burger in flashing lights literally and then produce a meager product on an appetizer sized plate well thats just bait n switch my friends They sold me a Lemon I tell ya My slightly underseasoned turkey burger with goopy eggplant lessthanpunchy blue cheese coleslaw and utterly boring ciabatta bun left me gobble gobble gloomy There was zero pizazz literally No wow factor no extras like I dunno toppings aside from what exactly was mentioned on the menu ie eggplant and coleslaw The term burger bar conjured images of multiple bun choices a veritable cheeseapalooza terrific toppings galore and ooey gooey loveliness Not here my moo muse not here While the beer selection positively rawks the deviled eggs are tasty fun and the fries are crispy crunchy perfect  especially the truffle and parmesan ones  the burgers were hardly worth the calorie sacrifice they without a doubt require DMK a bar for the recreational meat eater Youve been cow cautioned

Author: Stacey A.
Content: DMK is not the same as KumasYoud think this would be obvious as one place is named DMK and is in Lincoln Park and the other place is named Kumas and is in Avondale OBVIOUSLY THEY ARE NOT THE SAME PLACESo it would stand to reason that the food crowd decor and general ambiance would be different at each place because they areNOT THE SAME PLACEDont go to one expecting the other The same would go for cupcake places More  Swirlz Not the same and steakhouses Wildfire is not Primehouse Youd think this would be a given but people appear to be going to DMK expecting the second coming of KumasDMK is NOT the second coming of KumasDMK is a lovely comfortable minimally decorated stretch of restaurant its longer than it is wide that serves up some creative options that are not insanely expensive nor too big to eat  some really tasty sounding house drinks a lot of delicious craft beer options with a focus on local breweries in IL WI  MI and some beefy red wines to go along with the burgersEmily B and I stopped in here for dinner tonight We were really only intending for it to be snacks but I figured What the hell I never leave my house except to go to work might as well eat a burgerNow Em had been here before so she told me about all the delicious things shed had before and I poured over the menu and drooled about things like the LAMB BURGER with feta and Greek salad and olive tapenadeSince there were only two of us and only one of us me was getting a burger we settled on two small portions of fries  sweet potato with a lemon tobasco aioli  and regular potato with badass cheddar that tasted like Merkts and chives Perfectly portioned for two people to split and not feel overly full em told me that if you come with a big group to basically order one small thing of fries per person in the group and everyone should be covered that wayI ordered burger 2 they dont have names theyre numbered duh  which came with chipotle ketchup bleu cheese and those fried onion strawsAnd it was delicious And it was not KumasAnd I will totally go back and get that lamb burger thing because it sounded fucking good

Author: Colleen C.
Content: Errrrrrr DontMeasure up toKumasThe burgers Ok I find it very odd they serve just your burger on a smallish think tapas shared plate Like just put it on a normal plate Then you can split the fries out Salad yeah I know so very boring but they have ONE big one on the menu near the bottom and while it sounded good on paper the execution was drowned in dressing Fail But I get it Its a salad at a burger bar but do it well if you are gonna do it Salad fury Stellar beer selection local focus bonusMalts n ShakesLotsa Fries truffle fries just OKAOK certainly a good addition to this stretch but I wasnt overly impressed and would not pound the pavement to hit it up again If you are a burgers n fries fanatic def give it a shot

Author: Jelena Z.
Content: DMK youre my 600th review Only relevant to me I know but still felt like shouting it from the rooftopsWhat is relevant is that you can see that I eat out quite a bit A sideeffect of that besides a skinny wallet is that my expectations have grown a bit lofty Especially when it comes to burgers as I really like em Beef turkey bison greasy fancy small large I really dont discriminate My only requirement They better be goodAnd when the word burger is part of your very name your game best be stepped up Ahhhh DMK youre good youre really goodOur server Lauren explained that the meat would be cooked all the way through I typically order my burgers grilled to either medium rare or medium so I was concerned that it wouldnt be as juicy as I like I opted for the turkey burger which was topped with swiss arugula and dijonnaise held the tomato and a side of the blue cheese slaw Verdict Tastiest turkey burger Ive ever had Really Juicy and tender wellseasoned maxed out on flavor And dont get me started on the delightful bun too many restaurants ignore the power of a great bun The serving of coleslaw was huge and also very tasty But if you only go with one side item order the Parmesan truffle fries I stole two from my colleague before cutting myself off Gosh theyre addictiveOur server Lauren was a peach and extremely knowledgeable about their many offerings which is a must in my book If I could make one recommendation okay three offer free refills hot beverages and get some Splenda for the ice tea Otherwise DMK is bliss indeed

Author: Tammy L.
Content: I always enjoy my meals at DMK  I try and go at off times to avoid waiting because I just dont want to have to wait in line for a burger  I eat veggie a lot but here I typically get the salmon burger since the veggie options are on the heavy side fried portobello or fried veggie patty  I looooove the sweet potato fries but was a little disappointed to learn that they are not freshly cuttheyre frozen  They put vanilla on them or something because they taste like dessert with the lemon aioli  Their regular fries are good too  Anyhow I love to eat but I dont eat huge volumes at once so I personally think their portions are very reasonable  I have never ever left hungry thats for sure  I really like their housemade sodasyum  But I tried their house margarita once and thought it was terrible so I wont order that again  I have always wanted to try a shake but have never had enough room after the burger and splitting a small order of fries with my dining companion  Quality beer selection  Its a favorite

Author: Andy M.
Content: Do yourself a favor The next time you hear of a place having a burger as good as Kumas just walk away Its all lies This was the case with the DMK burger bar    Our visit came on the Saturday of CubsSox weekend at Wrigley We had a 45 minute wait to get seated but it was a beautiful Saturday night so we stood outside and kibitzed with our good friends The staff actually did a nice job getting us seated in a timely manner considering how packed they were DMK offers a nice selection of microbrews and a wide variety of different burgers and appetizer options The French Country Ale was a kick ass beer that I really enjoyed  I decided to stray from their normal menu and try something different  Being a True Blue Cubs fan I had to go with the special burger of the month which was the Ron Santo Burger It was their standard burger covered with Pastrami and provolone cheese The price for most of their burgers range from 811 dollars For that price you would expect a nice chunk of meat but I was I was amazed by how small these burgers were Not only were these burgers as thin as a anorexic on a hunger strike they lacked any type of flavor The Pastrami and the oversized bun completely overshadowed any flavor the burger had To be honest the Parmesan truffle fries beer and good service were the best things about our visit The burger was a afterthought Seriously people Wheres the beef The bottom line on DMK burger bar is a sad one A good waitstaff beautifully laid out bar and good selection of beers cant make up for how overpriced and bland the burgers are I would stop in any time for a couple of brews but I will pass on the paper thin burger

Author: Melanie S.
Content: I have been anxious to try DMK since it first opened but the long waits kept me awayLast Thursday before BAS seemed like a great time to make my first visit here since it would be early enough to avoid the crowd and long wait time And the fact that it was so close to Sheffields made it a perfect choiceI got there before my friend who was running late and had my pick of seats I took a two top and stared longingly at the menu The sweet waitress Kiley came over and greeted me I ordered their house cherry soda which was deliciously cold and refreshing I dont drink a lot of soda and this was a nice change of pace from the canned crapI waited and Kiley came over and asked me if I wanted to order anything to nibble on before my friend arrived Ok twist my arm I got the parmesan fries with truffle cream that Caroline M raved about All I can say is that its a good thing my friend came when she did as I had a really hard time not eating all those fries Holy crap were they good They were crispy and had a generous dusting of parmesan on top and the truffle cream was to die forSince it was my first time there I opted to just get the standard burger with no fancy toppings I figure that if they can get that right Id be back and go with a more adventurous burgerMy friend must have been thinking the same thing since she ordered the same We also got an order of sweet potato fries as we are big fans and an order of macaroni and cheese Yes were pigs and we always order too much foodI dont recall being asked what temperature I wanted my burger cooked but it came to the table mediumrare which is my preference The burger was perfectly adequate but nothing craveworthy I think I enjoyed my burger more than friend because she left half of hersWe both agreed that the mac and cheese was a bit oily and bland and I thought the pasta was dried out like it had been baked for way too longThe sweet potato fries were heavenly and accompanied by a lemon tabasco dipping sauce which I still cant figure out if I liked or not To be honest the fries were so good that they didnt anything but a sprinkling of saltAt 800 the burger prices are fair but theyre offset by the prices for the fries and other sides which I think are a bit high for the portion sizeDays later I am still dreaming and drooling over those fries so while I may or may not go back for a burger those fries are calling my name35 stars

Author: Lauren D.
Content: OK it is with great angst that I bestow 2 stars upon DMK burger  But I had to do it  mostly to save all the rest of yall from losing your hearing and maybe so that you can choose to spend 2 hours eating a burger that is at least as good if not better in a lets just say more desirable atmosphereI will never understand the restaurants that decide they are going to play music so loudly that you have to yell to the person sitting next to you in order to have a conversation  The ceilings are high the acoustics are terrible  A restaurantfull of people screaming to their neighbors  one giant headache  It also really prevented me from even enjoying my dinner I couldnt wait to get out of there so I could ask my dining companion what on EARTH we were trying to talk about because Im pretty sure that it would not have mattered if we had both been speaking different languagesAnyway  The Greek salad is good as is the caesar  The sweet potato fries are also good as are the salt and pepper fries  The burgers are fine  Personally Ive tasted juicier and bigger and more flavorful  but I guess thats subjective  Service and host staff  totally fine no complaints  For any of you who might go into DMK and ask them to turn the music down apparently the owner WANTS it to be that loud  I am in no rush to come back here  Id rather go somewhere I actually want to sit for a couple of hours or at least Kumas where there is an option to sit outside and NOT LOSE YOUR HEARING

Author: Andrea R.
Content: When a business first opens they usually have some kinks to work out  While free refills um bad economy and hot beverages um its cold in Chicago would be some nice improvements theyve got a good thing going on hereThere is a long list of burgers to choose from and if beef isnt your thing me you can always substitute a turkey burger I cant remember the name of my burger or actually I think they are numbered but it was topped with marinated portabello brie cheese yum and a dijonaise passed on this  It tasted unbelievable  may just be in the top 5 turkey burgers Ive had in my lifetime Yeah that goodEven better than the burgerthe sweet potato fries I ordered the small for myself but kind of wished I ordered the large And no I wasnt going to share them with my fabulous colleagues Jelena Z and Johnny TThe people who work here are as cool as the burgers Our waitress Lauren was a real sweetheart super helpful and was even apologetic that she couldnt give us free refills And the GM Eli was the host with the most not to mention easy on the eyes for any of you single ladies out thereI see many turkey burgers and sweet potato fries in my future

Author: Derrick T.
Content: Four of us come on a Thursday night to catch the Bears game and we have a one hour wait  This place is hoppin for its third night that its been open and theres no doubt why  This burger bar is the love child of Michael of MK fame and David of Mortons fame  No wonder the huge hypeNice layout two TVs above the bar but with this kinda yuppie business crowd no one was watching the game  Heck DMK wasnt even broadcasting the sound from the game though I cant complain with the nice selection of Sam Cooke and other classic musicians  Good selection of beers 30 artisanal  NiceCustomer service was phenomenal even if my roommates attributes it to Michael and David both being there who were playing great hosts btw  Friendly servers with lots of smiles starting up conversation and making you feel right at home  Id venture to say one of the hostesses was being fairly flirty  Onto the foodParmesan Truffle Fries  Excellent  What the heck is in that dipping sauce  We could drink that stuff straightSweet Potato Fries  Also excellent  Seasoned perfectly  Another great choiceMac and Cheese  Pretty good but not outstanding  If youre having trouble deciding between this and fries go with the fries  Much better choice1 Burger aka standard BBQ burger Aged Cheddar smoked bacon balsamic red onions bbq sauce  Good flavors well crisped bacon nice balance overall  An excellent goto burger that you know will be good 2 Burger aka blue cheese burger chilli rubbed onion strings blue cheese tomatoes chipotle ketchup  Again great balance blue cheese had just enough kick to stand out but not overwhelm nice4 Burger aka  Roasted hatch green chile fried farm egg jack cheese smoked bacon  This was my personal favorite of the night as the spice was deliciously sweet and spicy at the same time  What can I say Im a sucker for well made chiles12 Veggie Portobello sandwich Crispy portobello arugula tomatos horseradish  Only had a bite but not bad primary eat complained that the portobello really absorbed a lot of the oil from frying and it was a little too greasy for his tastesAnd I want to end with my all time favorite part of the mealCoffee milkshake  Homemade ice cream with chocolate nibs throughout  Im a huge sucker for a good milkshake and Im pretty ridiculously picky I have to say I was disappointed that there was no strawberry milkshake option my personal fave but this coffee was really a great treat  I would go back just for this shake alone even if the rest of the food was that greatVerdictService  ExcellentFood quality  Quite goodCost vs Value  Quite goodI dont know that Id be willing to wait an hour for this kind of meal again but I would be wrong in saying that this wasnt a great experience  The burgers a mere 8 each are conceived well and the flavors blend nicely  Unfortunately this place was more of a yuppiebusiness bar for people last night than an actual burger bar feel  It just seemed people were here more to be seen than to actually enjoy the mealRoom for improvement  Ask how customers want their burgers  With MK and Mortons at helm I have no doubt a rare burger would have been phenomenal here but they do they all to a medium or medium rare across the board45 stars if only I could give it on Yelp for being a phenomenal burger joint but the crown of burger places still belongs to another for nowCongrats on the successful opening  Cant wait to come back for more

Author: Michael G.
Content: There are only a few skills that I picked up in student government back in college that I still use on a regular basis  One is the ability to eat like the wind and still enjoy the taste of food  Running late for a relaxing facial how ironic is that I got to put this skill of highstress power eating to good use at DMKIt appeared to me that ordinarily DMK would be extremely relaxing  The dark interior and large tables from which easy banter floated to me at the bar seemed a counterpoint to my oneman burger eating contest  The beer list said to me stop and enjoy our huge selection of American craft beers  But my watch said enjoy your water and like it  Or maybe that was just my inner voice hopefully  Either way I have to say that DMK was an excellent enabler and my burger was out before I could even check my phone to do my first time checkThe veggie burger I got stands on its own as meal  which was good because this place is alacarte and I didnt have a lot of extra money though a Foursquare checkin is good for a free small fry of any sort here  It was sort of a mixture between a fake meat patty and a loose veggie one  It crumbles to the point where a fork is necessary but I was actually able to eat it like a meat burger despite the speed I was engulfing it  Or maybe it was helped by that fact  And the flavors were rich  From the cheese to the chick peas each ingredient made for excitement in my mouth  It was one of the best veggie burgers Ive had in ChicagoMy disappointment actually came with the fries because who doesnt love a side of disappointment  I got the sea salt and pepper variety  Its not one of their signature specialty fries per se but I figured its the old standby so they would do them right  They were flavorless  I tried adding the ketchup that came with them  Nothing  I asked for mustard  Nothing  They even supplied me with Dijon mustard  Fancy nothing  They were free for me as I mentioned but had they been the normal 2 it would raised my ire to the point where I would have really needed the neck massage I was about to receive up the streetI would definitely come back when I had some time to sample the beers  But as far as this review which I think took longer to write than it did to dine there Im just giving it an aok and not just because its the fastest rating to write

Author: Liz W.
Content: Burgers tasty fries and great beers What more do you people needStarted out here with beer Yes it was barely noon And After talking up my love of wheats that is what we had here I went with the smooth Allagash Just awesome It made me very happy My sister went with the much zippier Gumballhead good but I wouldnt have been as happy The pine is a bit too much for me My sister adored it thoughIt was tough picking out a burger I wanted everything Finally I settled on 5 bison goat cheese pickled onion and blueberry BBQ sauce My sister went with the 1 beef burger with aged cheddar smoked bacon charred balsamic onions and Rufus Teagues BBQ sauce I loved mine It was truly a perfect combo of flavors My sisters was really good but mine was the clear winner Burgers are perfect bunmeat ratio as is you can add a patty but I would notThe fries we selected were both awesome I preferred my pick of sweet potato fries with lemon tobasco aioli sweet heaven I wanted to bathe in that sauce Together with the fries it was the ideal sweetsoursaltyspicy feel Oh my The truffle cream fries are so rich with the thready parmesan and decadent sauce Wow are they lovely We got greedy and added on some deviled eggs that remind me of my Grans We were ready to bust but man what a way to go They were only 2 bucks so we figured what the hellJust when we were all blissed out they threw us a couple of freebie peanut butter malts My sister called it heaven in a cup and it was her fave part of this meal Good lord it was deliciously evilThe vibe here is great The server and hostess were friendly and speedy Kelly was way on the ball and we loved her Give this place a whirl you will not regret it

Author: Carolynne M.
Content: Hm There seems to be a little bit of a disconnect here  And I am pretty sure it is on DMKs end rather than mine  If you are going to call yourself a Burger Bar well then holy hoppin Jesus you need the burger to be the star of the show  After last night the burger I had was dead last behind the fries behind the beer even behind a 2 plate of deviled eggs  Did I order wrong  I mean I tried to order what I thought would be the most flavourful burger on the menu  the 2 which was topped with ChiliRubbed Onion Strings Amish Blue Cheese and Spicy Chipotle Ketchup  Except the bun was huge and overwhelmed everything The onion strings were completely flavourless There was a teaspoon of ketchup which tasted nothing of chipotle or spice and a rather meager bit of blue cheese  The meat itself was fine but the patty was supermodel thin  Had this been a 4 burger or an 8 that came with a side and a drink I would have been a lot more forgiving  But I cannot justify 8 for thatThey redeemed themselves with the fries though  we sampled both the Parmesan truffle and the sweet potato  Both were cooked perfectly with excellent ratios of spices and good dipping sauces that accompanied them  I also sampled the deviled egg which had a nice creamy filling and a firm egg white shell  The French Country Ale that I had to drink was a good beer too not too heavy or hoppyMaybe DMK should nix the whole burger idea and just stick with being a bar that serves snacks They seem to do that end really well  And as for the idea that they are Kumas competition  Sorry I just had a laughing fit  I am better now

Author: A W.
Content: Seriously Dont believe the hype DMK  Dinky Meat Krumpets yes I know its actually crumpets I dont care what kind of grass the cows they cook up eat They are not eating enough of it or they just are being stingy with how much of that grassfed cow they are giving me The burgers are the thickness of what you would get at like Steak and Shake BUT for 8 Dayuuuuuum You dont get a side with that either Just a really thin burger on a chewy dense bun I got the 6 Marinated Portobello Blue Brie Griddled Scallions Dijonnaise The scallions were whole and werent easy to bite into I took those off The brie did not complement the dijionnaise at all I tasted nothing out of the ordinary with the portobellos for them to have been marinated And then the burger was so nonexistent What little was there was very good but I felt like I was just having an appetizer rather than an entree For seriousMy dinner companion got the the 3 NY Pastrami French Gruyere Sauerkraut Leroys Remoulade I liked his much better than mine but still didnt think that much better of it He got sweet potato fries too tried one and it tasted like a slightly sweet white potato fry No really For seriousOh and drinkswise I saw housemade pop for 3 and the rest beer 3 pop You might as well just get a beer Now the service was great and friendly  Our food came out in a timely manner and was hot  We were well attended to and our waitress had a very nice demeanor I will say it is loud in there and not a good place to try to hold a real conversation Often I could barely hear him or the nice waitress over the loud volume of the music and the other patrons trying to talk over it as well It was like a shouting match with no prizes Overall meh Cute concept but for me it doesnt deliver much

Author: John B.
Content: So Im on the way to my dentist this morning and the Brown Line isnt stopping at Wellington or Diversey which means I walk down Sheffield from Belmont which is only three blocks so I should be walking anyway But the result of said walk is that I pass right by DMK Burger Bar DMKs been at the back of my mind for some time but it hasnt been in the front of my mind enough to make a special trip But here I am with a 1215 appointment which means Im out by 1 which means lunch is servedI walk in and I like DMK Its a little dark and its a little loud but its pretty laid back and welcoming which is what you want a burger bar to be First for the bar terrific Nice selection of beers a couple of big TVs but since its not a game day theyre playing A Bugs Life Interesting Its a seat yourself place but it doesnt seem like a seat yourself place but the bartender catches my eye and gives me the drill so were all goodThe tables are set with menus and drink menus knife and fork setups The flatware is wrapped in what appear to be bar towels which sets you up for a messy experience The menus are angled which sets up a nice tension I like the attention to detailI end up going with the bison burger because its highlighted on the menu and it sounds interesting Im torn between fries and the fried okra and pickles but the server tells me shes a fan of the fried vegs so I get them When the food comes out I get both the pickles and the fries  parm fries with truffle cream The server tells me she wanted me to try the fries and theyre on the house so thats a bonusSo the food which is what you came here for The fried pickles and okra are excellent Light crispy batter that doesnt overwhelm Side of ranch which works well The fries are good but the parm doesnt really work Its shredded parm and not really integrated with the fries so its like a plate of fries wearing a cheese wig The size of the order is perfect though An order for one is 2 or 3 bucks so its easy to get a bunch of these and share SmartThe burger is good  but Its a bison burger with blue cheese pickled red onions and blueberry bbq sauce The cheese is virtually nonexistent The sauce is a schmear Not even a schmear Now I dont need my burger drippings with goo but the toppings are there to set off the burger and my toppings set off for another burger barIm gonna use the K word here A lot of people are comparing DMK to Kumas I dont know if this is a rivalry DMK instigated or if its just in the minds of the reviewers or what But theres no point in comparing DMK to Kumas Not because Kumas is so much better  Im not a fan of Kumas whose burgers are drippings with goo But because theyre not even trying to do the same thing Yes they both serve beer and specialty burgers End of comparisonThe lowdown Three stars because Ill probably be back Theres a lot thats good about this place but theyre in their third year and I feel like theyre slacking off a bit Which would be too bad

Author: Richie D.
Content: An over all Good for DMKThe prices good food good ambiance goodI was happy to see some unique DMK trademarks  Housemade sodas blood orange cherry and lime lambturkey burgers homemade sauces smokey ketchup lemon tabasco alioli and dijonnaise the soft porn story on the wall of the mens washroom HA I bet I got all the straight guys attentionCoolWhat made my experience worthwhile were a free ale taster in a shot glass sweet potato fries duh option of turkeyveggielamb burger and our waitress  I loved our waitress Lauren for all the attention she paid to our table her lovely smile outgoing personality and willingness to alter premade burgers  They allow you to exchange a turkey burger for a beef burger but not when it comes to lamb  Thankfully they gave me permission to swap out a precreated burger with a lamb burger  Gyro in a patty goodnessAs for any newish restaurant a few recommendations to keep in mind Add a few more game burgers to the menu like bison my personal favorite  venison kangaroo perhaps  Learn from The Shanty up in Wadsworth IL  Put on the menu the option to switch in a lamb burger and veggie burger with the precreated creations  The cupcakes are fairly small in size for 250 but not overpriced I guess and the ice cream sandwiches were average  Im sad I didnt get a malt instead because I wasnt impressed  I still left here with a bit of hungies even after putting 20 down  Arg

Author: Sarah B.
Content: When I am looking for somewhere to eat out burgers are usually not my draw  I am not a big meat eater  But a date suggested DMK and I had heard good things so off we wentHoly cow or lamb in my case my burger was tasty  I had the lamb burger with feta cucumbers tomatoes and red onion  I have never had a tastier burger no joke  So juicy flavorful and filling  So GoodDMK was a bit loud for my taste and the communal tables never make me too happy but I cant stop thinking about that lamb burger so I will be back

Author: Melissa R.
Content: Here it is in a nutshell fresh and delicious burgers and fries good and friendly service weekend nights are very busy reasonable prices extremely loud DMK is a much needed addition to this area Surprisingly there arent all that many restaurants within a 12 mile radius but there is a brown line stop and lots of residents I wasnt sure what to expect of this place but it was better that what I anticipatedand now I come here fairly often Another great thing All ages enjoy this place Last time I ate here there were teenagers families babies senior citizens and your typical 2030s who live in Lakeview The ingredients are fresh and tasty You can tell when you dive into your meal that each burger is made to order I always go with 8 if it aint broke dont fix it and it never disappoints Besides tasting great they are also pretty normal serving sizes ie not the size of your head so you can leave feeling full but not uncomfortable The fries are fantastic with the skin on and salty a small order can easily be split between two people Watch out for the ketchup they serve with themit has a little kick to it and I always end up asking for a side of regular ketchup to go with them Here are a few reasons I know I am getting old all of the employees look like they are in college perhaps they are and the volume of the music is horribly loud I mean I just want to eat a burgernot have a dance party It is so loud that you have to yell to hear the person next to you and I really hate that Overall I am a fan of this place With minor improvements I would easily upgrade them to five stars

Author: Ryan Y.
Content: I wanted to love this place  When my wife and I went here last night I foresaw visions of bragging to my friends and bringing them back to this place I hoped could compete with the burgerheavyweights of Chicago  After all everyone and their cousin has been raving about itDisappointed does not begin to sum it up  Started off fine I thought as we were offered a variety of seating options by the hostess and opted for the bar  Nice beer list though being a frequent purchaser of such beers many were overpriced North Shore Distillery prominently placed on shelving  The menu was pretty good and my wife and I made our selections 1 and 3 Salt n Pepper Fries and Friend Okra and Pickles and waited  And waited During this waiting I was not offered one refill on my empty beverage a real petpeeve of mine  I started off with the Blood Orange homemade usually a favorite but theirs was a bit lacking  Wife had Diet Coke that was poured from a 2Liter bottle  I was finally able to snatch a refill Diet Coke this time and was told there are no free refills  So what that translates to is 250 per soda being poured out of a 2Liter bottle from Jewel that cost about 100 and will serve about 8 people an 8oz glass of soda  You can finish the math and realize how ridiculous this isNext I received my burger or should I say their burger since you are allowed no say in the cooking of said burger  It was good again even after the crap service I really wanted to like it but it was just good  The fries and fried okra and pickles were good too but it was just standardThe guy behind the bar playing the part of our lackluster server clearly noticed how unhappy I was with the experience and rather than try and improve service and my experience ignored us even more  Thusly losing a customer and gaining a crappy Yelp review  Even after he took our plates and brought a box for the 2nd half of my wifes burger he didnt bring our bill  NOTE TO ALL SERVERS Typically when someone is packing up  their food they are ready to leave  We honestly waited another 5 minutes or so hoping to catch his eye so we could get our check and leave  I paid 10 for 2 sodas each refilled once an otherwise reasonable fare for what should have been better food and the worst service Ive experienced in an overhyped restaurantSo long DMK I really really REALLY wanted to dine with you more often but alas your bartenderserver has ensured that shall never happen

Author: Leanne A.
Content: What a pleasant experience All the employees were incredibly sweet and helpful The room is crowded but warm and  cozy The food was incredible I got the turkey burger with swiss arugula and dijon I bit in to that thing and I literally paused for a moment to communicate with the Gods I even liked the sweet potato fries and rarely do My mouth is watering thinking of the little leftovers waiting in the fridge I cant help but compare to the Counter Overall the burger was better at DMK and the place is way better However I like that I can get extra things like tomato and avocado at the counter Because who can deny that avocado makes everything better No oneI will be back Probably soon before the lines start forming around the block

Author: Beth R.
Content: Note this review requires a sophisticated understanding of elementary school math specifically averages  This is a 4star review but thats because there were 5star elements and 3star elements to my experience  Those numbers added together and divided result in the number 4  If you are not too intimidated by this level of complexity I invite you to read on  5star elementsThe veggie burger was great  full of veggies crumbly but crusty around the perimeter It comes with a pesto mayo and just enough of it  I like pesto so so so much but only like mayo a little  The amount spread on the bun was perfecto  Theres a bonus veg eggplant  This burger rocks  In addition to the veggie burger theres another vegetarian option in the portabella mushroom sandwich  I do like me some portabella on a sandwich but at DMK my heart belongs to the veggie burger  Still props3star elementsThe fries were pretty standard  Im currently on a sea salt and cracked black pepper kick thanks Kettle Chips so I was psyched for their fries but I couldnt get much pepper essence  The service was a little meh  The drinks my dining companion and I had were both mediocre the Diet Coke is literally a can and costs 175 75 more than the vending machine at work  The iced tea was a little watery which was okay on the day in question since I was hot and schvitzy and needed to rehydrate  Plus it was refillable unlike the can of popSo all told Id make this a destination for the veggie burger but thats about it

Author: Misty S.
Content: 2 words  TRUFFLE FRIES  Wow were these amazing and why hadnt anyone told me about them  These perfectly cooked fries were covered in parmesan and accompanied by an amazing truffle creme sauce  My taste buds didnt know what hit them and were dizzy from rapture  MmmmEven though they have an extensive beer selection I was not in the mood for the usual libation  Instead I opt for a delicious blood mary which came with an okra of all things  OKRA  The drink was nicely spiced and was just really good  The service was great  There were about 10 of us and we were able to push a few tables together to accommodate the entire group

Author: An P.
Content: Walking in from Sheffields me and a buddy stopped into DMK Burger Bar to try out one of Chicagos newest and trendiest spots I was first surprised by the large DMK sign out front and noticed the big window as I stepped in It was around 730pm or so and DMK was jam packed to the brim There was nowhere to sit and I wasnt sure if there was a line or not but it was filled with the denizens of Wrigleyville and beyondFortunately for us we landed a seat right in the back of the restaurant in the corner It was loud enough that we didnt have to listen to the conversations of the other table although talking took a bit more volume due to the loudness of the whole place DMKs ceiling renders the place partdive while the new interior kind of reminded me of Simones in Pilsen The server came and took drink orders and came back in time for us to order We split an order of fried okra while I went with the 1 and my buddy took a 6 The okra came out quickly but I was disappointed by the bitesized portions Seriously it had the resemblance of 1015 small pieces of the length of a toothpick with the width of a pencil For 5 we housed through it very quickly and probably would have been better off with a 4 basket of fries seasoned with vinegar and saltThe burgers eventually came and I had a tall grass fed burger with bacon and fried egg Like most tall grass fed burgers the meat was tender but I was surprised that there was no trace of the flame broiled or charcoal on the burger It really did taste like a regular bar burger and didnt impress my palette even though the bacon was very good The meat just didnt do it for me and it lacked the smokiness or true flavorTo recap for 32  6 tip we got2 burgers1 undersized portion of fried okra1 Diet Coke1 beerThe value proposition is just not there this is probably why I avoid trendy spots

Author: Ariel L.
Content: Whoah Nelly  Whats with all the hype on this place  I keep reading about it in every paper and magazine i pick up  Find something else to write about people  On to the goodsThis place is Average at best  The burger was on the normal sized size had an average tasting bun and was cooked to a leathery consistency  That is not how i like my burgers  Yes they had an excellent selection of french fry choices and and beers on tap but if you want to call yourself a burger joint you better make a good burger  FAIL  I would go to Five Guys in a heart beat over this place  At least there you get free refills on your soda  And whats with the mention of burgers to come on the menu  You are advertising burgers that may or may not make the menu eventually  I dont get it  Save your money and go elsewhere  Id rather wait in line for an hour at Kumas then eat here again  There are just too many good burgers in the city to waste your time on a place like this

Author: Kathryn M.
Content: Ive been twice now and heres what Ive gatheredThe Good1 Price of burger compared to quality of ingredients  Mmm blue brie2 Beer list selection3 Chipotle Ketchup 5 stars just for this4 Fried pickleokra appetizer5 I actually liked that the burgers werent enormous  I only ate half my burger on both occasions plus the fries and fried goods and I was stuffedFor the neighborhood I much prefer a place like this over something like the Counter  DMK just felt warmer and cozierThe Not so Good1 Really youre gonna be a burger joint where everything comes cooked Medium Plus What the heck is Medium Plus anyway  Both of my dining companions were looking for a nice medium rare so this was a disappointment  2 and 3 Service was extremely friendly but we sat with empty drinks for quite awhile and we never got that extra ketchup we requested   Seriously empty beverages can ruin a meal  But Ill let it go    this time

Author: Jess P.
Content: 0 starsfor a HORRIBLE RESTAURANT1 TERRIBLE SEATINGthey sit you across from you party at a crowded table where you cant even hear the person across from you and are actually closer to the stranger next to youFUN2 my friend ordered the milkshakei tasted itmcdonalds mcflurry would taste betterand FIVE dollars for that3 After looking at the menu and realizing that the two things that appealed to me were coming soon and unavailablewth why were they even on the menu not goodso I had to choose from the ONLY SIX burgers that were on the menu and some fries4 Waited an HOUR for 2 burgers and some french fries It was a Sunday nightnot super packed how the hell could it take that long5 Everyone seemed to be complaining about the horrible service both people on each side of usI know this since I was forced to hear their conversations bc we were seated ridiculously close6 FINALLY get our foodSUBPARmy burger was DRENCHED in bbq sauce and was served on a 4 plate really Give me a plate to eat on  7 French fries were grosssoggy and drenched in feta cheesetooooo much8 Dont try to serve unique contemporary dishes until you can make a simple one correct or at least get your customer service under control9 VERY disappointedwe were not the only patrons that left angryI would suggest going anywhere but here10 Perhaps it is the kind of place where you need to be wasted to enjoy itwellyou can enjoy a burger that is probably better anyway from somewhere less that EIGHT DOLLARS for a crappy burger that doesnt even include fries I believe fries were an extra 4 or 5 somethingafter a milkshake 2 burgers and an order or fries that we split our bill was 33GIANT WASTE OF MONEY

Author: Diana R.
Content: Never argue with the chef  Sometimes you want a burger your way and not the way the chef has it laid out on the menu dijonmayonnaise Im really not a fan of dijon so I asked for it on the side but my lovely waitress informed me that its really good on the burger and that she too hates dijon I decided to try it as the chef intended and I am so glad I did It was delicious  Turkey burger heaven and the truffle fries were good tooSo why only 4 stars I like to have my own table not share with two other parties but thats just me

Author: Mike K.
Content: The third time was a charm  After finding a line and a wait on the first two attempts to dine at DMK we have finally hit paydirt and dined at DMK  Ill try to keep it simple since there are already 700 reviewsThe burgers  Like The Counter theyre all about the toppings which are good but I think the burger should be the main focus with the accoutrements only adding to the taste  The burger itself honestly didnt have a whole lot of taste  Id rate the burger about equal with Five Guys but not as good as Portillos  There are better sitdown burgers out thereThe fries  They have five or six varieties and two sizes  If youre a party of two opt for the small 2 version  We had the salt and pepper fries  The fries were good but the topping was overkill  And I like salt and pepper flavoring on chips  I wouldnt order this flavor again if I were to returnThe drinks  I had a blood orange pop  Three bucks  The flavor was extremely strong verging on the same overkill as the salt and pepper fries  It was served in a pint glass loaded with ice  I was lucky if I got 12 ounces out of it  The atmosphere  Its loud  The place was half full and I still had to lean over to hear the little lovely sitting two feet away from me  I would imagine if the place were full that everyone would practically have to scream to be heard and that the music would also be cranked  The value  The eight dollar burger is deceptive  Where DMK dings you is on the fries not included with the burgers and drinks  In the end youre paying 10 for a burger and fries anyway  Id return if there were no wait and if the place were not packed  Its 312 stars

Author: Jerry C.
Content: So I had gravy fries the salad with tuna and also the bison burgerThe gravy fries were awesome and the salad with tuna was not bad but it was more of an experimentation for me i hadnt had tuna in awhile and realized i still dont really like it  The bison burger was nice I believe mine was medium rare though they never asked and it tasted pretty goodI enjoy the atmosphere and the music was excellentMy only concern was the bill  See the burger was about 10 and the rest of the extras were probably another 10But my bill came out to be over 100 due to hidden chargesHidden charges you say  What kind of hidden charges  Well the medical bill that came along with the meal due to food poisoning that incapacitated me for the next 4 days and actually still counting  Along with only being able to eatdrink gruel chicken broth tea and water for that durationI mean if it werent for the bill the pain the sacrifice of good food for several days after my DMK experience and other unspoken additions diarrhea  I might go back and I would recommend it to everyone elseTo be fair I would give it a much better review and recommend it to other people if it werent for it promptly destroying me for several daysThough I might be the less than 1 who got it but would you like to play food russian roullette and possibly win

Author: Brian M.
Content: I have a feeling Im going to struggle with DMK A highly anticipated place from a respected chef thats right down the street from me AND serves classic cocktails and craft beers I was in love with the idea of the place The menu is superb and the alacarte style allows you to easily sample a lot of their offerings in a few visits Ive been in here a few times the first of which was for lunch on their second day open a couple of early weekday evenings and the most recent of which was this past Friday night so Ive seen them operate when its slow and when its slammed Afternoon it clocks in at a solid 4star spot Busy2 Like many restaurants opting for larger communal tables instead of the whole hostessstandandsmalltable thing its often a bit confusing upon entering On a busy Friday I saw quite a few different parties walk in and stand confused and ungreeted because the hostess was off looking for a party whose table was ready Our supposed hour wait turned into an hour and 45 minutes as we watched large groups seated quicker than our table for two Afternoons though Ive always been warmly greeted upon entering There need to be adjustments made to accommodate the busy times  At the bar like most of Chicago these folks know their bourbon and classic cocktails The bartenders are quick and attentive know their stuff and make solid recommendations Why do I know about recommendations Because the last time I was there they were out of two different kinds of bourbon yet they were still on the menu board You know the menu board made of movable plastic letters that is easily changed to reflect current offerings They try hard with the beer but there were a few things that irked this beer nerd First of all a farmhouse ale poured in an oversized wine glassglobe shouldnt have a 3finger head 2 at most preferably less Secondly if I order a bottled beer this was at my table on a nonbusy day you should bring the bottle out to the table and pour it there Dont just bring a glass of beer Thats a nono in the beer world As for the food I can only personally comment on the vegetarian options and sides Their homemade veggie patty has gotten better since the first time I had it and for that I commend DMK Spicy thick and now correctly sized for the bun Im a fan The stuffed portobello is pretty much just a fried shroom The breading is a bit thick  the outer edges are just fried breading thats a bit bland The middle of the burger was much better just because the mushroom made up for the overbreading Otherwise the portobello was perfectly cooked juicy and tender and well enhanced by the tomato and arugula Now when things got busy I dont know what happened back there The roommate ordered the burger with bacon and an egg on it It came out with a single strip of bacon Huh The fries here are solid especially at 2 for a small plate Ive had the sweet potato fries truffle fries and classic salt and pepper all of which were fresh and crisp When it was slower the lemon tobasco aioli that comes with the sweet potato fries was pretty good I thought it was a bit light on the lemon but my lovely dining partner thought it was a bit heavy Either way decent But during a busy dinner hour with my buddy who was there for the first time it amounted to nothing more than mayonnaise Seriously Thinking it was a bad cup the server brought another one Same stuffno bueno Perhaps Im being a bit picky but Michael Kornick and David Morton are respected professionals and the bar gets set a bit higher After my subpar experience DMK actually responded to my Twitter post Im glad theyre paying attention and Im confident they will not be content with average reviews even if the restaurant remains full I know theyre capable of delivering nearperfection but I havent seen ityet

Author: Anne C.
Content: The atmosphere is great for watching a game or just for socializing with some friends The menu is very limited and small They dont have a lot of familiar burger choices but more interesting combination of ingredients I chose the 5 which was the bison burger with goat cheese onions and blueberry BBQ sauce The BBQ sauce tasted just like blueberries which sounds weird on a burger but it was pretty good  I got it on the side I also like how the meat is grass fed and the bread is artesian very yummy The prices are pretty high considering its 9 for one burger bison was 11 and you dont get any sides with it The sides are all alacart Thus your meal can get pricey fast The servers were down to earth and chill and our waters were refilled right away One downfall is our server never asked how I wanted my meat cooked and I too forgot about it so it came out medium and I prefer well done Also the place had an odor of cat piss maybe the mix from cleaning solution and vomit from the night before Who knows but I did not enjoy the scent Our server gave us the bill too early making us feel a bit rushed but I guess as a server you never really know when the right time is perhaps we could have been rushing All in all Id come back here again for a drink and a burger

Author: David R.
Content: Back again so soon  Sure why not  Just like last time it was all about the location and circumstance  Monday midafternoon on a holiday weekend  Thank you for being openSome of the details rubbed me the wrong way though  Did I mention that it was a weekday midafternoon  You would never know by how LOUD and dark it was in the back of the place  Geez  And they didnt even have any cool movies on this time  It also annoyed me that the 175 soda is a 12ounce can  It was a hot day and I wanted to guzzle diet cola until I floated away  Also after being practically smothered on my first visit this time our waitress was an absentee  And most irksome of all  the dishtowel napkins left little white fuzzies on my clothes againI just didnt mention it before  ArghBut anyway I enjoyed my meal more than last time  The 6 burger was nearly perfectmarinated portobello blue brie griddled scallions dijonnaise  I ordered the macaroni and cheese 2 without the bacon I just wanted the gruyere and balsamic onions Id have to give the dish a B  But somehow I loved the salt and pepper fries even more than last time  I could eat those crispy little bastards until I keeled overI am kicking myself for neglecting to order a deviled egg  That would have been so perfectly decadent  Next time

Author: Andie S.
Content: YUM I got the 4 which had a fried egg bacon and something spicy pepper jalapenos and it was AWESOME I mean so awesome I didnt even want to tell anyone how awesome it was so they wouldnt take bites of my awesome burger away from me The sweet potato fries and the truffle parmesan fries were both pretty averagely good but extra good with their sauces But that burgerthat was awesomeTake your food to go though Its busy

Author: Kathleen M.
Content: Lamb burger  Baaaa DMK I am so yoursThis was todays destination in our Adventure Fridays quest  We arrived about 1145 on a Friday and snagged one of the last open tables  We got waited on right away and amused ourselves by trying to figure out the school group that was eating there  Field trip  Reward  New CPS lunch program In moments  our drinks arrived  Blood Orange soda was bloody brilliant  I had the lamb burger with the olive tapenade on the side which I loved  My sister had the veggie burger with the mayo on the side and my daughter had the cheese burger plus fried egg  We devoured every delicious morsel and made a good dent in a plate of sweet potato fries and a cheddar cheese and scallions fries  What a delicious mealMy only issue was that the music was VERY VERY LOUD WHAT DID YOU SAY  THE MUSIC WAS VERY VERY LOUD   HUH  DR SEUSS WAS PLOWED  SICK OF THE CLOUDSExactly

Author: MELEK L.
Content: I enjoyed lunch on a weekday at DMK and it was just perfect Youll find all kinds of folks munching on juicy burgers in this slick barrestaurant Mine came with cheddar and bacon I was surprised by how much I appreciated the bun and by how I ATE THE WHOLE THING Besides devouring the entire burger I scarfed the Sea Salt  Pepper fries Im not even a fry fan usually but these rocked my world I also managed to find one of my favorite Stout beers available here and for a great price nonethelessWith a friendly staff and fast service on a weekday for lunch I will definitely be back and will continue suggesting DMK for others

Author: Melissa R.
Content: DMK  Overrated My first time here it was just eh ok The bf liked it Me not so muchFirst off the servers congregated to the end of the bar and had mouths like truckers No bueno in my book Complaining about customers in front of other customers is not coolThe burger was ok I mean I wanted to add certain ingredients but there are no substitutions Who does that and I wanted it medium rare That means with a little pink in the middle Mine was well done BooOne star for the sweet potato fries though Nicely doneThe next time I came in with my friend on a Thursday night Place is packed The waiting time for a table was quoted 30 minutes for 2 people however we seen atleast 6 empty tables The bar was packed with people The bartender was not nice She acted like we were bothering her for our order Ewwww So we order our drinks A can of Brooklyn Lager and one of their specialty drinks The bartender says to the other bartender like i have fng time for this  Really You are a bartender You make drinks I liked the beer though And 12 dollars for a martini reallyNot a fan Go somewhere else in the neighborhood for a burger and friendlier service

Author: Tina W.
Content: Yum This is probably the tastiest burger I have had in Chicago Unlike Counter and Kumas DMK burgers did not fall apart upon connecting to my mouth They also didnt make my stomach feel like shit afterwards In fact I took a 12h plane ride immediately afterwards and had no adverse side effects The personnel consisted entirely of lovely young blonds which may whet some appetites They were very attentive conscientious and friendly The music was too loud for my liking seems to be a common complaint for me especially at noon when I went to eat there  I had the cheddar bacon and onion burger and it was delicious It didnt have too many flavors going on and the BBQ sauce was mouthwatering My boyfriend had a spicy burger with and egg in it that he liked but I thought was so so They have five  types of fries including sweet potato fries with a lovely lemon Tabasco aioli sauce that made me swoon The homemade sodas cherry and blood orange left something to be desired

Author: Jeff K.
Content: This place gets lots of hype and is good but not worth a wait though This burger joint is solid all around from beer menu to sides and different choicesThe negatives are its ALWAYS too loud to talk to one another and the beef just isnt there and the buns are too flimsy  Also they are touchy on their homemade ketchup Overall its just a place to be seen not get a top 5 burger in the city

Author: Chris C.
Content: I dont know what all the hype is about this place  The burgers reminded me of those at SteaknShakethinner and kind of loose for a lack of a better word  The toppings were interestingI got the 4 with fried egg green chiles and bacon and my wife got the 2 with bleu cheese and onion strips  We had to scrape the green chiles off of my burger because the taste was so overwhelmingit tasted much better without them but was still nothing special  My wifes burger was pretty good  It had a nice spice to it  We also ordered the Wisconsin cheddar fries with green onions  They were good but there was too much cheese on them  By the time we neared the bottom the fries were covered in the cheddar which had thickened as it cooled  We couldnt even eat the bottom portion of our fries there was so much cheese  For dessert we ordered the chocolate chip ice cream sandwich and the server was kind enough to have it cut in half for us without us even asking to have that done  The ice cream sandwich was yummy but kind of hard to eat since the ice cream was a bit on the soft side and kept squishing out the edges  But it had a nice freshly made look and taste to it which we found enjoyable  We actually went to DMK specifically for this dessert which was listed in TimeOut Chicagos Dish Wish List of 100 best foodsWe definitely wont be coming back to DMK  We tried it because we had heard a lot of talk about it but weve had better burgers fries and ice cream sandwiches elsewhere

Author: Milly P.
Content: Note this review is also a response to all the crying by other reviewersPEOPLE YOU GET WHAT YOU PAY FOR  If you want hormone and pus infested genetically modified cheapss burgers go to McDonalds Wendys or even Five Guys  Highquality grassfed beef is NOT CHEAP  DMK is my favorite burger place in Chicago  They use high quality ingredients and cook the burger to perfection  I absolutely eat my steaks medium or mediumrare my hamburger on the other hand needs to be practically well done  Who wants to eat bloody ground beef  I always get the 8 the classic burger with iceberg tomato and american cheese  The bread they use is so soft but dense enough to keep all the burger juices in  I personally enjoy the truffle Parmesan fries over the sweet potato fries This place has some downfalls like the overly loud music unnecessarily dark decor and the one time I got a margarita it was pretty mediocre  However the burgers more than make up for any downfalls

Author: Sarah A.
Content: Their burgers are awesome  I especially like the Bison burger with blueberry bbq sauce  a unique but great combo I cant seem to get enough of their parmesan truffle fries as well I love the concept and how the menu is both simple and has a good selection They dont take reservations which can be both good and bad its not as much fun to wait for 45 minutes on a Friday night They have a great staff though their beer selections are limited but I think thats partially because they are wanting to be ecofriendly Overall You cant beat their burgers for only 8try it

Author: Heidi H.
Content: Last Friday after a busy day at school the lovely Erin B IMd me and asked if I was up for meeting her for deepfried pickles I mean cmon Erin B pickles AND a burger  Hell yeah  So after getting my hair did I drove right over to DMK to meet Erin for dinner  She had been waiting for awhile at the bar seeing they wouldnt seat her without me being there but as soon as I told the hostess that  the entire party was here we were seated right away  We sat down and immediately went to the appetizer list to find our deep fried pickles but wait okra too  blegh  A plate full of deepfried pickle spears without the okra sounded so much better and our friendly waitress obliged us  I have only had deepfried pickle chips at the Minnesota State Fair and albeit quite tasty do not compare to the pickle spears at DMK  I remember deep fried pickles as being awesome because lets face at anything deep fried is pretty much awesome but most of the time they are a bit mushy and the batter comes right off  Not the case here  Crispy tasty sour yummy mmmmm I want some nowAnyway after the tasty pickles  our burgers and fries were next  I ordered the burger with onion strings blue cheese and chipotle ketchup with sweet potato fries  Now sweet potato fries have to be my favorite thing ever and these were great   A lot of restaurants will make them thin and crispy but I prefer mine to be a little on the thick side so I was happy to see that DMKs fries were cut a bit thicker  The dipping sauce on the side had a bit of spice that totally complemented the sweet potatoes and honestly I would go back to DMK for the pickles and sweet potato fries alone  The burger was good and washing it all down with a Crispin cider made for a really fun night with a great friend

Author: Van L.
Content: FAVORITE SPOTi try and bring everyone here i try to go once a month and i could probably recite the menuno reservations  so just wait and deal with it grab a beer and wipe your saliva as you watch other burgers pass you by ive had almost everything on the menu and all is great but this is why i love DMKtheir buns toasted so amazinglytheir beef grassfed and perfecttheir drinks beer list is great and i am in love with the whirling tiger cocktailtheir fries sweet potato and parmesan truffle are my favestheir burgers im a fan of 4 green chile  egg and holy guacaoili guac  chorizo i dietheir nonbeef turkey  lamb are my faves on this part of the menusigh i cant wait to go back when im hankering a burger nextthis is hands down the best burger in chicagothe best part you dont feel too full after DMKits just right

Author: Whitney L.
Content: The boy and I were biking home the other night when we passed DMK which I had heard quite a bit of buzz about So the following Friday afternoon I was looking for a big meal before I had to work a long night shift so we headed into DMK after browsing their menu briefly onlineBefore I go much further Ill just say this VEGETARIANS BEWAREIf youre going to open a burger business that you KNOW is going to compete with Kumasyou need to be able to COMPETE WITH KUMASMy boyfriend and I are both vegetariansand our options were frighteningly sparse Out of the FOURTEEN burgers they offer only oneONE can be enjoyed as a veggie burger The rest are straight up beef or portabello I really do not understand the principle of not being able to sub out any other burger for a veggie patty Kumas 1 DMK 0So okay whatever If the veggie burger rules then 1 is enough right Well the burgers seem cheap enough 8 but dont include anything As we were drooling over french fry options our waitress informed us that thoseas wellwere not vegetarian They were fried in some sort of meat by product and thus our only option was onion straws Alright So I have one burger choice and one side choice Kumas 2 DMK 0The food came out MEGA fast Way faster than Kumas and we didnt have a wait either Kumas 2 DMK 1 The onion straws were just fine I piled some on top of my burger The rest were a big greasy plate of them that Im not that stoked about as a side dish but ate them anyway The burger itself was decent Very very chocked full of veggies My boyfriend enjoyed his more than I didAtmosphere was nice I liked all of the exposed brick I was a bit weirded out after working in the service industry for the past 3 years at the roll ups being basically sanitowels used to mop up messes around the restaurant by staff Of course they were clean but when I get an attachment to a restaurant item as one thing then it is used as anotherstrangeOverall I was terribly underwhelmed especially after spending 40 for lunch I wont be planning on going back anytime soonunless they shape up and give the vegetarians a bit of a chance

Author: David G.
Content: Yes 2 stars I am fucking asshole and terrible person how can I say that about this awesome Placeblah blah blah Yes I am giving this 2 stars So shut the fuck up and read whyI am not sure if its one of those things where it got hyped up so much that when I went there it was ruined but here is how I rate a burgerFirst things first Portillos makes the best burger in the world according to me I dont eat red meat very often so when I do it better be fucking goodIts my opinion and I could give a fuck what you think                                                       SidebarSeriously let me know if you want a fuckI have many fucks to give                                           Now back to the actionWell we have already established that in my mind Portillos is what a burger should taste and act like when I order one I am flexible on this to a point but it better be in that fucking league So I finally went to DMK Burger Bar after hearing all this great stuff about the place and I was seriously underwhelmed It gave me Burger Blue Balls and I had to eat at Portillos the next day just to get my mind rightSo when I went here I was already biased but willing to take the chance and see what everyone was talking about                                                 THOUGHTS1 8 for a burger  This shit better be fucking good A Burger is an American tradition made for the common man with discarded beef parts that were ground up and served on a bun since their broke ass couldnt afford a steak So I order a 8 which by all purpose is there to be the regular burgerBun Lettuce Cheese Burger Pickles Onions MayoThe burger is thinner than your index finger and some how they under cooked it but I was down to go with the flow and I gave it a chance I house the thing in about 35 seconds since it was kind of small and for 8 I was expecting a Pub Style burger and got a greasy griddle fried burger that reminded me of a playdoh burger my daughter would make Im about 64 215lbs so I knew right away I was going to walk away hungery from this motherfucker right here but whateverI also got a soda and it was in a can and cost 175 which is hilarious My soda did include a pint glass filled with ice so that must have been worth the extra price since the water we got was room temp and served without iceInterestingWhat is funny was my wife and I also ordered mac and cheese and we were worried that we ordered too much food thinking that the Burger was going to be filling and that just wasnt the caseshe doesnt eat Red Meat or Pork so she got the Veggie Burger but that disaster is a whole nother review all togetherWe wanted sweet potato fries but if you dont eat red meat be aware that the fries are cooked in a beef grease  Not a surprise since I had a ton of grease on my dishit was kind of amazing actually how such a thin insufficient amount of meat could drip that much grease on my plateOverall I think the place will do well since it is like one of those places that everyone talks about  then you realize these people have no fucking clue about what good shit isSo it is basically not a REAL AMERICAN BURGER place its a presumptuous wannabe hipster burger place that gets talked about way too much for what it is I have had better burgers pretty much everywhere else I have ever eaten in my life I guess after hearing so fucking much about this place I was going to hate it but they really sealed the deal when I  actually sat down and eat herePros Right off the Brown LineCons Not a real dudes place for a burgerWould I go back  neverWould I recommend this place NoFinal thoughtSeriously go to Portillos if you like this place and see if you ever go back plus you will save a couple bucks in the process Which you can then spend on a pair of Thick Black Frame Glasses a plaid shirt and a stupid 10 speed that you paid 4k for but spray painted some ironic color

Author: Tera D.
Content: The two stars is based solely on the burger  I actually liked pretty much everything else about the place but if a gourmet restaurateur and the owner of a topoftheline steak place open a burger joint Im gonna judge them on the burgerFirst of all why oh why am I not asked to specify how I like my burger cooked  And why why why why why would a chef decide on welldone as the default cooking level  The meat isnt tender or very flavorful  The topping options are ok but you dont get an overwhelming amount of toppings so they dont really stand out  Theres just too many freakishly good burgers in this town to waste time on this oneThat said the mac n cheese is great the atmosphere fun service is good and the drink list unique  Sorry to have to go 2star with all that going for them but for heavens sake its a burger  Get it right

Author: Kara K.
Content: There is no better way to render a workout useless than to go and have burgers right afterwards Postgrueling workout a girlfriend suggested we go to DMK Burger Bar because she heard some great things about it Since I was starving and hadnt had a good burger in a while I said coolWe strolled into DMK at about noon and I wanted to run home and put on a hot outfit Ive NEVER seen a burger joint that looked as sexy as this place This dimly lit bar with dark wood and fixtures was a totally pleasant and unexpected surprise  A nice lunch crowd was already in place but it wasnt packed so we were seated immediately Our super friendly waitress came over and gave us the rundown and we placed our order I had the  6the portabella with brie and scallions my girl had the 1 which I believe was a basic cheeseburger and we shared a large order of friesAll I can say is hot damn This burger was sooo good I ate it very slowly so I could savor every delectable tasty bite And the frieswe devoured every single one of them This is the very reason I stay away from burgersif you get a burger you have to get it with cheese then you have to get fries with ketchup then you have to get a milkshake then you have to get the chocolate chip cookie ice cream sandwich Aaagh Its a conspiracyI guess I have to do an extra 30 minutes on the treadmill tomorrow

Author: Ben K.
Content: DMK is really really good  Like REALLY good  Items of noteThe 1 bacon cheddar  grilled onions is fantastic  Its served on some sort of toasty rosemary bun all the toppings fit nicely inside and go together perfectly  I savored every last bite  It goes well with beef or turkey  This is a home run The sweet potato fries with lemon tabasco aioli WOW  The fries are solid if unspectacular but the aioli is unreal  I was dipping every single item on the table into it wishing I had a cup or a pint or a quart instead of the small little metal condiment dish they give youLast time I was there for some reason our server gave us an order of fried pickles and okra on the house  These were a tasty novelty though I probably wouldnt order them myself for 5  On that note DMK is maybe a tiny bit more expensive than you would expect  Burgers are 8 a la carte and small orders of fries are 24  But really when are you getting a burger wfries at a decent restaurant in LP for under 10 anymore anyway  If you didnt enjoy your meal because it was too expensive perhaps you should try a little burger joint I think is called McDonaldsOn the negative side DMK is super loud  Its usually packed and even when its not the walls are very soundreflective and there is always a cacophonous din in there  Also I always end up having to ask for extra ketchup those metal condiment dishes are so small and ice water  A small drawback to an otherwise excellent dining experience

Author: Isla E.
Content: The problem with this place is they dont do substitutions and they only cook the meat really rare or super welldone We asked about their meatcooking and the table next to us did also They say the burgers are cooked medium but I had a bite of one and it was pretty damn pink The waitress said that you can either get it medium or welldone For all I know this is common practice with burgers but if you are picky about doneness or toppings this isnt your burgerFries with truffle cream are addictive The sweet potato tater tots werent bad either The gruyere mac and cheese was disappointing very bland If you care about my greek salad I will tell you it is averageStill I would go back to this place Really friendly staff and generally positive vibe

Author: David G.
Content: I think it had been two weeks The burger craving was going to devour me alive I needed some place that wasnt going to make me wait two hours for a good quality burger DMK popped out on the list Its a burger bar which meant two things they specialized in burgers and they had a bar Give me an A for genius thinking The bison burger was decent A quarter pound patty slapped on a fresh baked bun A little flimsy though For the price I expected a little more meat on the bun The burgers in general are basically guiltfree grass fed beef so I cant complain too much My burger just didnt meet my expectations for a bar specializing in burgers The fries were excellent We ordered the blue cheese and smoked bacon fries which I enjoyed more than the burger We also received a complementary order of deep fried pickles This was a little foreign to me but Ill try anything They were surprisingly good At the time I was coming down with a cold so I chose to go nonalcoholic something that was difficult to do after reading their expansive beer list I ended up getting a cherry lime soda which is made in house from scratch I felt a little immature getting a soda surrounded by big men drinking alcohol But it tasted good I would come back to DMK because of the fries and the beer and to give them a second chance on the burger Maybe order something different Even a salmon burger or a lamb burger Ill try anything

Author: Arash R.
Content: The best Bison burger ever  couldnt get any better  great ambience  not to forget the sweet potato fries

Author: Jason H.
Content: The shortA trendylooking burger gastropub Its clean the bar is visible and the waitstaff was pleasant Its a decent place to bring a casual date but nothing formal We went when it was nearly empty so I cant comment about how rowdy it might get on a busy day It was a comfortable place to talk with my friends but the food wasnt worth the priceThe longI was back in town for Christmas and met with some of my friends whod wanted to check out this place they heard it was great My friends seemed to be more impressed with the food than I wasI dont drink so I cant comment on the alcohol qualityThey have housemade soft drinks I ordered the lemonlime It did taste sort of fresh I suppose but it didnt taste better than Sprite So who cares 3 for a glass Should have been betterAll their burgers are 8 I ordered a lamb burger It was fine but too soft and falling apart for my preference Maybe thats how ground lamb is I dont know but I guess I should have asked for a firmer meat It was ok but it wasnt better than a Whopper It was worth maybe 4 but not 8 The bun was fresh but it was flimsy with no flavor or texture Why bother Its only been 2 days but I cant really remember anything else about the burger Maybe that says how bland an impression it made on me Im not going to complain about it but Im not going to praise it eitherThey have 5 types of french fries for 3 or 5 depending on size I got there after the Sweet Potato fries were eaten I heard they were good I shared parts of the Wisconsin Cheddar fries and a couple other fries I cant remember their names either because they werent that special The Cheddar was too heavy without a real cheddar taste It could have been stadium nacho cheese for all I care it didnt hit me as strong cheddar It was also too pooled at the bottom so the topsides had no cheese and the bottom fries were drowned Also all the fries were too oilygreasy for my taste I like crispy fries which still resemble potato rather than oilsoaked shoe laces OK it wasnt as bad as that but they werent crispy even when fresh The other two orders of fries came with some sort of zesty ketchup but WAY too little for the amount of fries Dont skimp on the special sauceOverall I paid 18 before taxtip for a burger some fries and a glass of pop Think to yourself how good it would have to be to be worth that much to you Well it wasnt worth nearly that much to me I feel like I was paying for the OPTION of drinking alcohol more than for the quality of the food I ACTUALLY ate And the atmosphere which I feel could be attained by dimming the lights in my own
