house Im not trying to knock the place but come on 18 for mediocreatbest food Thats not rightIt also doesnt seem right that the bathrooms are between you and the kitchen just weird to have to see your food being carried past the bathrooms They were clean but I would prefer my food is nowhere near thereIn summaryif youve got money to blow and want a very averagelooking and averagetasting trendylooking restaurant come here If you think 20 is too much to pay for a Happy Meal without the toy go somewhere else

Author: Kristine B.
Content: It would be a disservice to say I ate there  I would like to say I experienced a meal there  Staff was SUPER friendly Im inclined to believe the owners are actually working the floor this week and very helpfulMy friend and I both had the burgers  hers was the 8 a usual toppings type burger and mine was the 4 chiles fried egg and bacon  Both were amazing  The bun was soft and lovely but stood up to the egg middles  The beer selection is awesome no miller lite here and they are going for the oldbut new again cocktails  No coke or pepsi products either  a local soda with real cane sugar or their own flavored sodasThe Parmesan fries with truffle cream were good  even just on their own without the cream I was in heavenThe atmosphere was great  not too cramped but not too spread out music was at a good level I love kumas but I dont like to shout and there was adequate space if you were to bring a large groupNeedless to say Im a fan of DMK and will be happily recommending this place to others as long as they promise to bring me I want to try the milkshakes and ice cream sandwiches

Author: Todd M.
Content: I checked out the reviews of DMK Burger Bar before heading out to check it out for myself  Seems most people either love this restaurant or hate it  I fall in to the loved it campI enjoyed that in addition to an interesting selection of burgers and fries they offered a strong beer list as well I started off with a Great Lakes Dortmunder Gold on tap  My wife and I each tried a different burger and each ordered our own fries  We learned when they arrived we should have split the fries as the portions are large  We enjoyed both the Seat Salt  Black Pepper fries as well as the Wisconsin Cheddar  Scallion friesI think I won the battle of the burgers with a Burger served with Chili Rubbed Onion Strings and a Spicy Chipotle Ketchup I am now craving this again just thinking about it  My Wifes was also a strong contender it was served with aged cheddar smoked bacon balsamic red onions and a BBQ sauceThis place has been compared often to Kumas  One thing I liked about these burgers compared to the Kuma Burger was the size I felt full after the burger but did not feel overstuffed as I often do when enjoying a Kuma burgerIf you love a good burger this should be on you list to check out next

Author: cara y.
Content: Why do you need two pounds of meat to make a good burgerI dont understand this I like Kumas and all but eating a meat hockey puck has grown old And this is one of the reasons why DMK blew me awayIve spent the last few weeks obsessively drooling over the menu When I go Imma get this and this and this and youll bring the wheel barrow and cart me home My boyfriend had visited on a work lunch and set my attention on the place and I finally found time before work to check it outHonestly the inside wasnt what I expected in a good way I expected some burger joint like The Counter and was pleasantly surprised to find it a darker bar atmosphere We were quoted 20 minutes which is beyond acceptable and were seated within 10 Our waitress Kiley I think that was her name SHE WAS AWESOME greeted us within minutes and I geeked out at her over my excitement She was friendly without being wooden and didnt seem to mind my I want both but which one should I get questionsI orderedBlueberryLemon SodaBreakfast Burger Weekend specialBoyfriendTurkey Burger 9 I thinkSea SaltBlack Pepper FriesThe soda was incredible Strong flavor without being too sweet Very refreshing on a warm day As we waited for our burgers a runner came up with a plate of delicious fried things and let us know that our waitress wanted to give us something on the houseAnd thats when fried okra and pickle chips entered my life They were amazing Im from the south so Im no stranger to fried pickles but the mix with okra and the house made ranch Screw you DMK Why were they so goodOur burgers came shortly after before I managed to decimate the fried platter and they were once again nothing like what I expected in a very good way My breakfast burger was a turkey burger with a fried egg jack cheese bacon hash browns with a maple aoli I got the aoli on the side because Im not the biggest sweets fan but after tasting it I could see how it would rock the socks off someone The burger itself was much thinner than I had grown used to at places like Kumas but it was so flavorful and cooked perfectly I loved my burger I ate half without feeling stuffed or still hungry The fries were ridiculous Cooked crispy like I like em and the house ketchup was a perfect compliment All and all I want to give them 1 star because I want everyone to go away so I can always have a seat I give them 5 stars because thats what they deserve from the friendly staff the delicious food and the nonoverwhelming bar atmosphereThey also involve themselves in charities And they have a killer cocktail menu And a bloody mary barI need to stopThe best part Our okra was comped under the discount LoveI love you too DMK I love you too

Author: TJ C.
Content: I write very few reviews but given all the publicity about DMK Burger Bar I thought I would take a few minutes and post my thoughts  In a restaurant that is all about burgers an unwillingness to cook a burger to a temperature rare medium rare etc suggests one of three things  First we are so unsure of our product our systems and our training that we are unwilling to cook to medium rare  Another possibility is that the DMK team believes that they know better than the guest how the guest wants a burger  The last possibility is that they simply want to simplify things for the line cooks Lets discuss each in turn  If its the first possibility then thats truly unfortunate  If the Counter can cook a medium rare burger why cant DMK  Its about a focus on food safety training trusting your supply chain and taking the same reasonable precautions that seem to work for the other burger specialists  If its the second possibility it seems very out of tune with the current environment  Being guest friendly is critical for ongoing survival in the current recession  Lastly if its about ease for the kitchen then its a case of misaligned priorities    I had the burger with onion strings  medium plus  The bartender claimed that the burger would still be juicy  Usually when I am at a place that will only cook to medium or better Dennys for example  I just order something else  However theres not a lot to choose from at DMK if you dont want a burger so with trepidation I ordered the burger with onion strings   As I feared medium plus  turned out to be well done dry and tasteless  Grass fed beef tends to have  lower fat content than the standard product this makes if far more sensitive to overcooking not less   Okay what I liked was the roll not too bready and an excellent choice  The homemade ketchup and the blue cheese fries were pretty good  House cut fries are often tough to execute consistently and are often limp  These were reasonably crispy  The mac and cheese was okay but a little disappointing given MKs resume   Maybe its unfair but given his resume I would have expected more   The beer list was okay although skewed towards the national semicrafts Fat Tire Goose Island  but thats a personal preference  Service was good  We sat at the bar and were waited on by a good bartender with a fast smile and fast hands a bad thing in front of the bar  a good thing behind the bar  I could see him cringe when I ordered my burger mediumrare but he doggedly rolled out the we only cook to medium plus but it will still be juicy line as he has no doubt been trained  I sort of felt bad for him  DMK is a beautiful room and is well put together   Needless to say it was hopping and loud   Lots of hard surfaces make it loud but that is no doubt intentional on the part of the design team to give the room an energy  Most restaurants make mistakes its how you recover from them that matters  They have a great team and the concept works  They want to do only a few things and do them well  From an industry perspective burgers are on a tear  look at the headsnapping growth of better burger concepts such as 5 Guys and Smash Burger  In full service operations chains such as the Counter continue to grow despite some misteps   I wish the team at DMK luck and I would give them another chance if they rethink their decision to overcook their burgers for reasons of their own  I gave them two stars for the concept but as another reviewer said an overcooked burger is a dealbreaker if the name of your restaurant isnt Dennys or Burger King

Author: Ritu R.
Content: Im a fan Been here about 3 times  Each time was fantastic Tasty and clean burgers  That is almost unheard of They offer a variety of sides and snacks that are all delic Truffle and the cheddar fries Their deviled eggs are to die for too I had the portabella burger and it was crispy and tasty  I have no complaints I shall return to try the other burgers     Its one of those burger places that you wanna bring your outoftown guests too bc its so fun and good  Our last time there was on a Sunday and are not sportwatchers and were very comfortable and enjoyed our experience My husband says this last time was the best Yeay for DMK

Author: Zo O.
Content: I was greeted by David Morton D 1Went there on the 3rd day of opening wasnt very busyI was expecting the menu I saw online on the TOC site but their menu was different No substitutes  so try to be open to try what they offer I ordered 12 the fried stuffed portobello burger 8  Super yum My meat lovin friend thought it was just as good as his medium rare burger8 We both ordered the blood orange sodas and a order of two diff friessweet potato wlemon tabasco aioli  regular fries wketchup We also LOVED the bread for their burger buns Super soft  which youd think wouldnt work as a burger bun but it does Yummm

Author: Alysha P.
Content: Brought a couple of friends from nyc here last Saturdaywe were hungover hungry and ready to get busy on some burgersFood8 Pretty straightforward burgerlettucetomatopicklesonions­mayo and choice of cheeseI got the aged cheddarand since I am a straightforward kind of burger galI was very very happy with my choice Juicy and deliciousperfect sizenot too bignot too smalland it was cooked to a perfect mediumjust the way I like ityum 1 Bfs choice with bacon bbq sauce and balsamic charred red onionsI had a few bitesthought it was goodbut not as good as mine    bf liked itbut thought the onions were a little overwhelmingdidnt stop him from eating the whole damn thing thoughMac n Cheese 1 Soooooo creamysoooo cheesysoooooo frickin good Perfect dish for a cold hungover dayFries with Truffle and Parmesan I never met a french fry I didnt like and these were no exceptionflavors were beautifulI only wish there would have been more sauceBig Salad We got this to share so we could feel at least a little bit healthyand it was actually a really good saladdef enough for 4 peeps to sharelots of veggies involvedvery happyyayServiceOur server was super cute attentive and sweetNo rushing to order and lots of smiles They were out of the wine that I wanted so she offered to bring a taste of the substitutewhich I always appreciate The host and the bus person were equally nice and attentiveAmbianceDark and sleek but cozy at the same timeliked itOverallPretty damn good burgersI was very happy with the whole experienceand would def pop back in

Author: Emily C.
Content: I went here with the fam and the bf and ate entirely too much in the best way possible  This means I have to do the awesome breakitdownintocategories thingDrinksCool beer list with a bunch of local brews  I tried Crispin cider here which was cold and delicious  Cocktails look solid too sight unseen  I wanted to try the one with the cool name something about death and tigers  I forget but didnt get around to it  Next time hopefullyBurgersExcellent  I had the lamb burger with tapenade cucumber  tzatiki my mom had the 1 BBQ onion strings cheese  bacon my brother had the one with a fried egg peppers and bacon BF had one with a hunk of pastrami cheese and mustard and sadly I cant even remember what my dad had but we passed bites around the table and I was impressed with everything I ate  Such distinct flavors  The only teenyminute criticism here is that they might want to try other types of buns  Sometimes you just cant beat a pretzel roll  But dont let that distract you from the fact that these are some seriously delicious burgers  A few of the ones they arent serving yet look great too  Im itching to get at the one with prosciutto and fontina cheeseSidesWe had the fried pickleokra with herb ranch as well as the chilidusted onion straws  These both were incredible  The dipping sauce for the pickleokra combo was perfect for it and whatever they do to their house ketchup that makes it taste kind of smoky makes me want to consume it by the bottle  Mac  CheeseWe had the one with gruyere onions and bacon and shared it as a table  Mmmmmm  FriesBecause we have absoltuely no self control we got a small plate of every type of french fry on the menu  I was absolutely blown away by the sweet potato fries with lemontabasco aoli you dont think they go together but they TOTALLY do blue cheese fries with bacon and the aged cheddar cheese  bacon ones Seriously kids  Kormick  co really know how to combine flavors to put a fresh spin on stuff you think youve eaten a million times  This sweet little spot is likely going to be mega crowded and deservedly so

Author: Linda N.
Content: Do try grassfed beef  My first experience with noncornfed beef happened in Atlanta at Farm Burger and it nearly changed my palate foreverDo not come for a meal at this restaurant during peak times  DMK doesnt take reservations  we came here on a Sunday for a late lunch around 2pm and got a table right awayDo browse the craft beer list  I chose Dogfish Head India Brown Ale date had the Stone IPADo not think that you can substitute toppings on your burger  I had my heart set on the Patty Melt but I was bummed that I couldnt opt for aged cheddar as my taste buds care not for SwissDo try the 4 Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm EggSonoma Jack Smoked Bacon if you like spicy  date loved itDo not order any burger from here if you like it mooing  Requests for burgers cooked below medium will be deniedDo try the Parmesan fries with Truffle cream  can I say divineLiked this place and will be back someday to try grassfed Colorado lamb

Author: Mary B.
Content: Ok so this place got written up in the Tribune and my husband and I decided to try it out We both had shakes burgers and truffle fries Shakes were Okay nothing special Burgers had great toppings I had the one with the goat cheese and blueberry bbq sauce The goat cheese was fresh and the bbq sauce was quite good The burger itself was the size of a steak and shake burger It tasted kinda like it too I dont understand what is with the wimpy meat patty If you are gonna spend 800 for a burger sans fries there should be some meat in there am I wrong Truffle fries were great and Id maybe go back just for those Overall review meh

Author: Susan F.
Content: Finally got a chance to stop into DMK after about a year of wanting to go For some reason I never made it over here until now and now Im kicking myself for not have coming soonerWalking in I would have never expected it to look like this it didnt feel so much like Lakeview It was a really cool atmosphere not to say Lakeview isnt I mean I live here but it was just a different deal Long and narrow brick exposed wall some communal seating and ample bar seating I was surprised We actually got seated within 5 minutes prior to being told it would be 30 minutes wahoo 5 starsBefore coming I perused the burger list of course and made sure to check out all the burger pics I had made my mind up 11 lamb burger mmm We split a bowl of chili as our appit was super good and served with some toasted bread Now was the hard partFRIES Up to fryheaven The beau and I opted for sweet potato fries and parmesan truffle fries The SP fries were awesome as were the truffles The single servings were a perfect size2 and that sauce was amazing We werent too thrilled with the sauce that came with the parm fries we couldnt really place it It was just creamy I liked it but it was kinda like whatevs in the most lamens termsBurger run down Honestly I really liked the burger and the bread11 It was the perfect size and was also aesthetically pleasing to my hungry eyes The bf commented how he would have liked tomato and lettuce for the crunch but by no means complained about his dish Our server Katie was very attentive The service was quick and friendly The beer list is great they have all the good stuff running for 5506 for tapI will come back here again I liked the music too Great date spot

Author: Ramya P.
Content: Vegetarians are denied friesJust like Romeo n Juliet beer n football and wine and cheese the obvious eternal partner of a sumptuous burger is a bunch of crispy fries DMK has fries alright and from what I heard theyre pretty good too But theyre all fried in beef oil and we vegetarians have to feel incomplete There are however 3 nonmeat burger options Salmon veggie and the crispy portobello The crispy portobello is really good and is definitely one of the best veggie burgers Ive had The buns for the burgers were soft and felt like they were freshly baked The beer list features all kinds of ales and the service is friendly too

Author: Andres D.
Content: I have heard so much about DMK and I finally made itbetter late than never DMK tables get filled up pretty quickly unless you are a party of two Last nite myself plus two pals grabbed a seat at the bar since we didnt want to wait At first the menu was a tad confusing thank goodness the lovely bartender explained everything She had total patience and was helpful with our selectionsDMK serves qualityoh yeah Grassfed beef Colorado lamb Turkey and Veggie burgers They are covering it all whether you are a meatlover or not Hands down my favorite was the 11 Lamb Burger w Feta and Tzatzki sauce We also ordered the 1 Cheddar Bacon BBQ Beef Burger 8 Basic more tradtional Beef Burger 10 Turkey Burger with Smoked Swiss Side choices on our table was the large order of Sea Salt  Black Pepper Fries with HOMEMADE ketchup Wisconsin Cheddar  Scallion Fries and finally some HOMEMADE Creamy coleslaw  I washed most if down with Three Floyds Robert the Bruce and GumballheadThe burger patties arent thick so there is no playing room how would you like it cooked preference If you are comparing it to Kumas Corner 10 ounce burger patty you will be disappointed DMK will allow you to double up on the patties for an extra 3 bucks or add a fried egg on top for 1I will be back as well as the rest of my group Thanks for the awesome peanut butter malted shake

Author: cassie r.
Content: The food was excellent Everything else about the experiencenot so much We arrived around 530ish last night and though we sat right away we ended up sitting an inordinately long time waiting for our waitress to greet usThen we waited a long time to get our beer Then our food our bill etc You get the picture Id be a bit more understanding if everyone had been getting slow service but that wasnt the case The table next to us sat down near the end of our meal and yet they were already halfway through their dinner by the time we left Beyond that the place is ridiculously loud And no Im not a crotchedy old man   it was just straight up noisy And impossible to have a conversation when all you can hear is music and people yelling to be heard Like I said though the food was really good I had the 12  veggie burger with aged cheddar eggplant tomato and pesto mayo The eggplant was a delicious add and the bun was fantastically fresh  We ordered a side of sweet potato fries LOVE the aioli sauce and  tried the parmesan fries with truffle cream not bad  the cream sauce was definitely the best part of that combo The beer list is decent though apparently I dont like Three Floyds Gumballhead and the location is easily accessible from the train and parking was easily found Not a bad spot for a burger in Lakeview

Author: Mihir P.
Content: Oh hell no My burger was nasty Overlygamey beef rancidtasting cheese cold and soggy balsamic onions Burger was about 14 lb and it was 8 with no sidesThe onion strings were ok  overly greasy and underspiced The service was nice but not entirely thereI give an extra star for the blood orange soda and a solid beer list

Author: Amanda G.
Content: These are fancy fast foodstyle burgers Think Kumas I know but you were thinking Kumas anyway meets Tastee Freeze or something along those lines If it werent for the toppings Id roll my eyes at the 8 but I had a number 4 I looove eggs on burgers because all I want in life is to die of a heart attack before I reach life expectancy and I thought 8 was a fair price My burger was tasty and pretty spicy  keep in mind I am kind of a baby when it comes to spiceI love that the individual sides of fries are 2 Its great if you go with a group because everyone can order a different kind and you get to try them all I had the parmesan truffle cream which was heavenly I tried the blue  smoked bacon and those were amazing as well Basically for 10 you get a fancified value meal and its delicious Unless you order like a maniac or just ate you probably wont take leftovers home which for the price is fine Theres also a great beer list which is always fun Ill definitely be back to try other combos and probably to try the mac and cheese as well

Author: Tiffany S.
Content: I realize that fancy burgers are the all the craze right now  Ive also completely sold into the craze and will run full speed faster than Ive ever run on a treadmill to the closest burger joint to get my fixDMKs food was such a disappointment  The burger patties were so skinny and weak its was 90 bread and toppings  Their fries are terrible though I realize its a matter of taste but I hate being forced to eat pepper on soggy skinny overcooked fries  I also hated their prententious homemade ketchup  It was spicy Have you guys read the Gladwell article about how ketchup is the perfect food and to change it is actually takes away what makes our tastebuds go crazy for it  If people wanted icky flavored ketchup dont you think the idea would have caught on before now So gross and of course they looked at me like I was some kind of classless vagrant when I asked for HeinzMy friends macaroni and cheese committed the worst offense mac and cheese can do it was severely lacking in the cheese department  It doesnt matter if you put 5 different gourmet cheese into some noodles if you skimp on the cheese its not macaroni AND cheese its just noodlesI cant complain about the service our waitress was nice  The atmosphere is also very cool and I would totally hang out here for drinks  The beer selection was huge and they had a lot of local stuff that I appreciated  That being said they only have onesie bathrooms which results in such long waits for the bathroom that my order actually arrived while I was waiting in line for the bathroom which I ran to directly after order  So annoyingPretty much unless its for beer dont expect me back  I dont hate you DMK but until a massive overhaul happens I dont think I can ever even like you

Author: Crista L.
Content: Boyfriends cravin a burger  fries DMKAt DMK it is nearly impossible to find vegan fare HOWEVER there are a few vegetarian options I KNOW that I am reviewing a BURGER BAR just sayinI digressThe best advice I have to offer you is to skip the fries at DMK and go straight for the fried okrapickles and onion strawsThats all

Author: Jonathan H.
Content: I was happy to finally get a chance to try these burgers Id been hearing a lot about them and wanted to see if it held up to the other burger joints I loveI got the Number 3 I love a good pastrami sandwich and I also love burgers SO this was a natural choice for me Service was nice and pleasant and there was no line for a table Got my burger and some fries We ordered the regular ones which was lame because they had a bunch of other styles I bet I would have enjoyed Burger was cooked right and the pastrami mustard and sauerkraut were a nice touch and made the burger very tastyThe only thing that keeps it from being 5 stars is just that my wife and I were not a fan of the buns They were bitter Not sourdough but bitter And the price was a little high That will not stop me from going back because I really enjoyed it

Author: Virginia T.
Content: My friend grabbed DMK and brought it over for a quick dinner recentlyI ordered the Holy GaucAioli Buger turkey It was really tasty The burger came with chorizo guacamole chipotle aioli jack cheese P got the Patty Melt no onions He really liked it The smoked swiss was especially nice J got the 4 minus the fried egg green chile jack and bacon and said it was tastyWe split a large order of the salt  pepper fries which were good and probably are  more crisp for dineinOne thing to note The patties are not cooked to order they are on the thin side Our burgers werent dry though

Author: Liz K.
Content: I LOVE DMK Seriously cant say enough good things about this place The first time I went was in the fall and had a great experience FoodAmazing amazing amazing Not totally sure what I ordered the first time I went but Im going to take a guess and say the 1 Whatever it was it was delicious Ive also tried the 2very good as well However from what I remember the 1 was better Last time I went my boyfriend and I had the Wisconsin chedder fries Very good but a little heavy Probably wouldnt order them again Instead I would opt for the sea salt and black pepper It sounds so simple but these fries melt in your mouth And the house ketchup is a perfect dipping saucea little spicy which I LOVED Also huge beer list The first time I went I tried the beer on special basically because it was cheap haha Not a huge fan of it but oh well There are plenty to choose fromServiceGreat for both visits Moreso the first visit I went with a group of 5 on a Friday night The no reservations policy kind of sucks but we didnt have to wait TOO long so we didnt mind Plus on a warmer evening its nice to wait outside and chat with your friends When we were seated the waitress was great One of my friends was debating between her normal cocktail of choice and a new more exotic looking one The waitress recommended the exotic cocktail and my friend agreed to order it Unfortunately she didnt like it and only took a few sips The waitress without even asking promptly brought over the cocktail that my friend was originally going to order and said with an apologetic smile I noticed you werent really liking your drink so I got you what you originally wanted and its on the house After my friend thanked her the waitress came back AGAIN with a complimentary order of fries because theyre so delicious you guys have to try them We were blown away by her friendliness and attentiveness The second time I went the service was good nothing spectacular thoughAtmosphereVery loud Not a good spot for an intimate date With a group its fun though Also dark but it didnt bother me at all Very trendy and basically just screams that the place is a good timePriceBeing a broke college student I reserve DMK for a treatits kind of on the pricy side Most burgers are 9 beers around 68 fries 25 And yes its true the burgers do not come with fries Kind of sucks but the fries are worth the extra few bucks Also get a large and share with your group Burgers are a little small for the price but you have to consider the atmosphere and servicenot the mention the pure deliciousness Expensive Slightly Worth it DefinitelyA lot of people like Kumas betteras far as food goes its pretty much even for me Kumas definitely has bigger portions for the same price However I like everything else better about DMK Sorry Kumas DMK wins in my book

Author: Michael S.
Content: Took a hiatus from yelp but just couldnt resist reviewing DMKFound out about this place in an email I got and immediately contacted roomies Derrick T and Akash S about going and watching the bears game Dropping the names of Michael Kornick chef owner of MK and David Morton of Mortons The Steakhouse fame and mentioned the plethora of craft beers and we were set Arrived around 7ish and were told it would be an hour wait Not bad especially since it was the third night open The location is in Lakeview right by the Wellington stop for the brown line and parking was okay to find Inside was exposed brick and dim lighting filled with yuppies galore Not a bad thing really It just wasnt as casual as I thought Being told by Michael Kornick that our wait wasnt long was a nice touch The hostesses were really friendly as well and the wait wasnt bad at all considering all of us had a beer while we waitedSo craft beers were good I think I had the Two Brothers Cain and Abel Red Rye Beer Derrick T had the Left Hand Milk Stout and Akash S had a draft beer We all enjoyed our beers I especially enjoyed how the alcohol hit me as I didnt eat for a while beforehandSo we were all seated and picked our food Not to make Derrick Ts review redundant as we had some of everyones burger and also because Derrick T is a little more detailed I will just mention my burger I had the 4 with the green chiles fried egg and bacon Really good but I think if I let my burger sit a little more the egg would of made the bun too soggy The bun itself was nicely toasted and the meat was nicely prepared I think the beef is grassfed which had a different texture and taste but was good I would of wished it was a little juicier if I could of changed something Maybe increase the fat content a wee bit Of course we had sides too Ordered two small fries and the first mac and cheese For the fries we had the parmesan truffle and the sweet potato Both were good The sweet potato fries though didnt stand out from sweet potato fries from other places The sauce it came with though was impressive Just like other rave reviews for the truffle fries I would have to say they were outstanding The sauce with those were unbelievable If only there was more room in all of our guts I wouldnt of minded getting a large order of that The mac and cheese well its good Not the best Ive had but really good I liked the crust on top of it and appreciated how it didnt feel too rich like other places but I kind of wanted that gluttony Really well made thoughWatching the bears game here made us realize that two tvs at the bar isnt enough I do understand that the people there werent watching the game and that the crowd might not really care to watch a game while there but it would of been nice for few more tvs so we could watch a game and enjoy our food We all ended up walking over to Sheffields after to finish the gameOverall really good burgers I wouldnt say like Kumas as they feel worlds apart not just crowds and noise level but really good Kumas is more meat and well rock n roll for their food while DMK is a more refined take on the classic burgersides Definitely will need to go back to try the coffee shake Derrick T will gush about and also their ice cream sandwich

Author: Laura L.
Content: I would give the burger I ate a 1 however everything else was a 5 so thats why I gave this place a 3Why did I give the burger a 1  First of all they dont ask you how you want the burger cooked which is just weird for a BURGER BAR  But the weirder thing is that they default to medium well  Maybe they call it medium plus or whatever but bottom line  no pink  It is therefore pretty dry and not tender at all  The toppings that I chose sounded really good but I ended up having to scrape off the hot chiles because they were overpowering the whole burger  However they have a great selection of fries  I went with 3 of my girlfriends and we ordered an order of each kind of fries the small orders are super inexpensive  They also have a great variety of specialty drinks  the best being the Rhubarb drink I cant remember what it was called but Rhubarb was in the name  They had jam at the bottom which actually ended up being quite deliciousThe other really good thing is that it has a great space for a long wait  Yes there is a long wait however there is plenty of room by the bar to order your drink and stand and talk with the group that you came with  It was almost like we were just at a bar hanging out so the hour wait didnt both any of usOverall experience was great however the burger itself was not  Dont you dare compare this place to Kumas Corner as that is burger blasphemy

Author: Adrienne G.
Content: Let me begin by saying I dont really eat beef that much  so when I do go here I get turkey burgers or other nonbeef burgers  The turkey burgers and good the salmon burger disappointed me since it wasnt spicy at all  I wish that you could have anything made into a lamb burger that would be good  Overall the simple menu works for meSides The fried okra and pickles once was delicious but now I avoid it because there isnt an even ratio of okra to pickle  The gravy fries are delicious and remind me of mashed potatoes and gravy which is more than I could have dreamt of when it comes to gravy fries  The other fries with truffle oil and cheese are also yummyStaff is always fine  The beer list is varied enough that you will always be able to try something new  I have yet to try any cocktails here since beer goes very well with burgers  If you get one of DMKs homemade sodas ask for ice in a separate glass because they dont give you free refills and the glass will pretty much just be iceOverall DMK is just a great spot to go out in small groups or on a casual date  And I would say when you go get the gravy fries

Author: Randy K.
Content: Imagine walking into a crowded restaurant on a Sunday night to a bunch of hooligans cheering on a televised fight No not the UFC but Daniel San in the final battle of Karate Kid Crane kick to the face call it a night Any crowd willing to cheer on a movie fight scene is a place to call home And any bar that takes your suggestion of playing Space Jam while you eat is worth revisitingIf youve read this far you can tell the atmosphere here is awesome Not just the crowd or charismatic crew but the long tables and dim lighting makes for a cozy environmentBut you didnt read this review because you care about environment You care about food And the food was AWESOME Holy Moses I ordered the 4 after an informative discussion with my server are you feeling sweet or spicy I chose spicy Im not one for eggs on my burgers but this burger was so perfectly balanced I couldnt imagine it any other way Complemented with sweet potato fries for the table good portion size for 23 people PS  the sauce is great not sure what it isCome here with friends eat a burger a real burger and prep yourself for addiction

Author: Sam K.
Content: This is definitely one of the best burger bar in Chicago probably rival InnOut in west coast The vanilla milkshake is to die for and I would recommend 3 for the burger the green chille one Also get the truffle cream sauce fries With those 3 you are set leaving a happy camper A few things to beware and why 4star You cannot get seated till your full party arrive so that is kind of an annoyance They also do not take reservations so do not be confused if they told you you are set But other than that you will not be disappointed with the food

Author: Annie W.
Content: How coincidental reading omnivores dilemma and now fearing corn So its very timely I go to a burger joint with grass fed steers And to tell you the truth I actually can tell the difference 4 how can you go wrong with a fried egg and bacon no you cant 12 wow one of the best veggie burgers ever hearty beany  eggplant well done house fries were regular the sweet potato fries were quite heavenly mac and cheese 1 was super rich and creamy so much in fact that my last bit i felt a bit nauseous but then again i had just eaten a whole burger and a ton of fries serves me right for being greedy

Author: Heather K.
Content: Three visits in and still delicious Just a few things to add from my original review mac and cheese Ive tried the traditional as well as the onionbacon varieties is great but too rich to eat on its own as an entree so definitely think of it as a sharable plate you can sub a turkey burger for any of the beef burger options if youre not a red meat eater there isnt always enough space at the bar if you want to drink while youre waiting for a table so just plan accordingly

Author: Andrew B.
Content: Ordered the pastrami burger which is a hamburger with pastrami sauerkraut and a secret sauce on top It was pretty tasty but I didnt stop there Also ordered fried pickles which were very greasy and just OK Shared a plate of parmesan and truffle sauce fries which were tasty and once again very greasy Beer selection is solid They had 6 drafts and about 20 different bottles All of them are microbrewed and the menu lists where the beer is from Beer was 56 Burger is 8 Fries were 5 Standard pricing for that area Service was good I will probably go back to get a burger and a milkshakea 4star meal However I will be passing on the greasy sides because I just didnt like how they passed through me

Author: Jennifer B.
Content: Wow  These burgers are really freaking goodAfter two failed attempts at DMK waits of over an hour we decided to stop by on a Saturday afternoon and sit at the bar  Good thing we did bc I think the bar is the place to beeither that or up front at the high tables  The back of the restaurant looked kinda sadeveryone smashed against each other and right by the kitchenAnyhoo back to the bar  There are a plethora of interesting and oddball bottled beers  There are also signature drinks that seemed inventive especially for a burger place  Their menu is simple choose from 12 different burgers  Want fries  Choose from 5  I would definitely recommend the sweet potato friesI meanmy god  They are fantastic and much better than the normal fries on the menu  If you are a turkey burger fan the turkey burgers are aces  You can just tell that the meat is better quality  Our bartender was explaining how all the meat is aged grassfed etc etc  I didnt really get it until I ate the burgernow I get itChicago is lucky that DM and MK decided to open this Burger Barthey have certainly taken the standards ingredients and philosophy of their finedining restaurants and applied them to DMK Burger Bar

Author: Patrick P.
Content: OMG Becky  the guy who played Pams fiance from The Office was sitting next to me when I last ate here I dont know his name I just yelled Youre from The Office He didnt even register a reaction Oh wellMaybe if you come here you will sit next to a Clevel actor like I didI liked it here cuz they have burgers for meateaters and options for vegetarians like me  I had the Veggies and Grain burger and it was one of the best veggie burgers I have ever had Very fresh not a Boca burger The real deal I also had Sea Salt  Black Pepper fries and Sweet Potato fries both delishMy only complaint is that the music was up too high I was eating there at 6 and there were a ton of families and they had the nob on the stereo at 11TURN DOWN THE MUSIC a bit It makes it hard to talk to your companions Just saying

Author: Stephanie N.
Content: 11 starsThis burger place is AMAZING I got a 4 Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack Smoked Bacon and let me tell you these burgers are heaven The buns it comes in seem more like a thicker fluffier flatbreadesque bun which balances out the flavors of the burger Its incredible Between three of my friends we split 3 of the sides Fried OkraPickles Sweet potato fries and Garlic Parmesean truffle fries First off we probably should have stuck splitting the small sides instead of the larger shared sides we had plenty of food leftover And i dont know if being from the south has spoiled me but the fried okra was meh But the fries were amazing They have sauces specialty made to complement the fries The sweet potatoes came with a tabascolemon juice sauce which surprisingly tasted like blueberries Went extremely well with the sweet potatoe fries Then the truffle cream sauce for the parmesean fries didnt come in a big enough container and lacked a straw that I could have drank that amazing sauce withThe atmosphere is great Highly recommended for some of the most amazing burgers youll ever have

Author: Laura C.
Content: I have been wanting to try DMK Burger for some time now in part because I love a good hamburger and because I have heard great things about this place  The burger did not disappointthe service did disappoint  It took over 10 minutes for the waitress to come take our drink order the place wasnt even packed and we ordered the mac  cheese to split for an appetizer and were sent the wrong order  Just not a good way to start out the night  Other then some shady service everything else was great  Loved the beer selection and how it explained in greater detail about each one  I had the 2 which I would go back for but cant wait to get back to try the others

Author: Claudia F.
Content: We came to DMK for my friends birthday and we had a good time In a nutshell here is what I think about DMKBurgers were OK but overpricedGood selection of burgersSweet potato fries are addictingStaff is friendlyNo fries included with the burgerIf you want fries you have to order a sideOnly small brewery beersParking can be a pain in the behindIs always packed for dinnerPlace looked clean

Author: Tricia L.
Content: It is my goal in life to one day sustain myself on just the truffle parmesan fries and sweet potato fries from DMK  OMG  SOOO AMAZINGThe burger was pretty great too  I had the portabella brie scallion one again great combo of flavors though it was a tad salty The hostess told us the wait was an hour but we were actually seated before this  DMKs definitely hoppin for a Friday night  Youd be surprised at the number of toddlers and little ones brought in too  Note to self consider coming for lunchNext time Im getting a shake or ice cream sammich cookies for this pulled from the nearby Cookie Bar

Author: Stephanie H.
Content: Its ok Meh Ive had better burgers for sure The regular style hamburger I had the first time I went was good but I wouldnt say its any better than something you can get at Red RobinWhat DMK does have which is bananas are the parmesan truffle fries Yummy I tried the cheedar and scallion fries too but they were awful The vanilla shake I had was also fantastic so thick I needed a spoon at one point On my second visit I tried something different and did the salmon burger Yuck I thought it would be a salmon filet put on the bun instead it was a salmon pattie that looked and tasted like something you would get from CostcoI would go back and try something else but I may just stick the parmesan truffle fries and shakes

Author: Amy H.
Content: Things started out so well at DMK Burger Bar with great company a fun atmosphere a great beer list for my friend and Crispin cider for me vintage American Gladiators playing on the television behind the bar and a sweet and friendly hostess  I was all set to fall in love with DMK but the food really let me downWe had the fried okra and pickles as an appetizer and we both really liked them  My lamb burger was underwhelming  There are so many creative things that you could do with ground lambgolden raisins red peppers spinach etc  It was a shame that the best they could come up with was a gyro in the form of a burger  It was good but so incredibly average and uninspired  We also ordered the Wisconsin cheddar and scallion fries which were covered in that weird cheese sauce that you get with your movie theater nachos  No bueno  Dont insult Wisconsin by using neon cheeseooze and calling it Wisco cheddar  The only dessert offerings were two types of cookie ice cream sandwiches  They were good but again uninspired  If youre going to go all Americana with your restaurant theme you should maybe throw in some apple pie or a bit of variety  While the food was a bit sad I could see DMK as a place to grab a few drinks at the bar  With any luck you can watch Nitro beat up Laser in the Joust

Author: Jeff R.
Content: One of the most written about restaurants on my blog DMK still remains one of the few things I miss from living in Lakeview The burger bar is still kicking it very well and is always busy  for good reason Erica and I were craving the tasty options and good beer of DMK so we made the trek from Wicker Park to catch a meal and watch the March Madness final four yes thats how long ago we went and I still need to blog Erica loves the 10 Turkey burger and is always ordered for us to enjoy I have many favorites but decided to go with a special burger that was delicious and I forget what was in there avocados chorizo et al The fries are a mandatory addition because theyre so good  I like the classic salt  pepper and the sweet potato friesEven though Im always interested in eating the burgers the menu also has some other starters worth getting if you have the room as well as four great mac  cheese choices for main dishes After Ive had a great burger with tasty fries and one of the many craft beers offered  the only appropriate way to end the meal is with the cleaver and fun shamrock shake It even comes with lucky charms cereal as a topping they even split a single order for two because they are very largeDMK makes my Current Chicago Favs for good reason and I hope it stays there for along time since its my favorite burger restaurant in the city

Author: Katie H.
Content: I like a place that doesnt take itself too seriously that has tongue in cheek menu descriptions that has staff who actually seem to like their jobs and have fun at them I like a place that only carries craftindependent beers and that picks a monthly charities to donate to But above all that I like a place that just has really good food And DMK does The burgers are dressed up with toppings like proscuitto and fontina or smoked bacon and cheddar but the toppings arent there to hide inferior quality meat The burgers are on the thin side and easier to eat with all the toppings but still juicy and delicious Fries come topped similarly with truffle cream blue cheese and bacon or rich cheddar and scallions There are also salads sandwiches and mac n cheese Good people good beer good burgers What else do you need

Author: Gary C.
Content: TGIF And what a Friday night it was after my visit to DMK It was a last minute rendezvous with a couple of my friends and we kinda assumed it would be packed so we were ready to wait But to our surprise it wasnt terrible for 7PM on a Friday Our party of three wound up waiting for a whole fifteen minutesI think other bars and restaurants need to take a few notes from DMK1 While Japanese pornography is good and all Space Jam should be playing on your televisions2 Play nothing but F You by Cee Lo Green on the speakers3 Hire an awesome staffMy friends and I were greeted by a hostess as soon as we stepped into the restaurantbar The gal was super friendly and full of smiles As mentioned we waited for about fifteen minutes but the hostess checked up on us and let us know the status of our table every few minutes We were seated and met by our server who talked about the specials weekend bison burger limitedtimeonly Texas chili burger sweet potato tots She came back and took our drink order We went with a couple Gumballhead brews and DMK iced tea Both drinks were greatOnto the food which was divine We all ordered the bison burger the waitress described it so well that we drooled all over the table which was served with a berryinfused barbecue sauce Holy bison this thing tasted like heaven Besides the burgers we ordered a fullsized sweet potato tater tots limited time only a half order of sweet potato fries and a half order of parmesan truffle fries All were delicious but there was something about the tots that tasted so awesome Maybe because they were totsRegardless you really cant go wrong with any of the friesThere were two things that pushed DMK to the five star status service and free booze Youve already heard about the service But free beer While we waited for our table servers walked around with samples of beer Additionally I filled out the survey at the end of our meal and they emailed me the following daysaying that the next beer is on the house I will obviously be returning in the very near future

Author: Sarah L.
Content: DMK is probably one of my top burger joints I had the 10 turkey burger with Smoked Swiss Tomato Arugula Dijonnaise and it was out of this world I love the buns so light and fluffy The turkey burger had great flavor and wasnt dried out at all The burgers are not overly huge so you do not leave feeling stuffed to the gills I dont understand the super small plates Oh well the yummy burger made up for it We also had the sweet potato fries with Lemon Tobasco Aioli The sauce with the fries was amazing It had a nice kick to it The deviled eggs were so cute You get 3 small egg halves with fancy soufflé egg filling They were so good and a reasonable price My guy had the 2 ChiliRubbed Onion Strings Amish BlueSpicy Chipotle Ketchup burger He really enjoyed his as well DMK has a huge craft beer list sure to please any beer lover DMK Burger Bar is a great place to grab a unique burger minus the 2 hour wait that other popular burger joint has to offer

Author: Keely B.
Content: After some encouragement from Emily B in regard to meat options and learning that 25 of all burger sales were going to benefit victims of the earthquake and Haiti the husband and I decided to venture out  We arrived fresh from the gym well we showered first and starving  Unlike many we were able to be seated immediatelyI got the 12 he got the 6  I subbed turkey for veggie because I desperately needed some protein  The eggplant could have been sliced more thinly because it was a little overwhelming so I took it off  Both burgers disappeared from our table and into our very satisfied bellies in about 46 seconds  Followed swiftly by equal portions of parmtruffle and saltpepper fries  The fries were not as good as the burgers but still tastyI learned after I had ordered a coke that DMK has housemade sodas so I indulged in a blood orange soda after I had gotten my caffeine fix  It was similar to Orange Crush but better  The table next to us had cupcakes and the chocolate peanut butter one looked incredible but two sodas was enough for me  Downside  The place is very modern and chic but LOUD  I often judge a place by whether my 92 year old grandma would enjoy it and she definitely would have had to turn off her hearing aide  Also the tables are superclose together so watch your language  Your neighbors can hear you

Author: Allison V.
Content: Meh I was seated and I orderedI ran to the washroom and returned to food on my tablevery quickMy bacon was barely there the meat on my burger was super rawI was never asked how I wanted it cooked now that I think about itMy friessea salt and black pepper had neither but they did have some green stuff sprinkled on topI was disappointed by the service and really disappointed by the food I really wanted to like this place Oh wellBike parking on street

Author: Blythe D.
Content: DMK serves up perhaps the single best beef burger in the entire city of Chicago and very possibly many others  Their beef is grass fed which may sound a little hokey but it makes all the difference in the world in terms of taste They dont cook the burger to order because they know exactly how it should be done My boyfriend is a welldone kinda guy and was hesitant when I steaming mediumcooked patty showed up but it was this experience that converted him He has never gone back to overcooked burgers sinceThe ingredient list and options are divine I was told that the head chef traveled the world trying different burgers from different kitchens to get new ideas in terms of what works and whats new Believe me it showsDont forget to do yourself a favor and try the truffle fries Absolutely heavenlyAlso the manager Marina is quite possibly one of the sweetest and most charming people Ive ever come across Weve been in a handful of times but she always remembers me and comes by my table just to say hello And she has sent over some tasty goodies on the house tooCouple a wonderful menu with the best customer service in town and there is no way youll leave DMK feeling anything less than satisfied

Author: Chuck K.
Content: Well I was going to give this place 4 Stars but had to reconsider Went here on New Years Eve last week for their event The party was great They didnt oversell and it wasnt overly crowded The service was top notch we never waited for a drink and there was plenty of delicious food including burgers fries BACON POPCORN and milk shakes Even though this was an unique event two things were clear Their servers are AWESOME and quite attentive and accommodating The quality of food is good as well I wouldnt call it the best burger in town but it was certainly an enjoyable burger Now for the downgrade on the star rating There is only one restroom for men and women This is quite a problem and causes lines which is sort of a pain The the big thing that happened that was a bit disturbing DMK was advertising their NYE party tickets for 5075 depending if you wanted a table or standing room All advertisement and discussions with staff indicated these prices Well when they actually charged credit cards for these tickets after the event they took the liberty to include tip and tax This was not communicated effectively when purchasing tickets or discussing ticket price with staff members This kind of turned me sour a bit on this place But nonetheless it couldnt hurt you to check out this place if you are in the neighborhood

Author: Sean F.
Content: The short review Kumas without a 3 hour wait or vampire porn on the wallsThe longer review This has jumped to the top of my list of burger joints in Chicago  Thats right I enjoyed this more than Kumas and Im not ashamed to admit thatThe burger selection is manageable without being limiting and throws out some interesting combinations  The 3 with pastrami gruyere and remoulade is meaty salty a little creamy and a little tangy all at once  The 5 not only pays heed to the kid in all of us by putting the potato chips right on the sandwich but by adding pesto lets me consider the burger as healthy since something green is involved  The burgers Ive tasted have all been cooked right none over or undercookedThe fries are excellent here  The Amish Blue and bacon are powerful stuff and not to be trifled with by a delicate palate  This is a strong blue flavor that will beat the hell out of your tongue and you will love it like a gimp in a leather mask  The truffle fries are properly truffled without being so drenched in the flavor that it feels cloying or like they were uninspired and went with the Fit just cover it in truffle approachLastly they had Boylans Grape Soda there  This is the grape soda they serve in grape soda heaven  It is what Grape Ape drinks when hes hanging out at home  I want to drink this until Im the same shade as Violet Beauregarde in Willy Wonka  In a perfect world they would have wait times close to that of Kumas  In MY perfect world Id have priority entry to get in regardless  Until that happens go here and eat burgers  And drink grape soda

Author: Jeff W.
Content: Ive been here many times and left underwhelmed I want to give 35 stars but decided to round up based on my last nights experience Sunday night at 9pm no wait Seems like most of the bad reviews deal with their customer service and wait time Agitation leads to poor reviews but the food speaks for itself Got the Holy GuacAioli Burger Wow this was by far the best burger Ive had from DMK A juicy grass fed burger with chorizo guacamole sonoma jack cheese chipotle aioli cilantro and onions  Loved the chorizo and was not overpowering Kind of a delicious sloppy joe on top of my burgerI usually get the 4 with Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack Cheese Smoked Bacon Im such a sucker for a fried egg on a burger but every single time I hate how messy this can get Never again after discovering the GuacAioli burger I HATE that theyre 1011 for JUST the burger and no sides I could eat like 3 of these Its easy to rack up a big bill if you get a burger fries beer milkshake etc Fries are decent The Wisconsin cheddar and scallion is very underwhelming I would rather get ball park fries to tell you the truth The Parmesan Truffle Cream fries are pretty good The Truffle cream dipping sauce is really good I prefer the sweet potato fries with lemon tabasco aioli Atmosphere is great for friends or for a date The seating is a bit close and we could hear the couple next to us arguing Kinda weird but its dark and intimate and the bar is fun Seems like youre in a garage but the 1 person bathrooms are not cool

Author: Dave C.
Content: A review in 140 characters or lessPros No long wait good beer list reasonably sized patty Cons Burgers were fine but not exciting You could get better elsewhere Meh

Author: Michelle L.
Content: Not to be a Debbie downer but I really hated DMKIll start with the positive  the fries were amazing  They get the only star Im giving to this joint  The wisconson cheddar fries were deliciously cheesy  but not in the artificial way  The truffleparm fries had the perfect hint of truffle oil  YUM  Thank goodness the fries were so good as that was all I had for dinnerI ordered the patty melt for my burger  First off I was surprised they didnt ask me how I wanted it  Not a big deal but surprising  When the food came the burgers arrived on a tiny plate again not a big deal but presentation was lacking  My burger looked good I cut it in half and took a big bite and much to my dismay we didnt have paper napkins just cheap towel napkins that shedded all over my black pants btw so I wasnt able to discretely spit it out  It was hands down disgusting  The sauce that was piled all over the darn thing had the most unpleasant tang to it it absolutely had no place on a patty melt or a burger  As far as I was concerned it was a supertangy sauce sandwich that happened to have a beef patty thrown in there  I was with a decent size party so I didnt want to complain to the waitress that my burger was the worst thing Ive eaten in a very long time so I kept my mouth shut  I kinda figured she would ask me about it since the whole thing was still sitting on my plate and I would politely tell herbut no apparently the waitstaff is used to people just eating one bit of their entrée and throwing the rest away  It was very oddPlus my husband didnt like his burger either  Just didnt taste right with all of the extra ingredientsSo DMK thanks a lot for the long wait just to eat the worst burger Ive had in a long time or ever

Author: Don L.
Content: This place has had a lot of hype and was just average The burger I had was a 1 Tasty burger great bun but not the biggest burger I have eaten The sweet potato fries were awesome with  lemon Tabasco aioli sauce I dont understand how you cant offer different cooking temps for burgers My girlfriend ate the Veggie 12 I believe  The patty tasted decent but I think it was cooked in a deep fryer My Blood Orange soda was refreshing but her Mojito sucked We sat at the bar in which our bartender was awesome except she didnt notice that her mojito stayed full the entire time That would be a sign to me that there was a problem Oh turn down the music from the concert levels would be a plus

Author: Courtney C.
Content: Dont go here This place is awful At least at Burger King you can order things your way and you already expect the burgers to be flimsy and tastelessI really liked the options of one of the burgers but cant eat goat cheese so I asked to substitute the goat cheese for  blue cheese The waitress was so flabbergasted that I would dane to mess with the amazing taste profile their chef aka burgerflipper had designed She said substitutions were not allowed and told me some lame story about how the chef created these burgers to a science Really Its a burger Come onSo I ordered just a plain burger with cheddar because apparently that was the amazing taste profile the chef had come up with that I could actually eat It was the most disgusting burger I have ever eaten And for 8 White Castle does a better job and their cashiers arent mouthy and rude like the waitstaff at DMKOverpriced disgusting food served by rude and disrespectful staff

Author: Tina P.
Content: I ate here on a Sunday evening and had no wait for a table Previous reviewers mentioned loud music but that also didnt seem to be a problemTip Sunday after 9 pm is service industry night with 12 off burgers Too bad working in a hospital doesnt constitute as a service industry even though it definitely feels like itAtmosphere spacious area with an industrial vibe cool place to take guests and friendsFood Burgers are 5 oz patties that are smushed down to be a thin patty Interesting toppings Nice soft bun I tried the 2 and the 5 bison burger Both sounded more appetizing on paper I wish the burger would have focused more on the meat texture     Btw no substitutions allowed on burgersSweet potato fries were my favorite part of the meal Truffle fries were lackluster Fried pickles tasted fine The ranch dipping sauce contained dill which was interesting Deviled eggs were averageDrinks A few beers on draft a nice selection of beers in bottles They also have a cocktail menu And for those wanting something ETOH free theres also different flavored sodas and milkshakes availablePrice 811 for the burger only Summary 3 12 stars I wanted to like this place more with all the rave reviews but the meat patty here is overshadowed by the toppings

Author: Daniel S.
Content: As I walked in the place my first impression would be that its a hipster spot It was busy even for dinner on a Sunday Luckily I went with one person so we were seated immediately Everything looked clean and it was not overly loudI ordered a 4 and shared some parmesan fries The food was good as the meat was tender and you cannot go wrong with a fried egg AND bacon Im not a big fan when it comes to french fries but it was good It lives up to the hype The waitress was nice and I do love it when your waitress is attentive and refills your water without having to ask for it Thatll always go far in my books when Im thinking about leaving a good or bad tipIf I could id give DMK a 4 12 stars only because the burger was kind of small I feel that it was like a 14 lb and based on that price Etnos which is like 5 minutes away has a 12 lb burger and is around the same price Overall Id go back and try other items on the menu

Author: Julie P.
Content: Great burgers and the Parmesan truffle fries were awesome Just be prepared to wait if going on a weekend

Author: Jennie T.
Content: Ive been on a search for a good burger place and I think I may have found it last night when my friends and I came to DMK I do think that that restaurant could turn down the volume of their music a little bit though I mean a burger place is loud enough with everyone there do you really feel the need to make it so loud that I have to practically yell out my dialogues to my friends sitting next to meTiff H and I split our turkey burger 9 and the lamb burger 11 I think I prefer the turkey burger more The combination of the turkey patty eggplant and portobello was amazing I think I could care a little less about the coleslaw on it though because Im not that fond of the purple cabbage or any raw cabbage unless its drenched in nuoc mam Vietnamese fish sauce but that wouldnt be good on this burger so nevermind The lamb burger had just a little too much cheese or vinegar I couldnt really tell which but it was too sharp and definitely did not remind me of a gyro as much as most of the Yelpers here described it With a group of five we ordered a basket of the regular salt and pepper fries and a basket of the Amish blue cheese and bacon fries I liked the basket of fries with bits of bacon and blue cheese tossed on top of it Mmm delicious

Author: Anne M.
Content: Okay DMK Burger Bar you were good  I like you  Also liked the friendly and quick waitstaff and the lookfeel of the place  it was hip but not stuck up  Also excellent funlaid back music The bounty we tried parmesan  truffle oil fries sweet potato friescreamy coleslawturkey burger standard with tomatogreenscheeseturkey burger with charred onions bbq and cheeseANDpeanut butterchocolate shakeThe fries were awesome  both kinds and the sauces were good too  Though Im not a fan of having to order everything a la carte  throw me a bone and give me some fries with my burger dont make me order a separate order  Coleslaw was good not too heavy and topped with green onion but only greens in the coleslaw i missed the colors of carrots and red cabbage  Burgers were both great we split them so we tried one of each  The buns were very soft and fresh the burger itself was juicy and toppings were flavorful  yummy  Finally though we were stuffed we split the shake and it was fabulous  Im glad we tried it and by splitting it the little glasses were the perfect amount  I prefer Epic Burgers turkey burgers to DMK but everything we tried here was excellent  Ill most likely be back and Im getting a full shake for myself next time

Author: Rhoda G.
Content: I treated my friend out to dinner for her last night in Chicago so I took her to DMK The place was jammed pack and happening even for a Monday night but we didnt wait too long for a tableWe were excited to try out their fries but we found out that they use beef in their oil and my friend who is a vegetarian did not like that Instead we ordered the onion strings and deviled eggs which we both enjoyed For drinks we got 2 beers on tap  Gumballhead from 3 Floyds and the White from Allgash Refreshing Next we got our burgers I decided to get the bison burger which came with goat cheese pickled red onion and blueberry BBQ sauce I was somewhat disappointed with my burger The flavors were all there but I like my beef patties more firmer and thicker My friend really liked her vegetarian burger and she appreciated that it was homemade and not some frozen patty  AOK experience I wouldnt mind coming back again to try another burger and any of those fries

Author: Al D.
Content: I think 35 starts is fitting for DMKIts another overhyped hamburger stand Chicago has enough of theseThe service was attentive but we also went early on a Saturday St Paddys day to beat the usual weekend crowds My Italianstyle Burger of the Month was pretty bland with barely a dollop of sauce The prosciutto slice was pretty chintzy and flavorless too My burger also was dangerously undercooked in spots The fries were good but nothing amazing I did enjoy the the creamy cheese with bacon The parmigiana cheese for for parm fires kinda fell off in a fused mess Unique beer selection at least

Author: Justin N.
Content: Jen rocks Amazing host and approachable as one of the managers As far as the food it definitely lives up to the hype and wait The aioli selection that is paired with the fries are simply amazing The burgers had lots of flavor We finished our meal with the chocpeanut butter milkshakes That was my highlight of the meal Definitely going backAdvice make sure you plan on staying a while to accommodate for the wait and digestion of your food Thankfully theres a Bar there

Author: Christian H.
Content: As a man who loves burgers and I dont mean the greasy crappy McDonald burgers I have to say that I was very disappointed by DMK Burger Bar I expected something amazing but I just found a typical burger with different toppings Not to say the whole dinner was bad but it was not that great either One bad thing was the service My friend and I had to wait over an hour for a seat When we finally got a seat it was at the long community table I dont mind sitting with others but the table was so wide that I could hardly hear my friend And the music and people were so loud that I was glad to leave Our server wasnt all the friendly but at least the hostess was nice As stated before the food was just okay The burger wasnt amazing and the fries were good but not anything that I couldnt just make at home Though the dipping sauce was delicious Im not a huge beer drinker so Im looking for a beer that I can drink The beers that I tried didnt do the trick for me I had to force myself to finish them The only reason Im give this place a three instead of a two is due to the price and the fact that DMK cannot control all the complaints that I spoke about Would I go here again Only if someone forced me or I got a gift certificate

Author: Rich T.
Content: Loved the sides but the main attraction was not what I was expectingin a bad way  The fries are hauntingly good and Ive rarely if ever had a better mac and cheese at a restaurant  However my portabella burger was a bit of a cheap shot in my opinion  It was tasty no doubt but I tend to eat healthier when I go out and was annoyed when my seemingly healthy choice arrived deep fried  A little heads up that the healthiestseeming option on the menu was going to come to you fried would have been nice     I would go back for sure but a little transparency goes a long way with me as Im sure it does a lot of people in the trying to lose weight but dont want to sacrifice going out crowd

Author: Christina P.
Content: For a girl that loves her stilettos as much as her Pumas DMK Burger Bar is a love child of all things somewhat slummy somewhat classy and all around delicious Head here on a Friday night and you will expect a wait But thats part of the fun Grab a beer catch up with your crew and prepare to have your taste buds wowed Order up the cheddar fries pair it with some wasabi slaw and make the main event any of the burgers Personally I loved the turkey burger but you cant go wrong I dig on the bartenders and kind of want whoever created their playlist to make me a mixed tape From Pete Yorn to Rolling Stones they play some jams

Author: Jenni Q.
Content: We split a 1 burger which came topped with grilled onions bacon and bbq sauce 8  I really liked the bread and the burger itself was really juicy and tasty  We also got an order of the sea salt and black pepper fries 4large which were just okay  we couldnt really see or taste any of the salt or pepper and the fries could have been a little hotter and fresher  Definitely not on my list of favorites  The fried okra and fried dill pickles 5 were a little too sour for me  I was excited to try my first fried pickle but the breading came off pretty easily so most of the time I was left with just the pickle itself  Service was great and the atmosphere was very trendy but laidback  Prices were pretty reasonable except for the sodas  I did not enjoy paying almost 2 for a can  if you are going to charge that price then it should be fountain soda with free refills  I would probalby come back here again just for the burgers but skip out on the appetizers and drinks

Author: Katie T.
Content: I had to try the standard cheese burger 8 Im an american cheese girl so I got that on it and it came with lettuce tomato onions and mayo I liked it but I nothing I would rush out to try againThe fries were really good We tried the standard salt and pepper ones and the sweet potato fries We also tried the onion strings which were also very good I had a couple of bites of the other burgers and I liked the toppings on all Compared to the standard burger they didnt really stand out and they had a great flavor but left you wanting more I would have to make sure I had fries with these burgers because alone the flavor needs to be broken up make senseI also had an ice cream sandwich that was made with chocolate cookies and coffee ice cream I really like it Next time I may just ask for a scoop of coffee ice cream because it was so good

Author: Deena D.
Content: Veggie fed beef amazing burger combos and a wicked nice staff Ive had the lamb burger as well as the burger with portobella and have loved them both I like the fact how you dont feel guilty after eating it because its the perfect size Fries with the truffle dipping sauce are deelish as well as the sweet potatoes Youre best bet is to go in later if you plan on going on the weekend since they get so busy But hey why not turn that wait time into a pregame Especially with a kick ass beer list

Author: Molly L.
Content: Im a little upset with myself that it took me 5ish times of dining at DMK to come around and write a review in their honor Better late than never right Ive been on a quest to try the best burger joints in the city of Chicago and DMK is my favorite  thus far DMK is an all around knock out  from the delicious and perfectly sized burgers which many before have mentioned to their massiveunique beer list which is greatly appreciated to their AMAZING staff Appssides  Get the macaroni  cheese 2 w baconAndor sweeeet potato fires  I can die a happy ladyBurgs  Wide variety for whatever tastes you may have Whether youre tried and true  Ive gotten the one with blue cheese and onion straws 4 out of 5 times Or out of the box  theyre always pushing the envelope with new tastes and burgers of the month  ie my boyfriend got I dont remember the clever name burger which was a beef patty topped with a Chicago style dogveryyy good Beer  We get a new one each time Ive never been disappointed Mostly enlightenedStaff  Ask for DREW Hes the best Literally Tip  While this joint is crowded EVERY time weve been able to squeeze in at the bar quickly almost every time with a party of 2Get outta here Go

Author: Eugene C.
Content: 25 because the interior of the place is nice the service is pretty solid and prompt however I dont see the fuss about the burgers In a city where designer burgers are trendy as hell DMKs burger reminds me if Steak and Shake became a hip urban chain with booze this would be the result If youre going the way of the designer burger joint you need to have the option to cook the burger to the customers liking At a steep 8 per burger the price does not reflect this option unfortunately The fries are decent but nothing special You can put a bunch of toppings on it to mask its mediocrity but I suppose you can do that with pretty much anything

Author: Amanda R.
Content: I went here on a Sunday night it was busy but not packed where you couldnt move or get a table I waited for about 10 minutes chatting with the hostess about the newly opened restaurant and then our table was ready They have a good selection of specialty beers on tap so it was fun to try a new wheat beer The staff was very knowledgeable and informative for first timers to the burger bar they are not trying to be the counter the counter is a build your own burger place this is not The burgers are cooked all the way through which I was scared of at first because I like my burgers med rare but it was juice and not over cooked or dry The burgers are a decent size so you can actually finish it and try other appetizers like the mac and cheese which was good or the truffle or sweet potato fries The sweet potato fries were my favorite I also had the burger with the portabello mushrooms and chives It was good I will go back to this place to try the other burgers it was a nicely decorated and would be fun to hang out and have a cocktail or beer after a nice meal It would be a nice jump off point to a Friday or Saturday night I sat in the front and it was a nice view and great seating in the big red booth but I was a little chilly because it was right by the door as I walked to the back of the restaurant to go to the bathroom I noticed it was warmer so that might affect your seating preference

Author: Rachel R.
Content: Deviled Eggs as a side dish OMG SUPER AWESOMEhowever as much as I love the food at DMK well everything but the burgers I have yet to actually eat a burger there  it just feels like they made the seating as uncomfortable as possible  The tables are way too close to each other for in the winter no coat check ew and the tall tables are just difficult for eating but the bar is nice and everyone is friendly and DEVILED EGGSbut minus one star because of the cramped eating space

Author: Tabitha G.
Content: Yum yum give me some  You know a place is going to be good when you have a hard time deciding not only what to eat but to drink  My friend and I went to DMK on a Friday night roughly about 645pm and easily got a table  The place wasnt packed yet and there were plenty of open tables  Immediately as we sat down the first thing I noticed was the plethora of beer options on their menu  Even if youre not a beer drinking Im pretty sure youll find something you like  It took us a while to figure out a beer to order because of the large selection but our waitress recommendation is what sold us on what we gotChoosing a burger was no different  There were so many fantastic options but couldnt just pin point one  It was a game time decision for me between the veggie burger and a chili rubbed burger  After close to 10 minutes of figuring out what to get I ended up with the veggie burger and it was the best decision  Even if youre not a veggie burger fan this is the one that would convince you otherwise  Its a bold statement but I am confident when I say that it was probably one of the if not only best veggie burgers Ive ever had  The patty was so crisp and the toppings were icing on the cake  However the piece de resistanceTheir bun  Its fantastic and so incredibly soft  It really makes the burgerThe sides were also fantastic  We had fried okra and pickles which were scrumptious and also ordered the parmesan and truffle cream fries  Our waitress was so fantastic that she also sent over some cheddar fries as well  The small sides were the perfect size and totally innexpensive at 2each  Every bite of our meal was fantasticI would be remisced to not say how wonderful our waitress was  She not only was extremely patient with how slow it took us to order but she had great recommendations  and was very knowledgeable  Not to mention that she also sent us a fries Lastly as if I wasnt already sold on this place  One thing I love is that their beef is grassfed  which is a big deal for me  Considering that all their burgers are 8each serving grassfed beef just makes it that much better  Im particular about my meats by trying to eat organic and DMK just makes it that easyI highly recommend this place  I just cant wait to try their other burgers

Author: Shang S.
