Content: Ive been pretty excited for DMK and ordered 4 burger based on the below reviews I definitely think that the grass fed beef is worth it the texture just feels more defined flavorful I was a little too engrossed in my conversation to be able to fully judge the burger Its certainly not the best burger Ive eaten I cant even customize it and being the klutz I am the egg exploded over my plate as I bit into it augh no the yolk However I thoroughly did enjoy the burger there arent too many complaints about it from my end Its not the worlds biggest burger but it is satisfying for the average personWe also got the truffle fries I wish the fries didnt taste as dry as they did I think that the fries could have been better but the truffle mayo oh yeah that was totally worth itI didnt quite like my DMK Manhattan but I think thats mostly due to personal preferenceAlso one thing I didnt like about DMK are the cloth napkins that didnt feel so sturdy to me They reminded me of my mothers kitchen towelettes that shed use to wipe the countertopThe service was prompt friendly We went on a Tuesday night and even then there were many people in this place so I cant imagine how crowded it must be during the weekend

Author: Brian S.
Content: I am not particularly a strict burger connoisseur but I was rather disappointed with DMK I got the 2 The patty was pretty pathetic if youre as hungry as a bear However if you suffer from bulimia or wish to eat a make believe burger it might satisfy you The thing I thought was silly was the separate order of fries for 24 depending on size Ok So my burger was 8 to begin with now I have to push it up to 1012 to feel somewhat full The beer selection is decent and the service is ok I dont understand how this place is considered to be one of Chicagos finest for burgersIll give you a recommendation for a solid burger at an appropriate cost  The Big Square   Square Bar on Belmont  10 and worth every cent

Author: k e.
Content: The good great burgers great beer selection great friesThe bad every time Ive been there its super crowded and incredibly loud

Author: Deepika T.
Content: DMK was a great burger place Be prepared to wait unless you come in at around 10pm over the weekends Much can be said about that great bread the sweet potato fries with the lime tabasco aioli and the veggie grain burger But theyre pretty particular about not giving you the veggie burger on anything but their 12 A big downer if you ask me They do have a 13 which is a fried crispy portabello version umm not the best or worst Ive had My meateating friends did love their beef versions though Be prepared to fork over mega bucks for the alcoholic beverages though The desserts were very unimpressive I can do cookieice cream sandwiches myself thank you Also dont drive over parking in the neighborhood is a serious pain

Author: Gary R.
Content: I have to say this place was good as hell I had a lunch there on a Saturday afternoon and you might be astonished to learn I purchased a cheeseburger This wasnt your run of the mill McDonalds burger oh no It contained Pesto Prosciutto and meat McDonalds doesnt have anything like that at their storesThey also put salt and vinegar chips on the burger which was awesome as heck The fries were good and really arent all fries good The burger also came with a little Italian flag I think it was meant to make the customers feel like they were in Florence Unfortunately they were in Chicago instead I went with a small child who when asked about her Mac and Cheese stated Its yummy Small children are always saying shit like that My only real issue with this place is that I want to call it the BTK burger bar I suppose it might as well be called that in the cow community but in the human community that is a worse connotation The price was pretty reasonable as well I didnt feel like a giant held me upside down and shook all the change from my pockets after the meal so that was a plus In addition if that were to have happened Id likely have barfed Not because the food wasnt good but rather because I was being held upside down by a giant

Author: sheena r.
Content: i like the idea of this place more than i like their burgers BUT i do like their burgers  the fact that they use grass fed beef for their burgers is what wins me over their sweet potato fries are tasty and it may have something to do with the aioli i will be back to try their truffle fries and shakes

Author: Ellen D.
Content: Eh this place was not as good as I was hoping it would be I guess I thought it would be similar to The Counter where you can build your own burger but its not Oh and there are no substitutions which kind of blows The fries are really good and the turkey burger wasnt bad either I guess I was just expecting more Overall not bad but not amazing

Author: Matt H.
Content: I try every burger joint that rolls through town and this is without question my favorite I keep my burger simple and usually go with the No 8 The DMK 8 reminds me of an uppity single layer 5 Guys burger and I consider that to be a complimentDMK has really good fries and onion strings for sides I havent tried some of the more rich menu items bleu cheese and bacon burgersfries but I plan on going back to try them all eventuallyKiller beer list but not an overly complicated menu and once you get the hang of it it all makes senseWish there was one in my W Loop hood

Author: Sarah L.
Content: Ive been here twice and both times received superb service Once on an extremely busy Friday night the host offered to move us to a new table after we were sat next to an an extra loud speaking patronnot DMKs fault at all Then on top of it they gave us a complimentary mac and cheese Well above expectations On top of this great beer selection  They even had the rare game of thrones edition of ommegang beer on tap Finally of course burgers had unique toppings  cooked perfectly and flavorful If youre debating between DMK and Kumas  pick DMK

Author: Jaime G.
Content: Really good burger place In a cluttered part of town lakeview but def worth coming Ive got to admit the thing that attracted me the most about this place is the beer selection Wide variety of beer from all over the country On tap and in bottles  I tried the great lakes porter and the left hand milk stoutGood for kids too They gave my son a little cup of fries as soon as we walked in Great service all around and everyone is really friendly A little loud  its more of a bar that restaurantBurgers are super good We tried the green chili burger and the lamb burger Both excellent Have to admit that the green chili burger is really hot so not for the faint at heart I really like the burger build They let the burger meat and the fine ingredients shine because the bum is so soft and light Love that They get 5 stars for the combination of beer selection excellent service and burgers

Author: Rick M.
Content: OH EM GEE DEE EM KAY IS THE BESTI came here on the 18th of April my birthday and cannot believe I havent written a review yet This place is AWESOMEI am so serious these are some of the best burgers in the Chicagoland area that I have ever tasted The service is great and their Cokes with Cherry grenadine were just sweet enough it made me super happy yeah I had to add that The decoration of the place was nice Black and red always go nicely together Theres a big bar in the center of the restaurant and it was pretty busy even during a weekday Yes the place is loud as many have said but it didnt detract from our experience at all Its loud because its busy Its busy because its good SeeAnyway looking at their menu I was completely flabbergasted  and when I use big words on Yelp you know its truly amazingTheir burger combinations were great and they seriously had something for everyone  even vegetarians Im not a vegetarian though and stuck with some delicious juicy decadent meatymeat meat When we were waiting for our burgers to come out we were given free deviledeggs which were seriously fantastic We were going to order them anyway so it was a nice little birthday surprise When the food came both of us were blown away by how delicious it was and how much food came on our plates Oh yeah and the Wisconsin cheese fries were freakin great If I remember correctly we were both stunned by the good price and exceptional quality of the food we orderedSurprised we havent been back since After dissecting our last experience I can absolutely promise you we will be back again and again Absolutely delicious food good service fantastic prices All the right ingredients in a place to make you WANT to keep coming back

Author: Juliana R.
Content: Our server CARLY was great When we arrived it was busy and she was just on top of it Besides thatthis place is OVERRATED go to Kumas instead The seating here is AWKWARD I am definitely not into the last supper kind of tables And the burgers were the size of a burger you get from Culvers And they DONT include frieswhat Stupid No thx

Author: nancy r.
Content: Best deal in town during Industry night on SundaysI ordered their local beer Goose Island MatildaAlong with the Patty Melt and added a fried egg which blew the burger out of ranksWhen I recieved my burger it was perfectly cooked medium and super juicy with a nice over easy egg which ran down my burger after the first bite It was love at first bite and I didnt want to finish it because after I was done I wanted another one Along with the burger I ordered the parm cheese fries that were great too No ketchup Served with a super yummy aoli that I forget because it was done in mere minutesHad an order of deviled eggs too which were BOMB Super simple with a a nIce little kick a bit of cayenne kickSuper impressed with the foodThe service was okay the server messed up a couple of times and apologizedWe got our deviled eggs a bit late as well as a wrong order of fries but the manager stopped by to only give us FREE dessert I was so full and stuck in a food coma that I could only eat several bitesOur bill afterwards was DIRT cheap with the Industry discount So if you or any of your friends work in the Industry stop by Great food

Author: Kevin W.
Content: We had a bunch of burgers that were not meat and they were fantastic I had the veggie burger and the Big Salad Yummy My mom had the portebello mushroom burger which is flash fried in panko Really good Fries are great Try the basis salt and pepper with the homemade spicy ketchup Also Wisconsin Cheddar and scallion Really good Great beer list Half Acre is always a hit Only complaint is the noise level in this place It is insane due to the construction They need to add some sound buffers or rugs Service was phenomenal Servers are young bright and cheery

Author: Brian E.
Content: I think Yelps 3 star rating describes DMK pretty well AOK Its not mindblowing but its not badI decided to do some research on our visit to Chicago and DMK seemed to get pretty high remarks from the various comments sections that I viewed So it was planned to end our trip with a late afternoon stop here before heading backAh Chicago how your parking is atrocious Not a knock against DMK but this city needs JetpacksWe timed it perfectly While DMK was packed at around 445 a spot cleared up for my small group straight away We were seated and soon there after we had the attention of our waitress whos name eludes me She did a great job from beginning to end and really made us feel welcomeIts really a mixed bag here Its rather loud and pretty dim Reviews citing the use of cell phones to read menus makes sense On the plus side Top Gun was being played on the TVsWhen you look over the menu they definitely have some creative burger ideas I kept it simple and ordered the 1 which was aged cheddar smoked bacon charred balsamic red onions and Rufus Teagues BBQ sauceThe burger itself done properly but the balsamic was overwhelming It really sounded like it had potential but the execution wasnt there I could almost swear there was marmite in there The fries are a side note really Its friesEveryone else in my group enjoyed their meals Though similar comments were made about the 1 by a friend If i am in the area again they do deserve another visit Though Chicago seems to have plenty of other choices when it comes to burgers  DMK comes in at slightly above average

Author: Samantha L.
Content: Its a little hard to review because I split a fifth of vodka with a friend shortly before coming here Yes I mean we finished the bottle Aka I was SUPER drunk when I got here Hopefully my drunk taste buds werent too deceivingTheir truffle fries were DELICIOUS and I was craving them throughout the following day Their burger with egg and peppers on it was fairly good but too much flour was on the bun and it comes with NO sides despite being 89 I had some special mac and cheese with bacon and grilled onions that was also deliciousThe combination of all the great greasy food and the waiter keeping up with refilling my water magically prevented me from getting sick or hungover so I am grateful All my friends were surprised I wasnt hungover the next day so thank you DMK I will try you again sober and hopefully like you just as much

Author: Cara T.
Content: I have to go back here at least 13 more times because I only had one burger and I need to try every other burgersandwich on DMKs menu I wanted to try the Salmon Burger but they were sold out Not a problemI would eat any of those burgers they put in front of me I ended up with the Bison burger The combinations on this burger are out of this world You can taste each flavor in each bite Mind blowing As a table we shared the onion strings and the Parmesan fries  That truffle cream is to die for Just give me a spoon DMK is guaranteed my business for at least 13 more trips For sure And probably long after that

Author: Andy S.
Content: Going into DMK I wasnt sure what to expect  Bits and pieces of information about it have been leaking out for the past several months all contributing to a fair bit of hype from Timeout to The New York Times  For some reason I hadnt quite bought into the hype but at the same time was really looking forward to going as I cant turn down a good burgerAnd you know what  I didnt turn down a good burger I ate it right up  I had a burger with NY Pastrami Grand Cru Gruyere Cheese Sauerkraut Leroys Remoulade and it was delicious and so were the sweet potato fries some of the best Ive had in the city  At 10 for the burger and fries combo I was pleasantly surprised  So why the two stars  The service and the drinks  Our server while nice belied a fair bit of passiveaggressiveness with us and was a more than a little pushy regarding drinks It actually seemed the only time she paid us any attention was to ask if we wanted more drinks beyond that the service was slow and not very attentive  Additionally the man who I can only assume was the manager was unpleasant in his own way constantly glaring over at us as we ate and talked with a look that was unmistakable for hurry up and leave while coming over at regular intervals to move our unused seats to other tables seemingly randomly granted shortly thereafter the place did start to pick up but his behavior was odd uncomfortable and unfriendlyOnto the drinks oh my  While I suppose DMK stems from some nicer places I still expect drinks to be a bit more reasonable when youre operating a burger bar  Please dont offer me a 12 barcreated cocktail that is fairly weak and nothing save for averagefor the same price you could go to one of several bars around Chicago that have incredible mixologists making amazing original drinks  And while I dont drink beer allergies my friends scoffed at the beer prices for the most part not a good signI REALLY wanted to have a great experience at DMK and a REALLY hate writing overly negative reviews when nothing overly horribly occurred but sadly DMK has found its way into rarefied air in terms of my reviews  I intend to go back though and if things are any different Ill be sure to update

Author: Jon E.
Content: As trendy Chicago burger joints go I really enjoy DMK as a riposte to the Kumas love For starters their angle is different and executed well along that axis They use grassfed beef which is pricier easier to dry out and less forgiving of massive patties  yet the burgers themselves are always excellent The menu is neater rather limited but has a full range to satisfy most appetites Except maybe vegetarian but cmon why would a vegetarian expect that much out of a burger joint The fried sides are great as are the spread of burger toppings Some have said they dont care for the bread much but I personally enjoy the rolls they use  Theres a french place I loved in San Francisco that did stellar burgers this way same bread  so I gotta give props to DMK for continuing that For those who insist on standard aka boring ketchup in bottleslettucetomatoonion burgers than DMK is not for you If size of portionssandwich is your primary motivation for rating food highly then again DMK is not for you I think DMK has successfully created an alternative burger bar experience that doesnt have to compete with Kumas I enjoy both but for totally different reasons

Author: Lindsey W.
Content: BEST VEGGIE BURGER IN CHICAGO I love DMK for its veggie burgers and greek salads  BEST ive had in chicago and recommend this to any vegetarian NOTE VEGETARIANS  do not eat the amazing looking french fries they are cooked in our animal friends fat

Author: Steve T.
Content: I wasnt sure what I was going to think of DMK yet another restaurant trying to cash in on the burger bar craze as of late  Ive been a few times and had been waiting to review because I was curious of consistency and overall experience  Its pretty good but I dont ever find myself thinking wow I want a burger Im going to go to DMK  There are a lot of other restaurants with just as many good options for a burger  It has an upbeat atmosphere but can be pretty loud  The proximity of some of the tables to the door can be troublesomely cold during winter and there isnt much waiting space inside for those lurking for tables other than the bar  I also find there is an odd amount of children in the restaurant in the early evening which was a bit shocking for me but I guess it could have just been the luck of the draw for me during the few times Ive been  Nothing against kids but the tables are sometimes shared with your neighbors think dining european style with a large table of 12 that can be split up with multiple seating arrangements immediately next to each other and unless you had been geared up for dining with the family next to you your evening might have become a little more interestingannoying  Overall its an OK experience and you wont hate your burger  The parmesan fries are somewhat addicting and will probably make you fat if you keep eating them every time you come in and dont follow them up with 2 hours of cardio  The beer list is pretty large and has a lot of unique options  Though Im not a beer drinker and would much rather prefer a vat of Belvedere so I cant vouch for the selection being great but my friends tell me its quite good

Author: Livvy O.
Content: This burger has to be one of the best burgers Ive had I loved the idea of the fried eggWhen I heard they put fried egg on their burgers I was intrigued by it and couldnt wait to try it It was brilliant The only con about this place is that it is extremely loudboth people and music and of course parking is always a hassle in this area But I would definitely go back WAY better than Kumas Corner Overrated and pretentious crowd This is a much more mixed crowd

Author: Ehrin S.
Content: I really wanted to like this place I did Truly And I hate to say the previous because its so cliche But it is what it is and I just cant give this place more than two stars Honestly Ive had much much better much less expensive burgers Epic Burger for one I was expecting a thick juicy patty with topshelf toppings but what I got was just a mediocre sized burger on a way too thick bun It was a little dry a bit too covered in the condiment and just disappointing Plus sides Very nice space nice bar plenty of flat screens to catch a game great sides truffle fries are tasty and nice beer selection Other than that if youre in the mood for a great burger try Kumas Corner

Author: Riz A.
Content: Im only giving this place 3 stars because the drinks were strong  i love the neighborhood and i really liked the simple bar type decor the food however not all that great the parmesan truffle fries were goodthe burgers ehh i hate to be one of the people that always compares restaurants  but this place holds no flame to kumasi mean actually i  think rock bottom has better burgers honestly 8 bucks for a gourmet burger isnt that bad of a pricebut the burger just wasnt all that greatit had some gross cheese that was way overpowering and just overtook the taste of the meatthe portions are pretty tiny as wellfor 12 bucks  cost of burger toppings and fries i expect a bigger burger than a big macnot really worth a return there are much better burger spots in this town

Author: Francis K.
Content: A burger bar Say wha Okay seriously a burger barGood thing it works otherwise it is too easy to mock this place For starters what on earth does DMK stand for anyway Oh the food you ask The burger list is impressive I will have to return because a lamb burger was beckoning but started easy by choosing their 1 instead This was an Aged Cheddar Smoked Bacon Charred Balsamic Red Onions took a pass on the BBQ Sauce burger was was out of this world good The burger bar also has an equally impressive beer menu The location of the bar is in the high rent part of Chicago which means it is accompanied by the inevitable above 90 hipster quotient I cannot hold that against them but consider this fair warning

Author: Donna C.
Content: All burgers at DMK are grassfed so it can be a little pricier than what people normally expect out of the size of those burgers I dont have a problem with that since a grassfed burger simply tastes BETTER They have 8 options well one is actually coming soon I ordered 5 and husband had the 8 5 comes with brie and portabella and 8 is a straight up classic I have to say that having tried both you need to experience 8 for a true taste of the burger Its simple deliciousness at its best without all the fancy cheeses and savoury toppings Of course we love that it was made with loveOur waitress was great and we loved the variety of beers they have on tap Allagash wheat was awesomeWell be back

Author: Erica S.
Content: I moved Thats where Ive been guys I moved on the first day of an internship and also had class Because I moved on this day I had to hire out my boyfriend and his brother to move me Which they were ok with until it actually happened Then they were mad I needed to make it up to themEnter DMK Burger BarMy boyfriend loves burgershe hates steak but he loves burgers His brother is a vegetarian Ive wanted to try DMK Burger Bar I live around the corner This was the timeWe walked in pretty late for a Wednesday and were seated right away We wanted waterand nothing else at this point so we asked for water It was filled up continuously throughout the night We were never without water and it was greatThe food was also great I got the 3anytime you put pastrami on a burger Im there I didnt share it was so good And grass fed My boyfriend got the 2 and also didnt share He ate it slowly savoring it Thats a signal The brother got the vegetarian burger which he then proclaimed the best hes ever eaten which made me feel good because I was paying and because Im glad he had food to eatWe also got two kinds of friestruffle and wisconsin cheddar and scallion They were both good and because we shared I didnt feel like such a fat ass eating themWhat really did it for me and this is not a lie was the fried okra and pickles Really it was the pickles In the herb ranch Did I mention the fried pickles Blow your mind amazing I will go back to eat those over and over4 stars cause Im a broke ass graduate school ho but if I wasnt Id eat all of this as much as I could

Author: Jane L.
Content: A for effortB for the onion ringsC for the tasteD for the loud atmosphereF for the fact that the waitress didnt taste all the items in the menu  Isnt that part of training

Author: Samantha H.
Content: Fantastic lunch or dinner spot I had the veggie burger something I NEVER order over red meat but I absolutely loved it We also ordered four different types of fries for the table and they were all incredible  parm sweet potato and cheddar fries are all must haves The only bad thing was no free refills on soda and they could have been more watchful of our empty water glasses  we were all parched because we loved the food so much I will definitely be going back

Author: Dina G.
Content: BISON BURGER whats a bisongoogle itSweet potato fries with cheese dip and a fat american burgerhats off to america I salute thee I mean why is it so hard to find stuff like this at home Im either eating at the wrong joints or blind and missing the good stuff This place is small but full of flavour full of soul and drink A great hang out Just opposite the VIC theatre what more can you ask for Ever since I left the place Ive craved the burger just to feel the burger touch my lips and take in its scrumptious self  someone take me back please

Author: Mike M.
Content: I finally fell to the hype that surrounds DMK Burger Bar Im convinced they are good friends to 90 of food bloggers The place is cool has the hipster beer menu thats becoming a must for local stops I dont mind communal tables that much but maybe the issues is that youre in the deep end of pretentious conversations such as but not limited to the guy next to me wishing his pregnant wife has a boy To the food The menu is very compelling but falls short I ordered the 4 and the the 1 piece of bacon broken into 3 doesnt make it a bacon burger Using the freshest bread for buns is great but when youre a high end burger joint why do you smash a burger like a Steak and Shake The burgers dryness rivals that of the artisan bread they tout This is the 3rd burger Ive eaten this week with essentially the same ingredients and Id rank it third Monks on Lake St was better hell even Bar Louie Why The burgers there are juicy and they ask how Id want my food cooked DMK Burger bar falls into the  been there done that category of Chicago burger joints

Author: Anh N.
Content: I came here with 3 other people so each of us ordered different things in order to try them all We got the parmesan truffle fries and the Wisconsin cheese fries which was on the house Both were good but not very memorable to me I personally prefer crispy fries but they got a bit soft under all the toppings  Its also a huge serving so I would order it in a big groupWe tried the Bison burger the bacon fried egg burger and the lamb burger  All were great because of their soft and savory patties  The lamb burger especially tastes like a greek gyro  The burgers are all 10 give or take so its a bit on the pricey side The BEST thing to get here though is the espresso shake Rich in coffee flavors with little bits of chocolate crushed in it  Probably the best shake everat 5 a pop its pricey but its a must try

Author: Cam M.
Content: Twas a great date destination  LocationAtmosphereThe atmosphere was nice  I liked the vibe of the joint all of the staff members were extremely friendlythey seem to enjoy their jobs food was great beer was awesome and it seemed to work The locationI dont get to that neighborhood much so it was great  Trendyrich enough to feel safe after several drinks but wasnt so wreaking of hipsters that I need to walk around with a sign that says TAKE A SHOWER  FoodDrinksBurgersI got a 1 aged cheddar charred balsamic red onions Smoked Bacon and Rufus Tegaues BBQ Saucedescription co their site with an added fried egg  I know that sounds odd but it works  They use grassfed beef and I never realized the difference that that makes  My grandpa raises black angus cattle aka awesome beef cattle and this burger rivals the fresh from the butcher beef  I forget what my date orderedit looked good but between the conversation and the fooddrinks I dont remember that part  FriesWe got an order of Amish Blue  Smoked Bacon fries for the table large order  We didnt finish half of them  They were great the fries are fairly standard seasoned fries but the toppings were great  DrinksBeerhmmmm beer  Their beer list is nice  I had 2 of Victorys Golden Monkey  The last time I had it was back in Virginia where it was on tap  It was equally good out of the bottle  If I lived closer I could see myself going there just to sample the variety of beers So I liked it  I plan on going back bringing the same company along

Author: Julie B.
Content: I like this place and would definitely come here again  I came on a thursday night around 8 so it was pretty busy  We had to wait about 20 minutes for a table but we got 2 seats at the bar so it wasnt badOrdered the deviled eggs delish and I had the burger with green chilis and a fried egg yum My dinner companion had the blue cheese burger which he refused to share  They have different fries to choose from and the ones we shared were greatI left off a star because the ambience is a little weak  The lighting is weird along with the decor Is it trying to be a sports bar Trendy Upscale  I definitely do not get it but enjoyed the food so I will take that sacrifice

Author: Heather M.
Content: Kinda pricey good burgers but nothing I cant live without  Ive tried the 1 and the 2 very pleased but I was expecting more considering it was a burger bar  There is a must try the wasabi coleslawomgamazing

Author: Nicole H.
Content: I live on the Southside but I get around I have no problem traveling to try new spots I actually enjoy exploring However it saddens me when they arent really worth the trip but hey I guess thats part of the experience I came here on a Thursday night and it was packed Thats not a problem for me It is a problem when you are directly in my face ignoring me How many people are going to look at me and walk off Seriously  When I finally was able to order I decided on a patty melt sweet potato fries and one of the house sodas I really enjoyed the soda My food tasted okay but the service was definitely lacking I probably wouldnt return

Author: Donnie B.
Content: I am giving this place 2 stars  not for quality of food but for quality of comfort and service I accompanied my girlrfiend there we are neighbors of the joint and were told itd be a 45 minute wait on a Tuesday at 8pm Once I gave a lets go somewhere else the host said Actually let me check the back Sure enough we were immediately seated  great service right Wrong The seating in the place is like a high school cafeteria You can hear a persons conversation from three tables down I felt cramped and distracted When a server walks by with orders she has to squeeze inbetween tables I watched a server dump some water on a customer because it was so hard for her to get by I dont blame the server I blame the owners for designing it so poorly DMK would be unable to accomodate any obese couple from eating here discrimination Lastly It took us 20 minutes for 2 glasses of water alcohol came right away and 25 minutes to get a servers attention to get our check We werent the only ones waiting on service I noticed many heads looking around for their servers This is poor because there were over 15 people working at the time Food  Awesome Really enjoyed the portion sizes and the tastes I enjoyed the number 1 and did not feel too fullBut the hype should die down Just because some trendy rich restaurant owners open up a new one doesnt mean its gonna be the best I say redo the entire set up give people privacy and we will have a 5 star restaurant

Author: Matt K.
Content: Visited DMK in the first couple days of their hard opening The interior is a bit dark with most of the light coming from a few plasmas on the wall There are a couple high top bar tables and some standard 4 top tables in the rear We were greeted and our name was taken for a table Perfect time to check out the bar Love the whiskey and micro heavy beer options It takes guts to do it in this areaWe were seated at a low 2 top in the rear of the restaurant The tables are way too close together Literally 4 inches apart They really need to sacrifice a few tabs to increase the comfort level back there As for the food hit and miss Calling yourself a burger bar in a burger loving city like Chicago is risky business if you dont have a great burger Their burger was not great The beef portion was on the small side and the flour based bun cant compete with the pretzel rolls of competitors Very average at best The mac and cheese was better than the burger and the fries were the stand out item We had the sweet potato fires They were very good although the lemon aioli was an odd and unsuccessful pairing I realize the place just opened but if I go back it will be through a friends request and not my own  Really wanted to love it but many better burger options exist

Author: Pat D.
Content: Full disclosure I am a vegetarianThis place has the best veggie burger in Chicago hands down Anyone who says otherwise is a fool Great beer selection too

Author: Roxanne P.
Content: BRING AIR PLUGS  I saw this burger joint on Diners DriveIns and Dives and have wanted to check it out for months  On the program they had a salmon burger stacked high and looked very appetizing to meWasnt worth the wait  skinny dry and fishyBut that is not why it received the low rating The low rating was issued because the sound system was set to eleven   The music and the people screaming were so loud I think the staff must need to read lips  Forget about having any conversation with your friends  The hostess stands up front with a clipboard and takes your name but you need to keep going back to check with her  It was odd seating too My friends I was with liked their food  bison burger and regular beef burger  The onion rings are the string onion ringsPut it this way bait and switch  It was not at all like they showed on DDD

Author: Jason W.
Content: I hit up burger bar last night with a few people and came away pleasantly surprised but with a few minor disappointmentsThe wait was only 45 minutes for a saturday night which is pretty good for a new restaurant especially one that has been hypedmarketed as much as this one We started off with 4 different beers and all were really nice craft beers and the overall selection is very goodFor our meal we ordered 4 small orders of french fries so we could try the different flavors  We all decided that the sweet potato fries won with the salt and pepper fries coming in a close second  The parmesan with truffle oil were good as well but the bleu cheese were disappointingI had the 1 and was very pleased with the burger it was flavorful cooked well on the amount of toppings were just enough  They portions are just right as well not too big not too smallMy friends had a 4 and a 8 and all came away happy as wellWe all decided that we should try desert and the cupcakes were very underwhelming  The carrot cake was moist but the frosting was lacking in flavor and the Chocolate PB frosting cupcake was very dry  So Id say skip dessert there you can do betterThe high point for me though was the cocktail that I  ordered while eating  I had the Death and Companys Whirling Tiger and it is amazing  The base of this drink is bourbon which Im not a huge fan of but this drink may start changing my mind since it was so smooth I could have had a few more easilyIm sure people are going to want to compare this place to Kumas Corner because theyre both burger joints  But Id avoid that comparison since they each have a distinct vibe and point of view that they are going for Overall Id like to give DMK a 35 but cant so Im going to go with a 3 to start and see if it stays consistent  If it does then a 4 will be in its future

Author: Ryan K.
Content: I order the 1 and was satisfied not the best burger Ive had but it was above average  The people I was with ordered the Veggie burger quite bad she didnt finish it because it tasted like it was a breaded deepfried mess and I tasted my friends turkey burger which I thought was good but he didnt The sweet potato fries were meaty and good better than Rock It  The mac  cheese was too oilyOverall I think it is a good addition to the scene  The beer selection is good and the atmosphere of a bar is cool  Burgers go great with beer

Author: Kimberly S.
Content: I really dont like burgers but I actually enjoy them at this place My favorite is the lamb burger but I have even tried the beef ones and theyre great They have an awesome late night menu where you can get a few sliders to try The bacon and blue cheese fries are incredible They also have a nice beer selection

Author: Patrick G.
Content: I have been here a few times now and can conclude that this is a very solid 4 star pushing 5 restaurant One can definitely make a case that this is the best burger in the city and should at least be considered to be in the best of category I really enjoy the blue cheese fried onion strings and chipotle ketchup burger The beer selection is very good and they try to focus on having local Chicago  Midwest beers on tap The fries are very good all around I personally like the parmesan and truffle fries the best followed by the sweet potato fries and then finally the blue cheese and bacon friesThis place can get a bit busy and the wait can be longer than an hour but you can usually hop on the bar and eat if theres only two in the party A number of the tables are like communal seating so if you dont want to be at a table with other people this place might turn you off Also slight minus points for having 1 person at a time bathrooms for such a large place The location is really close to the Wellington brown line stop so it should be pretty easy for most people to go to So go get yourself a yummy burger at DMK

Author: Diane G.
Content: The first time I came here they were SOLD OUT of the House Veggie  Grain Burger I had the Crispy Portobello burger which was good but Ive had so many portobello burgers that theyve lost all meaning to me ButI came back just to try the HOUSE VEGGIE  GRAIN BURGER can you tell Im excited and it was WORTH THE WAIT Soo moist flavorful smothered in pesto mayo klsdfjsd and the bread had that perfect crispy factor one of my top veggie burgers for sure Kind of pricey at 8 tax but baby girl deserves a treat every once in awhile Sweet potato fries were good but you really cant screw up swt potato fries And if you did Id judge youPumpkin ale also a win Warning to vegetariansvegans their fries are cooked in beef fat  I know I shed a tear when I found out too

Author: Kaitlin M.
Content: Well I had high hopes for this new age burger bar and they miserably failed me in a couple of areas To start off I will state that they did not fail in the food area so I might be back to give the rest of the place a second shot A friend and I wanted to get some unhealthy grub after a couple of hours of drinking down the street DMK seemed to be perfect because the menu had vegan options for myself and good old beef burgers for my friend Not to mention we could keep our high class beer drinking going We walked in and were immediately told that we could sit anywhere we liked So we planted ourselves at a large communal table across from the bar There were a couple of different groups already sitting at the opposite end of the table I think we waited almost 20 min before anyone acknowledged our presence When our server finally did she took our drink orders and dropped off menus Probably another 20 min later we actually got our beers and were able to order I ordered the homemade veggie patty with no cheese and sweet potato fries The server did ask if I was vegan and confirmed that they wouldnt put butter on the bun either after I told her yes This was a very exciting surprise to me My friend ordered his fish burger and cheddar fries Our food came out in a decent amount of time and we both thoroughly enjoyed it My burger was well made with some great spicy flavor to it Unfortunately I was told by the server about halfway through my fries that they were cooked in beef oil fat Totally annoyed I stopped eating them and knew I would pay the price for her lack of information transfer later My friend enjoyed his entire meal especially the cheese fries Sadly we still walked out of the place frustrated that burgers and beer took so long It took us hunting down our server to actually get our check too Like I said might be back to give the service another chance

Author: Steven W.
Content: Pastrami with a full burger Id like to think I inceptioned it with my own dreams We came here because their fries were featured as one of the best fries in America so we actually decided get more plates of fries than the number of people we had Unfortunately they were relatively underwhelming While they were seasoned well and had a good texture it was nothing spectacular Certainly nothing to rave about nor should it be featured on any best of listsThe burgers however were prepared to perfection The ingredients were portioned really well and my mouth is watering just thinking about them Prepare for a long wait and grab a couple beers while oogling other patrons food

Author: Vivian H.
Content: Severely disappointed We stopped by around 10pm and the place was packed we got seated after a little wait and a peek into its neighbor Fish Bar also packed We tried the salmon burger  kinda bland for such a yummysounding dish The hatch green chili  better but still underwhelming had a much more delicious version at Umami Burgers were also kinda small Parmeseantruffle fries were good though and the lemon meringue special shake was todieforAs for the scene obviously the type of hoppin place thats packed with burgermongers at 10pm dim lighting exclusively hipster chick staff Which is fun and stuff but doesnt make up for disappointing food

Author: Grey W.
Content: This is a pretty good burger place They place a lot of emphasis on toppings and they do not disappoint They come up with some exceptionally creative burgers I got the 4 with Hatch Green Chile It is really hard to find good green chile outside of the southwest and DMK did well Also a super good beer selectionThe burgers are all cooked the same medium I believe This is a HUGE downside Also the amount of meat is small compared to similar places The Butcher and the Burger the now closed Counter There are better burgers in Chicago but it is hard to go wrong hereIt was somewhat crowded when I came here but that was after a Cubs day game and we were seated really quickly which was very nice

Author: Eric V.
Content: The burgers are ok but its the fries and shakes that bring me back  Burger wise I usually get the 2 sans BBQ sauce  Definitely not as beefy or juicy as the better burgers Ive had perhaps due in part to their smaller 5 oz patty  I appreciate their use of environmentally responsible grassfed beef but I just cant say its in the ballpark of my top burger options  Whereas I find the burgers a little lacking the fries are straight up redonkulous  Perfectly crisp exteriors pillowy soft interiors and a tasty dipping sauce to complement your fry of choice  Im partial to the sweet potato fries with lemon tabasco aioli and my wifey cant get enough of the parmesan and truffle cream  To wash down your meal you could easily choose from their extensive beer list but I personally cant leave without a milkshake  The chocolate shake is the best Ive had in recent memory and the peanut butter shake is like drinking down icy cold reeses pieces candy  As many people have mentioned they dont take reservations and wait times can get rather lengthy  The wife and I were able to grab bar seats pretty easily on two separate occasions so Ill just consider myself lucky for that  I dont think the burgers merit a long wait but Ill gladly nosh on the sidewalk with my bag of fries and shake to go

Author: Joel M.
Content: I heard some great buzz about this place and decided to check it out  The location is perfect  the heart of Lakeview and steps away from the Wellington CTA stop    The atmosphere is modern open and upbeat  We came in on a Sunday night and were seated within 10 minutes  The service was solid out waiter was friendly and recommended some good dishes  We ended up going with the  1 Aged Cheddar Smoked Bacon Charred Balsamic Red Onions Rufus Teagues BBQ Sauce and the  10 GrassFed Lamb  Sheeps Milk Feta Olive Tapenade Tomato  Onion Salad Tzatziki burgers  Both were great  the meat bun toppings everything worked together and made a perfect sandwich  My only compliant might be that it was a little small  I honestly could have devoured another one immediately after I finished my first burgerWe had 2 sides  the parmesan fries with truffle cream and deep fried pickles and okra with a side of some sort of ranch  The sauces might have been the best part  the truffle cream was AMAZING  I also ordered a side of chipotle ketchup which was a great dipping sauce for the burgers and fries  Definitely order a couple beers when you are here  we got sodas and soon realized there werent free refills  This was probably our mistake  a beer would have complimented the burger perfectly  Otherwise this was an awesome dinner for around 35 dollars  I will definitely be back

Author: Jessica K.
Content: I live right around the corner from DMK and have been wanting to try it for about five months nowaka when I got here  I decided to get dinner to go HIGHLY RECOMMEND because this place is insanely packed all the time it seems and wellit wasnt bad butLet me start by saying I dont eat beef  Ive been slowly unvegetarianing but I opted for the crispy portabello burger instead of the turkey veggie or salmon options  I love mushrooms and all of the ingredients sounded pretty rad  But for some reason my brain didnt put two  two together and equate crispy with FRIEDLightly fried I guess really  But friend nontheless  I hoped grilled  No  The sandwich got pretty soggy about halfway through too  But it was pretty decent up until the middle  Nothing really to write home about thoughIt wasnt a bad burger but this is a place where I think Ill read their menu then go to the store and figure out how to make my own  The fries were really great  I got the Wisconsin cheddar and scallion stuff on the side thats how it comes with take away and barely used that because it was too salty for my likingThe closeness in proximity and longing for a milkshake is what will cause me to go back here but probably not until 2012 what with the delicious holiday time upon us

Author: Marisa A.
Content: I checked out DMK over the weekend for lunch It was a lot more of a dark loungey type place than I was expecting I love me some dark wood and all but it was kind of gloomy on such a beautiful summer day Anyways my boyfriend and I walked in and there was a guy standing at a dining table to our left He looked at us for a few seconds and we looked at him He finally asked us how many and thats when we realized he was the host Mmmkay Our waitress was much friendlier and professional She explained the menu to us made some recommendations always had our drinks filled and the food got to us super fast I got the 6 burger which was topped with marinated portobellos blue brie grilled scallions and dijonnaise My boyfriend got the 8 which comes with all of your basic burger toppings I was pleasantly surprised at the patty thin uneven dare I say like Steak n Shakes patties I love the hulk patties at Kumas but I really feel like thats comparing apples and oranges The plus side to DMKs patties is that they make eating a whole burger feasible for me please dont judge me I normally have the eating habits of a morbidly obese man but something about burgers fill me up fast My burger was pretty dang awesome Im fan of the ciabatta bun As a rule I love everything that was piled on it It was also SUPER buttery and juicy and when is buttery bad Well unfortunately I think that the butter took the salt content over the top Mushrooms were salty brie was super salty and the dijonnaise was salty The burger was delicious yes but it was making my mouth pucker it was so salty My boyfriend said his was a little less salty We also got the salt and pepper fries which were tastyWould I do it again Probably The host needs to check his attitude and Id probably order something with more veggies on it to soak up the salt but I see the potential for a great burger

Author: Patricia K.
Content: Between raindrops David R and I scooted over to DMK for a postcomedy show dinner on Friday night  The place was close to full but certainly not packed  Im unsure if this is typical or if we lucked out due to the weather report but we were seated right awayI ordered the 1 loaded with bbq sauce bacon and balsamic onions  It was delicious  It was hard to put it down even when I was totally full  We split an order of fries which I know David enjoyed more than I did  I thought that while they were decent they didnt possess quite the flair I was expecting  I also tried a forkful of the cole slaw which I thought was a bit boringThe service was quick and friendly  However within a ten minute period of time our waitress asked if we needed anything four times  It seemed a bit overboard to meThe place itself is not at all what I expected  in a good way  They are certainly playing to a specific audience  feeding high end burgers in an upscale trendy bar  In fact walking in it feels far more like a bar than a restaurantOverall I enjoyed my experience and would consider a return visit

Author: Andrew S.
Content: Good Very good Great even in some ways ButA burger bar may be chic nowadays but even then the best burgers are the most unpresumptuous ones most of the time I did not have anything close to a great burger by my standards Give me InNOut anyday over their foodied up burgersAgain kudos for what they make and the ingredients they use but theres nothing to write home about here

Author: Angelique R.
Content: After looking at one too many burger ads in the Red Eye left me with an urge to get my burger one Being a vegetarian I am left with only a few options Kumas just takes too damn long to get into so I went for something new and Googled Best Veggie Burger in Chicago Lo and behold a new restaurantThe wait wasnt too bad for a Saturday and though it took longer than usual for our server to come over she was all apologies and gave us free deviled eggs The burgers were delish The fries were crispy The soda was yum Why 3 stars It was just really loud and dark which was kind of a bummer Not quite sure Im return Maybe a seat by the window would make a difference Or maybe not a Saturday

Author: Alejandro T.
Content: Holy wow Do yourself a favor and try one of em burgers Patties so juicy and yummy Pure deliciousness Only thing I would argue is their prices to quantity ratio You certainly pay a lot for one hell of a delicious tiny burger That said I think you should still come out and try iteven writing a review about it makes me wanna go back and eat oneRemember this place is also a bar with a good brew that changes depending the day Great for beer lovers or for a much desired escape from the usual suspects at your local pubTheir service was stellar when I was there and I have no reason to believe it would ever be considered bad Both the hostess and bartender were super friendly and we even got an appetizer on the house because it was our first time there oh yeah Good stuff

Author: B.D. K.
Content: I really liked DMK No complaints Burger was awesome and definitely not as expensive as Counter Burger I would say they could only make it better by dishing out fries with the burgers but then they would probably just charge 10 for a burger making it the same price as everywhere else In any case a side of sweet potato fries is only 2 and my girl and I shared it and it was a decent amount if youre not ravenous I did see the 4 plate of fries and didnt think that was worth it They should up the fry count on the bigger plate a little  Great burgers looks like theyve got awesome drinks which I really need to go back and check out the sweet potato fries were A exactly how they should always be made and prices are better than I expected  hope they keep it that way

Author: kiley w.
Content: After seeing some pictures on a friends blog and reading Johnny Ts review I just had to give this place a try myselfI got here right before they were about to close but the girls still welcomed me with opened armsI had a 4 it had a fried egg ontop I never had a egg in my burger but I loved it The bun was the softest bun I ever had my teeth sinked right into it The burger was cooked to perfectionI also had a order of Wisconsin cheddar and scallion fries which was really good But after eating the burger I was pretty full and didnt finish the fries But I do want to try their fried pickles and okra next timeI also had their homemade lemonade soda which was pretty good and not overly sweetService was one of the best I will definitely return

Author: Francesca L.
Content: Finally got to have a burger at DMK after hearing tons of good reviews from friends I am really not picky but this place was just ok to me I was really impressed with the prices I felt that 800 for a grass fed beef burger is good However I thought the burger was super greasy and really thin The fries was also just ok I wasnt a big fan of the noise level My friend and I were screaming to one another across the table and still lost out on much on the conversation With the tvs on and the music so loud it just felt like there was way too much going on It took away from being able to enjoy the food and the company Why not let people enjoy their beers and burgers and chat with their friends at the same time

Author: Brett P.
Content: What I had Salmon burger with sweet potato friesThe Good                 The patty was delicious fresh and handmade                 The sauces and accompanying condiments were especially good Notably chipotle ketchup truffle creme and lemon tobasco aioli                 Many of the other burgers looked delicious as well                 Prices were fairly reasonableThe Bad                The sweet potato fries were just not that great They were served rather cold and didnt seem to have any appreciable flavor by themselves               It was very loud making it pretty difficult to talk without yelling               Where we were sitting it was so dark I had a little trouble seeing what I was eating               The waitress dumped half my plate of fries on the table and didnt really seem to careBottom line                 Was it the best burger Ive ever had No Was it good Yes                       I wouldnt mind going back to try some of the other burgers but Im not in a hurry

Author: Lala S.
Content: I cant imagine that I havent written a review for DMK but Yelp is telling me that I havent So here goesThis place is pretty amazing Unlike some other burger joints in the city these burgers are a lot easier to handle and the chances of finishing your burger in one sitting is very likely Dont get me wrong I still love Kumas but DMK is also spectacular in its own wayI recommend their take on the Big Mac the name escapes me but you cant miss it The Bison burger is also exceptional and while the Green Chile Cheeseburger is very good it just didnt pack in the heat like I had expectedThe fries here are also delicious You cant go wrong with Truffle Cream and hey if the 86 the frites at MK just mosey on over here and get your fixThey also have some tasty cocktails I like that they arent overly sweet

Author: Taylor D.
Content: DMK is a musttry burger joint in ChicagoTry the 4 It has green chili bacon jack cheese and a friend egg The bun is just perfect It is incredibly soft but it holds up The beef is grassfed cow and you can really tell it is high quality meat Do not expect to get a huge 10oz burger They are the perfect size to full you up with a side of friesThe salt and pepper fries are really good but only if they come out piping hot I have got them when they were sitting out for some time and they were not good at allThe parmesan truffle fries were just okay I would stick with the original or sweet potato friesAlso the mac and cheese is pretty good for a burger joint The only real complaint about this place is the service from the waitstaff They are always hanging out by the service area chitchatting and they take a long time to get to your table I was sitting for about 6 minutes before anyone even came up Also there really is no hosthostess so it can be kind of confusing and awkward when you walk inOn a positive note the food does come out fast thanks to the runnersOne of my favorite burger places in ChicagoPS ask for the rewards card if you like it and want to come back It can also be used next door at Fish Bar

Author: Christa R.
Content: Really Really good I would recommend everything I had Definitely try the deep fried okra pickles Surprisingly delicious and relatively light I tried the Crispin Apple Cider which was really refreshing Perfect for an end of summer into the fall type drink And ofcourse I had the best patty melt of my life It was a little small and a very loudWent in for lunch on a Friday and there were plenty of seats at the bar which is just fine with me Service was decent pricesa little high

Author: Pamela P.
Content: Amazing Out of this world Hands down the bestThe veggie burger is just beyond words I used to think that Bandera had the best veggie burgers Nope I was wrong Must must must eat here if you love yourself some veggie burgersThe sweet potato fries disappeared in mere minutes The deviled egg appetizer was sinful and delicious at the same timeWill most certainly be back many times over

Author: AJ P.
Content: Seriously this is one of the best burgers in the city Do not come here expecting a gigantic too big to hold burger  but expect gourmet ingredients and terrific flavor The parmesan truffle fries are OUT OF THIS WORLD So good If only we could petition for the old 6 to come back  the portabella and brie was my favorite

Author: Ann C.
Content: Ive eaten here twice now for lunch  No wait Good service  AttentiveIve sampled 4 of the burgers and havent been disappointed yetThey dont ask how you want your burger cooked because the patties they use are too thin to do so  Thats fine by me because I like a thin patty  They have a decent beer selection and there were blue cheese olives in my dirty martini  I love the fact that they have deviled eggs on the menu  You really dont see that anywhere  The fries are awesome and the small portion is big enough for two people  I personally love the cheddar fries and truffle fries the best  If you like burgers this place wont disappoint

Author: Annie G.
Content: There are some things that no matter how much you hate the neighborhood and 90 of this places clientele you just cant deny And here they are 1 hot sauce  DMK makes there own hot sauce I wish they sold it but our waitress had to tell us they didntthe red stuffits spicy and smokey and enduring Hell yes I put this on everything I got 2 Fried pickles That needs no further explanation 3 Simple wonderful menu  all burgers 8 All are turkeyburgercapable  music to my ears 4 Fabulous ingredients 5 Awesome unexpected beer selection though a lacking winebytheglass selection 6 Fries that make you want to sleep with them the first time they meet your eyes Our server whos name I wish I could recall was wonderful So helpful knowledgeable about their beers and really really great Theyd probably get AOK but I thought she was the tops

Author: Elle M.
Content: Id really like to give DMK 25 stars but Ill round up on this one Three of us got there around 5pm on a Sunday and the place was pretty empty perfect timing on our part the rush started shortly thereafter Service was friendly and prompt and I liked the menu The burgers are inventive and theres a good variety of different preparations and meatsThe fries were great Very happy with those But to be honest I was pretty underwhelmed by my burger The first thing that made me nervous was when our server didnt ask us how we wanted our burger done I like my burgers rare to medium rare end of story If youre going to serve me a well done burger Ill just skip it They cook all the burgers past medium As it turns out it wasnt much of a problem because the toppings completely mask the taste of the meat anyway It was sort of just a filler to add height It was thin and dry and kind of boring However the buns were lovely and fresh and their drink selection is very cool I had the Death  Company Whirling Tiger Delicious And the prices are completely reasonable The three of us ate and drank very well for under 100 Id probably go back but I wouldnt have a burger Maybe next time Ill try the mac  cheese

Author: Andrew M.
Content: Enjoyed the burger the room was nice as well waited over a hour for a table then another 30 minutes for the food put my wife in a really good mood I love when shes pissedI can live with waiting as long as I have some cocktails to play with I did my problem is  they forgot about us and we watched 5 groups of people eat and leave before we were even seated Incuding a self centered fat couple that thought it was funny sitting real fast as seats opened before us maybe Daley is right about the gun thingy kuz Eyeda shot that bitch the staff was very apologetic but also very young and inexperienced I was expecting more from a world renowned chef but hey they gave us a round of drinks and some fries aology accepted well be back saw a few more burgers that sounded goodThat is all Andy

Author: caroline k.
Content: Showed up 7pm on Friday night expecting to have an incredible wait but had got there just before the rush  Cool trendy but casual good atmosphere as a bar and resto  We chose to sit at the bar rather than elbowtoelbow at one of the communcal tables I was craving a burger and this place just hit the spot  We had the  1 beef burger cheddar bacon onions bbq sauce  12 lamb burger tsazikiGreek style sweet potato fries w tobasco aioli truffle fries with parmesan and all were great  The burger menu had plenty of creative beef lamb turkey and even veggie burger options many also included blue cheese and several varieties of fries    Would definitely come back to try the rest of the menu

Author: Erin V.
Content: I am a vegetarian and I absolutely love veggie burgers Yeahfine I know they are not really burgers Theyre patties Nonmeat Made from veggies and grain and blah blah blah I get it But I like them so stop arguing with me about what they are called And I like burger bars that serve them even more DMKs take on a veg burger yup i said it is pretty stellar While I tend to prefer mine a little firmer than their creation the taste is definitely delicious and unique It has a good blend of spices that doesnt try to trick you into thinking youre eating a burger vegetarians you know what I mean Its its own tasty sandwich and I was entirely pleasedNow for my one issue This place is praised for their sweet potato fries My roommate legitimately has a semiserious relationship with them Half the reason I went was for these droppedfromheaven treats But guess what their secret to awesomeness is beef fat or bacon fat or some sort of meat non vegetarian friendly fat I cant remember exactly So I had to settle for onion strings Which were good Dont get me wrong But after all the hype and build up of these colossal fries that Id added to my bucket list I couldnt even eat them ok all you non vegetarian people who will argue my wording there i COULD eat them but because of my life style choice i CHOSE not to same thing whateverSo what I am saying is meat eaters go duh vegetarians you should go too and I wont judge what you decide to eat while you are there wanna try a sweet potato fry go to chances are the veggie burgers are made one the same grill as the meaty ones anyway

Author: Richard A.
Content: Came here on a Friday for lunch  We ordered two burgers1 Aged Cheedar Smoked Bacon Charred Balsamic Red Onions BBQ Sauce 6 Marinated Portobello Blue Brie Scallions Dijonnaise Also had a order of the fries with Parmesan and Truffle CreamThe fries were amazing  The truffle cream tastes awesomeMy wife had the 6 and enjoyed it very much  As for my burger I felt the meat patty which should be the star of the show failed to impress  The patty itself is thin and not very tasty  I also felt the BBQ sauce overpowered the burger

Author: laela l.
Content: Judging from the menu this place looked schnazzy and sounded absolutely delicious Unique meats deepfried pickles and beer The outside and interior really makes this place look like something special We expected a wait group of 6 on a Saturday night i know and it was fine since there are TVs And we waited and waited2040 minutes we were told by the waitress who looked so out of place with Forever 21 gear in a sports bar The young people were out in full force  I didnt see a soul who looked like they were over 30 Nearly 2 hours later we got to sit down The menu and style of this place really made me think the food would be amazing especially because there are so many reviews The burgers were pretty bland and extremely flimsy Really its just a burger on a plate Call me a presentation lover but it didnt look that awesome We all had a variety of burgers  bison lamb etc and we all agreed the burgers didnt stand out above others in the city If you want a true burger experience theres this place called KumasI get it were at a bara bar So its cut and dry nothing fancy But they shell out this image that its fancy and the burgers werent I will give points on the fries though Those were great This is a place you go to watch a game meet with friends and drinkmaybe order fries and only a burger when youre trashed Seriously DMK market yourself as a trendy sports bar

Author: Mike K.
Content: We were here on a Saturday afternoon and the wait was very long  longer than we were quoted But they play great music and the hostess kept us updatedThe beer list is wonderful but I really wanted a chocolate shake so I asked for one with a shot of Makers Mark Get this Their shakes are nicely thick without an overbearing chocolate richness which lets the bourbon shine through Burgers except for specials are only 9 but you have to get fries separately We had the truffle fries which were the best Ive ever had The truffle was not cloying or faketasting the fries were crispy on the outside and pillowy in the center and the sauce was understated The deviled eggs were way too salty The burgers were delicious and wellcooked The only one I would not get was I believe the turkey burger which my friend had It had so many strong flavors that my mouth and tongue hurt My other friend had the portobello burger which she really enjoyed Next time I want to try the bison burgerStick with the classics because DMK does them well  burgers fries and shakes

Author: Grace G.
Content: Good burgers fun atmosphere and a good craft beer selection Service was fine took a while to get our check but it was very busy so we understood the delay

Author: Mike P.
Content: The ball and chain and I went here on a random Sunday to satisfy a burger cravingBurgers 4 star  I actually got a turkey burger which goes against my entire philosophy on burgers  It totally exceeded expectations  Juicy flavorful and hit the spot Frankly the burger was a bit small but in this case it was ok as I wasnt looking for a pound of meatFries exceptional sweet potato fries  crunchy most likely twice fried The regular fries were crunchy and well seasoned as wellDrinks  we had the house made colas which were delicious  Frankly I was very unimpressed with the beer list My will is VERY weak if theres a good tap list  It speaks volumes that I didnt order anythingService  well meh We sat for 20 minutes before our waitress greeted us During our meal she never asked how our food was  Another waitress had to come by to drop the check after we waited for 10 minutes  I know the restaurant is relatively new and figuring our their service process but come on now  There are basic elements of food service missing that were missing and I got the feeling other customers were noticing it as well  Its obvious they are hiring eye candy that lack developed service skillsOverall the food and pricing was very good  Service tap list atmosphere meh  Doubt Ill be back

Author: Jessica B.
Content: Went for the first time today and I absolutely know I will go backTo start it has a great beer list and atmosphere with communal and bar seating along with individual tables I had the 4 beef burger with fried egg bacon and jack cheese along with the Parmesan truffle fries and was in heaven The portion size was perfect and I didnt feel ridiculously full afterThe burger list is pretty eclectic and has interesting pairings including teasing a few coming up I already have my eye on the upcoming prosciutto burger no more details provided and I am dying to try the sweet potato fries a weakness for meI heard they have good milkshakes but I didnt have room for one and the side of deviled eggs are supposed to be great too I cannot wait to try themPlus the food prices were really reasonable too for the great ingredients and presentation I was shocked that my burger was only 8 Be aware though that seating fills up fast and its notoriously crowded especially on weekends I arrived just after noon it opens at 11 and got a seat but by the time I left at 1230 it was completely full But I loved my burger and fries and I cannot wait to go back and share with friends

Author: Jennifer S.
Content: Where to begin To start bartenders Lauren and Drew are absolutely amazing We popped in on a Sunday night expecting to have to hit the road because the wait was so long but were thrilled to find 4 open bar stools in front of a huge flat screen tv We really wanted to watch USA Hockey Big win for them and a big culinary win for usOur foursome tried the whole gamut from beef to turkey to lamb and even a friend egg on top of a traditional beef Everyone was delighted by the taste and portion sizeNo 2  ChiliRubbed Onion Strings Great Hill Blue Marinated Tomatoes Chipotle KetchupNo 10  GrassFed Lamb  Sheeps Milk Feta Olive Tapenade Tomato  Onion Salad TzatzikiWere two of the big hitsNot to mention the awesome parmesan and sweet potato fries and DLish bacon mac and cheeseAs I mentioned the service was exceptional Drew and Lauren treated us like royalty giving us little tastes of specialty beers and cocktails and introducing us to the to die for ice cream sandwiches If you have room go for the double chocolate espresso sandwich It might change your lifeAnother MAJOR bonus they pick a charity each month and donate a portion of the proceeds DONT MISS MARCH They are donating to our own Chicago Public SchoolsHit them up in March your stomach and CPS teachers and students will appreciate it

Author: Luis L.
Content: I am definitely a new fan of this place I REALLY like beef and I REALLY like a good burger so this place was calling my nameOne of my favorite burger places in the city is Hamburger Marys not because their burgers are particularly high quality but because theyre so creatively prepared DMK however gives H Marys a run for its money without having to go all out with their preparation or the showmanship of female impersonators or should I say showwomanshipThe beef at DMK is from GRASS FED cows and if youre a more sophisticated meat eater you might notice the difference in taste Its distinctly more earthy but also a bit richer or bolder They dont season it much which is a big distinction between their burgers and the burgers at H Marys Its also something I really like I should add that the way H Marys prepare their burgers DOES actually enhance as oppose to mask the flavor of the meat but its great to get such good flavor as you do at DMK from the beef itselfI believe fries are generally overrated but also I simply dont like fried food very much anymore I didnt order any fries but I did order a greek salad which was perfectBTW my burger was the number 4 It had on it some roasted green chiles from a place called Hatch in New Mexico a fried farm egg sonoma jack cheese and two thickish yet short strips of baconI may not like fried food but I will have a SMALL bite of bacon These two strips of bacon however were a bit too thick for my liking I guess if I were to have eaten the bacon on my burger it would have been fine But I got the bacon on the side and only ate a SMALL bite off one piece That was MORE than enoughI had a couple of glasses of a Pinot Noir too which was very juicy and went fine with my burgerThe interior of DMK is set up like a bar tables along the wall and a bar with stools and a seating large area in the back nicely arranged in a lofty and loud space with TVs near the bar and plenty of room to walk throughout The environment is good mix of casual and stylish Also the staff was VERY pleasant polite and promptExcellent experience on my first try Ill definitely go back

Author: Matthew G.
Content: I was first introduced to DMK in the summer of 2010 Coming from the suburbs the chances of finding a gourmet burger spot is slim to none After hearing about DMK a few friends and I decided to try it out late one night after spending the day in the city We got there a little past dinner rush but it was surprisingly empty even the bar area First off great service Workers are super friendly and chill no not the fake friendly like you get at ChickfilA eitherSecondly the fries are legit We started out with a small order of Sea Salt  Black Pepper fries just to make sure their most basic fries were worth it ON POINT Then we upped the ante to the Sweet Potato Fries with Lemon Tobasco Aioli Again ON POINT Talk about the perfect combo of sweet sour with a slight touch of spiciness My personal favorite was the Parmesan fries with Truffle Cream  DMK does not fake the funk with the friesNow for the few times that Ive been to DMK about 68 times Ive gotten a burger on about 4 of those occasions and Ive had the same burger every time It is the 3 NY Pastrami French Gruyere Sauerkraut and Leroys Remoulade with of course the grassfed beef patty Flavor Flavor Flavor And Pastrami AND a beefy patty YES The option to add a fried egg adding to the flavor and juiciness of the burger is always welcome I cant say much about the other burgers of which there are 8 more options with a beef patty and 5 more that are either turkey lamb salmon or veggie but I do hear the Portobellow 13 is just as flavorful as any beef patty burger Mind you the burgers are not Kuma sized but theyre not sliders either Id say a perfect medium sized burger and defintely not overunderwhelmingAfter stuffing yourself with burgers and fries what would you consider washing all that down with Water Sure A coke Why not But there down at the very bottom of the menu were 3 words that made my first DMK experience as memorable as it ever was PEANUT BUTTER SHAKE 3 words so simple yet so interesting What was so special about the PB shake you may ask All I can say is imagine PB Capn Crunch but in the form of a shake yeah Yeah YEAH Thats right Its THAT good ehem THAT GREAT After the first I had to try another Yep 2 Peanut Butter Shakes Its what keeps me coming back to DMKAll in all my first DMK experience was great to say the least Great service complimented with great burgers fries and the greatest peanut butter shake you could ever have Luckily DMK made its way out to the suburbs in the eversoevolving LombardOak Brook area not too far away from me The atmosphere at the Lombard location is totally different from the Lakeview one Service isnt as good but the food and drink certainly is So whether youre on the northside looking for a late bite to eat or in the westernsuburbs tired of fastfood head over to DMK for a great burger frie and shake experience

Author: Tracey H.
Content: DMK is incredible I think they have the best burgers in Chicago Go aheadcomplain and argue all that you want that Kumas is better It is not They do not even form their own meat patties anymore have skimped on the toppings and overall are just going through the motions That saidDMK is incredible I went a few weeks after they opened and thought it was a nice touch that Chef Kornick was seating  bussing tables The burgers are incredible The bleu cheese  bacon fries have my heart The truffle fries are amazing too I think it is very reasonably priced Also dont forget to the  chocolate malted milkshake  chocolate chip cookie sandwich Both incredible I will be back And props to bartendress Safia for making a killer ManhattanUPDATE 51610 DMKs Veggie burger is quite possibly one of my most favorite things to eat I am not a vegetarian and I love my meat I meanI REALLY love my meat But DMKs veggie burger is SO amazing it doesnt feel like you are missing out Try it

Author: Janis W.
Content: We went back the other night and sat at the bar  Just drinks no foodDelicious mojitos and a very nice bartender  I wasnt expecting either so a nice surprise

Author: Jeffrey H.
Content: Its hard to criticize this place They serve good food at a good price in a good area with a good atmosphere The burgers are great They arent too big and leave enough room for you to enjoy your craft beer and gourmet fries without feeling like youre going to have to go to the gym afterwardThe service is always great Ive been there many times and requested additional seating changes in drinks answers to items on the menu and the staff has always been courteous and forgiving They dont take reservations but the wait times are never ridiculous and there is usually space at the bar to hang out while they get a table ready for youThe atmosphere is relaxed but its still feels sophisticated The poetry on the bathroom walls is pretty entertaining and the overall decor is modern without being in your face Overall a great place for a casual date get together or quick dinner

Author: Derk R.
Content: I was specifically looking for natural fresh and tasty food after a long run and I found it Even better the beer selection is fantasticsome of the countrys best craft breweries representedand the bourbon selection is well curated and a fantastic value given the generous pour The vibe here was great too The staff is friendly knowledgable and fun the decor is tasteful and the music selection was spot on and no it wasnt too loudSpecifics I started with a Great Lakes Dortmunder Gold Great beer Wedge salad was one if the best Ive hadthe tomatoes were perfect Got the 1 burger with sweet potato fries gratis with a foursquare checkin All good Had an Alpha King with the burger and finished up with an Eagle Rare 10yr bourbon Really couldnt have asked for a better meal

Author: Jenna M.
