Content: Ive been to DMK twice now and each time I have LOVED it The 4 is very good if you like a little spice The egg is the proverbial cherry on top that just oozes and makes all the flavors come together nicely The blue cheese and bacon fries were PHENOMENAL My boyfriend who doesnt like blue cheese could not stop stealing them from me He got the Wisconsin cheddar and scallions which were a severe let down I do not recommend them at all He had the 1 sub Turkey burger and sans BBQ It was delicious The balsamic onions were amazing 8 for a burger 3 for fries that were great If only the beers werent 550 Oh well They do have a great selection of microbrews on tap and bottled I dont know if its daily but between 5 and 7pm there is a happy hour where you get free salt and pepper fries with your burgers We got there a few minutes before but decided we wanted specialty fries instead Thought that was kind of neat

Author: Ross N.
Content: Yes burgers are ahopping in Chitown and youve got to be living in an igloo not to have noticed not that theres anything wrong with that  I agree with several other reviews that the burgers are good but lack the punch in the gut Im used to for beef  I had the green chile egg bacon 4 and it was tasty but I had to double upwhich is fine by me happy to pay for it  Wifey had the Big Salad and enjoyed it  Fries with the truffle cream gobble gobble  I ran out of stomach space to try the bacon infused shake  Maybe next timeId go back but definitely some new places Id like to hit before returning

Author: Kathleen M.
Content: Yum yum Got the BIG Salad  Super delicioso And since I was good with the salad I decided to have an ice cream sammie In a word perfect Soft cookie and soft ice cream  it is a MUST on the menuOur service was wonderful  attentive personable and gave great tips on the menu Definitely check this place out

Author: Dan H.
Content: Burgers were good Beer was alright It was Halloween yet the service was terrible Service can make up more than half the experience at any restaurant Thus the three stars Deviled eggs were good but nothing fantastic I got them because they were cheap  2I got the Bison Burger 5 It was decent I expected it to be something amazing and big But it was small and it was quite anticlimatic The fries I got the Wisconsin Cheddar and Scallion were alright The cheese looked like nacho cheese Looks can be deceiving Cheese was actually decent Also got the Mac  Cheese 2  basically the maccheese with bacon Again nothing special Ive been to many other bar and burger places throughout the city There are quite a few that have better food beer and service

Author: Anant J.
Content: We swung by here last night because I had heard good things and wanted to grab a quick dinner The place was pretty crowded and loud so we decided to get our food to go I got the 2 onion strings Amish Blue chipotle ketchup as a turkey burger and shared the sweet potato and truffle fries The fries were both pretty good each paired with interesting condiments but Ive had better fries in the area they were a little thick for my liking BUT my burger was absolutely amazing 9 is a bit steep for a burger and no sides but this was DEFINITELY worth it Possibly one of the best turkey burgers that I have ever had Everything worked together really well and it was a total treat to eat I will definitely be going back herethe menu had a bunch of other super tempting items and it was quick and easy to order the food to go Be sure to check this place out if you are looking for a great burger in the area

Author: Jennifer M.
Content: Whats not to like about this place Maybe just the wait for the restroomThey host nightly weekly and special events This restaurant gives off a sports bar feel but its really family friendly and good food for kidsThe burgers atmosphere and service replaces my desire for a Neurosis beef burger at the obnoxiously loud Kumas Corner Nah I wouldnt go that far but its closeWe got really lucky on the day we arrived The place was crowded but we managed to share the table attached to the bar with 3 gents who made room for usWe were able to order Bloody Marys and beer Ive never heard of right away They also have housemade sodas and shakesMy boyfriend loves Bison This one is served with fresh goat cheese pickled red onions and blueberry BBQ sauce He loved it so much he ate twoI ordered the 1 with beef which is served with Artisan aged cheddar smoked bacon charred balsamic red onions Rufus Teagues BBQ sauce Sooo goodYou can order an individual size or share portion of fries We chose to share the Sweet Potato with Lemon Tobasco Aioli I look forward to trying their onion strings or  fried okra  dill pickles

Author: Mary F.
Content: 1 BurgerAmazingParmesan Truffle FriesAmazingThree Floyds GumballheadAmazingCouldnt ask for a better comboLove DMK

Author: Jason C.
Content: People indicating this place has the best burger they have ever tasted must of either been drunk or mistaken that they were at DMK  Average average average  The patty is smaller than a cheeseburger at McDonalds  Five Guys crushes this place and is half the price  And whats up with the small plates they serve the burgers on  Too cheap to buy normal size plates  The only positive are the fries  tried three different kinds and all were generally good  If you want a real burger in Chicago head to Kumas

Author: Wyman T.
Content: Just had lunch there with a friendI love burgers and this place got some tasty burgers  The burgers are a little smaller than I imaginednot sure about the big DMK but the taste is exquisite juicy burgers  The number 1 burger was awesome enjoyed the grilled red onionsAlso ordered the truffle cream and Wisconsin cheddar fries both were great I recommend the truffle cream

Author: Caroline M.
Content: With all the burger joints in town these days its hard to choose however DMK is my solid goto What I love so much about DMK is that their menu isnt overwhelming like most other burger establishments in the city Here youre safe with whatever you order because the guys behind DMK know what tastes good  thus they dont allow you to build your own burger Go to The Counter if thats your thing Recently I came here on a Sunday night for dinner with my sister and we were seated right away at the bar Every other time Ive come with one other person weve never had to wait longer than 15 minutes  Side note Rick Bayless and his fam came in for dinner that same night and sat next to us So if my review isnt convincing enough maybe a Top Chef Masters cred will add to it And no I didnt bother them   I digress The Burger The burgers are an appropriate size so one person can easily finish one on their own though with all the mouthwatering sides fries and mac  cheese options you may want to split with a friend And all the burgers come on their freshly baked buns  a nice added touch The Bar Great Beer selection a full page in fact with clever descriptions for the amateur beer drinker  ahem myself check it out on their website And a full bar and cocktail list I highly recommend Gregs one of the bartenders signature drink  forgetting the name but its similar to a mojito with a refreshing sage twist My favorites Fried Okra  Pickles  best breading hands down in the city Sweet Potato Fries  ask for a side of their House Ketchup  its got a spicy chipotle kick it comes with the Chilirubbed Onion Rings 5 Burger Bison Goat Cheese and Blueberry BBQ Sauce Genius combo They also offer Milkshakes and Ice Cream Sandwiches which Ive never tried because I never save enough room by the end of my meal but they always look great on the menu You can also get them in togo cups

Author: The Humane Choice S.
Content: Without hesitation DMK Burger Bar deserves five stars when it comes to sourcing humanelyproduced ingredients for their sandwiches and sides The food is also incredibly tasty which is a major selling point  We indulged in several of their burger and fry options including the 2 awesome chipotle ketchup and the 4 the roasted green chili gives it a nice kick We also particularly enjoyed the parmesan fries with truffle dipping sauce Even though the restaurant is relaxed and casual its commitment to using organic and grassfed ingredients is second to noneFirst and foremost the burgers are made with Tallgrass Beef  Tallgrass Beef is completely grassfed and grassfinished meaning that the cows are never fed grain We have yet to find another restaurant in Chicago that only uses grassfed beef in their menu items This sets DMK apart from the competitionThe rest of the ingredients are grassfed and in many cases also organic Their bison meat comes from the North American Bison Coop an association of ranchers whose animals have never been fed hormones and thrive on a diet of natural freerange grazing DMK sources organic lamb from Black Earth Meats in Wisconsin This farm is also certified by Animal Welfare Approved an independent organization that certifies for excellent humane husbandry practicesThe cheddar cheese that tops the burgers and fries is from Otter Creek Organic Farm and the turkey burgers are made from Golden Legacy Organic turkey Otter Creek emphasizes rotational grazing and pasturebased living for their organic cows when the weather is hospitable Eggs come from Milos Organic Poultry  In a recent report by the Cornucopia Institute Milos Organic Poultry provides ample outdoor space and encourages their birds to go outside  According to the report the farm offers the birds an excellent outdoor environment often either rotated pasture or wellmanaged outdoor runsIf there is one area where DMK could improve it would be to list their sources brands and farms on their website  DMK Burger Bar should be very proud of their success in procuring and using grassfed beef and other humanely raised products Customers are interested in knowing where their food comes from and would be impressed with the fine list that DMK has to share   The Humane Choice is a project of Food Animal Concerns Trust FACT  This restaurant was reviewed by FACT staff members Larissa McKenna Lisa Isenhart and Jacki Rossi  FACT is a Chicagobased nonprofit organization dedicated to improving the way animals are raised on farms  For more information on our work and mission please visit foodanimalconcernsorg

Author: Dave W.
Content: I love this place  Excellent burgers and a very good beer selection  Although they are a tad bit pricey for drinks I dont mind supporting small craft breweries  Ive tried at least 5 different burgers here and all of them have been superb  On one occasion I brought up my slightly undercooked burger to a waitress and was brought another one immediately  The only side Ive ever ordered are the sweet potato fries like the burger they are always spot on  I have also been offered free drink coupons by more than one of the waitressesbartenders  Excellent customer service and consistently good food no wonder this place is packed every time I visitedit the marshmallow shake at Lakeview is awesome

Author: Chris O.
Content: The basics 2 out of 5 stars Decent room to improve not a good valueI had the basic hamburger 8 on the menu With the hand cut fries The burger itself was tasty but thin on an artisan roll The best part of the burger was the aged white cheddar The fries are what you would expect but what was surprising was the slightly spicy homemade KetchupPresentation left much to be desired One would expect some flair for a 9 burger but the small saucer could barely hold the sandwich My companion David Gutowsky had the fried pickles which I will recommendOne of the rules of thumb about a restaurant is that if it is loud with talking the food probably isnt the best otherwise peoples mouths would be full eating The first thing that strikes you about this place when you walk in is how very loud it is inside I do not understand why bars and restaurants insist on piping in music at rock concert levels to begin with but it is very unpleasant to have to yell to talk to the person across the table from you As well a minor thing but a personal pet peev is servers who dont know how to place the drinks on a table Drinks go on the right of the patron not dropped all together on one side of the table

Author: Ruben K.
Content: Best veggie burgers in town The fried okra is delicious too Their reputation as a gourmet burger place is well earned The ambiance is that of a sports bar which is perfectly fine

Author: Nathan J.
Content: Kane burger Thats the special Get it dog

Author: Darby A.
Content: Yum yum yumPost Marathon feastpumpkin Sour ale and a breakfast turkey burger covered with bacon hash browns fried egg and maple aoliperfect burger still craving itStaff very cool Megan rocks helped us find some boystown drinking spots after

Author: Laura H.
Content: Ive really enjoyed my visits to DMK though its crazy busy on weekend nights The burgers are tasty fries delicious and waiters are generous especially when its not busy Ive had free things offered to me a few times  It may be sacrilege in this neighborhood but I also prefer these burgers to Kumas though perhaps not the atmosphere

Author: Mandy P.
Content: DMK has been on my list for awhile and Im glad I was finally able to come The service was incredible definitely the best part Someone overheard my dinner date saying hed never had the blue and bacon fries in previous visits so we were surprised with a small order The burger options were great delivered timely and paired well with PBR The extra order of sweet potato fries ordered guaranteed no room for a milkshake

Author: Jessica V.
Content: I absolutely adore this placeIf I could Id here here every dayWe have been coming here since we moved to Chicago and have NEVER had a single bad experience The burgers are insanely good My goto is definitely the 4 Bison patty with goat cheese and blueberry BBQ sauce DELISH I order this EVERY time we come and I have never gotten tired of it Its just sooo good I think at this point we have tried every burger on the menu with the exception of the lamb burger and love each and every one The chili they serve in the fall and winter is incredible They have 45 different kinds and it changes every few days Theyre all amazingId say this place is tied with Kumas for my favorite burger in Chicago but when we want a good burger without a 2 hour wait we always come here

Author: Christie L.
Content: Stopped for lunch on a Friday with a group of four We had quick friendly service I ordered the Bison Burger 5 with picked red onion and blueberry BBQ sauce I also added fried egg The burger was greatnot the best Ive ever had but really good The truffle fries were good too At the end of the meal the server brought us all a free sample of an alcoholic milkshake drink made with andes creme de menthe I dont even like mint and I LOVED it

Author: Andy B.
Content: Big fan of DMK Have been 4 or 5 times now and the only downside I have experienced is the wait although it has never been unreasonable Even that has been alleviated for large 68 parties by grabbing seats at the portion of the bar which sticks out so you essentially have a table Service has always been excellent and when we swung through for dinner during my bachelor party we received a couple plates of fries and one of everything on the dessert menu on the house This was not a Oh dont tell everyone its my birthday Im so embarrassed why yes I would like some free cake situation either we never mentioned anything and we were not a good looking crowd sorry guys so we appreciated the generosityI am sure some folks have burger places they like better but I have really enjoyed every burger Ive ordered here big fan of the bison weekend special While burgers dont come with fries 4 gets you a huge plate of the sweet potato fries my personal favorite among other options which is plenty for 23 people Even dessert is done well with the carrot cake in cupcake or slice form being the one I enjoy the most  The beer options are plentiful and varied so there should be something on the list for everyone DMK also donates to a different charity every month based on items you order so it gave my wife and I an excuse to drink for charity The Jesuits would be so proud of meI wont claim they have a better burger than Kumas but they also dont blast heavy metal have an 60 min wait nor are they hard to reach steps from Wellington Brown line Im a fan

Author: Kerri M.
Content: The caveat to this is that I am vegetarian but as a vegetarian I still appreciate a burger with all the fixins and DMK allows for a veggie burger substitute for each of its specialty burgers for 2 more Since I was with visiting meat eaters I figured we could each find some comfort food hereI ordered the number three with a veggie burger sub It waswell meh dull boring The burger itself appears to be made in house but it lacked any touch that makes it unique from something store bought Ive had better Amys burgers for instance even with their spicy kick To charge an additional 2 for something that doesnt pack much punch seems a bit egregious to meWe also ordered the chilirubbed onion straws for an appetizer the rub was a nice spicy touchMy dad had a regular old burgericeberg lettuce and tomato and yes spice in the burger Seems to be a pattern and one that isnt all that uniqueI am thankful that the waitress did warn me that their fries are made in beef oil so other vegetarians make noteI have had far better burgers at places like Lockdown on Western Ave

Author: Cristen H.
Content: LOVE this place Excellent burgers sides beer ambiance energy level desserts service crowd  everything is applaudable Stayed in the neighborhood while in town for marathon  we came for burgers and beers on day of marathon returned next night for dessert returned the night after that for drinks We just love this place First visit  server brought us a free appetizer and also a free round of shots shots of cider Second visit  bartender gave us all coupons for a free draft beer Third visit  server brought us free fried pickles YUMMY Crowd is young and music is entergetic If I lived in town I could see myself going here by myself  sitting at the bar  and making friends with the bartenders Everything on the menu is delicious especially the peanut butter milkshake

Author: Stephanie K.
Content: Came in at 200 in the afternoon on a Monday and it was pretty empty besides a couple or two who were enjoying their lunch I had the Mac and cheese with bacon and caramelized onions while my boyfriend had the number one burger with smoked bacon and onion We shared the Parmesan fries and they were REALLY GOOD some of the best fries Ive ever had really fresh The meat on the burgers were delicious with a nice soft bun compared to the substantial and much more hardier pretzel buns The service was awesome and our waitress even gave us complimentary vanilla milkshakes which I could have had a gallon of The only reason I didnt give this five stars was because it was a little overpriced for the portions But overall really good place for a burger and awesome service

Author: Anisha A.
Content: Perfect buns and beef Thanks to DMK grass fed cows and potato buns are now a permanent fixture of my fantasies Soon theyll replace Fabio on the cover of romance novels  The 4 is one of the tastiest and most reasonably priced burgers youll find in Chicago masterfully topped with jack bacon a fried farm egg and the magical wildcard a roasted green chile Will also put out for the lamb burger 10 Those are the two to bank on some of the others disappoint Of the fries the sweet potato ones reign supreme After some of the early kinks get worked out eventually this place will join the ranks of Kumas While it lacks the tattoos and metal it just may be more deserving of burger deity status

Author: Megan S.
Content: Ugh just fantastic I had this buffalo burger and it was incredible Plus they offer truffle fries and sweet potato fries

Author: Sarah S.
Content: I live right around the corner from DMK and have been wanting to go there since it opened Went with some friends last weekend  We got there around 745 and had to wait about an hour for a table  We were able to sit at the bar and have a drink while we waited so we didnt mind Now I went to Kumas Corner the week before and I will say that I liked DMK better Yes I said it The burger I had at DMK is one of the best ive ever had  I had the one with portobello and eggplant on it  It was so juicy and full of flavor We got a side of the truffle fries and sweet potato  Again they were delicious and cooked to perfection I will definitely be going back to DMK and would highly recommend this place

Author: Jon G.
Content: Been here a few times and have been pleased overall Nice selection of burgers beef turkey organic veggie etc Try the mac and cheese which is very oilytasty with chopped bacon sprinkled on top Sweet potato fries are also always a winner Only knock is that sometimes it is very loud and dark inside So basically a good place to take a date that is ugly and annoying

Author: Bill C.
Content: Just spent a lovely evening at this establishment  All around awesome well run place  especially for the third day since opening their doors  The menu is creative  it includes lots of items that arent necessarily obscure but are not typically found at a burger joint like this  mac and cheese several gourmet variations deviled eggs and ice cream sandwiches  Needless to say the food did not disappoint  My two roommates and I split three of their original burgers  plus a side of truffleparmesan fries and bacononionguyere mac and cheese  all incredible In addition to scrumptious food they also offer an impressive beer selection Lots of great craft brews that are hard to come by  two brothers three floyds victory and great lakes to name a few The service was friendly and sincere unlike the attractive yet ditzy and fake waitresses at similar bars in the area The one gripe I have is the music playlist  I respect Bob Marley but I must have heard ten of his songs throughout the night including Jamming four times If I heard that song one more time Id have had no other option but to roll a joint and sit back with a Red Stripe  Im sure the iTunes shuffle issue will be resolved shortly Definitely work checking out

Author: Suzanne B.
Content: Great Food Great Service Great drinks I couldnt say anything bad about this place if I triedI guess if anything they could turn the music down just a notch that really comes from others I have talked to more than me

Author: Ted C.
Content: I hadnt seen my friend  Scott for a while and was in the need for a Friday decompression I went down to his house and since we were both hungry I suggested DMK Scott had been there before liked the food but didnt really like the atmosphere Atmosphere doesnt really factor into my food consuming decisions so we went I got the 4 burger green chiles egg jack cheese and bacon I asked to get it medium rare since I figured a place like this has good quality beef I was a little disappointed to find out that all burgers are cooked the sameit kind of reminded me of the pretentiousness at this place in LA I was surprised though to find the burger tasty juicy with the the chile being subtly spicy not a kick per se but a little knee that mixed with the slightly medium egg and bacon Kind of like a really kick ass breakfast with a burger in itI ordered the salt and pepper fries Scott got the Parmesan fries Scotts garlic parmesan fries were the definite winner here but it was my mistake to get plain fries really Their house made ketchup though was good tangy but not overly sweetI started out nonalcoholic with their bloodorange soda which was interesting I saw our bartender Lauren make house made syrup with a seltzer and mixeda little new school flavor with old fashioned techniqueI definitely need to write about Lauren our bartender She was really friendly knew her bourbon she was even a member of the Bourbon Heritage Society gave us a free order of sweet potato fries when my buddy and I decided on getting other fries Not only that but my friend Scott was reluctant to get an order of bourbon and I started calling my Stacy and Stephanie and Jocelyn Lauren even jumped in on it and Scottys reluctance turned into less reluctance and he got a glass of Elijah Craig with meagain a suggestion from Lauren and an excellent one We settled out and she said to come by and see her again Oh yes Lauren we definitely will Thanks for a great time and changing Scottys mind about the place Hopefully it wont be too long before we come by again

Author: Sara C.
Content: Came here with a group of friends on a Friday night  It was bustling and became quite packed before we leftThe boy had the number 4 and I had the number 1  He also had the Arcadian Ale and I had the blood orange soda  Around the table were the lamb burger sweet potato fries and salt and pepper fries  The sweet potato fries are incredible  It was a bit of a wait for the food and the fries came out after the burgers but otherwise everything was very goodHowever about half an hour afterwards my tummy was in distress and we had to make several pit stops during our journey back to Wheaton which definitely puts a damper on my enthusiasm for this restaurant

Author: Mark T.
Content: The Chicago Burger Bar with exceptional Quality GrassFed Beef Fresh Baked Buns Artisan Cheeses  Love After this place opened up two years ago it has been on my list of restaurants to check out I finally got the chance to today albeit only for take out Ordered the Big DMK burger a triple decker treat with special sauce and a small order of Chicago fries Let me tell you for the most expensive burger on the menu this thing was MASSIVE Holy freaking smokes Still with my enormous appetite I took that thing home and downed it in 10 minutes The burger wasnt spectacular but it was quite tasty The special sauce lookedtasted like they just mixed catsup and pepper together not so special now isnt it Either way it did give the burger a special kick The fries were ok thankfully I only had a small orderAs I waited for my order I scoped out the place It was normal for a saturday afternoon crowd family wkids at one table young group of girls at another  and couples scattered around as well I can olny imagine how it would be on a Friday night Sort of a trendy place but during certain hours Service was fast too which surprised me I got my burger in about ten minutes Would I go back Maybe just to capture the whole experience Although I know what to expect which helps

Author: Jeff J.
Content: Its been awhile since I knew exactly what rating to give a restaurant after my final bite of food  DMK is 5 stars hands down  My bison burger with blueberry BBQ sauce and an egg was mind boggling delicious  Each ingredient was purposeful yet restrained  The meat while seemingly thin is just filling enough moist tender and perfect  The blueberry BBQ sauce yes blueberry is actually bluish in color and you can TASTE the blueberries  Its not some gimmick where the blueberries are purportedly in the sauce but you cant taste them  And the blueberry flavor that shines through is actually of utmost importance to the burger  And the egg what a suggestion by the waiter  Just runny enough didnt fall apart in the sandwich We also got sweet potato fries some of the best Ive had and an awesome aioli  We did get a cheddar and scallion fries that I thought were a bit on the heavy side  The burger made me go ooh ahh and mmm with the noises I was making Im glad there were no children seated near me  This place is the BEST burger place Ive ever been to

Author: Marc R.
Content: I walked in here after a friend of mine gave me a haircut and can say that on walking in the staff were very attentive and friendly girls I think they have a uniform but I am not sure Our server was a nice all American blond with ballet shoes She was very attentive and nice The set up is like a bar but it is a kid friendly place where you can take the family or the parents for burgers There were some cool wordplay dare I call them poems in the bathrooms that seemed to be talking about West Town Nelson Algren was mentioned The burgers We had a lamb burger and a regular with an egg on top Both were solid They were not as thick as other burgers and had a traditional bun  very drive in it seemed The fries we got regular were also good I would not class these among my top burgers in the city but they were well done and yummy The fries These were better than most Overall if you find yourself in this hood and want a burger hook up I would check it out

Author: Taylor O.
Content: Ive been meaning to stop by here since it opened I was just waiting for the right time when my exgirlfriend moved away from this neighborhood  I love burgers I may name my future son Kobe and Im not a basketball fan so I found myself on a rainy day here at Kumas which with its dark glass looked like a river north modern furniture store closed for the evening  I knew better and poked in to find a nice young clean modern atmosphere  It was nice sitting at the bar in front of their pegboard menu with the decent beer list including an quip about Amstel if you insist listening to the staffs iTunes playlist  Im about the red meat only burger and bacon  The grass fed burger was perfectly cooked to medium rare and was of the steak burger quality  I wish it was thicker but cest la vie  By the way cows should only ever eat grass not grain not be finished on grain etc  Trickier and less sweet but much more flavorful and definitely more healthy Omega 3 and Vitamin K2 fans  It was an awkwardly tiny plate though what is this a slider  You know Ill be back  Definitely in part to it being super convenient to the recently refurbed Wellington Brown Line stop

Author: Thao N.
Content: Its been about 4 months since Ive written a review but DMK Burger Bar you have brought me back to Yelp because my experience at your establishment had been so pleasant It was my first visit but it sure wont be my last I brought my best friend here as one of the surprises I had planned for  his belated Christmas gift When we arrived we were promptly greeted by a friendly host whom stated it was a 15 minute wait I decided to order the blood orange soda Made in house the old school way and waited at the bar Five minutes hadnt passed when our host approached to say that a table towards the back was ready Once seated my friend looked over their selection of domestic beers Some were brewed right in the city saving on carbon footprint Yay for going greenWhen it came time to order one of the many different grass feed beef burgers I went with the  1 Aged cheddar smoked bacon charred balsamic red onions and Rufus Teagues BBQ sauce Oh my It was a great burger and it didnt have to try so hard They dont ask you how you want it cook because they know how it should be cooked I love it when the cook grill master can be cocky and back it up Even the fries were in your face and didnt back down From the first bite to the last bite everything was scrumptious

Author: Robyn T.
Content: What a crowd Glad my friend and I came early to nab a seat just before 7 There was a mix of families with young kids a few dates other groups of girlfriends and some guys at the bar The hostess was SUPER friendly greeting us like long lost friends and giving us her undivided attention to recommend her faves on both the mixed drink and extensive beer menu The crowds began to build and I can only expect that this place is going to be slammed on the weekendsSome people like big burger patties Me I actually prefer a thinner juicy patty so this was my cup of tea I could appreciate the delicious brioche style bun and the spicy hot sauce blue cheese and onions that sat in my burgerCome for the burger but go hog wild on the sides Mac  cheese with bacon and balsamic onions thats mc 2 the pepper fries and truffle fries were all recommendations Id make Deviled eggs weredeviled eggs No surprises there but if its not something you get to enjoy often then splurge the 2 and get the 3 eggsI was too full for dessert and rolled out of here 20 including tax  tip later

Author: Margaret N.
Content: The GoodMadame Genevas Rhubarb Delight a ginbased cocktail and damn is it delightfulParmesan fries with Truffle CreamA customer survey at the end of the meal I get the impression these guys actually give a damn about what their customers think The beer list is creative and extensive nice workThe Bad Cherry housemade soda  a giant glass of carbonated Dimetapp complete with medicine aftertaste  Pricey I know this is LP and I will pay the price for an amazing dining experience but this just wasnt it Also my cocktail was 10 bucks my burger 8 bucks I think both should be in the 6 buck range for what it was I was full when we left but 3 other people I was with complained of still being hungry Maybe I just have a freaky small stomachThe AverageThe burger I got a 1 with a turkey burger Not very flavorful very meh It satisfied my burger craving but it was not the orgasmic burger I was expecting especially for 8 bucks Flub a Dub Chubs is still my burger goto spot in the neighborhoodThe Weird Our server was like 14 years old Seriously it looked like she just got her braces off yesterday Wow it felt weird to receive alcohol from her We all agreed she had to have been someones daughter to get that jobOverall I might give them another try someday but theres nothing new or interesting about the place As a Twin Cities native I have two burger words of suggestion for these guys Juicy Lucy Now thats something that hasnt really hit the burger scene in Chicago yet but its something I think we desperately need Get on it DMK

Author: Andrew T.
Content: More of a 35 but someone said it best  a Kumas for the LP set  Went late on a weeknight plenty of open tables by the time we left the bar had pretty much cleared out the website says open late  i take that to mean 103011The lamb burger was good reminded me of a gyro The small fries are good sized for two bucks and the mac and cheese is good sized too although it is six bucks  All in all a good burger joint and tasty saucesflavors for the fries and mac n cheese  The india pale ale was tasty too

Author: Abby Z.
Content: Major letdownThis was our second attempt to come here  the first time was a Friday night where the wait was too ridiculous so we went next door to FishBar also a 2 star experienceThis time was a Sunday around 1 pm We put our name down and were quoted around a 30 minute wait Once 30 minutes had passed and we started noticing people who got there long after us were being seated we inquired with the girl whose only job was to take names and seat people as to our place on the list Surprisingly she had passed us by even though we were standing practically next to her the entire time and had gone to the next page after crossing us off Whatever we arent too picky about stuff like this and she had a table for us once she realized we hadnt disappeared into thin air But that was just the start to a bad dining experienceWhat we orderedPatty MeltBurger Number 1 with bacon bbq sauce and aged cheddar cheeseFired Okra and PicklesSmall parmesan fried with truffle creamMilk Stout the only thing worth returning for poured wellAll of it including the service throughout was dry and subpar When they brought the fries they came with no truffle cream so we we asked about it oh yea I can get some said the server Well yea duh you can its stated as being part of the plate so it shouldnt be a request only sort of thing That said the fries had good texture and were crispy but not oily Not so for the okra and pickles These looked appealing on the plate but were a soggy mess and the batter fell right off making it basically cooked pickles with one or two pieces of okra The ranch dressing had no zing so this dish got a major thumbs down for bad texture and bland flavorsThe burgers pretty much sucked Can someone explain the hype to me The burger itself was very very dry We made no special requests for how it was cooked hoping that however they have selected to prepare them is what is right Maybe they effed ours up and cooked them to death but damn they were so dry they were crumbly and had no seasoning to speak of With that said I really dont understand why in a city who loves meat so much so many people are flocking to a place charging 8 bucks for a dry patty Not that I think thats expensive but for something that sucks and is bland I doMaybe Im spoiled being from CA land of InNOut but I wont be returning here theres far better to be had

Author: Charlotte F.
Content: Loud and overpriced Everyone in my party got the runs for 13 days Why the hype There are a number of better burgers in a one mile radius Also not sure they had actual truffle fries at some point but when we visited it was normal fries with grated parmesan cheese and truffle dipping sauce

Author: Justin S.
Content: I came here for their Valentines Day special with my girlfriend A 1 and 5 were ordered Both were quite delicious My 5 was awesome even though I have intense hatred for salt and vinegar chips The milkshake was great the deviled eggs were good satisfying from start to finish I was expecting an overly well cooked burger but maybe my ESP shone through because mine was at an ideal medium I didnt sample the drink list beyond the Three Floyds Gumballhead that was offered with our meal but their beer list is extensive Craft beers from start to finish Id love to go back try another burger try the famed blood orange soda and eat more parmesan fries with truffle mayoAnd no I wont compare this to Kumas Corner

Author: Afton A.
Content: Um delish  The 1 burger is my favorite Bacon balsamic caramelized onions aged cheddar BBQ sauce 4  heart attack special my name not theirs with a fried egg  Fries Swoon Parmesan truffle cream friesa fat kids heaven They make their own delicious soda We watched The 3 Amigos while we ate FTWIf you dont feel like you need to be rolled out of the bar when youre finished eating to immediately slip into a food coma you didnt do it right Just sayin

Author: Melody C.
Content: Good burger  i prefer the glossy brioche buns  but what i ordered  i think it had the 2 ChiliRubbed Onion Strings Amish Blue cheeseSpicy Chipotle Ketchup and i asked them to add bacon and a side of bbq sauce  it was SOO goodterrific sweet potato friesyou can add a fried egg on top  having already added bacon on top of the fried onion and cheese i decided to hold off on that one for next timereally good and large dish of gruyere mac and cheese  it had soft red onion baked at the bottom of the dish with bacon bits on top  I LOVE BACONi had the home made cherry soda  it tasted sort of like diet soda with less sugar  maybe the other flavors are betterall in all burgers are not my favorite thing in the world but a good burger like the one i had at DMK is TERRIFIC  good enoguh to make me ignore all the guilt from gobbling down fatty mac and cheese and bacon and fried food

Author: Jerry G.
Content: The aged cheddar and smoked bacon burger I had was underwhelming due to a lacking in flavor beef patty so I was a little sad that DMK couldnt provide anything worth comparing to Kumas Yet the place was saved from getting a 2 star rating by how awesome their fries tasted in combination w their accompanied sauces I would even suggest to get at least two styles of the fries when you eat here Maybe consider passing on the burger to add a third style of fries yeah theyre that goodMust Have Any style off fries

Author: John M.
Content: My quest for the best burger in Chicago took us to DMK one saturday afternoon for lunch DMK had been recommended by friends as a place a burger lover like me should definitely try After previously suffering through two lousy recommendations J Wellingtons and Longman  Eagle I did not have high hope for DMKWe sat and examined the menu in the straightforward dining room A lot of prebuilt burgers The Saturday special was the Bison burger with goat cheese My girlfriend opted for the special to satiate her love of goat cheese and I the purist went with the 8 medium which is a cheeseburger with American LTMO We also split an order of the cheddar and scallion friesThe burgers here are wide smashed patties cooked on a griddle and served atop briochestyle rolls The tell tale signs of a smashed patty are the irregular edge shape flatter proportions and a good crunchy crust This is also the preferred cooking method of my holy grail of burgers the Shack Double from Shake ShackWe got our food shortly with little fanfare The burgers were served on small plates and looked deceptively big I bit into mine and it gushed The inside was pink throughout almost medium rare But with a patty this thin the difference between rare and well could be only 30 seconds or so The toppings were fresh and the cheese was perfectly melted The beef had a good subtle beefiness about it but was missing some of the more pronounced sirloin flavor the Shack Double hasDid I say this burger was juicy I ended up with a plateful of grease and the roll was falling apart I will give kudos to DMK for using a less bready version of the seemingly ubiquitous brioche which would have sucked up a lot of the excess juice However had they toasted the inside of those buns I think the roll would have stayed intact Also cutting back on the amount of fat in the beef blend would allow them cut fat an introduce more robust beef flavorsThe bison burger did not seem to suffer the fat issues of the regular beef patty However the amount of goat cheese was overpowering A little goes a long way All in all it was good but not as good as the bison burger from Bluebird on N DamenWe left pleasantly surprised with DMK So far it was the best burger we have had in the city Hopefully they can correct some of the mistakes and it can get even better

Author: Julia D.
Content: I want to go to there All the time Somehow I didnt know about DMK until recently I need to get my burger radar checked I think but I want to move closer to it One of the best burgers Ive ever had We waited awhile to sit at 2 pm on a Saturday but thats fine I understand the NEED for a good ass cheeseburger We has a rockin server who suggested great burgers and great drinks I had the 1 the parmesan fries and some lovely little rhubarb cocktail that I wanted a pitcher of It came with a tiny spoon full of rhubarb jam I love tiny things I was sold on that alone but it really was a great cocktail Manfriend had the 4 some dark beer you could probably chew and sweet potato fries He was in loveFor whatever reason we decided to come here and then go shopping for pants Probably the worst plan of all time The pants shopping was a total bust but the DMK portion of the day was a 40My mouth is watering just thinking about it

Author: David M.
Content: First visit today  Probably picked a bad day for that since it is amateur hour St Pat Day but they did well anyway  First offexcellent local based beer listgood okay not great tap list but an excellent list of bottled beerSecondalso a good selection  menu of burgers chili really hot excellent chili based chiliguess it changes more or less daily mac and cheesemy chili was excellent and so was Todds burgerThirdserviceour bartender  wait person was knowledgeable and helped explain  recommend items on the menufood came a little slowly but do have to remember the day and the crowdWe will be back

Author: Janet X.
Content: Wow this place is LOUD  A friend and I were hankering for burgers and thought that this would be a good place to grab some and catch up  Little did I know that I was going to leave the restaurant hoarse from screaming across our tiny little table  The lights were also dim making it feel like I should be here at eleven oclock on a Saturday night rather than seven oclock on a SundayThe food itself was okay I guess  I had the plain hamburger with tomatoes lettuce and some buttered pickels  Thankfully it did not come with its own stretcher but I cannot say with any assurance that it was less of a heart attack than anything McDonalds serves  The sweet potato fries were very good but the bloodorange soda was too much soda water and not enough taste  Would I come here again  Maybe eleven oclock next Saturday when I feel like a midnight snack

Author: rebecca g.
Content: The communal bar seating is a bit weird but service is prompt attentive and thorough  I think 3 different serversmanagers checked in on us during dinnerFoodwise I was more impressed by the sides than the signature burgersthe parmesan fries with truffle cream were out of this world and the sweet potato fries with lemontabasco aioli were a lovely second  The baconcaramelized onion macncheese wasnt bad but definitely nowhere near as unique as the fries  My friend and I split a turkey burger which was good but kind of meager in size and  I couldnt really taste the many condiments that were supposedly on it  The housemade sodas are a nice touch I tried the blood orange which was a nice not overly sweet flavor but perhaps a bit too carbonatedId probably go back for beer and friesgreat latenight bar snack foodADDENDUM January 2010  went back for a friends birthday Insanely long wait but wellworth it  Had a lovely seasonal gin cocktail served with a little spoonful of local rhubarb jam another yummy turkey burger sub for one of the beef options on the menu and everyone in our large group had a grand time sampling all the assorted fries fried pickles etc  WIN

Author: Lauren G.
Content: DMK DMK DMK Just the thought of it makes me want to chant What can I say This loud burger bar is a place I want to take my mother Not in a shell really appreciate this and think this is so darn cute way but in a shes going to think these burgers and fries are damn good way DMK has come out on top as both a rowdy dinner stop as well as a chill afternoon barhopping post The burger concoctions are just the right flavor The french fries come in any taste youre craving DMK DMKOh and did I mention the drinks Bartender Gregg will whip you up anything that your heart desires Lets just say for my  make me something refreshing request G never failed to wow me with tasty sips of boozey drinks  including one of a kind rhubarb brews and deliciously muddledandsweet lemon licks Mmm And if DMK is your usual spot be sure to grab one of their frequent visitor cards Good food and prizes Um yep

Author: Linsey C.
Content: Super impressedWalked in on a Friday night around 5 and was seated right away by a super friendly hostess  The service in this place is good but a little overkill  I know they are new and are still figuring things out but probably 4 different people stopped by our table a total of about 15 times to see if we were okI mean Im all for attentive service but thats just ridiculous  Also after all that checking at the beginning of our meal we had to wave down our server to get the checkby this point they were pretty busy which generally means they want to turn tables quicklynot the case apparentlySo the foodI had the 1 burgeraged cheddar bacon onions and bbq sauce  Im not a big bbq sauce fan so I asked for it on the sidenext time Ill just let them put it on the burgerit was delicious  The buns are amazing and I was slightly worried about the doneness of the burger when the server said all burgers are cooked to medium Im generally a MW person but it was perfectslightly pink but not in a creepy blood on your plate cold in the middle sort of way  My dining partner had the classic burger 8 and he loved it  We got an order of the salt and pepper fries which had a little too much pepper for our taste but were still delicious and I dont really like fries all that muchThe music wasnt too loud as others have commented but I didnt like how close the tables were  We sat along the back wall which is the half boothhalf table thing and the tables were so close it was impossible to not overhear the conversation at the next table and pretty tricky to get out of the booth side without bumping into the person dining next to youI hesitate with the 5th star because I feel like they are going to get even better and I want to be able to update my review when they do  Also hopefully after the initial opening period they will allow substitutionswould have loved me some avocado on that burger

Author: Laura M.
Content: I was surprised in how good DMK was  The fried Okra  pickles were excellent I love friend pickles and they were the best I have ever had  And the parmesan truffle fries were also outstandingWell the burger wasnt the best I have ever had in my life it was still VERY good I personally didnt like the bun but it wasnt badWe will definitely be backOh I also thought the service was great  We were seated immediately on a Saturday at noon they were quick and very friendly  The decor was also more upscale and nicer than we expected

Author: Jeff W.
Content: Let me say the website is NOT the reason to come hereI can only imagine the scene on a weekend night at this must see and be scene new high end burger joint on North side Great deviled eggsnice beer selectionblood red orange soda also yumi would avoid the other home made sodas BEST sweet potato fries I have ever tastedperfect crunchnot greasy perfectly seasonedalso tasty the chili infused onion straws Avoid so so mac n cheese had 2 varieties and both are average The burgersYUM2 of us had the pastrami burger with cheese and sauerkrautI skipped special sauce I f you are super hungry it may be worth getting double as the burgers are NOT huge nor are the prices 8 bucks a burger My other friends had a lamb burger that looked very tasty and he loved it with a Greek flair I will be back

Author: Rudra B.
Content: This place has great servers good beer and excellent burgers  Many of my friends consider this the best burger in ChicagoThe fries are excellent

Author: Matthew L.
Content: Service sucked some of the worst service Ive ever had  Couldnt get a bill or a drink refill and our server never even told us they had specialsThe food is okay the burgers arent much better than other good burger places  The drink menu is great and the best part of our meal was the side dishes  But I still cant get over our serviceNote to barbusiness owners  Just cause a girl is cute doesnt mean she canshould waitress  As one of the best movies states  The world needs ditch diggers too

Author: Ron T.
Content: The cab ride felt like an eternity and the anticipation was killing me I was getting close to eating my arm off in the cab but I told myself to wait because this is going to be so worth it and DMK did NOT disappoint First impression this is a burger joint So trendy looking but yet they are serving me an 8 burgerI LOVE IT We had an hour wait but we were able to snag a spot right by the bar and dined there As I glanced over the menu and had way too much salivation going on I had to make the ultimate choicefirst time here get the biggest burger they make so I took on the Big DMK Do I normally do this no because my diet has changed over the years as Ive gotten older but this one time being in the city and feeling young again I took a step back into my yesteryears Along with it I ordered the Parmesan Fries with the Truffle dipping sauce probably the best fries Ive EVER had without a doubt The burger  HEAVEN and what makes it like this is the fact that all of the components with it create and work of art on a bun Love love love the beer choices that they offer Im a fanOverall great atmosphere great burger and fries service was stellar and I just cant wait to go back Also so happy they have one in Lombard close to me

Author: Burger Guide D.
Content: The burgers at DMK Burger have a lot of ambition but it gets lost somewhere in the essentials The beef patties are a little too thin bun are too dry but they have some creative and tasty toppings My major problem with the burgers I tried was that the patties were too dry This is probably a result of the patties being very thin which can lead to easy overcooking on the grill DMK has some great fries drinks and is in a fun neighborhood Overall the burgers are pretty good and the fries alone might be worth a visit

Author: Carrie M.
Content: This place is pretty average  good for lunch if theres no wait but I wouldnt go out of my way to come backWe came here around noon on a Saturday and were seated right away  Everyone working there was friendly attentive and VERY enthusiastic about the burgers shakes iced tea  pretty much everything  It felt very cold and warehouselike which is probably what they were going for but to me it felt uninviting and uncomfortableAs previous reviewers have said the burgers are on the thin side and as we were told by our sever inspired by In and Out Burger  I got the classic without mayo or cheese and it was pretty dry and a bit on the bland side although the bun was fantastic and you cant forget how important a bun is to the entire burger experience  I really wouldnt compare their burger to In and Out but can see how they triedSticking with the classics I got the salt  pepper fries  They were good and crispy with a mild smoky flavor and come with house made ketchup  I was apprehensive about that part lets stick to Heinz please but it ended up being pretty good for what I was expecting and did the job just fineI didnt drink but the beer selection was impressive  As for nonalcoholic drinks expect a lot of craft sodas and no free refills  Really DMK  No free refills on a 2 soda  Overall  I wont go out of my way to come back again but wouldnt mind if Im nearby and a friend wants to try it  This gets a big meh

Author: Joey B.
Content: This place is right around the corner from me and it took me quite a while to go in  From the outside its nothing special  In fact it looks more like a douchey bar than anything else  However once inside I realized that this place has more to offer than standard bar fare and Miller LiteFor starters the beer list is exceptional  Plenty of local brews on tap as well as in bottles and some impressive imports  I enjoyed several Two Brothers beers of which they had three different varieties on the menu  Moving on to the hamburgers I found the eclectic creations to be striking  Many different styles of burger as well as bison turkey salmon and veggie options  I hear they have a good mac and cheese though no one in my party ordered itI settled on the Italianthemed burger complete with prosciutto fontina cheese roasted red peppers pesto and to top it all off a handful of salt and vinegar chips  The classic pothead move of putting chips on a sandwich made my decision easy  The doughy Ciabatta bread it was served on combined with the crispy chips made for a very fun creation  You dont need to be stoned to enjoy a sandwich this flavorful and packed with goodies but it never hurtsI was also able to taste the patty melt which came complete with cheddar bacon and grilled onion  It would be damn near impossible to screw a sandwich with these things on it so needless to say it was good  Several french fry options are available our table ordered the sweet potato fries  Quite good I must say served with some kind of flavored mayo  Im not a huge fan of mayo on fries but I hear that Canadians are  So if youre Canadian you may enjoy this establishment  Overall the food was quite good at a fairly reasonable price  8 burgers a la carte is not so bad for the area but not great either  A basket of fries will run you 4 and is plenty to share  I would recommend DMK to anyone looking for an interesting burger good beer and Canadians  Especially Canadians

Author: Liz P.
Content: Food coma I couldnt even write this review last night when I got home because I had eaten too much to even think about food postdinner We had a group of 6 and went at about 730 on a Tuesday night Wait was about 20 minutes which was totally acceptable Our waitress was fantastic and was able to keep up with my friends occasional inappropriate humor She even participated in the boys brainstorm of a baconranch soupAppetizersSidesWe ordered the fried pickles to start  honestly can you really go wrong with fried pickles answer NO We then ordered three kinds of fries for the table to have with dinner sweet potato blue cheese and bacon and truffle Personally Im a huge fan of the sweet potato friesone of my friends wanted to drink the truffle sauce so I think those were also a hitBurgers I ordered the bison burger and was very pleased The burgers are the perfect size to be able to order a few other sides on the menu which is really how it should be done at a place like this It came with goat cheese pickled red onions and blueberry bbq sauce To be honest blueberry bbq sauce made me a bit uncomfortable so I asked for it on the side just in case I was worried it would be much too sweet especially when paired with the picked onions  not so I ended up adding it back on the burger after the first bite and then even dipping the burger in for extrasOverall everyone enjoyed their burgers Beware the number 2 apparently has a bit of a kick to itas does the number 1 according to my fellow diners The lamb burger was also given a thumbs up but I cannot speak to it personally since I didnt have itDesert For some unknown reason we thought we had room for desert so a peanut butter shake and an ice cream sandwich was ordered Beware the peanut butter shake has a LOT of peanut butter in it Still delish but very heavy There are two types of ice cream sandwiches and we opted for the chocolate chip cookie with vanilla ice cream Solid ice cream sandwichFun extraSomeone asked jokingly about the deviled eggs We didnt order any but the waitress sent some out for us on the house  SO GOOD If for some reason you have a cravingdefinitely recommend them When we got the bill it looked like we had been charge for the eggs until we went to the total and there was a deduction for love which totally made our day Simply fantastic little treat to end a solid meal

Author: Janice M.
Content: Stumbled on this during an afternoon in this neighborhoodWe considered the Fish place next door same owners but opted for DMKSat in the bar area at the long high top table  Server came right over  discussed the beer offerings  and brought us out a few to try since we couldnt make up our minds  LOVE when places do thisShe recommended trying a couple smaller portions of the fries  which we did the salt and vinegar and the wisconsin cheddarStarted off with the wedge salad  Perfectly executedWe had the Bison Burger and the Patty Melt  Both delicious  Fries were really good tooOverall the food and service were top notch  Good value  2 salads 2 burgers 2 small fries 2 beers  45 before tipHowever  if I could have given it 4 12 stars I would  due to the noise level  The music was soooooo loud  to the point where we considered leaving during the first 5 minutes after being seated  I actually asked our server about it  and she said that it is the vibe that the owners are going for  Hence Burger Bar  Bar being the operative word  While the place was not busy we were there around 2pm midweek I could not imagine dining there during peak hours  when the place is packedSo  I will go back  but will stay away on weekends and dinner hour

Author: Foodie B.
Content: It is very hard for me not to go here every time I come to Chicago One of my all time favorite burgers which is really saying a lot Food drinks and service are all on point

Author: Chay K.
Content: Their burgers were good but nothing outofthisworld I was expecting more especially for a joint in ChicagoThe one thing I did thoroughly enjoy was their fries  In all fairness if you are looking for a lighter burger that wont leave you overly stuffed than this place will do This is coming from a 130 lb 20something female Or if you are going for a wide selection of beers that arent too overpriced this place will do  Otherwise I would head over to Kumas or the like

Author: Jay W.
Content: I was never a huge burger person but this place turned that around The burgers are awesome just the right size and the perfect bunburgertopping ratio I have only had the one with portabello mushrooms and brie because I cant bring myself to even try anything else Fries also amazingThere are always people there but weve never had to wait and the servers are always very pleasant It can be a little loud but that goes with the burger bar  territory

Author: Irene W.
Content: Awesome burgers Must order the double patty  meat patty plus the portabello mushroom patty I ordered 5 Bison patty with extra portabello mushroom pattythey are huge well at least for me Also ordered the mac n cheese 2 the red onion makes this mac n cheese different in a good way Been here twice and always go home satisfied and full

Author: Annie D.
Content: YES YOU ARE CORRECT  I HAVE THE CAPSLOCK ON  WHY  BECAUSE ITS THE ONLY WAY OF APPROXIMATING THE VOLUME AT WHICH I WOULD HAVE TO SPEAK IF WE WERE HAVING A BEER AND A BURGER AT DMK RIGHT NOW  I struggled with the rating  It would have been only one star because of the sheer ungodly volume of the place  But I added a star for the friendly server whos probably going slowly deaf and another star just because I hate that Yelp uses the word Meh to explain the two star rating A word of caution  ask for a side of earplugs with those fries

Author: Molly R.
Content: This place is fabulous  I cant stop thinking about it  After just one visit last Thursday night I am ready to declare this the best burger Ive ever hadLet me start by saying I am so glad to have DMK Burger Bar in the neighborhood  I live just two blocks away and although we have plenty of great bars and fast food joints around theres nothing as refined yet affordable in the BelmontSheffield area  I told David Morton just that when he kindly came around to our table to ask us how our meal wasOn to the food  I ordered the Lamb Burger 11 with feta cheese and olive tapenade My burger was absolutely delicious the meat just melted in your mouth and wasnt at all overwhelmed by the toppings  I managed to snag a bite of two of my friends burgers one with marinated portabella mushrooms good but nothing to sing about and the other with bacon  barbecue sauce the sauce was really great Id order this one again if I can ever tear myself away from the Lamb Burger  We all agreed that the Lamb Burger was the best on the tableWe also ordered three kinds of fries the original seasoned fries with housemade ketchup the sweet potato fries and the truffle oil fries  The original  truffle oil fries were not crispy enough and we didnt really enjoy them Everyone gobbled up the sweetpotato fries however they were perfectly crisp and were served with a lemon aioli sauceTo top it all of was a short espresso milk shake  I ate it all I didnt want to share and I could have ordered another  There were crunchy bits in it maybe chocolate covered coffee beans  If you are a coffee lover like I am order this one  Its only 3 and the perfect size if youre drinking it aloneOne more thing about the crowd  When we went last Thursday night around 6pm our party of four was seated pretty quickly  Last night I returned around 8pm to revisit the Lamb Burger I had been dreaming about all weekend and another couple walked in right behind us  There was a bit of a crowd waiting with drinks at the bar and David Morton who I recognized from my earlier visit walked straight up to the other couple and sat them totally ignoring me and my friend  I was a little pissed off until I looked at the couple and realized it was Alpana Singh from Check Please  Minor Chicago Celebrity sighting  Ill give em that one but when he returned and told us it would be a 35 minute wait we decided to pass  Go early to avoid the crowdsSo there you have it  5 stars for delicious burgers shakes and sweet potato fries they make up for the crowds and the soggy truffle fries

Author: Marne O.
Content: My friends and I tried to go to Kumas while I visited Chicago but the wait was 2 hrs So someone suggested DMK GREAT IDEA the wait was about 15 mins I had the 5 burger which has prosciutto and fontina cheese it was delicious The burger wasnt too thick like most gourmet burgers It was a nice size but thin enough so it was easy to handle I couldnt resist getting the battered pickles  okra with ranch dipping sauce Fantastic Id recommend this joint to anyone in Chicago They even serve a veggie burger which catered to my vegan pals Yay

Author: Steven R.
Content: Burger wars began after I moved to Chicago  Id heard of so many great places serving up meat n cheese on a bun that I was determined to try as many as my cholesterol level would let meDMK is kind of your great postmodern burger bar  I feel there is a lot of style over substance  DMK makes tasty concoctions but I cant help but feel that Im really paying for the flavor and not the size or being truly full  Dont get me wrong the burgers are good but I dont know theres just something missing here that keeps it from being an instant place that comes to mind when I want a burger  Natural fed beef does make a different but it seems like the cooking of the patties is somewhat arbitrary as Ive had one that was brown all the way and one with a whole loooootta pinkAlso Im not sure what it is but this place seems to always have some group of insanely loud middle aged people going crazy at it  The seating is close together too so you may catch more of other conversations that you want  Thankfully the situation is ameliorated by a great selection of local beers and wines  The wait can be a little nutty depending on the night so keep that in mind

Author: Ashley B.
Content: Loved it We got in and out pretty quickly despite the fact that it was packed and the food was great I went with some diehard burger fans and they loved it but they still had some interesting choices for the nonconventional burger person like me I had the lamb burger with tzatziki sauce and the works and it was delicious Every burger was pretty much 8 and you could add sides for a few bucks more Or if you use foursquare you can check in and get a free side of fries We tried out the truffle cream and Wisconsin cheddar fries and they were so filling and rich it was ridiculous I definitely recommend it for a nice lunchUDPATE Added another star Thats right I went back here with my parents and boyfriend My dad is a meat and potatoes kind of guy and was craving a burger I mean I love their burger concoctions and sauces but I was nervous that his plain ketchuponly burger wouldnt impress him I was wrong he loved it and said the meat quality made that burger one of the best hes ever had which if you knew my dad says a lot Not to mention I came back and got the 2 and it was just as good as my previous favorite the 11 Seriously if you havent been here yet GO NOW

Author: Aaron T.
Content: 1 star to startFood 1 starIn the mood for hamburgers for lunch and stopped by this trendy spot  Per the recommendation of my friend I got the 4 Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack Smoked Bacon and it was delicious  The fried egg was the perfect complement and the burger was cooked to perfection  The bun was also great and didnt get soggy or mushy like with other burgers but definitely added some good flavor  We also had garlic fries and sweet potato fries both of which I would recommend  We downed all of this with blood orange sodas which are homemade though this was probably the least tasty part of the mealService 1 starThe service here was pretty good as they get you seated quickly and check on you constantly  Our waitress was very friendly and made some good recommendations and shared a few laughs with us along the way  They are very quick and you definitely feel the attentiveness hereValue 05 starsPricing was very reasonable here though it would have been nice if the burgers came with a little something extra like standard fries  That being said all burgers are 8 and are worth the price as everything about that screams fresh and highqualityExperience 05 starsWhen we first walked in it was hard to tell this was a burger bar because of the dark interior and trendier atmosphere  Seating is very open and spaced out  I found myself craving for a bit more lighting inside but overall I enjoyed the simplistic and clean appointments  I would definitely recommend checking this place out if youre craving a quality hamburgerOverall10  Baseline10  Food10  Service05  Value05  Experience4 stars

Author: Kristy H.
Content: YuckI would have given this place two stars one for the interior design and one for the beer selection had I not just been sick from it 3 hours after eating itFirst the beer selection is good Not Hopleaf great but good My beer arrived in a red wine glass which was kind of cool but also kind of cheap It definitely wasnt a pint 1 starThe food is terrible They are trying super hard to be cool and trendy I can appreciate that I mean I love the kitsch at Eleven City Diner Do your food right then worry about the environment that goes along with it My burger the one w the sea salt chips went halfeaten and I was starving The meat was thin and served a bit cooler than medium The parmesan fries w truffle aioli were uninspired We asked for ketchup and even that wasnt good The place was incredibly overpriced too They should charge 10 and give you your choice of fries at least you feel like youre getting something for the valueAlso there should be some drink specials for weekends during the day Every bar on Clark Broadway Sheffield Diversey and Halsted had a special going on from 2 PBR cans to 3 Goose Island drafts DMK has to offer something to compensate for the food

Author: Jennifer M.
Content: FOODGOOD DELICIOUS quality burgers You can definitely tell the difference in quality between these burgers and fastfood burgers The meat is fresh and the burger combos are original Pretty reasonable price for them too Their FRIES were pretty orgasmic especially the sweet potato fries Im a sucker for them 2nd best sweet potato fries Ive had next to Ruggles in Houston ATMOSPHEREReally chill and comfortable Nicely decorated inside kind of sexy but not a dark sexy More like a chic and modern sexy Most of the time theres  a wait but its not too long and you can walk around the area while waiting

Author: Rachel S.
Content: A bit out of the way for this BucktownLogan Square girl but worth it  One tasty grassfed burgerI got the one with prosciutto and it rocked  I cant wait to go back and try moreThe only reason I had to bump this down from 5 stars was that the noise level was at 11  Unlike many of my midtwenties peers I dislike noisy places  Keep in mind too that I patronized DMK on a weeknight

Author: Grant G.
Content: Went on a Tuesday evening around 830p with a friend and got a table right awayThe good Fantastic burger  The bun was surprisingly soft and just enough bread  Everything came together perfectly  No condiments necessary  The meat was extremely savory probably had a lot of sodium Fries were really tasty albeit a bit greasy  When it comes to ketchup Im a diehard Heinz fan but their house stuff was good even with the slight chipotle flavor even given that I think chipotle is overplayed Great beer lineup  Wish there were some imports on the list though Our server Marina Z was fantastic in every way  Perfect timing demeanor and responseThe soso The tall chairs suck  Too small and not the most sturdySummary is that they keep it simple and do it well  Sit booth side if possible  Wait worthiness  less than 45 min

Author: Stephanie L.
Content: Holla new burger joint  For the first time I was excited to go to a burger jointbecause of my new found love of beef Well this place was JAMMED on a Tuesday  Not when we first walked in but by the time we left there wasnt a seat in the joint  Now they must be doing something right  So I have to admit I can put away some food  and drink  I slooshed down some hefeweizenthey have a pretty good beer list  Which I was surprised byI ate the fried pickles and okra  the 2 burger yummy fried onions blue cheese and saucePERFECTION  We also had the standard fries along with the truffle fries and the sweet potato frieswe were celebrating okdont judge  It was totally CHEAP too  And surprisingly I was just right as far as being fullwasnt stuffed and definitely not still hungry   Service was just ok and they only have one bathroom per genderwith a packed house of people throwing back good beers and burgersmaybe want to reconsider that minus a starOverall I would def go back  I really wanted to try the lambalas I had to go with the beef burger  But next time its a done deal

Author: Lia V.
Content: Truffle Cream Dipping Sauce I want to swim in a kiddie pool of this amazing substance If you like truffles you MUST get the Parmesan fries with truffle cream I really dont have anything else to say except oh  thats right their burgers are FANTASTIC Bison Burger  heavenly Portobello Burger  defreakinlicious and largest portobello Ive seen in my lifeTurkey Burger fresh and phenomenal But wait I can go on PACKED on a tuesday night I mean what Ive lived down the street from this place for over a year and have never been What was I thinking DELICIOUS BEER Amazing selection and they give out free beer coupons I mean come on now Hot bartender Whaaat This is like becoming my favorite neighborhood hang outSo basically I highly suggest this place

Author: Marjorie F.
Content: This place has really grown on me  I have tried almost of all of the burgers and have found a few favorites  Top on the list is their Turkey Burger  Havent found another place that can beat itNow that I have given up meat for lent Im all about the mac n cheese  Not the same without the luscious touch of bacon but Ill liveIt has become my goto place after work with friends  Keep up the good work

Author: Liz K.
Content: For some reason I decided it would be a good idea to come here on a Saturday Dont ask me why The wait really wasnt terrible though The bar was extremely crowded but people were polite and made room Beer list was decent and everything was priced as youd expect in ChicagoAs for the food though First they sat us at a shared table Across from each other And it was so loud I could basically not hear what was being said to me Other than that though service was quick Everything on the menu is decently priced I had the 1 burger which was bbq bacon cheddar and onion To be honest I couldnt really taste the cheddar bacon or onion But it was still pretty tasty They sort of drowned it in bbq sauceAlso we had the amish blue  smoked bacon fries And those were great Overall the food is pretty good here but as everyone says it doesnt measure up to Kumas in portion size or taste

Author: Tina M.
Content: My first bite was just of the burger and it was amazing Add the other flavors with the rest of the sandwich ingredients and I was happy Definitely overfilled my stomach and was far too full for the rest of the nightFirst went here on Saturday night at 8pm and the wait was 130145 Came back the following day at 5pm and the wait was quoted 2030 minutes but ended up only being 5 minutes The food was really good but Im glad we didnt wait for over an hour on Saturday night Our waitress was really cool and seemed to be excited about the food The beer menu is also pretty good although they only have the breweries on the wall  not the beers  so you need to get the menu from someone

Author: Ehow C.
Content: My friend and I ordered an awkward takeout of truffle fries during our wait for Fish Bar The fries had a good consistency but lacked a little salt and any sort of truffle flavor Not worth the 4Whomp maybe well sit down and order something next time

Author: Charles H.
Content: So if Kumas is the 1 burger spot in Chicago then perhaps DMK is 2 The dining experience was fabulous  I ordered a 1  aged cheddar smoked bacon charred balsamic red onions rufu teague BBQ sauce  The beef was tender as advertised from being grass feed  The only drawback was the over abundant amount of BBQ on the burgerFor sides we ordered sweet potato fries with lemon tobasco aioli and the wisconsin cheddar  scallion fries  Perhaps we got a bad batch of cheddar as the cheese taste was hidden  The sweet potato fries rocked  My buddy enjoyed his 4  roasted hatch green chili egg sonoma jack smoked bacon  As with any good restaurant in Chicago theres wait for a table no reservations at DMK or first come  first serve at the bar  Expect a 45 minute wait during a peak hour or come at 8pm for immediate seating

Author: Emily C.
Content: Best burgers Ive had in Chicago I also admire their commitment to American beers This place only serves domestic beers and it really shows the customers how far domestic craft brewing has come in recent years They consistently have 6 options on tap as well as an extensive bottle list I live right down the street so Ive tried almost everything on the menu My three favorite burgers are 1 the green chili burger with a fried egg on top  note the green chilis are delivered fresh from New Mexico 2 the patty melt  the rye bread really brings out the meats flavor and 3 the Amish blue with onion straws  strong blue cheese flavor with some added crunchId also like to give a shoutout to the Big DMK which is actually a Big Mac in disguiseThe macaroni and cheese is fantastic and often overlooked It comes baked in a little dish with a hard crust on top I like the one with grilled onions on the bottom Even the salads are goodWhatever you do dont forget to order fries for the table All of them are fried in beef fat which makes them extrasavory and delicious My favorite are the sweet potato fries with lemon aioliThe only downside of dining at DMK is the food coma that inevitably follows After eating a full burger and small plate of fries I literally had to take the afternoon off last year in order to rest So take it easy but dont let that stop you

Author: Kevin C.
Content: Its been 3 years since Ive last visited Chicago There were so many restaurants that Ive been wanting to visit As a regular visitor of ahtseriouseatscom I read up on DMK and immediately wanted to visit Truffle oil in juicy burger on fresh baked bun WTF How can I not want to have thatI went in Thursday afternoon during my visit for LOLLAPALOOZA It had a nice ambiance in the restaurant Dim with some jammin music but not too loud to distract you from your burger and beer enjoyment This cute yet articulate waitress named Arianna served me that afternoon and she recommended number 2  GrassFed juicy beef on fresh baked buns with chilirubbed onion strings amish blue strong blue cheese and spicy chipotle ketchup I also had a small order of russet potato fries with paramesan and truffle creamI loved the burger I love blue cheese strong blue cheese Having the amish blue on the juicy beef was fantastic It sorely reminds me of having steaks at Ruths Chris topping it with blue cheese Maybe Im easily satisfied Maybe I have been craving for a delicious patty for WAY too long but what I had and felt about the burger that day was awesomeness I loved the chili rubbed onion string in the burger That was a nice touchThe fries with the truffle oil cream and the parmesan was pretty good but the juicy patty and the buns and the blue cheese stood out for me Thinking about it makes me crave for another one I wish there is a DMK out here in LA Nice beats cute waitress awesome burger what more can you ask for Thanks Arianna

Author: Evelina L.
