Content: I am ALL about perfect food bites and ratios  So in my book  DMK has it all and definitely delivers the meat to bun to toppings ratioAll 6 of us ordered different burgers and they were all FANTASTIC since we all had to share the deliciousness and pass around the joy My bisonblueberry bbq sauce one was the best of course but I would take the rest of the ones at the table any day of the week  Too bad the lines are so long and its not in my hood otherwise I will be there waaaay too much

Author: Mary H.
Content: I am still utterly shocked by how much I loved this place Mainly because 1 Im not a big meat eater and 2 Id heard mediocre reviews about it so was anticipating a let down But I could not have more wrong I demolished the Bison burger with goat cheese and blueberry BBQ sauce and it was absolutely delicious and I never eat burgers We also ordered the sweet potato fries and the salted fries both of which were AOK They have an extensive and reasonably priced cocktail list with something for everyone Perhaps I eat out too much but I didnt find this place to be as pricey as many of the reviewers have said 40 for two gourmet burgers two orders of fries and two fancy drinks is a good deal in my book I will definitely be back

Author: Troy D.
Content: Visited here on a recent vacation at the recommendation of some friends  Id definitely recommend it to others and recommend going backFair warning  the place is going to be busy  Guaranteed  Thursday night wait was a little unusually long but certainly not unbearableThe beer selection is pretty good  A friend from Cleveland joined us and he was able to order the Cleveland hometown specialty Great Lakes  And  the prices were pretty reasonableFoodwise wow they did a good job  The burgers in my case turkey with baconcheddarBBQ sauce was pretty darned good  the fries one order of sweet potato and one order of truffle accented things pretty well and we had enough to go aroundIts perfect for a casual dinner with friends

Author: Patricia S.
Content: The best casual burger place Ive been to my whole life hands down Nuff saidThe service is impeccable They read our minds literally I mean we walked out thinking they had the table bugged We just start talking about our thirst and they come over and ask for our drink order We order mac and cheese to share and it literally gets put on the table as we finish saying  cheese 1 AND it was on the house For free WHAT We start biting into our burgers and rave about how good it is and we mention ketchup to each other The waitress comes over with ketchup and asks us how its going We say Great but wed like some ketch and she says oh did you want ketchup and sets it down Come On you have to admit all of that is ridiculousThe house veggie and grain burger was the best veggie burger especially house Ive ever had in my life And it had eggplant on top My favorite vegetable The bun is nice and fluffy The chipotle ketchup is a perfect touch I was partial to the Wisconsin cheese and scallion fries My friends loved the truffle and parmesan Oh and the mac and cheese is prefect I didnt want to shareWe didnt order alcohol but I noticed that they paid homage to some of my favorite drink spots in NYC Madame Geneva and Death  Co They both have absolutely amazing drinks so I highly recommend Note If you ask for ketchup they give you the chipotle ketchup by default Slightly sweet smokey and spicy The specialty sodas are flat and bit too sweet Skip it

Author: Lauren F.
Content: A solid 4 stars  DMK is no Kumas Corner but I think theyve got a good thing going here  Great beer selection grass fed beef and unique toppings set DMK apart from some of the other burger bars that seem to have popped up everywhere  We started with some onion straws and the fried pickles and okrawho doesnt love  fried vegetables to dip in ranch or DMKs tasty House Ketchup  Our server also gave us an order of the Mac  Cheese 1 not sure why but we were very appreciativeit was delishAs for my burger I tried the Holy GuacAioli Burger and it was sooo good  Chorizo guac sonoma jack cheese chipotle aioli  Yes please  We cleaned the plates of both the sweet potato and the parmesan fries with truffle cream they were tasty  We were so stuffed that we didnt get to try the Pumpkin Milkshake that they had on specialguess that just means that we need to go back and save a little more room next time

Author: Claudia D.
Content: The husband and I like to drop by after out patient visits to Illinois MasonicAt our last lunch we received terrible service compared to that received in the pastWe were happy that DMK was busy at midday but we had to ask 4 times to get water to drinkOur waitress basically ignored us to wait on a large party of men  The other wait staff and bus boys took care of us as best they could when walking by  However she was very efficient in handing over the billI had a turkey burger fixed like the lamb burger and was very happy with it and a lemonade  I convinced the husband to try the bison burger which he didnt enjoy nearly as much as his usual the number 8I hope that the service change in direction doesnt become a pattern because if it does we wont be continuing customers at DMK

Author: Rebecca N.
Content: Awesome place Very extensive beer menu and very interesting cocktailsPeople at our table got hot spiked cider delish tequila w honeylimetea cocktail even better and the rhubarb cocktail the bestWe shared the bison burger crispy protabella and the patty melt All were excellentmy favorite was the bison burger The sides are probably the most fun part of the mealwe split  4 overkill but why not1 truffle fries2 cheddar and scallion3 sweat potato fries 4 onion stringsi cant even say which were the best because i was obsessed with them allI would definitely come back to try the lamb burger and holy guacamole burger

Author: Emily B.
Content: Whether you are looking for a casual date venue are starving and want to dive headfirst into a plate of fooooooood or have a sweet potato fry fetish sometimes all you need in life is a burger and a beerDMK is a great option for that Essentially they do a a few things burgers fries beers and they do them right Contrary to other wellknown buger places like The Counter DMK gives you several creative options for prebuilt sandwichestoppings with the option to sub 12 things  The beef is grassfed but I went with a veggie burger because Im a sucker for a good one and heard great things Ultimately youre getting a gutbusting burgernot a patty from Portillos Was it the best Ive ever had Not quitebut it definitely will do the trick if you have a cravingThe downsides are that the place doesnt take resos so youll be standing for a while in a loud fullof20somethings joint for a bit before you are seated I think we waited about 30 minutes on a Thurs night  745pm It also took quite a while to flag the attention of the bartender to fetch us a brew while we were waiting which was kind of a bummer Its also not the most intimate place in the world with a long bar communal tables and twotops that are very close together as the seating optionsOther things Food comes out fast Fries come with dipping sauces Super easy to get to off the Wellington Brown Line

Author: Leslie B.
Content: Regardless of how fantastic DMK was I believe theres something morally wrong with waiting an hour and 45 for a burger However my party was well prepared for the wait so we went to Kirkwoods for a couple beers and came back in time to be seated Luckily we were seated in the back otherwise Im not sure we would have been able to hear each other talk at all Our server was great she was attentive and helpful without being pushy She also recommended that we order two large fries instead of small individuals which was a good callThe only blip in the service was that we got our drinks right after our meals came I think we all hoped to have our beers a little earlier They do have a fantastic beer list though really difficult to choose from The food was awesome but I was expecting more of a wow factor than I got They werent overwhelming huge or overflowing with toppings but it was very tasty I had the number 1 and was not disappointed at all The toppings were flavorful and the bun was great We had both the truffle fries and sweet potato fries The sweet potato were some of the best Ive ever had Super tasty and the lemon tabasco aioli complimented them really well They also brought us fried pickles and okra on the house for the long wait which I think is a great move on the managements part Overall delicious food and service besides the crazy wait Our server even gave us 5 off the bill for Love which was cute Will definitely return but during the week or at an offhour

Author: Jenn G.
Content: Ill get right to the point  it aint no KumasGreat space cool vibe inside good drink selection and good food  But definitely doesnt hold a candle to Kumas which is the golden standard in my bookThe fries were the best part of my meal we sampled both the sweet potato and the cheese and scallion varieties   So much so that we almost ordered thirdsThe holy guacaioli burger was good but just wasnt as flavorful and memorable as I had anticipated If you can walk right in and get a table definitely check it out  If I have to wait an hour for a table the only place Im willing to do that is Kumas

Author: Amy H.
Content: We are faithful watchers of Diners DriveIns  Dives so we were looking forward to checking out DMK after a Cubs game last Saturday and it did not disappoint  We had a big group but were seated right away  We started off with a couple orders of the fries regular and sweet potato and they were some of the best we ever hadThe menu offers some unique flavors making it difficult to make a selection  I opted for the Bison Burger with blueberry BBQ and goat cheese and it was simply amazing  We also tried the Lamb Burger with feta and tzatziki and it was equally as goodDefinitely worth a trip

Author: Karen C.
Content: Finally hit up DMK on a Saturday night party of 2 so the wait time wasnt horrendous I think we waited about 20 minutes We were seated by the waitstation which always irks me but it wasnt too shabby Elliot Ness beers were on special for 2 a pop which I decided was the best deal in the entire city for a Saturday nightAnd heres where I have to enter my disclaimer I dont eat beef So Im not comparing this place to Kumas or to any other burgeroriented eatery I had the Salmon burger delicious the slaw on top was great I really liked the bun too and my friend had the Santo burger We both had the Parmesan fries with Truffle Aioli Good good stuff Those fries were amazing Also our waitress Carly was super niceThe crowd was mostly mid20somethings with sprinklings of their parents I had to laugh because I saw no fewer than 3 people using their cell phones as flashlights to be able to read the menu due to the darkness of the restaurant Overall it was a great experience  Im glad we went

Author: Dan L.
Content: This is a solid burger place I dont know why anyone compared this to Kumas but I guess if you put anything other than the usual on a beef patty you have to be crazy and compared to the best I went here with my fiancee and my gluttonous partner in crime Bart I forgot how many patties he actually added to their rendition of the big mac but the waitress had to make sure he was ok with how big it would be and he didnt disappoint I had the special which was supposed to be spicy but Id have to call bullshit because the sauce wasnt that spicy at all The fries were good and we all left happily full Also had some good beers to finish the meal Good times

Author: Anna A.
Content: GREAT FOOD GREAT SERVICEMy boyfriend recently moved to the area and we walked past this restaurant that was super crowded on a Wednesday night and we knew we had to try it The music was too loud but the hostesses sat us very quickly and were so friendly The waitress was also very attentive and friendly despite it being completely packed The cocktailbeer menu was amazing we ended ordering mojitios and they were delicious For food we split the parmesan truffled fries macaroni and cheese and a Number One burger Everything was fabulous We cant wait to go back

Author: Damian C.
Content: Torn  Like I liked it but is it the cats pajamas  I dunnoFor starters the burger is 5oz  So if you need to satisfy a raging hunger and are expecting a half pound slab or redmeat goodness youre SOL  If youre expecting a puffy brioche or dense and salty bun to hold together your beefy and condimenty concoction think againIts all a la carte  That 9burger price tag  Know that the standard sides are NOT includedIf you want to delete an item fine if you want to substitute fahgettaboutit  Want to customize your burger temperature  No bueno  This aint no disco  And it aint no Counter Burger eitherAll that being said the food was good  I wasnt overly thrilled but I wasnt a hater either  The service was fairly quick for a Saturday lunch and though the tables were a bit too cozy I was able to enjoy great lunch conversation  The options were not overly plentiful but enough to satisfy most palettes  The overriding reason for our trip here was for truffle fries SERIOUS CRAVING but when it came to the actual burger I was on the fence between the 1 bacon cheddar BBQ sans onions and the special chicken caesar burger with garlic and other goodies the waitress recommended the 1  For 13 it was not a lot of food but everything did taste great  Honestly my favorite part of the burger was the bun fairly thin super soft just delicious  If I could buy a bag of just those I would be happy  I also appreciated the side of truffle aioli that came with my fries I spread a good portion of it on my burger to add some extra flavor  Good  Yes  Overpriced  A bit  Maybe its the neighbors cats pajamas

Author: Bobs C.
Content: I had the Patty melt and Wisconsin Cheddar and Scallion fries and they were amazing I took one of my buddies who was visiting from Tampa Fla and he thought this place was Heaven I would recommend DMK to anyone coming from out of town or local I might have my wedding reception here hahah1010

Author: Jessica H.
Content: Get the sweet potato fries with the lemon tobasco aioli and know that youve found heaven  Pair that with the 2 chili rubbed onion strings chipotle ketchup and amish blue cheese and youve got yourself an amazing take on the traditional burger and fries  I just wish I had tried the fried pickles and okra to round out my meal  We had a great time here with great craft beer and delicious burgers  It was fairly easy to get a table but we were here on a Sunday at an off time  Our server was great and everything was cooked perfectly

Author: Kristin S.
Content: If you want a gourmet fantastic burger that you dont have unhinge your jaw to eat look no further Im stopping just short of saying DMK is my new favorite burger place in Chicago but Im pretty sure theyve taken the crown We went on a Saturday night so yes there was a wait No big deal for us at all We just went down the street to have a couple beers at a less crowded establishment I would say that I probably would have preferred to sit at DMKs bar with their interesting beer and soda lists so next time Ill come early or on a week night to avoid the crowdsThe atmosphere is fun and lively with a great beer list and an amazing burger menu that includes about 8 different burgers so you can be sure to find something fun without being overwhelmed by a laundry list of options The french fry list is also fun to peruse and at 2 for a healthyportioned single order why not try them all We went a little overboard and ordered a burger and fry for each person plus an order of the mac  cheese I had the Italian burger which had pesto fontina cheese roasted peppers and salt  vinegar potato chips Yep chips on the burger It was marvelous All the toppings stayed put while I shoveled it in So fantastic I also tried a bite of the burger with the peppers and the fried egg Also delicious but I think my Italian was just a tiny bit better The parmesan truffle fries are a must but the sweet potato fries with their citrusy dipping sauce seriously rocked my world With so much food we couldnt even touch the mac  cheese but it was cheesy and delicious heated up for lunch the next day so I can only imagine what it would have tasted like fresh crisp and bubbling from the oven Overall it was a great dining experience with helpful service gourmet burgers and unbelievably cheap prices for the quality of food you receive Im already trying to find a time to head back

Author: Shaun S.
Content: Finally got a chance to visit DMK this evening My wife and I were in the city for an appointment and timed it just right Ive been to Kumas and this is a much more enjoyable environment quieter and less snarkyThe burgers were much more reasonably sized I got the 5 an Italian themed with proscuitto roasted red pepper fontina and basil pesto Nice bun great flavor throughout  My wifes taste are tomato and ketchup only yeah I know We added the salt and cracked pepper fries very nice fries crisp and full of flavor I dont want to know how many calories I consumed Our server was great helpful and explained all our options very well My wife has already given the go back thumbs up

Author: John S.
Content: Ate some deviled eggs and Fried Okra and dill pickles DelishHad the Bison burger I was kinda bummer there wasnt a pretzel bun but got over itWashed it down with a Great Lakes Dortmunder Gold Lager Starched it up with Parmesan truffle cream fries and Amish blue and smoked bacon friesThen washed all that down with a Vanilla Espresso Buttershake I felt like a millon bucks after a visit here

Author: Molly L.
Content: Ive been to DMK 4 or 5 times and every time Ive been very satisfied with my overall experienceDrinks They have a great list of beers to choose from and they make their own pop which is greatSides The parmesean and truffle french fries are my favoriteThe Burgers Amazing Truly the main event at DMK The quality of beef is excellent Ive also had the turkey burger which is very flavorful The combination of toppings is sometimes surprising goat cheese and blueberry bbq sauce but you can trust that the chef knows what hes doing No substitutions are accepted but you can leave off a topping if you want Did I mention that they run between 811 Practically a steal for such a highquality mealOverall DMK is a great place to grab a fantastic burger and an offthebeatenpath craft beer for a very reasonable sum of money Minus one star for loud music and toodim lighting

Author: Sherry F.
Content: Seriously the best fries I have ever had Never been here before had a Tuesday off and stopped in for lunch The two of us had the deviled eggs app split a small cheddar and scallion fries he had a 1 burger and I had mac and cheese 2  All of it just great  The deviled eggs were like a perfect spring picnic  About the fries I really hate to over exaggerate something but both my husband and I said almost simultaneously best fires I have ever had Our server pretty sure it was Jack was exactly what you want in a casual place like this Super helpful not at all cheezie no type of programed upsell type of dialog not that you would need to push their offerings  If I owned this place I would be glad to have this waiter representing itFood service and price all spot on I so will be back

Author: Gareth D.
Content: The pastramiReuben burger is great  the tasty salt and fat from the pastrami melts into the burger making it even more tender and mouthwatering The size of the burgers is very manageable which is appreciated and gives you a chance to try the fried picklesokra and some of their fries Im not a fan of the cheese sauce for the fries bc while it doesnt seem like real Wisconsin cheddar to me they were very responsive and informative about the wiener circle inspired recipe Service has been good Also discovered my absolute favorite beer here the Domaine Dupage by Two Brothers Yumm

Author: Doe L.
Content: I got a 4 burger based on some recommendations i found online The green chile was a little spicier than i had anticipated but the burger was rather yum The bread was super soft and felt very nicely proportioned to everything elseThe fries were DROOL we had the sweet potato and the parmesan Very opposite choices one sweet one rich and savory  but i enjoyed both of them a lot The cons of this place is that its very loud and the wait kind of long during busy hours Theres not a huge selection for the menu but they have some interesting things herewell worth checking out at least once more often if you live in the area and can come during slower timesNOTE show the waitress you checked into foursquare for a free small fry salt and pepper only i think

Author: Mike M.
Content: It was at the Chicago World Fair of 1893 that the hamburger made its American debut and has since become an undeniable precept of American cuisine However sometime between its introduction and 2009 something went terribly wrong Did you know a McDonalds burger comes from factory farms and is made from roughly 400 cornfed cows hopped up on antibiotics and then doused in ammonia to kill the crap literally GrossAlternatively if Ronald McDonald had grown up in Berkley California wearing Birkenstocks instead of clown shoes DMK is the type of burger place he would have opened The Lakeview burger joint a product of Michael Kornick mk and David Morton offers 9 intriguingly topped grassfed burgers priced at 8 though their uniqueness can be alienating The potato bun is a worthy delivery vehicle for the burger the texture against the juicy burger is exceptional and it doesnt disintegrate into your hands  who wants to fork and knife a burger My 3 favorite burgers2 ChiliRubbed Onion Strings Amish Blue Spicy Chipotle Ketchup4 Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg9 The Patty MeltCondiments align with the establishments food philosophy and are all housemade Kornicks signature parmesan truffle fries from mk also make an appearance on the menu and are highly addictive While the bar is committed to craft beer and offers customers straightforward descriptions the 6 taps and 26 bottles do not rotate  perhaps my only knock against the place Overall come here for a burger made with ethically and sustainably raised beef and wash it down with a decent craft beer No reservations

Author: Diana P.
Content: Sorry DMK you did not do it for me  With that said Im a vegetarian so I had the veggie burger which was yuckyway too many means and you can taste them with every bite  The thin onion rings were greasy and the fried ocra and picklesdont both  My husband had the most popular rated burger and he wasnt blown away but said it was just good  This is one of those places weve been wanting to try for a long time but will not be backService was great barlike atmosphere however food needs to go up a notch Def better places like this in the city

Author: Adam S.
Content: OK with a couple caveatsIts a little disheartening when the fries are better than the burgers We were a larger group 5 so we got two large orders of fries the WI cheddarscallions and the amish bleubacon both of which were outta this freakin world Id srsly come back there just for the fries they were amazing in every way possibleThe burgers were good but nothing too special Also they call themselves a burger bar but only allow you to have you burger cooked medium w grass fed beef That knocks a star off for certain It was also loud as fck inside we were in the back and it was nigh on impossible to hear conversation at a normal volume cue yelling the entire time we were in there Thats not a big deal for me perse its just a little annoying when youve got outta town pals want to show them a cool place youve heard about but never been to and you cant freaking talkAll in all good Id like to come back but theres no way Im going to wait for an hour not even for those fries

Author: Randy R.
Content: Have you ever had the pleasure of being served an amuse of french fries with two dipping sauces Wisconsin cheddar and truffle aioli  If you answered no then you need to make your way here because this place is the perfect blend of comfortable cuisine with playful upscale twists Food was almost uniformly excellent the one exception was that neither I nor my wife cared for the homemade ketchup at all which is saying something because my wife might love ketchup more than me Very nice beer list provides perfect accompaniments to the food and help cut through the richness Finally friendly and professional service was on point

Author: Rachel Z.
Content: I always have trouble giving 5 stars to a restaurant because a dining experience is never perfect in my opinion  We found parking right in front of DMK burger bar which was great because we could see our dog who we left in the car from the windowI rarely review parking availability because I travel solely by the CTASo we sat down and ordered a couple of their house made sodas careful no free refills here so you will be charged for each soda  But the sodas are great tasting and worth the costWe tried the sweet potato fries and the fries served with truffle sauce which I did not enjoy but I LOVE SWEET POTATO fries  I enjoyed a burger all burgers are cooked medium temperature  with bbq sauce fried onions and bacon my favorite burger and it was cooked to perfection  We came here with a large group and everyone enjoyed their dining experience  We even got a free carrot cake cupcake  Yum yum yum  The tab was 80 for 5 people   Nicely done DMK I will be back

Author: Borracho G.
Content: When did the upscale burger craze start Just glad to see that there are more options popping up to go get a tasty burger other than Kumas I mean Kumas is good but its almost become a Chicago point of interest with its wait times DMK is definitely a hipper joint with good tunes playing continuously and the menu is straight forward with good bar options While Kumas burgers are bigger in size DMK offers some unique side items that make up for their smaller patties Deviled eggs being one of those sides and a must to try if you dont mind eggs or reliving childhood memories when the fridge was full of them after Easter at least in my childhood Another awesome side that  I tried was the wasabi coleslaw so simple and yet the kick in the ass that coleslaw always needed The fries are great and I swear are made in a nonvegan way by cooking them with some kind of animal fat like Hot Doug fries Oh if you couldnt tell by now this is not a place to start of a diet My only negative about the place is that you cant choose how you want your burger cooked and no substituted toppings so your forced to choose their custom creations You can take off toppings though like leaving the fried egg off since you may have had 3 deviled eggs alreadyI did give this place a extra star because the green chile they used on the 4 burger comes from Hatch NM and if you know about Hatch chile then you know its some of the best tasting green chileTo sum it up I say give this place a try and if you dont want to wait then go fairly early because they do not take reservations It will get packed and when it does the waitresses though cute and spunky start to be less attentive and forgetful

Author: nicole h.
Content: Hungover  This is your spot  Itll fill up your tummy with classic bar goodnessand youll be inspired to live again because of the FREAKING FRENCH FRIESYou can tell the dude in the kitchen knows his stuff  The menu presents burger after burgereach as unique as the next  They can tailor your pick if youre a noncarnivore and their veggie patty is awesome  The milkshakes are PERFECTbut oh my GOD the FRIES  Get the parmesan fries with the truffle sauce  Im in love  I think everyone whos had them is tooJust one request DMKif youre listeningplease put a special twist on the bloody mary  Its goodbut I KNOW you can do it up right

Author: Meghan P.
Content: So you want to have a good burger well Id say its a pretty DARN good one  I went during the week and we still had to wait a good half hour to get seated  We did however enjoy some choice beers at the bar while we waited  The place can get a bit crowded but only due to popularity  Service was mediocre our bartender was knowledgable of beers and a pleasure to chat with  Our waitress seemed a little overwhelmed and not as helpful as we woulda liked since we hadnt been there beforeBurger quality was good a few unique choices made it difficult to choose from in a good way of course  Fries were by far the highlight they are ordered a la carte and they have some unique choices for toppingsseasonings  Overall its pretty good negative things that make it lose a star or me coming back is the wait overall atmosphere is a little too wrigleyville and Id rather wait any day for Kumas  Sorry doesnt measure up

Author: Anna P.
Content: My search for the best burger and brew place in Chicago recently brought me to DMK the last place on my list of the most popular and talked about joints in the Second City Overall I had a great experience The beer list was excellent  on the rec of the bartender I tried a fantastic beer Id never heard of called Brother Theolonius The service was good  our waitress was attentive but not annoying and everything was as we asked for itThe atmosphere is sparse and a bit industrial but comfortable and its convenient to the Red and Brown lines The food was decent  I had a turkey burger with horseradish arugula and tomatoes and my boyfriend had the lamb burger greek style In general I wasnt super excited about anything on the menu but the burger was good and juicy and the price is right 8 We also split two orders of fries sweet potato my usual favorite and parmesan with truffle cream I was a little disappointed with the fries I think the ones at the Counter are much better Id go back if I were in the neighborhood but since I live downtown if I truck all the way out to this area again Ill prob just end up at Kumas AGAIN Yes its a sickness

Author: Pascal M.
Content: I dont know if I can give a burger join less than 4 stars The best I can do is explain WHY I gave this one 4 stars The restaurants cool nice lighting and pretty chill The bars long so a few friends and i took a seat and ordered some craft beerProps for having a decent craft beerlist The selection of burgers is great a solid bouqet of combinations The french fry options are nice and different so everyone can get something else My only quarrel with the burgers were that the patties were a bit thin I like my burger between rare and medium This particualr patty is one I would order rare since its thin enough to simply sear quickly on each side to meet my personal preferance of texture Other than that its a great choice to bring some friends to pregame catch a meal after a ball game or just get a good burger without a long wait

Author: Christina F.
Content: Yummmmmo Marie was our server and she was awesome Exceptional service great recommendations and fast Try the vanilla ginger soda We started with fried pickles and okra then moved to the 4 and 9 with a side of blue cheese and bacon fries We will be back

Author: Rouzhna N.
Content: Good burger spot especially if youre a loadsofdifferentingredientsonyourburger kind of fellow The parmesan truffle fries are good I was actually surprised when the fries just came out with truffle oil not actually fried with it MMMM and maccheese is muy bueno They also have a good drinks menu This place is nice for getting together with friends for beer and burger their kitchen is open late which is really nice

Author: Amanda G.
Content: Went to DMK Burger Bar the week it opened but just getting to writing the review    I enjoyed the atmosphere of the place and luckily we just got here before the rush turned into an 15 hr wait  Its good but I wouldnt wait that long for itWe had the Green Chile Burger w Fried Egg and 2 Burger with onions and spicy chipotle ketchup   Out of the two the green chile burger was by far my favorite  The fried egg on top made a great combo with the other ingredients I thought that DMK beer selection was amazing They had some great options on the menu to try although the table next to us recommended us not to get the martinis because the size of the martini was small with an 11 price tagAlso got the sweet potato fries Not my favorite sweet potato fries ever in fact thought they were too salty for my tasteAll in all you can get a good burger here so try it

Author: John W.
Content: Ive criticized other burger joints for throwing exotic toppings on a bun just to be the crazy burger place DMK doesnt do that Everything on the burger is made to enhance the meat and its good eat to start withA lot of people complain about the noisy space Im almost deaf thanks to a wellspent youth but everyone Ive eaten with says its true I didnt noticeMaybe I was just in a good mood tonight but everyone from the host to the waitress was completely crushworthy

Author: Frank L.
Content: HIGH expectations not metAll burgers 8 with a 3 option to double up The triple deck burger is 11most french fries comes in 2 single serve or 4 table sizeI ordered the 1 bacon aged cheddar balsamic vinaigrette sauteed onions and bbq sauce Upon first bite the meat and bun were perfect However something was really lacking from this bbq bacon cheeseburger The aged cheddar was barely noticeable But when you tasted it it tasted like aged cheese The bacon strips were two thick and when you bit into a piece you couldnt bite through it because it was so thick The onions failed to offer anything positive to the burger Onions on a burger is such a simple concept but by making the onions gourmet and sauteed in some balsamic vinaigrette made the onions way too sweet in conjunction with the bbq sauce call me crazy but i would have loved some large raw onion rings on this burgerMy fiance had a crispy portobello sandiwch Crispy here means the portobello was battered and deep fried One bite and you get a myriad of flavors but you also get a distinct taste of deep fried oil because the mushroom has so much room to soak up that oil After a few bites it can be tough to stomach the oilyness of this sandwichWe tried the salt and pepper seasoned fries with spicy ketchup and the sweet potato fries with lemon aoli Both were good The lemon aoli was sweet and surprising It is one of those things that you dont want to eat on a french fry but once you dip it you just want to keep dipping againThe ambiance was too much for us The music was blaring so loud in the barlike atmosphere that we could barely hold a conversation because we were screaming what did you say at each other all nightthe house sodas I would avoid I thought a cherry homemade soda would be really great  but it tasted like fizzy cough syrup The waitress kindly switched it with a blood orange soda but it wasnt all that much betterCheck out DMK burger ifyou want your burgers more gourmet than extra value and you want fries that can withstand even the fiercest french cuisineSkip the DMK for the MCDs ifyou prefer your 8 to get your more than a burger and want to be able to enjoy your meal without shouting to your dinner companions how fancy your food tries to be

Author: Christine M.
Content: The burgers in this place definitely live up to the name of it if youre going to have Burger in the title of your restaurant you better have a darn good one Lo and behold it was fabulous I had the BBQ Burger cant remember the name and split an order of the BaconBleu Cheese Fries I have never tasted something so heartattack inducing delicious Im not sure what they do to the Bleu Cheese but somehow its turned into almost a sauce on top of the fries I could have just eaten a bowl of thatAtmosphere is good seems more conducive to smaller groups or daters Service was also good I was a bit surprised and a tad annoyed that they dimmed the lights down as much as they did was difficult to see my food they were so low But bonus points for having EXCELLENT music taste and playing really great nonmaintream tunes Not once did I hear Lady Gaga  props to that DMK Burger Bar

Author: Not Eileen R.
Content: Really expected more  love mk so why not dmk burger bar Heres whysome creative combos some run of the mill  I had the lamb burger with taziki  good not greatMy husband had something with bacon  it looked very fast foodfries are a la carte thats fine  but no onion rings whatno fountain pop  no free refills boothe service  I get it this place is minutes from DePaul get ready for itim about to be an ageist but does my waitress have to look 17yr old  This has a hot spot feel why have minors working hereIm a big carnivore so I want my burgers big and juicy  Not some wimpy over worked flat patty  idk  Maybe I was in a bad mood the weather was crappy the day I went  I will try again solely for my love of mk but seriously you know there have to be expectations ie Daniel Bouloud has a burger and the salivation starts just at the look of it not here  Its really good but my socks were still on my feet if you get my drift

Author: Amy H.
Content: I think my hopes were too high for DMK I truly have no active complaints the beer list is fantastic the space is comfortably chic and the food is great But for some reason I walked away feeling meh I ordered the first burger on the menu which includes barbecue sauce onions bacon and cheddar We also ordered a side of the famous truffle fries Everything was delicious but I thought the burger could have had a larger patty fatty coment and been a little juicier Id had the truffle fries at the MK restaurant a few years back and this lessexpensive version lived up to those memories Id definitely return to DMK to try one of their more creative burgers Ive especially heard amazing things about the greekinspired 10

Author: Kyle P.
Content: 45 but would be a 5 star if the crowd was different and it cost just a little lessGreat burger and the bun is off the hook  I actually like the fact they are not 34 lb burgers like everywhere else i go  The service is nice but a little bit of a wait because of douche bags love this place because red eye and chicago magazine rate it and the 25 year olds come runninggood food try it and you will be able to go out after instead of rolling home like most of the killer burger places i go to

Author: Andi M.
Content: Solid burgers grass fed beef turkey lamb veggie and portobello I have had 6 of the 14 ways to have the burger and so far no disappointment   I loved the number 11 turkey with roasted chiles The parmesan truffle fries are great They blood orange soda is great as well  Young crowd but who cares sit at the bar and talk and have a good meal Most nights during the week they are not busy   I ate here 4 times in one week  I never do that This is a burger place  Love it for what it is   Good meat consistently good service and great beerwine selection  Simplicity and deliciousness Oh its LOUD  But I dont care

Author: Jackie L.
Content: Best burger Ive ever eaten and I mean itHad the DMK 6 marinated portabello blue brie griddled scallions dijonaise topped with an egg with a side of parmesan truffle cream fries

Author: Katie M.
Content: Not worth the hype at allIt was okay  Average beer list  Decent crowd  Decent burgers but nothing at all to write home about  For some reason it bothered me that my 8 burger was served on an appetizer plate  I sort of like the idea that you can buy fries separately but I felt sort of cheatedIf this were an upscale burger place in say the middle on nowhere Iowa it would be topnotch  But in a city with a place like Kumas or Urban Burger Bar on Halsted save you money and go to a place where youll be totally blown away

Author: Kim A.
Content: DO go here if you dont mind waiting over an hour for a table enjoy cheese fries appreciate delicious beers and yummy cocktails are not on a diet or dont mind breaking your diet do not mind being kinda sorta smushed and not in the Jersey Shore way in a booth or tableDO NOT go here if you get cranky waiting are not comfortable with consuming mass amounts of fried foodred meat need a giant plate for your meal are on a dietCame here with a group of 5 on a Saturday evening so yes we had to wait While it isnt the ideal situation its a reality of going to a really popular place on a Saturday When we were finally seated it was a little tight but not too bad Our server was friendly and the service was prompt The burgers were good not great Not Kumas I question some of their combinations I also think I made the mistake of ordering mine turkey I guess I should have gone with the beef I had the 2 which is Chili Rubbed Onion Strings Amish Blue Spicy Chipotle Ketchup like I said not Kumas Also someone had the bison burger and said it was delicious next time I think Ill try thatBut the fries oh wow Cheddar and scallion fries I repeat CHEDDAR AND SCALLION FRIES Get them Devour them Maybe share but you dont have to It was a fun place for sure I think its best for coming in later ordering food and lingering and enjoying all their cocktails Ill be back but still waiting to be wowed by a burger

Author: Karyn K.
Content: So DMK has certainly upped the ante since I last reviewed The 9 is my favoriteThe beer list is fantastic and if youd like the cap from your Magic Hat 9 they can make that happen Mine last night was you get what you give so dont forget to live Thanks to the bartender and waitress that got that to me because its an awesome capThe fries are delicious and so are the shakes Fun place to have in the neighborhood

Author: Sid V.
Content: Decent place good burgers and fries and a solid beer list  Younger crowd epitomizes the Lakeview neighborhood  So why only three stars  I feel similar such places like Burger Bar and Bad Apple transcend DMK in food slightly beer list variety esp Bad Apple atmosphere again only slightly and value  So Id go again for sure if nearby but wouldnt seek it out  Bonus points for offering a burger with Hatch peppers although it was really messy

Author: Sadat A.
Content: BOOM A solid top burger spot in the cityDMK Burger Bar you had me at HELLO with Gumball head on tapThe waitress was awesome that we had today very friendly and well educated on the menu She had a fun attitude that made our party feel comfortable  The menu was full of tasty creations that made it hard for me to choose from good thing Honestly I was looking for a burger that was unlike all the other burgers in the city At DMK I found that burger today The burger bun was perfectly made and different from other rolls I ordered the Big DMK and it was amazingly tasty The fries and tater tots were fantastic addition to the meal I was a little sad about the burger not coming with fries but it was cool Good beer selection on tap and bottles There cocktail menu is super bomb and well pricedI will be back soon

Author: caroline e.
Content: Geeze I couldnt believe how full this place was early on a Thursday evening They must be doing something right They had a great beer menu but some of it was a tad overpriced IMO The food was really good but not all great I liked the mac  cheese the one with the bacon A LOT and those fried pickles were super tasty too We couldnt decide which fries to order but eventually went with the sweet potato  so good The waitress had told us that the cheddar cheese were her fave and ended up sending us a small plate of them on the house That was really above and beyond and much appreciated All in all I liked the place but prob wouldnt go out of my way to eat here Definitely stop by if you are in the area though

Author: Audrey W.
Content: Three words SWEET POTATO FRIES OMG the sweet potato fries are probably the best I have ever eaten Lemon aioli dip makes it even better Perfect to pair with a nice cold beer and a good burger It is a little too loud in the burger bar but it seems to be the trend around Chicago My buddies also didnt enjoy their burgers as much as I enjoyed my green chile fried egg bacon burger YUM

Author: Kelli A.
Content: We had lucky timing My hubby and I showed up tonight and it was almost completely packed There were 2 spots left We chose the spot at the end of the bar Shortly after we were seated a crazy number of people were there waiting for tables This place definitely gives off more of a bar than a restaurant feel but dont be fooled because the food is quite tasty I got the bison burger with fresh goat cheese pickled red onions and blueberry bbq sauce Cooked to perfection all of these flavors mixed very well together It was so good I would definitely order this again My hubby went with the beef burger with chilifried onions amish blue and spicy chipotle ketchup It was a solid burger It was cooked perfectly and the chipotle ketchup was delicious almost like bbq sauce We shared a large order of the amish blue and smoked bacon fries These were super tasty The melted blue cheese was a perfect match for the bacon and fry combo They have a great selection of beers and spirits Their bottled beer list definitely caters to the American craft brew palette We had good service We were seating quickly approached rather soon and every time our drinks were almost empty the waitress appeared

Author: Melanie H.
Content: DMK Burger BarThe next time I am in Chicago you can count on me to seek you out for another good buirger  brew ps I hope you rotate your beers on tapSo let me take a couple of steps back and tell you Yelp readers why I love DMK Burger Bar I was in Chicago a couple weeks back and was looking for a place within walking distance of my hotel where I could have something tasty with a couple of good local brews I stumbled upon DMK burger bar looked at the beer list and thought Not only do they have midwestern brews on tap but they also have Allagash Must be good I took a seat at the bar and ordered myself a turkey burger which came with free fries and started with Half Acres Daisy Cutter Pale Ale it was hoppy but not too much that it overpowered my turkey burger After I finished my turkey burger I had a nice conversation with the bar tender about various craft brews I was impressed with how knowledgeable he was about craft brews nationwide After a couple of complimentary samples I told the bar tender that I wanted to try something else that was local that I would not be able to get on the east coast he said ill pour you something that i know you will like His pick was Two Brothers French Country Ale It was rockinI went to the Allagash brewery in Portland ME the following week and since then have been telling every craft beer connoisseur about this new and upcoming brewery out of Warrenville IL called Two Brothers Im even following them on TwitterWindy CityDMK Burger BarLincoln Park Two Brothers winning

Author: Sandy N.
Content: Went for dinner with some friends a few weeks ago on a Wednesday night The annoying thing was that we were waiting for one more person out of a group of 4 and the hostess wouldnt seat us And 60 of the tables were empty WTF Anyway it turns out the 4th person was just sitting at the bar so then we got seated a minute later But seriously though that was lameWe all ordered different burgers and cut them into quarters to share We had the bison burger the big DMK triple decker the aged chedder burger 1 and the crispy portabello I definitely liked the bison and the crispy portabello was really good especially texturewise We also tried the deviled eggs and the sweet potato and truffle fries They have a loyalty card I will never spend enough to get anything Other than that DMK is good for groups and burgerlovers alike

Author: Angelica S.
Content: Went here for dinner with a few friends I was really a fan It is very different from Kumas so dont compare the two The portions are smaller and they also have bison burgers pretty good must try But the style of their food is different in a good wayI do love the fries We had the blue cheese and bacon ones and the other were I think parm cheese with truffle cream We got the second ones for free We were debating which to get and went with our first choice Our server came out with both What a doll I love places that do stuff like thatThey have a nice beer selection A lot of beers Ive never heard of but I love trying something new Definitely need to come back to try some other burgers I really enjoyed mine

Author: Annie K.
Content: Got the number 4 It was a decent burger but didnt exactly bring tears or anythingWhat WAS amazingly orgasmic though was their pineapple basil soda Oh my le drool My prior beverage obsession was Native Foods lavender lemonade but thats starting to look like an old ex you want to forget The pineapple basil soda has a very strong basil flavor but I love that Pieces of freshly ground basil and sweet pineapple with a tiny bit of fizziness Super refreshing especially when youre eating a greasy burgerOh andI did find a hair in my cheese fries which was doubly gross because it was all stringy with cheese but the manager seemed very apologetic and took that right off our tab and gave us 2 drink cards Meh It happens I guessIts also nice that they have smaller portions available for fries so you can try a bunch of different ones

Author: Gigi Y.
Content: Absolutely love this place Cant go wrong with great quality burgers and astounding fried pickles and sweet potato fries Their parm fries are good but too much parmesan and saltiness for my likingFirst time I tried DMK i got their grassfed lamb burger with feta  Tzatziki sauce amazing Its like having a gyro in a burger duh At any rate it was delicious My boyfriend had the Bison burgerblueberry BBQ sauce Enough saidNext round I got the 4 although Im a bit of a health freak this burger didnt stop me and it was sure well worth it The smoked bacon cuz bacon makes everything better and roasted green chile was ridiculously awesomeWhat can I say 4 starsYay Im a fan indeed

Author: Matt K.
Content: The atmosphere in this place is awesome the seating is interesting and almost forces you to meet people The long table where everyone shares a seat reminded me of something like a beirgarten Friendly people good conversation and great foodbeer is what youll find hereThe sweet potato fries are amazing and the portobello mushroom burger is fantastic The pattie for the burger was very tastyThe servers are nice and the vibe is chill This is a must go place for tourists like myself If only to get a flavor of Chicagos hipster culture

Author: Kevin N.
Content: My girlfriend and I went on a random Tuesday evening The service was great and the food was even better I ordered the Veggie burger 15 and my girlfriend the the Greek burger 11 we think Both were extremely good and pretty unique We plan on going back to try many other things on the menu that caught our eye I strongly recommend

Author: Megan A.
Content: Food is so delicious 7 is a juicy big DMK burger that is well worth the 12 The truffle cream sauce with the Parmesan fries are awesomeI would definitely recommend going hereThe only thing I wasnt too thrilled with was that it was too loud you had to scream to talk to someone

Author: Heather K.
Content: Turkey burger was awesome Truffle fries were fantastic  Cupcakes were OKIll be back

Author: Tu'ens N.
Content: They make really good burgers and they are 850 which these days isnt too expensive for fancy burgers half the price of rocket whose burger tastes like the embodyment of 2007 cheap Chinese truffle oil  They are also kind of thin which I really like  The buns are really good  soft and fresh  The fries are also superb  With various toppings I tried the blue cheese something and the salt  pepper w home made ketchup  And they too come in pretty small sizes also come in larger ones  so for 2 or 3 per type you can get a couple of different types and not end up with a lunch bag full of fries like at Five Guys

Author: Irena A.
Content: I went to DMK bar on a Friday night around 8 I was so happy that we did not have to wait to be seated I wanted to try DMK because I wanted to compare it with the counter And also because the reviews on yelp were pretty good My fiancé ordered the number 4 and he said he loved it He really praised the bacon also I ordered the veggie burger which left me kind of disappointed The patty was fried and very greasy On a better note we shared the mac and cheese and that was perfectly creamy and cheesy We ordered to small sides of fries and they were OK The sweet potato fries were not all that and the Parmesan ones just had Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top Kind of bland Service was OUTSTANDING The waitress brought us a survey to complete and I really liked the sense of humor they used in creating the questions We will definitely return

Author: E F.
Content: Forget the yuppiehipster atmosphere the only thing thats truly AMAZING about this place is the fact that they serve grassfed burgers and their onion straws THE best sht ever promise In addition Im happy that they have decent cheeses Wisconsin cheddar hello the fries for those who like the friesI dont and some decent beer selections However at the end of the day this is nothing but a burger place and theres better options out there who happen to not attract yuppie asshles by the way BUT DMK is at least trying and headed in the right direction with their grassfed burgers

Author: Matt M.
Content: DMK Burger Bar is a crowded popular place that says theyre a burger place  While they do have some marginally innovative burgers I think that the place is a 3star joint  Pros great beer selection fantastic fries parmesan with truffle cream and sweet potato with tobasco aioli  Decent burgers if very small  The portions on the sides make up for the smaller burgers a bit thoughCons there werent really any but given the hour wait at 8pm on a Thursday there are definitely places Id rather go  Summary Undoubtedly worth a try but not the return trip and dont wait too long for a table

Author: Jessica G.
Content: Sterile atmosphere mediocre food and sweet potato fries fried in beef fat  No thanks  My partner and I arrived before the rest of our table and so we were asked to sit at the bar  Usually completely understandable but seeing as the restaurant was more than half empty this seemed a little strange  We both ordered a beer and when I asked if the total could be added to our tables bill I was met with some attitude  So we paid our tab  That was that   I ordered the sw black bean burger and chili rubbed onion strings  All just average  Clumps of my onion stings were not properly friedwho wants wet batter in there basket  Not me  It is pretty obvious that the veg options here are an afterthought  The only plus was our great waitress  She was well versed on the menu  treated our table to free fried pickles and had a great attitude

Author: Shakeia T.
Content: DMK  delicious mmmm insert your own k word When I first walked in I wondered if the D in DMK stood for dimly lit This place is very cool but it was just really dark Like strainyoureyestoreadthemenu dark The burger choices are great but they do not allow substitutions You can have items removed from your burger but you cant switch it It clearly states it on the menu So if you dont like the cheese on your burger you cant switch to a different one I know I asked  Substitutions aside the burger  small fries was a great filling portion I also really liked the drink selection DMK is definitely a cool trendy burger spot

Author: Jen S.
Content: Nice burger choices with quality ingredients Took out a star because they dont allow substitutions You can remove items from the burger but you cant switch it with something else The portions are fine A few have complained about small portions but seriously I think its because everyones used to gigantic portions in this country Anyway I recommend the Parmesan truffle fries Nice drink selection I feel that Kumas has better burgers though

Author: Justin G.
Content: The burgers are pretty delicious  There were a few more things on the menu that I want to go back and try them  Of course I cant remember exactly what those are or what was even on the burger I ate but thats mostly because their burgers have numbers instead of names and therefore make them difficult to recall  The beer selection was good  Not as good as Kumas or the Bad Apple but better than say The CounterSome of the seating is a little close for my tastes but that seems to be standard now when youre only dining with one other person  Enjoyed it will go again and probably enjoy it againAfter Kumas DMK is 2 for my Chicago burgers  And number 2 to Kumas is not a bad place to be at all

Author: Bonnie L.
Content: Had the everpopular 4 which has bacon green chile and fried egg served up on a pillowsoft bun I really enjoyed it though my heart probably didnt  Also had the truffle fries which were good too We were there on a Wednesday and the place was packed They looked like they were understaffed so the service was slowOn a side note I dont get why people are so hung up on not being able to customize their orders Its a burger not world peace If you want your burgers done your way go to Burger King

Author: Mark F.
Content: Great burgers and fries  I had the lamb burger 11 and it was wonderful  We got two large orders of fries for the table and loved them  Got the Wisconsin Cheese and sweet potato fries  YumThe only problem I had which is a personal preference was that I ordered a diet Coke and it came in a can  When I go to a restaurant I usually expect a fountain Coke which is always a treat  If I wanted cans of Coke Id just open one up at homeGood night now

Author: Claudia C.
Content: I was here on a Friday evening from about 7309 and had a great experience We didnt have to wait at all got a table well end of one for 6 of us and were wellwaited on by a kind staff Their beer selection is very good if not a tad overpriced but for the quality of beer I cant complain too muchThe winners of the night were definitely THE FRIES All of them We had the truffle oilparmesan fries the sweet potato fries and the onion strings sure technically not fries They were all amazingThe burgers were pretty good Nothing to write home about but quality ingredients and interesting combos If DMK werent so far from the South Loop I would probably be here a lot more

Author: Melissa S.
Content: I just came home from watching one of my favorite bands play at the Vic Correction Having missed most of performance by one of my favorite bands playing at the Vic and spending the time instead in their basement bathroom barfing up my dinner I just came home Reason DMK Burger Bar WTF How much grease is in this burger The bun was soaked through the center when I got it I have weathered grease before I am no stranger to it But alas my tummy and my love for this band were no match for the stomach wrecking destructionAnd yes I have been perfectly fine all the day No sickness nothing And the only booze I had was hey my beer from DMK But two stars because we had the bestest bartenderserver lady Super friendly super patient and super fast without being disingenuous Now all we need to work on is that ridiculously expensive stuff you guys dish out A friend and I got between us a large fry plate two burgers all 8 and 2 beers paid 34 without tip Really guysEDITBoy says Any place that does NOT ask you how you want your burger done I mean Come on

Author: Julia R.
Content: amazing burgers  im a fan of burgers that arent 30 inches thick  so this place is perfect for me They have a large selection of burgers including veggie if thats youre thing   Ive tried a few of their fancy burgers but overall my favorite is their classic plain ole cheeseburger  It pretty much blew me away for some reason  There is something to be said when you can take a very classic thing and execute it perfectly  Ive never had to wait for a table here  but maybe ive not been in at peak times  The servers are really nice and very attentive  and food always comes out fast  Decor inside is trendy and music selection is always awesomeLast time I went I tried their ice cream cookie sandwiches  yum  i will be doing that againOh yeah  GRAVY FRIES GRAVY FRIES GRAVY FRIES  so good  so so good

Author: Jill S.
Content: This place was hoppin It was a Friday night my boyfriend and I came to DMK We got seats at the bar until our table was ready At the bar we ordered beers unfortunately they were out of the heffeweizen I wanted to try but alagash was a great substitute and the mac and cheese DO get the mac n cheese seriously great stuff thereWe were seated pretty quickly Tables are close together and its real loud in there so you will find yourself screaming across the table We both ordered burgers mine came with prosciutto and sea salt  vinegar chips which was real good I didnt realize however that there were chips both on my burger and on my side because I also ordered sweet potato fries Holy overload My boyfriends burger was a tad bit better than mine It had green chiles on it that gave it a nice kick A little disappointed that there are no choices when it comes to buns but the bun was fine The burgers are big not thick but big in circumference Maybe expected a little bit more Had wanted to try here for quite some time but the burger was just alright Think its the toppings that make it The service was great really nice people Seriously dont forget to order the mac n cheese though

Author: Kelly W.
Content: Listen since becoming a yelper I usually obsessively check up on a dining establish before for embarking on a food endeavor there This did not happen in this case A friend and I stumbled upon DMK and decided to give it a go for dinner We were pretty convinced it was new and had just opened but apparently its been around for just over a yearAnyway I wasnt really sure what we were in forWe grabbed some seats up at the bar and explored our dining options while enjoying some two brothers they have some great beers on tap btw After drooling over the options I decided to go with the 2 onion straws blue cheese variety and chipotle ketchup My friend did the 4 with the fired egg And we added an order of sweet potato fries for good measure I was digging the whole vibe of the place great old flicks on the tv and the BEST variety of tunes Seriously Al Green to Death Cab to Prince to Sting Swoon The burger was wonderful I love that they do they more diner style thin patties really showcases all the flavors accompanying the meat really well balanced The guy next to me at the bar must have noticed my revelry because he tapped my shoulder and asked if I could confirm if I was indeed eating the 2 I did and he confirmed what his order would be Oh and the sauce for the sweet potato fries was heavenly as in the fries could have merely been the vessel for the sauce to reach my mouth but the fires were great too in this caseReally satisfying food service and atmosphere Will definitely be back

Author: Mindy S.
Content: DMK on a Saturday night at 1030pm was so busy It certainly has become one of the neighborhood hangouts which I am happy to see since I was there about a year ago and they were closing early due to lack of patronsChicago Grass Fed beef is their deal and I have never had a bad burger here  The standout dishes are fries  get any of the fries just get them  the parmesean  truffle cream fries are mouth watering and any of the burgers particularly the 1 2 4  The specialty drinks are nothing short of great and I think their beer selection is worthy of a mentionI would definitely recommend DMK to get a fantastic burgerfries experience

Author: Claire M.
Content: It is truly rare I travel into Lincoln Park for well for anything but going for a burger odd move but my friend had been told it was great so f it why notThe environment was I guess what I would expect in lincoln park hip and trendy there was a big neon sign on the back wall that to be honest I dont recall what it said but I do recall looking at it and then wondering why but as stated before a burger joint in LP okee dokeeThe burger Thats the important thing Now i am a huge fan of Kumas I LOVE a good burger capital letters love my mouth drools And for the burgers to be grass fed  organic pretty much makes me swoon Red meat is not unhealthy people it can be exceptionally good for you i digressMy friend was starving and so we immediately put in an order for the mac  cheese 2 gruyere and bacon um uh huh this is awesomethen the burgers To be honest I was sort of hoping to have my burger jump off the page at me but I kept wanting to combine different burgers in the end I decided with our amazing waitresss helpI got the number 6 it had portabello and blue brie scallions and a dijonnaise  it was the perfect size it was perfectly cooked I was thrilledThe friend got i believe the 1 and it was devoured before I could suggest trying itHe also did the profoundly delicious thing of ordering a milkshake A peanut butter milkshake Now may I say holy shit Thats a really good milk shakeSo all  all I liked it Really good beer selection they have an AWESOME beer selection I only drink porters or stouts and they had several to choose from Im usually lucky if a place has guinness and they were mostly maybe all small breweries I was pleased and impressedSo I didnt like the decor it felt a little cold but man everything else was so very very worth the trip to an area I avoidwell doneOH and we were told hours later by the friend that suggested it the fries are insane so maybe 1 more trip to LP for some more burger Ill get some fries with that shake next time yeah I totally just said that ugh

Author: Andrew R.
Content: Generally dont go with a full 5 stars for a place like this but I thought the concept execution ambiance and food was perfect for a hipster burger joint in Lincoln Park  It was nothing fancy but it couldnt have met our expectations any better  Exposed brick chalkboard menu good music and a packed house at 2pm on a Saturday  The craft beer list was very impressive with many regional beers that are unavailable in STL  Dogfish Stone Aligash Two brothers and many more  They even had many Goose Island products that we can not get our hands on  It was packed but we were able to get beers and seated in a reasonable amount of time  The list of burgers was extremely impressive and the quality and taste were right on  I had the chili verde bacon and fried egg burger and was in heaven  It was messy but the bun held the contents in perfectly as to make it still enjoyable  My wifes bison burger with goat cheese and blue berry bbq sauce was exceptional as well  We had two different types of cheese fries for the table that were gourmet  One had blue cheese and bacon and the other came with melted age chedder and scallions  Thanks DMK cant wait to come back  Also thanks to Stone for making a great IPA  And thanks for being extremely affordable  Cheers

Author: Andrea B.
Content: I was hoping to write a review on a second visit but since I havent yet been back I have to get it out of the way and unfortunately it will be a bit biased but eh My boyfriend and I love a damn good burger so on our hunt for yummy burgers in Chicago we came here I was getting over a cold unfortunately so my mind and attitude werent completely down with the idea of eating red meat but I figured Id be fine as long as I could sit down right away and relax Wrong Why would I think that there would be empty seats on a Saturday night We stood awkwardly by the front door with a few other parties while we waited for tables  I was wobbly and really wanted some water in all respects I should have gone home but the plan was if we had to wait longer than 20 minutes or so we were gone ok fine We were actually seated in about 10 minutes near the corner of the restaurant If i werent sick i would have had some beer instead we got milkshakes which are thick and delicious and I totally recommend them if you arent of the beer persuasion I ordered a basic cheeseburger with bacon and we also ordered fries The food is meh the atmosphere is meh i couldnt hear a lot of what my boyfriend was saying because it was pretty noisy which was to be expected The burgers themselves arent tastebud explosive but in many respects they are good just not Kumas good sorryi have to compare almost everything to Kumas its like my standard for analyzing burgers Im hoping that if i return here Ill have a better update than this Well see maybe if I get some beer in me Ill be a bit more open to what DMK really has to offer

Author: Colt E.
Content: I had heard a lot of good things about DMK Only a few of those high hopes were met though First off I can say that DMK service does an excellent job of flipping tables and keeping the line of people to eat moving Our 20 minute wait went buy in a flash and the place was packed Our waitress was very friendly and even though there was a slight mix up she more than made up for it with a free dessert The beer menu is great and exactly what youd want at a burger placeBut on the the burgerThe menu wasnt quite as interesting to me as I had hoped but there were a lot of good choices I also applaud them for serving only grass fed beef and having turkey and veggie options However the burger patty was just so smallI feel like I could easily eat two burgers here I guess thats why theyre 8 If this place would double their patty size and increase the burger price a few bucks my rating would immediately jump up to 4 stars Oh wellback to Kumas I go

Author: Sonia L.
Content: Wow  How convenient that this is placed at this prime location  I came here drunk after the barand it was amazing  I am not saying that either because I was drunk  I really do think it was amazing  First of all our waitress Rene was adorable  Edward tried leaving his number for her but that went to shit  Anyway the Bison Burger with Goat Cheese is phenomenal and the Patty Melt with an egg on top looked good thanks for sharing Edward  We got sweet potato fries for the table which obviously were scrumptious  THEN  Then Raymond the manager chatted us up for awhile and gave us PB Vanilla milkshakes  Delicious  Cool  One time I will come here sober  Then maybe I can tell you a little something about the ambiance

Author: Sonal S.
Content: Holy burger  This place is amazing  Not only does this place offer grassfed beef burgers but you can get bison here too  I recently became a huge lover of bison  Its healthier for you and tastes so much better  My bf and I shared a couple burgers that were so fresh and clearly hand made  You can tell that the burger patties are made by hand  Picking a side proved to be difficult because they dont just give you an order of fries  You get to choose toppings  The parmesan  truffle oil fries were really good but the blue cheese and bacon fries were SO ridiculous  I couldnt stop eating them  We also got a mac  cheese that was to die for that had bacon and gruyere cheese YUMDMK also has an eclectic selection of beer to choose from  So for all you burger and beer lovers this is definitely a place you need to check out  I think it was also recently checked out by Guy Fieri  His signature was inked on one of the walls at DMK  Its has been Food Network approved

Author: Manuel F.
Content: Great service Gregg the bar tender took great careExcellent food too  I thoroughly enjoyed the lamb burger that was uniqueLooking forward to going back soon

Author: Genevieve S.
Content: Although I dont eat meat my husband and I love to check out burger places Until we went to DMK our favorite burger place was Captain Mikes in Kenosha they also sell grassfed beef DMK seems to have a gourmet edge The ingredients are purposeful and blend effortlessly without overpowering one another The veggie and grain burger is out of this world The fact that they sell grassfed beef burgers and organic foods when possible puts them head of other burger places automatically I love to support places that support sustainability

Author: Jason P.
Content: Walking in on a Tuesday and sitting at the bar is an easy way to make sure that this place is not crowded at all  Wearing Illini gear and talking to the bartender about the state of Illini sports got us a couple of free dishes as well even though my vegetarianism did not let me enjoy them  I went in knowing exactly what I wanted to order  Veggie burger with eggplant and a decent helping of fries was calling my name  The wrench was thrown in when the bartender informed me that the fries were made with beef fat  Disappointed I went for the mac and cheese as a consolation prize and it was ok  Either way I appreciated the heads up as well as the attempts at free food that my friend got down on

Author: Mike B.
Content: DMK Burgers  stands for Da Most Krunk Burgers  This one is certainly worthy of the 5 star rating  Great burgers fantastic sides good beer selection a hoppin crowd  My experience was nothing short of amazing  I am proud to add DMK to my definitive list of good burgersBurgers  I got the 1 my mom got the 8 yes I treat my mom to epic burger meals0 not to be confused with Epic Burger which makes crappy hamburgersBoth were really good  The 8 is your traditional burger but the 1 blew it away in my opinion  NOTE  both were on the spicy side  I LOVED this my mom didnt  Take note of it for what its worthSides  Got the Fried Onions and the Sweet Potato FriesThe Fried Onions were very thin onion rings fried to perfection  YOU MUST GET THEMThe Sweet Potato Fries were tasty and delicious  A lot of places dont get the recipe right and they end up being too sweet or tasting weird  DMK nails itAgain they were on the spicy side  I loved it my mom didntDrinksHuge list of beersLots of good craft beers on tapNo prices on the menu  I HATE THISAtmosphereThe place was packedEveryone was youngEveryone was having a good timeThe wait was 15 minutes Friday night 7pmI WILL be back

Author: Sibi J.
Content: Hands down this place is in the top 5 burger places in the city Generous portions great craft beer and incredible burgers What more can you ask for Since it is somewhat of a touristy area the parking is harder to get the service could use a little more attentiveness but apart from that this place rocksDefinitely worth a trip if you are in LP

Author: Dex Y.
Content: Impressed on my first visitOrdered lamb burger and Parmesan fries Satisfied The feta cheese in the burger definitely kicked it up a notch The patty was juicy and flavorful Buns were fresh and soft but not macerated The Parmesan fries was one of the best Id ever had Their food wasnt cheap at all but I feel its worth the pricesAfter a whole day of hangover I still remember the goodness I think that says something

Author: Matt B.
Content: Went here with a group of coworkers before we were going out for a night of drinking Got in early so they were able to seat our group of 8 pretty easily The place filled up incredibly fast after we sat down The staff were great and the service was quick This was one of the best burgers I have had I went with the champion formerly named the Kaner which is all based on Buffalo This thing was awesome Go get one Also the truffle fries were amazing Will be going back here soon

Author: Anne L.
Content: My hubby and I love this place It is right around the corner from where we live so super convenient and we have only taken it to go cause they are usually packed I always get the number 8 which is just an all American burger It is always cooked perfectly and the meat is so tender and juicy My husband on the other hand has ventured out and tried a few different burgers such as the number 5 the bison burger number 9 the patty melt number 11 the lamb and the number 14 the salmon He loved all of them and had no complaints Fries are great and the special ketchup they make is delish We love this place need to actually eat in sometime

Author: Suzanne H.
Content: GREAT food very good service wonderful ambianceI had the turkey burger hubs had the lamb burger  Both were great I liked mine better  Only turkey burger I have had that is better was the hubs made at home  It tasted like turkeynot some mash of mystery meatWe also had the fried pickles and okrathey were awesome  I love fried pickles  Very lightly fried almost tempura like  French friesvery goodOne of the best things was something I have never hadthe home made sodas  Hubs had a gingervanilla oneit was good  But I LOVED mineit was strawberrylemon and it was so refreshing  Wanted to try beer snow cone but didnt

Author: Sarah M.
Content: For my boyfriend and I the key to getting seated right away was to go on the really freezing snowy day last week at about 6pm However it did get packed shortly after we arrived Fairly small place but nice and cozy The TVs played fireplaceSomeone asked me why does the vegetarian go to the new burger joint Well they did have veggie options I went with the grainbased burger I did get it without tomato and eggplant but hi I do like lettuce That would have been a nice addition basic for burgers I thought The burger was decent the pesto mayo was tasty Meateating boyfriend loved his burger and was done before I was I like that you can get the french fry option as small portions or larger portions We chose to get two small portions 2ea which I felt were totally fine for both of us plus we got to try each others The sweet potato fries were fabulous and I dont even like sweet potatoes I had the parmesan fries Yay fries boo weird truffle sauce that accompanied The bar was good tasty mojito and a decentsized beer list for the beer drinking meat eating boyfriendBeware this does add up Two burgers two fries a beer and a mojito ended up costing us 50ish with tip included in thatBoyfriend and I will go back theres some mac and cheese waiting to be sampled by us both

Author: Alexander C.
Content: This is NO KumasI have to get that out there right now  If you are looking for the best hamburger please move on  Even with Kumas now seemingly cutting a few corners frozen patties it is still head and shoulders above this placeMaybe a bunch of under 25 kids from the sticks who just got to the big city think this is the best but hey there is a sucker moving here every day  Getting by on your name and the location of the business will only last so long  You will not be the new on the scene restaurant for longGrass fed beef is a nice change taste was good excellent bun it was AOK but not the best or even in the top ten  No soda refills is crazy  Serving your small gourmet burger on a 4 inch plate is funny  Tasty sweet potato fries  Two of us got out of there for 50 with two burgers the small sweet potato fries a soso vanilla shake and a couple of cocktailsI will say this after my visit  It made me want to visit Kumas again

Author: Justin R.
Content: After reading so much about this place my wife and I finally tried it last night  Its as good as advertised  The burgers were terrific as was the mac  cheese 1 and the salt and pepper fries although they had a bit too much pepper  Make sure to try the carrot cake cupcake and double chocolate ice cream sandwich if you have room Probably the only drawback is the wait but hey the place is good so its not a surprise and the volume  Youre pretty much yelling at each other when its crowded

Author: Unknown
