Content: The burgers in this place definitely live up to the name of it if youre going to have Burger in the title of your restaurant you better have a darn good one Lo and behold it was fabulous I had the BBQ Burger cant remember the name and split an order of the BaconBleu Cheese Fries I have never tasted something so heartattack inducing delicious Im not sure what they do to the Bleu Cheese but somehow its turned into almost a sauce on top of the fries I could have just eaten a bowl of that Atmosphere is good seems more conducive to smaller groups or daters Service was also good I was a bit surprised and a tad annoyed that they dimmed the lights down as much as they did was difficult to see my food they were so low But bonus points for having EXCELLENT music taste and playing really great nonmaintream tunes Not once did I hear Lady Gaga  props to that DMK Burger Bar

Author: Duane M.
Content: Walking in the place is darker than most burger joints but not clublike The atmosphere is comfortable enjoyable and well they were playing a muppets movie on the TVs I really enjoyed the decor and the hostess was really on the ballWe showed up at 630 on a Thursday and were seated immediately Our waitress Kelly was very prompt and courteous She wasnt flirty or using any of the classic waitress moves she was just genuine and pleasant which is refreshing Our drinks were delivered within a few minutes Speaking of drinks the beer selection isnt extensive but the beers they have are quality There wasnt a single beer on the menu I havent had but I have enjoyed each and every one in the past I might add a few to their list but theres nothing Id take off As for liquor they know their bourbon but they seem to neglect their scotch Not that theres anything wrong with that just not what Im used to seeingThe food ordering process was simple tip as of the time of this writing you get a free small order of fries if you check in on foursquare and well laid out One of the things that caught me off guard was that the waitress never asked how we want our burgers prepared Instead the came out somewhere between medium and medium well At first I was a little taken aback but then realized that this isnt your standard burger joint nor is it a steak house They know how their burgers are supposed to be made and each one is prepared to the chefs specs It may be a little arrogant but the burgers came out perfectly so they obviously deserve to be a little arrogantWe had three kinds of fries on the table  truffle fries sweet potato and cheddar Of the three the cheddar were my least favorite but they were still great The sweet potato fries were damn near perfect This place is a bit off the beaten path for my typical commute or night life but if I find myself in Lincoln Park and someone asks where to eat were going back to DMK

Author: Vicky L.
Content: Positioned between the Belmont and Fullerton train stops closest to the Wellington station actually DMK Burger Bar is a good place to go if you are looking for a solid bite before attending a show which is what my friend Brandon and I did yesterday evening For a burger bar the alcoholic beverages seem to dominate the burger selection so you get to choose among 14 burgers and I believe the small print at the bottom noted that subtractions but not substitutions were allowed There goes an opportunity for disappointmentFor me I had a pretty good time I enjoyed my fresh salmon burger with red Thai curry sauce and some other ingredients that I cant recall The sea salt fries with black pepper were very tasty The meal overall left me quite thirsty and Im glad I stuck with just water The atmosphere is obnoxious for its noise and it reminds me of the Clark and Addison intersection which I always keep out of as if its pollution The menu prices are not the friendliest8 every burger 28 fries I didnt look at the drinks But as someone who finds it difficult to eat fast or even finish overwhelming portions of food the size of the burger is easy to eat I like it Its worth returning back here once in a while but I would make sure youre going for the food not to enjoy any kind of conversation or anything Eat Pay Leave

Author: A.J. M.
Content: As far as the food and drinks go I was impressed I had the number 2 which I enjoyed very much even though I am not a big fan of bleu cheese But nonetheless it was an excellent burger but not the best burger Ive ever eaten Its hard to screw up sweet potato fries and DMK sure didnt cause they were tasty The beer list was pretty solid especially the tap selection I cant deny that I am more than happy to come back here and try their other burgers Im curious to see how good they are compared to the 2 So that being said I really enjoyed this place10172010 NOTE I have been here again The 1 was better than the 2 in my opinion Regardless I love that this place is close to my apartment And only 8 bucks a burger talk to me

Author: Lisa K.
Content: If I could give DMK 35 stars I would  Alas I do not think DMK is worthy of 4 stars so 3 it isIts not that I disliked the food at DMK  My burger the 8 was very tasty and just the right size so that I didnt feel stuffed  And the pickles were amazing  We ordered a round of every type of French Fry on the menu so that we could taste them all  The blue cheese fries are the way to go in my opinion  I had one of their homemade blood orange sodas  I had an ice cream cookie for dessert  The food was definitely tasty but not mindblowingly goodThe noise level is unbearable  At times I couldnt hear what the person across from me or the person next to me were saying  As the restaurant filled up the noise just got worse and worse as everyone in the restaurant was screaming  In addition to the horrible noise the lighting was so dark  Stupidly dark  Its OK to have enough light to read the menu DMKSo would I go back  Probably not  If I lived in Lakeview I would probably return to DMK if someone suggested it and I had no counter suggestions  However not living in Lakeview I wouldnt make a return trip just for DMK

Author: Danielle L.
Content: The food was amazing  The burgers were tender and juicy the buns were fresh I understand that they are made at the restaurant  Everything was bursting with sophisticated flavor  I had the 6 a burger with a portabello mushroom brie and scallions the gruyere mac n cheese and a couple of sides of fries  Even the fries had amazing flavor  The drinks were delicious and potent I had the sweet tea and a mojitoThe only drawback to this place is the noise  FYI  Despite the classy food it is a very casual barlike atmosphere

Author: Elizabeth S.
Content: This is one of those Id reallyliketogiveit35stars type of reviews If my expectations hadnt been so high going in I might be generous enough to give 4 but since this place is much hyped 3 it isHeres the fundamental flaw of this place in my opinion for a gourmet burger concept its much more about the toppings than the burgers themselves I ordered a turkey burger call me a wuss if you must and the meat while well seasoned played second fiddle to the bread and toppings It was a thin patty I can be down with that at Mickey Ds but at a highfalutin burger joint I want the meat to be the starThe other thing I didnt like was that everything seemed VERY salty And youre talking to the girl who has the worlds biggest salt tooth I would freebase it if I could But the deviled eggs  too saltyAs others have mentioned it IS loud But the decor the atmosphere all that  I liked Service was good But after all was said and done wed spent about 60 and felt like we couldve gotten more delicious burgers at Rocks

Author: Linda G.
Content: This was a good choice for a beer and an ART BurgerThey have very creative burgers and a fine selection of craft beersI might be an eager eater I feel like the burger could have been 30 bigger and Idve been happier Next time well each order one and another to split The atmosphere is Industrialhip We sat at the bar and our bartender was very pleasant

Author: Amanda T.
Content: Holy hamburgers Theres likea lot of burgers here  The burger list is quite extensive and it definitely took me a minute and a half to decide what I wanted  And then it took me another minute to decided whether or not I wanted a beef or turkey or crispy portobello  I opted for the beef this time but next time I think Id get the turkey I sampled it from one of my friends and I actually think it tastes better  The burgers are pretty good especially with the fried egg on top  What makes DMK great is the other stuff  the long list of craft beers yum the onion strings yum the fried pickles and okra yum and the fries oh my goodness YUM  I came here with six other people and lets just say we may got carried away and ordered too much We ordered three types of fries to share between the seven of us sweet potato parmesan with truffle cream and the Wisconsin cheddar  There was a food surplus but it was worth it  Everything was delicious   The service was a bit slow but it was a Friday night so it was expectedly busy  And it would be so much easier if they took reservations  Prices are decent and not overwhelming  DMK is definitely one of my new favorite places My Spidey senses tell me there will be many more turkey burger adventures here in the future

Author: Charlie M.
Content: The thing I like most about DMK is that yeah its a burger place but its approach is much more about an entire meal than it is about the burgers themselvesYou go to Kumas or Moodys and youre sitting down for a big goddamn burger At DMK youre sitting down more of a meal with a great burger as the cornerstone The difference boils down to two things burger size and everything else on the menu The burgers arent small here but theyre not the mammoth side effects include drowsiness coronary blockage and sore arms types that other burger places make Sometimes its kind of nice to roll in and know youre not only getting a great burger but that youll probably be able to make room for cheese fries maybe some mac a couple great salad options and a beer or three Someone below wrote that their beer selection was average which it is not to the point where its ridiculous to even say A wide range of beer types are represented from pilsner to imperial stout though its smartly skewed towards hoppier options perfect for cutting through greasy fries and quality red meatDMK doesnt lack the appreciation for burgers youll find at the other great burger joints in Chicago but it just seems to understand that burgers can be better off playing a role in something a little more wellrounded

Author: Jayne K.
Content: To be honest IDK why I dont love DMK more Been here on Sun Mon and Thursday nights so far and all of them have been super busy so they must be doing something right but its far from my favorite burger place in the ChiDMK has several good things going for it The beer selection is large and boutiquey Cant speak to the shakes but who can go wrong with chocolate peanut butter and ice cream And its one of few places in Chicago thats paleo friendly The beef is grass fed and the fries which are all off the chain are all fried in beef fat rather than oil For me its a decent choice when Im tired of cooking at home and for all its boutiqueyness its actually pretty affordable But the same things that make DMK good also make it fail to stand out I mean spit in Chicago and youll hit at least 5 bars who cater to the craft brew afficiando And any burger place worth its salt is going to have a fried egg and bacon burger DMK tries to distinguish itself with unique pairings and seasonal offerings but to me they pale in comparison to what Kumas offers on the regular And unlike Kumas or Twisted Spoke the atmosphere does little to make the wait palatable Like I said its always packed but that means youre cramped when youre waiting cramped when youre eating and cramped when youre paying your check Also good luck trying to hold a conversation above the music and crowd noise Overall Ill probably go back to DMK particularly in light of my current carnivorous diet and the bomb ass service from Arianna Shes the bestest But Ill be wishing I were at Kumas Twisted Spoke or Pour on Ashland

Author: Jenna M.
Content: Considering the location and reputation for long waits I was pleasantly surprised with the service We arrived at 630 Friday night to put our names down until my friend arrived to complete our party Grabbed some chairs at the bar and watched Talledega Nights while drinking some beers The hostess came up to let us know she hadnt forgotten about us which I appreciated The bartenders were surprisingly easy to grab for reups and our waitress was friendly attentiveThe food was fine  our table had the 1 4 6 Mac and Cheese 2 Parm Truffle and sweet potato fries I wish I had the simplest burger there so the beef could stand out The patty size 14 pound and bun generic white do not hold up well to the more aggressive toppingsIm glad I tried it but probably wont go back Will add this to my good if you live in the neighborhood but wont make an effort to return list

Author: Evan S.
Content: Im down with DMK I really like what they are doing in general Local beers involved with local nonprofits real food Its cleverSometimes its a little too local Case in point you have to sit at long tables so while you may be out on your first date the couple next to you could be breaking upyou all get to share in the moment Hooray ok that exp ample may be a little extreme but you get the point Another thing on the ambiance Im not entirely sure what they are looking to accomplish with their TVs Avatar was on without sound It was weirdThey are burger joint so get the burger Dont waste you time with the lamb burger or anything else its not worth itFinal thought if you arent a foodie you may not LOVE this place

Author: Adam K.
Content: I give DMK Burger Bar an 82 out of 100Minus 18 points for being a hipster enclave that really makes you feel ridiculous about going to a trendy and fashionable bar with loud music and a clubby atmosphere and then sitting down and orderingA burger  At the end of the day I just feel like Milton from the Miller High Life commercials would go there and revoke their Miller High Life privilegesPositive points for a wellpriced awesome perfectly executed burger  You really cant argue with the quality of the burgerPositive points for fantastic fries and their cheddar sauce is amazing on the cheddar fries  Again just awesomePositive points for Chili that was terrific  It was like Cinci Chili minus the noodlesPositive points for a good beer selection served in the great low ball pint glassesPositive points for a good atmosphere good people good music good staff good décor good lightingPositive points for relatively good service no complaints  Good waiter good bartenderPositive points for the guy on his double date next to us that fell off his stool and into my brother  Friggin hilarious  Second date chances after that little stunt  ZEROPositive points for our party of 6 all having rave reviews of ANYTHING that we ate thereOther  I think Milton would go there revoke their high life privileges but then as hes waiting for his guys to haul the high life out of the place hed sit down and have a great burger served by nice people and hed change his mind

Author: Kelcey K.
Content: I think I ordered a number 10  Turkey with smoked swiss tomato Arugula and Dijonnaise and we also shared a sweet potato fries I loved my burger The bun was crispy on the outside and ultra soft on the inside and when you bite into it it still held up firm it didnt crumble making it a mess to eat Fabulous The patty itself was juicy and yummy I think what beat this burger though was their sweet potato fries That was simply awesome albeit I thought it was too salty and tried to shake the salt bits off before consuming it It wasnt too greasy but it was crispy enough and the sweet taste of sweet potato was just heavenly Ill be back DMK

Author: Jason B.
Content: Epic Got the number 2 burger and you cant go wrong think spices awesomeness with blue cheese  yum We also had the sweet potato fries which were a wonderful spicy flavorgasm just made that word up Epic

Author: Yackisoba Y.
Content: The burger  100 percent delicious The wait  50 percent worth itThe noise level  25 percent too loudTheres nothing worse than an overrated burger ehmKumas but DMK burger lives up to its reputation This hipsterheavy dining establishment has a great menu that you dont have to make any alterations to in fact you cant ask for your burger a particular way  theyre all cooked the same and there is no rare or well done Ive got the bison burger and the veggie burger The bison was so juicy and ridiculously flavorful The veggie burger hands down the best veggie burger Ive had in the city It has eggplant on it and a spicy kickThe sweet potato fries are SO worth the calories I know calories shouldnt matter if youre in a burger bar but still a calorie is a calorie The one thing I havent had yet but looks delicious is the chocolate milkshake Thats next on the listThe only reason this place doesnt get five stars is because of the noise level We sat at a picnic style table across from each other and there were a lot of Whats and What whos The wait is a little high about 3045 minutes both times Ive been but turnover is fast  its just that its a popular place Overall I rate DMK the highest on my list for a burger in the city at this point Definitely take an outoftowner there

Author: Johanna P.
Content: Pros Decent burgers really good friesCons Super loud super crowded slow service

Author: Adam M.
Content: DMK Burger Bar is solid They have a very good selection of different burgers I went with the 4 Roasted Hatch Green Chili Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack and Smoked Bacon Burger This burger was very good This place also has a bunch of different options for the fries which I think is great I really liked the Sweet Potato Fries and was also a fan of the Parmesan and Truffle Cream ones Next time I might have to try the Amish Blue and Smoked Bacon The specialty burger area is becoming slightly crowded with many good options in Chicago but the location for DMK makes it very convenient so I will be going back

Author: Jennie P.
Content: Burgers Burgers Burgers thats me chanting and banging my silverware on the table at the same timeWhere do I begin  besides saying this was close if not THE best burger Ive had  The bun was soft but toasted a little not too big and not too much bread which is the WORSTI had the Bison Burger with a blueberry bbq sauce and onions on top  my mouth is watering again as I type this  It was amazingWe ordered a small fry to split for two people their standard fries which were sea salt and pepper and it was the perfect amount for two people to shareMy husband had the burger which comes with tomatoes iceburg lettuce pickles  but he had the double patty  He was LOVING it and admitted he had to slow down in an effort to not devour the whole thing in a milisecondBeer selection was quite extensive  I didnt have the attention span to read all of them and settled on an India Pale Ale which was goodAmbiance was cool a little dark but I liked it  We were there on a Sunday and there seemed to be a lot of parents there with their kids  After thinking about it I actually think its a great spot to bring family andor friendsTrust me you wont be disappointed  Im looking forward to the next time we go

Author: Helena G.
Content: I loved the number 5 burger It comes in a very thin bread so I could appreciate the juicy and tender meat I also enjoyed the berries sauce and the cheese goat I highly recommend this place

Author: Tone F.
Content: DMK is my default Burger place on the north side NO QUESTION Grassfed hand formed patties with bread made inhaus Dont event get me started on the fries One word Truffle They also do great with the beer and adult beverage selection The staff take care of you and the food is in front of you before you expect it They also have a loyalty card that also works at the Fish Bar right next store They also have a featured item that benefits a local nonprofit in Chicago land on a monthly rotating basis Do note that DMK is no reservatoins but theyve seemed to figure out the flip rate of the joint Go hear and you will come back again and again

Author: Molly B.
Content: So far DMK is the best burger Ive tried in Chicago What do I love the most The variety They pick out the most incredible flavors case in point the guacamole burger and I also love that the sizes arent too big Im not afraid of a large meal but I never leave DMK feeling overwhelmingly stuffedThe secret aceinthehole here are the french fries The bacon bleu cheese fries are a personal favorite but dont let that prevent you from trying the truffle oil fries the salt  pepper fries or the sweet potato fries Theyre all deliciousThe last thing Ill mention are the monthly specials If there is any doubt in your mind let me clear it up for you you want to order them Theyre always fresh and new once I had sweet potato tater tots and they were soooooooooooo good I went back twice that month

Author: Vivi W.
Content: LOVE LOVE LOVE their burgers and truffle friesThey have great cocktail tooHowever wait can be long i mean long And the restaurant is very noisy and I always have to scream in order to chat with my friends

Author: Katie S.
Content: Mmmm DMK  I want you all the timeMy personal favorites the bison burger with goat cheese pickled onions and blueberry BBQ sauce OMG ITS SO GOOD AAAAHHH onion strings deviled eggs just like my mama makes them truffle fries mac n cheese and any of their amazing milkshakesAlso  beer selection is not to be missed and they make a very swiggable cocktailService can be a bit spotty but overall is pretty solid

Author: maurice s.
Content: This is a nice bar with some pretty good food but its far from a high quality burger joint  As others have mentioned they dont allow you to specify doneness  Thats ridiculous for a burger bar  In my case it resulted in a substantially overcooked dry burger  That sin alone makes them ineligible for more than 2 stars  Also its insanely loud and expensive for what you get  On the flip side the salmon burger was one of the better fish sandwiches Ive ever tasted  Its not really a burger but thats a good thing in this case  Also nice beer selection and good sweet potatoes fries

Author: michael s.
Content: best turkeyburger ever these guys take burgers to 11 amazing thin soft potato flour bun flavorful turkey burger was perfectly crisped on the outside moist  delicious inside sheep milk cheese and some kind of heavenly condiments on top just flat out delicious

Author: Jeff D.
Content: DMK is without question my favorite burger in Chicago  Every time I go I get a different burger and every time Im amazed at the quality Not the giant burgers that youll find at other places just great quality ingredients cooked flawlessly  I love the ciabatta buns and you can add an egg to any burger for 1 Beer list is good the fries are fantastic and they make their own craft sodas  Anytime I have someone in from out of town I take them here for a burger and theyre always amazed  Plus theyre open pretty late even on weekdays  If youre any kind of burger fan you have to check this place out

Author: Carrie C.
Content: DMK is a great place for a burger  fries I havent had anything that isnt amazing there The Amish Blue burger is my favorite with the truffle fries Its reasonably priced and they have a wide drink selection Definitely try the monthly milkshake Theyre always out of this world

Author: Dustin P.
Content: I got the number five with the shake of the month cookies n cream base with peanut butter and the sweet potato fries My girlfriend got a burger I cant remember whichI enjoyed the service incredibly friendly server We would have gotten some of their drink specials but they were very priceyThe burger was flavorful and deliciously my only qualm with it was the size I was expecting the type of burger thats a challenge to finish this was sizable but not huge Good quality all around The sauce pairing with the sweet potato fries was greatI recommend going there and trying some of the extensive beer list It would provide a more substantial meal than I had Still a very nice place with quality foodOne more thing its pretty dim in here I dont really go for dim dining atmospheres Not a make or break for me though

Author: N.A. S.
Content: Very nice spot Often too loud and too crowded also the musical selection is often a pity But there is definitely something special there The TVs will display the game you want to see but if nothing is on they play stuff you wont see elsewhere on TV from classics like Pulp Fiction to corny blockbusters from the 80s that will make you laughThe crowd and noise can become ridiculous but if you finish work late like me youll find sitting for one or two and a noise level that will allow you to talk unlike what is said in previous comments If your concern is the noise avoid early evenings and Saturday afternoons it is nice the rest of the timeThe staff also is very nice The manager is a great guy and a couple of bartenders really like their craft and will discuss cocktails with you as elsewhere a few employees are meh but who caresThe drink selection is serious the beer selection beats of a lot of placesThe food also is amazing The beef patties are not too big so that you can eats burgers on a regular basis the fries are very good and the milkshakes are to die for Check for their monthly specials Lucky Charms milk shake or PeachesnCream milkshake this monthOnly drawback about food is that the guys in the kitchen only let you remove ingredients not substitute so if you want to remove something funny you dont have much left I dont eat pork anymore so the 1 burger even though it is delicious is a little bit too simple once you remove the bacon from the equationThe number 8 burger is the sure choice if you want nothing surprising in your burger and it tastes great They are also renowned for their veggie burgers but I did not give it a try yetIf you like burgers you cant go wrong here and if not youll probably find something you like starting with an unusual atmosphere

Author: Derek B.
Content: Ive only been here once but its a burger I still think about  Im a pescetarian and the server was very knowledgeable about the menu and my options This is cooked in    The two burgers on the menu that I could have were amazing  I split them both with a friend and we left happy  The drinks are great reasonably priced  And its a great location

Author: Becky C.
Content: The burgers were great here but the noise was a bit much  However not enough to keep me away  I liked how thin the burgers were and the fact I could take an entire bite without making a huge mess  I feel like so many of the good burgers now need to be cut in half and eaten with a fork I could hold this in both hands take a bite and the burger didnt fall apart nor make a huge mess Good beer list and the fries were good too  I would love to see them add a porch too as that might make up for the noise if outside seating was an option

Author: Maxfield R.
Content: SO and I hit it up hard on their third night  Burgers 2 and 3 a couple beers a couple wines truffle fries sweet potato fries short shake deviled eggsWrecked it allLots of love for the cheap Big Red wine and burger comboGreat service from our maitred MK himself to our cute charming server Katie  There was a little chaos all around us being that it was night 3 but our service was spot onGreat beef flavor in the burgersAnd how can you go wrong with deviled eggsShortcomings  Chocolate shake made with lousy chocolate syrup  What passes for a shake here would insult back home  Burgers are not cooked to order they arrived a lovely medium but nobody asked

Author: Trey A.
Content: I really enjoyed this place I tried it with a buddy of mine who lives right down the street and Wow what a treat it was Originally I had my heart set on Panes a sandwich place next door that I cannot get enough of however he recommended DMK and I reluctantly agreed We both had number 1s which were good We had a few locally brewed beers they do have a nice selection which is always an added bonus In addition we had the cheddar mac and cheese which was solid and some sweet potato french fries which were also very goodService was also very nicepolite and timely for being so busyThe only reason I did not give it 5 stars was because of communal seating Sitting right on top of people sucks as I have stated in previous reviews Anyway I think its good I would compare my burger experience to somewhere in between 5 Guys and Kumas Corner Prices are more like Kumas  Would recommend

Author: Lisa K.
Content: As everyone has said 1  it gets really really busy so get here early if you dont like to wait  We ate at 6pm on a Wednesday and by 630 there was a wait2  burgers are amazing  on the smaller side which I prefer  Buns are nice  I hate having too much bread and not enough burger3  fries are goodI tried three kinds4  service is great  the man at the door seemed sincerely happy that we came by to eat and the servers were attentive but not overly so5 great beers on tap  not a lot but enough to satisfy whatever youre looking forIll be going back for sure

Author: Chad S.
Content: To compare DMK to Kumas is like comparing apples and oranges  theyre just not the same thing At allThat said give me a burger at DMK over Kumas any dayThat Lamb Burger is out of this world and tastes EXACTLY like a greek salad its delicious and about half way through eating mine I wanted to order another Bonus for the vegan bunsGood cocktail menu and huge beer selectionWe ordered the Parmesan Truffle and Cheddar Scallion fries  they were good but almost too flavorful and I found myself just wanting regular fries The cooking and texture of the fries was so perfect they didnt need anything elseDo yourself a favor and order an ice cream sandwich for dessert You might think that you wont be able to handle it that itd be too much that it wont be that good  Youd Be Wrong

Author: Neil R.
Content: Im not sure how this place is getting such positive feedback on the burgers  Maybe people havent been to Kumas  I fell for the hype and stopped in for lunch  It was a mistake  I ordered the Chili Rubbed Onion Strings burger and was informed that it came with no side  I have a real issue with serving something all alone but anyway I looked over the selection of fries which all sounded interesting and went with the truffle fries  When it all arrived I thought I was at Minis remember that joint at Halstead and Armitage  The burger was small  I think the miniature plates are there specifically to distract you from the portion size  DAMN thats huge Its as big as the plate One highlight was the beer  They have a decent selection but that alone cant overcome the tiny portions high prices and unimpressive burgers  Sorry DMK FAIL

Author: Cassie B.
Content: This place is pretty awesomeI have spent a large amount of time and money here  The burgers are great  I especially like the lamb one  The Parmesan fries with truffle cream are delicious too  There is an amazing selection of very interesting beers and the service is great  The people here are super friendly and cool  All in all this is a great place to sit at the bar drink good beer eat great food and chat with good people

Author: Derek M.
Content: Arrived at about 130 pm to a pretty empty restaurant which was nice because the two of us were able to hear each other just fine and the music in the background was great  Perfect volume and style  Okay lets get to the meat of this conversationThe burger I had was great  I like my burgers served hot and this one was just warm  Cooked to perfection but just a little cool for my taste The fries are amazing  Lauren was our server and was awesome  I wish Lauren worked at every restaurant in Chicago  Its not often you get a kind genuine funny server in Chicago full disclosure Ive never met the girl before  Waters came to the table right away without ice which is perfect so youre not asking all the time for a refill and you dont have piles of ice falling in your face Get Lauren as your server and go get a burger here  It is great  Sure wish there was an outside on a nice day

Author: Chris L.
Content: So let me preface this review by saying that there were parts to our experience that were worth of 5 stars and other parts that justify the 3 star rating  So the wife and I went here after hearing all kinds of great things from friends and coworkers  We arrived a bit early on a Friday night around 6pm since we had heard that waits could reach around 45 min  Being that we have a needy puppy at home we wanted to avoid that kind of wait  Thankfully we were seated immediately We were greeted by our waitressor who we thought was our waitress shortly after sitting down  Shortly after that we were greeted by another waitress  Im not one to complain about 2 people making sure things are going well but it was a bit odd  Wifey and I ordered a beer off of the nice list  We were impressed with the selection  I had an Allagash and she had a Great LakesI think  On to the foodI ordered an 1 and my wife ordered a 2  With those we ordered the sweet potato and the parmesan fries  The fries were the highlight of the meal  The sweet potato fries were paired with a great lemon aioli dipping sauce while the parmesan were paired with a truffle sauce  My oh my  The fries were crisp the sauces provided a perfect compliment  Frankly I could have made a meal out of the different fries  As for the burgers this proved to be a little disappointing  Quite frankly when Burger Bar is in your name you should spend a bit more time on the burgers  All in all I would say that my burger was just OK  It was DEFINITELY NOT worth the 8 I paid for it though  The wife seemed to like hers but I am not sure if she felt that it was worth the price either  Our recommendation would be to make the burgers worthy of the 8 price tag  I know this is become the en vogue thing having an 8 burger that is  But its quite disconcerting  Kumas has 10 burgers but it is worthy of being a 10 burger considering the amount flavor and quality of the burger  Others have noted that the music was loud  They are correct  It is really loud  Ultimately we would come back to give it another try  However Id hope that we find a burger worthy of the price tag and critical acclaim  As of this time I find that it has lived up to neither  Maybe DMK should become a Fry Bar since that is where they shine

Author: Liz L.
Content: Yum yum yum Stuff my face Yum yum yumI have to preface this review that the only way I will eat a burger is with nothing on it except bleu cheese  SeriouslyDMK is delicious  Their 8 burger altered to be plain with just bleu cheese is awesome  I usually like a mediumrare burger but these patties are pretty thin so it was leaning more towards medium  However I could still taste how good the meat was and the delicious cheese on top made it perfect  The bun was tasty too not overpoweringAs for the fries you cant go wrong with the truffle parmesan or the WI cheddar  Seriously I would take that cheddar and smear it all over my face if it meant I got to keep eating it  Its THAT goodMy only complaint is the noise level  We went at 7PM on a Wednesday and I could barely hear my friend across our 2top table  Plus I couldnt tell if the waitress had heard my order correctly because I couldnt hear her repeat it back to me  Turns out she got it right so no worriesThe staff is all really nice even if they do all look 16 years old

Author: A. A.
Content: Eat it Kumas  DMK just Slayed you  Great burger concoctions fries that can easily become a vice to the weak willed especially the parmesan truffle fries watch out and theyre not total douchebag tools  Everything I had tasted GREAT  Yes the meat was maybe not how Graham Elliot would rock a burger but for what you pay and the toppings you get which is what I think is being focused on here it is pretty killerMy only issue with this place was the speed of service and that wasnt even that bad  However when the server did come around the service was great unlike some burger places cough Kumas coughGood thing this place isnt close to where I spend any good amount of time or else I may frequent it so much I would own stock in the place

Author: Steph P.
Content: I was told that DMK had the best burgers around so I went to try it out obviously Turns out that they dont just have the best burgers but they also have the best fries and an awesome beer menuI am always down with a burger fries and beer so I suppose Ill always be down for some DMK Our waitress was Marina or at least thats what it said on the receipt and she was super nice and attentive throughout our entire meal Good food great service fun atmosphere  good great grand

Author: Sophie S.
Content: Just came back from DMK It was a Friday night so the wait was 40 minutes but we walked around and came back The atmosphere is very loud and some tables are communalThe food came in reasonable time considering the night The burger was great The bread was pretty unique and the flour added a nice texture Extremely filling but not in a bad greasy way We also got the sweet potato and Wisconsin cheese fries to share The sweet potato had a nice salty alioli to go along with it

Author: Shawn K.
Content: DMK has the best burger I have ever eaten no I havent been to Kumas and yes I know that is sadThe various menu options are put together really well They also have turkey and lamb burgers if you want to avoid beefThe fries are excellent They have several styles to choose from at really cheap pricesThe drink list is excellent They dont have as big of a selection as Coopers but the list is a lot longer than most places of this kind Most of the drinks are not served a lot of places so it is a great place to try new drinks

Author: Kenneth L.
Content: I would like to open my review by stating that you can add a fried egg to anything OMG Other customizations include x2 or x3 your burger patty This is definitely NOT the best burger Ive ever had  not even by a long shot Its actually a little bit disappointing considering that this place is advertisedspoken of as THE burger joint With that said I found my burger to be OK The setting lends itself to being a really loud establishment with the bare brick walls concrete floor and other hard surfaces Im not kidding when I say its loud  be prepared to yell a conversation with the person sitting across from you Truly a bar feel maybe due to the huge BAR As far as seating is concerned you will find counter height tables in the front regular tables in the back and a full bar in between Expect a fairly long wait to be seated Service can be a little difficult to come by Friendly staff but not enough people to satisfyingly attend to everyone This place has a great selection on the menu and very creative burger combos With a price of 8 a burger I would definitely return to try other menu items EATEDCheddar fries  actually a salty salty cheese sauce Im beginning to notice that this cheese sauce seems to be very popular in the Chicagoland area and its reminiscent of the cheese spread in handisnacks The jurys still out on whether I like it or not 1 Burger  Aged Cheddar Smoked Bacon Charred Balsamic Red Onions BBQ Sauce Please note that the ingredients list is indicative of a surefire winner so you can imagine my dismay upon finding the final product to be only ok Grass fed beef patty was a bit mushy and lacking in flavor Bun was delicious but the burger was a little bit of a disappointment overall Portabello burger  surprisingly very good The mushroom was lightly breaded w panko crust The burger had a fantastic balance with the horseradish arugula marinated tomatoes and fontina cheese Same delicious bun As I said above I would absolutely return but I find it difficult to leave Evanston when Edzos is right around the corner from me Nevertheless Im still looking forward to round 2

Author: Jessica S.
Content: Realllly yummy Pretty cool atmosphere goodlooking staff huge craft beer selection I dig itAll of the burgers are 8 which is cool they dont come with fries or anything but they are pretty cheap to order on the side 14 My boyfriend got some interesting burger with prosciutto on it and said it was the best burger Ive ever had he also hadnt eaten all day but still They have a good interesting selection of items and plenty of options that dont have meat veggie burgers portobello etc I got a crispy portobello burger and it was delicious We split some blue cheese  bacon fries which were AThe beer selection was vast and interesting although pretty pricy but its whatever considering how relatively inexpensive the food is

Author: Brian S.
Content: Im not the sort of reviewer who often puts on the loud accoutrement of superlatives but if someone forced me  at gunpoint preferably  to name the best new restaurant of 2010 I might be inclined to name DMK Burger Bar Sure its mostly just burgers on the menu featuring ingredients were all pretty familiar with but DMKs philosophy shines like a gold thread through the fabric of their restaurant I typically review food before finances but the reasonable pricepoints at DMK  for MKquality ingredients preparation and aesthetic  is the real sell here Whats more several of their avantgarde cocktails are listed with a highend and middleground spirit choice depending on your budget That way everyone gets to enjoy the craftsmanship of a wellmade mixed drink without having to pay 11 for topshelf boozeFlavor profiles are pleasantly unbefitting a neighborhood that features such culinary and drinking atrocities as Uncle Fattys Rum Resort which manages to stay in business despite promoting itself as Lakeviews 1 cover band venue Sure its burgers but these are thoughtful burgers  burgers that defy ketchup unless its homemade seasoned with chipotle peppers and accompanied by blue cheese and housemade onion strings For months the best burger on the menu featured prosciutto and vinegar potato chips  a righteous combination of flavors and textures The rest of the burgers Ive had most of them come with tender highrise buns grassfed beef and generous portions of great ingredients Sides and desserts are great fun too The parmesan truffle fries best similar offerings at higherend restaurants A more palatable version of ranch dressing for the Uncle Fattys crowd no doubt comes with a plate of perfectly fried okra and pickle spears Really we havent had a real miss in terms of sides and weve nearly tried them all thanks to their generosity Either were the most polite or criticlooking folks around but Daniel and I consistently get offered free sides with our meals Last night the gravy fries we debated over getting choosing instead the creamy forkfriendly bleu cheese and bacon fries arrived at our table on the house We liked them too but wondered where the rest of the poutinesque accoutrements wereI give this place my heartiest recommendation Its the best resto Lakeview has seen in years and the best interpretation of the burger trend of 2010

Author: April S.
Content: This was by far the BEST damn veggie burger that EVER hit my lips  No lie  And not only was it freshly made and not some frozen crap that has been sitting in the freezer for yearsbut they had more than 1 option for vegetarians Very rare Fresh cut fries with truffle sauce was also amazing Try a local beer They were so good And the bartenders were great at suggesting just what I wanted  Def be willing to waitbut SOOOO worth the wait

Author: Steven C.
Content: DMK is a straightforward take on the burger bar trend that prides itself on grassfed beef Ive only had a few things that were truly outstanding but I like the simplicity and have only good things to say about the food and the serviceThe decor is a bit dull but the bar restaurant is lively and welcoming of all ages Ive been twice on Sunday nights and have never had to wait to sit down despite a solid crowdThe menu is a onepager so not too many tough decisions unless you like decisions then you might feel limited There are about a dozen or so burgers on the menu 34 of which are traditional beef and the others range from turkey and lamb to vegetarian options Ive tasted the lamb burger which is treated exactly like gyros which was kind of cool if youre looking for something nontraditionalThe burgers are really the perfect size and most of the flavors on them are pretty rich so dont be shocked when a Kumaslike behemoth doesnt show up on your plate My favorite thing here is the 2 with Amish blue cheese and chilirubbed onion straws It also comes with their chipotle ketchup which is the only ketchup they serve and its really excellent I would buy it if they packed and sold it there My absolute favorite thing here is the sweet potato fries with the lemon tobasco aioli I was told this was the place for parmesean truffle fries but I found them disappointing and still dont get the truffle oil thing Just get the sea salt and black pepper or sweet potato friesThe craft beer selection is among Chicagos most respectable here as well so it will be hard to pass up a drink if you are a fan of all the popular craft breweries in Chicago Michigan and Indiana

Author: Steve W.
Content: Sweet potato fries You need them Now beyond that the burgers are delicious At first glance the bread overhwelms the meat but you take one bite and your tongue tells you otherwise The bread is light and fluffy  not bready and dense The 4 oz patties are so deliciously beefy that it just overwhelms your tastebuds Now your choice of toppings can overwhelm the burger  stay away from the pastrami  its unsurprisingly a bomb of salt Im partial to the more simple preparations  lettuce tomato onion pickles  just because that beef patty is so delicious I enjoyed the brie and portobello and the bacon and cheddar ones as well Also since youre partaking of fries and burgers anyways you might as well inhale a milkshake The vanilla malt I had was delicious Thick with that malty tang that you just need to have Your body will forgive you Come on it was my first shake in at least a year

Author: Melissa W.
Content: No I will not wait over an hour for a burger in an odor intense shouldtoshoulder packed place where I need a megaphone to converse with one sitting 12 inches away  This decision in combo with a recommendation from a friend took us to DMKBurger  Ive been here twice and foresee many more visits  Why you askFood  love love love  Seriously the burgers are yummy and the truffle fries makes your inner fatty cry out for more  This is coming from someone who isnt a burger person yet who now randomly craves the loveliness that exists on DMKs menuBeer  Wide ranging and delicious  We sat at the bar both times   My boyfriend tends to be rather verbose with all He was filling the ears of both the bartender and the manager with his chatter of beer brewing  To his credit we were directed to some rather tasty and obscure beers  I thoroughly enjoy a good beer menuVibe  DMK isnt pretentious while remaining upscale and energetic but comfortable andchill When we came in the second time the manager I think hes the manager recognized us and told the bf about a new beer on the menu that he thought hed like given his love of all things hoppy  I was impressed that he made the connection  The guy has some social superhero strengths  And we appreciated the free beer card that he gave us from our first visit  People can make or break a place  He adds value

Author: Peter H.
Content: I am surprised this place only has 35 stars  I think its the best burger joint in Chicago  5 stars because1 has a great beer list2 wait is not bad atleast when I went there on a Thursday evening3 burgers that you can actually eat without a forkknife 4 awesome fries and a variety of them 5 fair prices for quality of food

Author: Kate P.
Content: The burgers here are great My only knock aside from how constantly busy it is are the descriptions on the menu They dont specify that each burger comes with a hamburger patty and everything listed is extra For example we wanted the mushroom blue cheese burger but werent sure if that was a veggie burger  Either way the food was great We had the fries which were delicious and great for sharing I have not had the mac n cheese but it always looks tempting when I see people get served itThe drinks are fantastic as well  Wide variery of cocktails but ask for the list They dont always offer it up and the chalkboard does not list drink descriptions

Author: Keith C.
Content: Drinks Good craft beers and margaritas were good tooAppies  Fried okra  why have I never experienced you before DMKthis was my favorite thing about DMK  Dinner Wife loved the grilled cheese My buddies and I did family style with a few burgers

Author: Eli S.
Content: Good ambiance and decent burgers with really interesting combinations I tried theyre blu cheese burger equivalent with fried onion rings Pretty good though the burgers werent that big The buns were really good They were very busy so we werent doted on by our server but it wasnt too much of a botherThey also had a really great looking beer selectionIt wont be my new go to burger joint place but for a weekend night out eat it would be sweet every once in a while

Author: Maggie M.
Content: Disclaimer Im a vegetarian We started with the Parmesan truffle fries which I have to say were amazing Pretty much anything with truffle oil is fantastic I ordered the House Veggie and Grain Burger and wasnt disappointed but was not impressed The patty fell apart quickly it was difficult to eat and wasnt the delicious veggie burger I was looking for From what I saw the real burgers looked very impressive and I highly encourage the meatlovers out there to dig in However if youre a vegetarian I would maybe opt for one of their salads or the portobello mushroom burger

Author: John Z.
Content: I had the Bison Burger with Goat Cheese it was great I also had the fries with Wisconsin Cheddar they were good very cheesy Also a good selection of local brews The place is not very big and there can be a long wait but its worth it I will be back

Author: matthew S.
Content: Great burgers great sides great beer In the class of burger bars this is as good as gets The place is always busy and it is often very loud but mostly in a good way DMK is fully ADA Accessible as far as I could tell

Author: Lauren C.
Content: I like this place better than Kumas The proportions are much more feasible and they still have creativity with what they serveI like that they do not have standard beers on their list and they make you get creative with what you orderI also like that they periodically give you free beer coupons to use on your next visitThis place is a win

Author: k E.
Content: love love love this placeInventive combinations  Great prices  The truffle fries are amazing

Author: Kristin S.
Content: Ill be honest after seeing DMK Burgers profiled on Diners Drive Ins  Dives I was interested in checking DMK out but didnt want to put my hopes up too high Wellwas I wrong This place blew out any burger place sorry Umami Burger Ive been to in a long time First of all the bison burger with blueberry bbq sauce and goat cheese smear  lets all just agree it should be illegal If I lived in Chicago I would be like 500lbs from heading to this place every chance I get That burger alone would make me throw out my I should step away from red meat tendencies My friend and I also ordered a small order of fries  which were phenomenal and big enough for the two of usAnother highlight was how great the waitstaff was  our waitress was so sweet and very accommodating as I asked her for suggestions and then about Guys visit She also awarded us for my obvious tourist awkwardness with free Shamrock Shakes  mint chocolate chip ice cream shake withready for thisLucky Charms sprinkled on top That officially did me inother than I need to walk this off  I had no words after that If you didnt get it from this review  definitely check DMK Burger out You dont be disappointed  Im already planning my next trip to Chicago so I can try the salmon burger

Author: Alicia D.
Content: I ordered my food for carry out and while the food itself was well made it was cold Cold burger and fries is never that good Not to mention that whoever took my order had the worst customer service ive ever experienced Kelsey was it I have dietary restrictions that make it so I needed to modify my burger only after I got the well HONEY that is our menu so thats how it is did I explain that she could do whatever she needed ie charge more for sides or whatever so that I could order a meal that I could actually eat When I picked up the food I didnt get any enthusiasm or smiles from the gentlemen that rung me up but nonetheless my food was good considering the temperature and yes I arrived at the quoted pickup timeWill I return probably on occasion only because I live a block away and their burgers are better than 711s Heres hoping its hot and friendly next time

Author: J F.
Content: Great burgers  Ive always been a simple burger on starchy white bun guy think Melons PJ Clarkes but this place does them differently and does them right  Great beer selection and every burger Ive had was delicious  Even though Im basically a meatatarian the salads and fries are really very goodAlso it takes a lot for me to say this but I think the milkshakes might be better than the burgers  I think they add a little malt at the bottom of the glass which adds such a nice touch

Author: kamila O.
Content: This place was oh so good I fell in love with the guacamole burger Im still dreaming of this divine burger The service was great but the place was super loud for dinner I would turn the music down just a notch so I can have a conversation with the person sitting right next to me  Regardless loud music or not I will be back

Author: Hector M.
Content: The best burger Start with the 8 It is the classic iceberg Lettuce tomato and pickles Its good Add Gruyere Then add a breaded Portobello cap Truffle fries Then report back Keep it clean please

Author: Jason J.
Content: Theres a debate to which is better DMK or Kumas but I say why both have kickass burgers but are different The smartest thing I did here was to try two different burgers in my first trip by splitting them with my buddy The blue cheese and onion strings burger was awesome lots of blue cheese and pulled with chili dusted onion strings The bacon BBQ burger with the balsamic grilled onions was an orchestra of flavor and although the burgers are thin they do pack in a ton of flavor and the fresh made buns were the icing The cheddar scallions fries also rocked Our bartender gave a few samples of beer and also the chili which was real tasty as well as packing a punch Service was excellent and the place is clean and very laid back overall a great experience I will be back

Author: Tom D.
Content: This is a great burger bar in fact most burger bars should visit DMK to see why each night this restaurant is packed with a goodlooking crowd Its important to have friendly staff and this place has an incredible lineup Burgers taste as described so if youre looking for a spicy patty or a sweet tangy sauce have no fear You will find great variety in the onepage menu Try the sweet potato fries

Author: Arde H.
Content: I was a little thrown off by the unconventional buns and the thin patties but the burgers were GREAT  I especially liked the turkey burger Im typically a beef guy  My favorite was the Kane burger in honor of the Blackhawks recent Stanley Cup victory which was a spicy buffalo burgerWe got the spicy onion rings which were great and the special of the day which was french fries with ranch dressing bacon and chives  It was FANTASTIC  They also have a lot of great beers on tapsFinally the wait staff is super nice  Only complaint is that they only have one womens and one mens restroom and theyre onesies  Makes for a long wait to go pee

Author: Theresa V.
Content: The only reason they get a two stars was because the fries saves them   The meat patties are tiny  Im very disappointed  I was expecting more

Author: Matthew G.
Content: Lacking a good vegan variety they already have everything they need though to custom make great stuff

Author: Samantha E.
Content: Came by with my family for lunch one weekend While it is not my favorite burger in Chicago it is still pretty high up there They have some really unique burger options and some amazing fries Although it was really busy our server always kept tabs on our table and made sure everything was going well I cant wait to come back and try out a breakfast burger

Author: Ripley W.
Content: Yes It is loud  Expect to yell across your table and have trouble hearing what anyone is saying  I guess its called Burger Bar because it is a bar that serves burgers  CleverBesides the noise this is a great place and Ill definitely be back  We were told it was a 90 minute wait which ended up being 20 minutes Not bad for 7p on a Friday  I think it would have been cool to get the communal table but we had a standard 4top in the back  It was noticeably quieter back there so thats a bonus  There were 4 of us for dinner and we totally overordered  Wedge Salad Fried Okra  Pickles Mac and Cheese Truffle Fries Salt and Pepper Fries The 1 bbq sauce and bacon  2 fried onion and bleu cheese  4  chile bacon and a fried egg and the 11 veggie  Key pointsThe fried okra and pickles is in fact 2 pieces of fried okra and a huge mess of pickles  We ordered them specifically for the okra and would  tolerate the pickles  We were disappointed to say the least  Mac and Cheese is not creamy or rich  It had a nice Parmesan crust but its really not good  Unless you dont like rich and creamy mac and cheese in which case youre crazy anyway so Ill save my breathBurgers rated from best to worst1 BBQ and bacon2 Chile with bacon and fried egg the chile gave it a kick and the egg was nice and runny3  Veggie it has pesto and eggplant nice4  Fried onion and bleu cheeseWe each had a beer with dinner and the grand total for 4 without tip was 86  That was pretty sweet especially considering we ordered too much  Tip Dont say youre going to share the fries  If you do youll get a sharing portion large  Order the small portion

Author: Jules H.
Content: Sooooo glad our stand by was closed  for the holiday today forced my friend and I to venture outside our norm and try DMK  First off I have no business being here on Christmas Eve when Im about to have a huge meal wth the fam tonight but my friend and I needed a place to have a drink and exchange gifts WOW Drew was a gracious bartender Very friendly and insightful no recomendation went unappreciated I love that this place uses grass fed meat and much thought goes into the ingredients  My friend had the 4 burger with green chilis which they ship in from New Mexico  I tried the deviled eggs and sampled the sweet potato fries and truffle fries LOVE it We were lucky that we didnt have to contend with crowds going for super early lunch on a holiday I heard this place gets super busy

Author: Todd N.
Content: We couldnt get in without a long wait a few weeks ago but had the chance to go right before Christmas We were prepared to wait but got a table right away it was on the early side  maybe 630 or 7 the Wednesday before Christmas Service was pretty good although we never received water we requested which was mentioned in a couple of other reviewsThe food was very tasty We normally dont like fussy burgers with too many toppings but the burgers were good and the fries were very good The vibe was great Were very happy to have DMK right around the corner

Author: Maria V.
Content: First time here and I am so excited about the explosion of flavor I experianced after my first bit of number 11  Thats a grassfed lamb burger with feta olive tapenade greek salad and tzatziki  Oh an by the way the Parmesan truffle cream fries are outstanding

Author: Jake M.
Content: At here with 3 friends of mine on a Friday night Was busy bit I didnt think the wait was too long Burger I had was delicious and beer selection was pretty good We ended up ordering two large fry plates to split between the four of us and with each of us ordering a burger that was more than enoughOne of the fry plates was a truffle fry plate I would highly recommend this

Author: Julia L.
Content: I went here on a whim today with a couple of my friends and let me just say this DELICIOUS I was pretty surprised at the burgers because after Kumas I definitely raised my standards on burgers DMK did not let me down I ordered the number 2 with chipotle ketchup and spiced onions with what I think Gruyere cheese The buns were also delicious too with the perfect amount of fluffiness not too dense and just the right amount of toasted edges My friends also ordered the number six with portobello mushrooms and a cheese that they could not figure out but raving about and they were just as ecstatic about their burger as I was with mine My other friend ordered the bacon with fried egg and he savored every minute of it If you decide not to order an alcoholic beverage they also have the homemade bloodorange cherry and lime sodas which we also ordered and those drinks were the perfect complement to our burgers A must have when ordering the burger since it only comes with the burger are their frenchfries We received complimentary fried onions and ordered Parmesan cheddar and chives and sweet potato fries My favorite was the cheddar and chives but the other fries were just as good We were all very satisfied and it was not overthetop full like how you get at Kumas I live within walking distance from this place so DMK is definitely going to see more of me in the future

Author: Coco O.
Content: Delicious   Minus one star for the unbelievable volume of the music and the extremely high price for the beers  I had the 11  lamb burger  and it was wonderful  Incredibly moist and juicy  just the right size patty  topped with olive tapenade feta greek salad fixings and tzatziki  It was definitely a little better than my husbands burger with fried onions blue cheese and a chipotle ketchup  We also enjoyed the truffle and parmesean fries small was big enough for us to share and the fried pickles and okra  I consider myself a fried pickle officianado weird I know and these were certainly topnotch  Well definitely be back

Author: Lexi F.
Content: This place was wonderful To drink I got a Metropolitan Krankshaft and my friend got an Allegash White I got the 2 burger with chipotle ketchup onion strings blue cheese and added a fried egg My friend got the italian burger that has prosciutto The only thing is that they dont ask how you like your burgers cooked After I realized this  I tracked down my waitress and she told me that they cook all burgers to a medium However I like mine medium rare She said that the medium would be fine for me since the burgers are thinner than averageWe got our burgers pretty quickly as well as a large order of parmesan fries with a truffle aioli Everything was delicious and I did notice that my burger was much more pink than my friends so I bet the waitress told the kitchen to make mine more of a medium rareEverything was great and I will definitely be going back

Author: Denise F.
Content: I went to DMK just a few days ago for a late dinner with my husband and a couple of friends I have very few complaints about the placeIm torn between 4 and 5 stars We started with the sea salt fries and the truffle fries split for the table which were both delicious The homemade ketchup was really something special It was spicy and there was just something there that was amazing I ordered the 1 burger and the hub and friend ordered the 2 burger We were all very impressed The meat was juicy and the toppings were creative and fresh Definitely one of the best burgers Ive had in Chicago and the prices were pretty good too I wasnt impressed with their draft beer list but they had a great selection in bottles so thats alright

Author: Alessandra M.
Content: HANDS DOWN 1 BURGER BAR IN CHICAGOThis place is absolutely impressive from their beer selection to their food and atmosphere For having attractive employees its not a pretentious place either I come here all the time and every time its phenomenal Ive had just about everything on the menu and ive like it no joke But I think I can eat their lamb burger and parmesean truffle fries everyday and not get tired of it I usually hate veggie burgers but DMKs veggie burger is to die for Its also a great place to take guests from out of town who arent used to eating gourmet burgers But what makes this place so great to me is that I can eat and eat and eat and not feel one bit guilty because all their meat is grassfed which makes a HUGE differenceIf I could be DMKs mascot I would

Author: Geoff S.
Content: My brother and I went here after floating in a sensory deprivation tank but thats another story The burgers were amazing I had the burger with fried egg bacon and green chilies Thinking about it now makes me want anotherand its 900 am You could tell the ingredients were fresh and the patty was handmade We shared a couple of baskets of fries  sweet potato and the parmesan fries with truffle dipping sauce I had a blood orange soda and my bro had a peanut butter shake I honestly have no complaints Everything was amazing So many different flavors going onWe got seated right away Our waitress was very helpful and responsive All good Absolutely one of my favorite burger places Maybe my favorite Cant wait to go back

Author: Tristan C.
Content: Everything about this place was good Not amazing but some things were pretty getting close We had a little bit of a long wait for our table of 6 but nothing out of the ordinary we thought However when we were seated and it might be worth mentioning that much of the seating is on elevated large tables so you sort of squeeze in between other groups of people anyway when we were seated they apologized for our long wait and gave us two different appetizers on the house They were delicious Most other places wouldnt have given it a second thought probablyThe beer menu was good but I have seen more extensive ones not that it really would have mattered they had my favorite and they had it in 22 oz The food was good yummy burgers truffle and Parmesan fries One thing perhaps worth noting the burgers were not overly large Also I would not say that they are the BEST burgers but they are VERY GOODMy friends liked their milkshakes I got a cupcake for dessert which was just the right size after everything else Another friend ordered one of their ice cream sandwiches it looked amazing all homemade chocolate chocolate chip cookie with espresso ice cream YeahIts a little out of my way but I would go back again definitely They have some other things I would like to try It had everything I wanted and they were friendly SummaryFood deliciousService awesome and the wait not too badAmbiance like a bar

Author: Neil G.
Content: Food  4Service  3Atmosphere  4Value  3You might be asking why someone who doesnt eat meat at nonkosher restaurants went to a place like this  Well burgers happen to be one of my favorite foods and I have slowly grown to enjoy a good veggietunaportobello burger  Like most red blooded American males Im also a sucker for anything deep friedfrench fries and onion rings in particular  Anyone can make a good burger but making a great veggie burger takes real talent  Having enjoyed an excellent meal at MK last year I was excited to try this place outI went with a friend on a Tuesday night around 730 and while the restaurant was crowded there was no problem getting a table  My friend does not keep kosher so he went with the 3 Burger with Pastrami Gruyere Saurkraut and Remoulade and I had the 12 Veggie Burger with Cheddar Eggplant Tomato and Pesto Mayo  We also ordered a side of Mac N Cheese and Parmesan Truffle FriesThe Veggie Burger was a beautifully constructed colorful masterpiece  The cheese was melted perfectly and the bun somewhat of a potato roll I believe was just the right size and thickness to hold everything in place when you took a bite  The burger tasted incredibly fresh and what made it unique was that it had a slight crisp the way a charred hamburger might have on the outside  The eggplant and pesto mayo also gave it a hearty rustic feel  As for the sides the Mac N Cheese was baked on top which is not my favorite preparation  It was crunchy and a little dry on top but creamier underneath  Although I much preferred Handlebars see my review because it was creamier and simpler this is still a solid option if you enjoy a more refined Mac  The Truffle Fries were also pretty good but nothing spectacular  They were crispy and had that nice buttery taste you get from truffle oil but were a little heavy on the parmesan  I would definitely opt for a different fried side next timeAlthough I couldnt eat it my friend called his burger amazing and by the look of it I dont think he was mistaken  Ive also had a few burgers with fried pastramibeef fry in my day and they have always been delicious  Overall I would recommend trying it but it probably wont become a staple in your dining rotation  Youre mostly paying for the MK name and the trendiness but if youre really in the mood for an upscale burger topped with fresh unique ingredients it may be worth the price of admission  Thanks for reading my review and be sure to check out my other reviews on Yelp  My mission is to find restaurants that have great vegetarian kosher and vegan fare  On every review I rate food service atmosphere and value on a 15 scale to give you quick and easy overview of the restaurant  I love cooking eating and doing both with my friends and family  I always welcome your questions comments and suggestions so contact me on Yelp or Facebook if you want to share ideas

Author: Tyrell C.
Content: This is the place for Burgers in ChicagoDMK just GETS IT  You dont need GIANT burgers  You dont need crazy amounts of fries  You dont need wacky names  You cant make up for bad burgers with 100s of beers DMK burgers are just about perfect  Lean grassfed beef  24 toppings in great compliment to one another  A wonderful selection of gourmet fries  And a solid beer list  There is literally not a bad burger or fry on the on the menu Ive tried just about every one  Prices are also decent My personal favorites 5 Prosciutto Fontina Pesto Red Pepper Sea Salt  Vinegar Chips Sea Salt  Black Pepper Fries Fried Dill Pickles and Okra possibly the best appetizer at any burger placeAnd you dont have to wait 3 hours in line to get in  DMK youre the best

Author: Gregory H.
Content: I have been here three times and had the 4 each time Great burger I brought my friend here for lunch and we had some good food nice atmosphere and good service I like DMKThumbs up and here comes the butt Guys do something about the greasy chili The idea of having brisket in the chili was great but man the bowl was covered in grease much like the gulf of Mexico in oil Thank goodness for the sponge like toast on the side of the plate or I would not have found the tasty brisket

Author: Lidia L.
Content: Holy Moly This place was GOOOOOD I ordered the 2 which had BBQ sauce in it  I forget what else but everything just tasted so good We also ordered a small side of truffle cream fries and man were we wrong to have ordered a SMALL WE SHOULD HAVE GONE FOR THE LARGE ORDER They were so delicious with a lot of truffle flavor I am a truffle fries kind of girl and Chicago has the best ones We also ordered the 2 mac and cheese which had bacon and other things in it That was just as tasty I also ordered a vanilla milk shake as I got my meal and it was yummy as well It was a nice dessert like drink to top it all offEat in the aura is great Nice and busy But get there before the rush  The service was wonderful and we got our food right away good thing too because we were hungry for burgers I will definitely come back when Im in Chicago

Author: Lindsay D.
Content: Checked out DMK yesterday for the first time Being a vegetarian it is difficult for me to find a burger spot thats accommodating and tasty DMK was able to follow through on both accounts Not only was my veggie burger delicious but I got to end my meal with a decadent espresso shake I would highly recommend this place for meat eaters and vegetarians alike Not only do I want to try their other flavored shakes and the portabella burger but their mac and cheese looked fantastic Hopefully I will be back soon

Author: Omar G.
Content: Took the wife here as part of her bday since they serve turkey and vegan burgers I had already looked up the place here in yelp first so I kinda got her excited to go All I can say is that we both really enjoyed our burgers an fries She order a turkey burger with arugula dijonaisse tomato and i think munster cheese I had the bison burger which im gonna ask for double patty next time with blueberry bbq sauce with goat cheese As for fries we order a large one that came with parmesan cheese an truffle Which was soooo delicious Me and the wife plan to go back soon an try different burgers an fries

Author: Jonathan T.
Content: Great casual dinner location cool interior Creative burger toppings all of which can be substituted for turkey or chicken Decent beer selection and great fries Also pretty cheap for the city 8burger 2friesNot quite on the same level as Kumas for a burger joint but definitely a good place catch dinner in Chicago

Author: Jeff N.
Content: After the hype in the Trib earlier this week about the best Veggie Burger anywhere I had to try this place  Took wife and younger daughter there today  Great and attentive service thanks Austen  The veggie burger melted in my mouth  Very very tasty Mac N Cheese 2with gruyere and bacon very good as well  Sweet potato fried ordered by my daughter very good  I didnt want you to think I am a total pig by getting Mac N Cheese AND fries  Wife had the BIG salad which was also very good  Place is noisy as mentioned in other review  I will definitely go back  As far as the Trib article proclaiming this Veggie Burger clearly the best I cant say I have had enough of them to agree  But I know the Veggie at Citizen Bar and the Veggie at Atwood Cafe are in the same league

Author: Mayu N.
Content: There were definitely a lot of mixed reviews that I had read which made me rethink my decision to go here but it was late and we were hungry and we didnt want to trek it to Chinatown Yes It is loud in there Was I surprised No I knew what I was getting into The staff the hostess and our server was great They were nice they were informative and were attentive We ordered the chili that was either the special of the day or the special of the week the number 3 and number 6 and a large fry with parmesan and truffle cream and two beers HOLY MOLY The chili was amazing It wasnt your average texmex chili it was almost light and refreshing is that possible it was probably the best chili Ive had in a very long time The number 3 with pastrami and sauerkraut was okay it wasnt my personal favorite The number 6 on the other hand was AMAZING The fries were good but the truffle cream is what made them to die for My boyfriend and I were talking about how the beef was grassfed and their motto is grassfed beef makes the difference and he thought that maybe the other ingredients may be covering up the taste difference I pondered it for a bit but I didnt care that much because I devoured my entire burger The buns were toasted warm I love that Yes the patties do seem a little thin but hey not everything should be 12 pound and 200 The beers were great and before we left we were given two business cards that were each good for one free draft beer Yea its expensive for the burgerfriesbeer meal but is it worth it I think it is

Author: Liz A.
Content: Went back here with a friend on a random Saturday around 3pm We got seated immediately which I was very happy about given my last go round hereWe split two burgers  the Bison Burger w goatcheese  blueberry bbq sauce  some other one which I dont remember I dont remember because all I remember is the blueberry bbq sauce It was so good We were very happy with our experience

Author: Sarah I.
Content: I had very high expectations for DMK after hearing a lot of friends talk about it It was super crowded but we got sat right away since we had a smaller party The tables are kind of close togethera waitress was serving a sauce or aioli to the next table and she dropped it so it went all over the bottom of my pants and shoes as well as the guy next to me I was a server in grad school so I understand when things happen so I wasnt upset about it but I would have asked my manager to take something off the bill She apologized but I was surprised that she didnt take something off or offer us somethingoh wellI really enjoyed the interiordecorations of DMK I went with the 4 Roasted Hatch Green Chili Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack and Smoked Bacon Burgerit was pretty good Ive had better burgers What made it was the delicious bunso yummy The fries were okI prefer Burger Bars burgers and fries

Author: Kevin C.
Content: I set the bar higher than I should have with DMK  People I know have had nothing but good things to say about it  Food was pretty good but not sure that Ill be back  I think I was immediately turned off when the waitress asked if wed been there beforewe hadnt  So the first thing she says is Well we cook all our burgers the same way a little pink in the middle thats the only way they come  Second there are no substitutions  What it says on the menu is the way you get it  So if you want to leave a cheese off a certain burger thats the only change well make  No adding or subtracting toppingsI guess I dont understand why leaving off some onions or mushrooms would be that much of a problemI ended up getting the bison burger with some sort of blueberry BBQ sauce  It was really good but it didnt really fill me up all the way  Made me realize why the burgers are 8Pros Great tasting burgerGood selection of beersFRENCH FRIESDecently priced foodConsBurger was really smallVery loud for dinner at 600pmDisinterested wait staffNo adding or subtracting garnishesNo choice in how the burger is cookedFrench fries are a la carteFood served on these mini plates

Author: Federica L.
Content: Very good burgers and sweet potato fries with lemon tabasco aioli are the bestNice place and awesome playlist

Author: Tal C.
Content: This place has really great burgers great beer and reasonable prices Keep in mind though this is NOT the place to go have a quiet romantic evening This place is loud probably one of the loudest restaurants Ive been to in Chicago even at lunch time So just keep that in mind if you hate noise or not really being able to hear your dining partnerIf youre coming here for dinner expect to wait Sometimes spots open up in the bar where they serve their full menu but generally the wait is long with nowhere to really sit or hang out so wear comfy shoes One thing that I actually really like about this place is that there are often people alone at the bar drinking a beer and having a burger while watching a game Its so loud and everything is so packed and close together that nobody really
