notices if its a Saturday night and youre alone definitely a place Id go if I wanted a burger last minute and had no one to go withTheir burgers are all precreated by the chef so you cant build your own burgers No substitutions but you can take certain things off your burger Im generally a beef lover but I have to say the veggie burger here is SO GOOD I probably go about half and half between the veggie burger and a beef burger The bison burger is also delicious but of course it is because theres goat cheese on it My favorite part of eating here though is the fries First of all I will say I think the fries here are made to be eaten with the sauce that is the flavors dont really work unless you dip each fry into the sauce it comes with The fries alone are good but with the sauces it all comes together The parmesan truffle fries with truffle aioli are to die for I crave them all the time The sweet potato fries with lemon aioli are also really good Those are my favorites Mac and cheese is also great very thick cheese The prices are very reasonable 9 for each burger except the Bison which I think is 11 I usually end up with about 2025 with burger fries a drink and taxtip which is really not bad for the amount of food you get

Author: Tom R.
Content: Extensive 5 oz burger menu with unique and seemingly excellent combinations Fries are ordered separately and also include many different options  salt and pepper sweet potato parmesan truffle etc The beer list is large and somewhat expensive as is their list of signature cocktails The food we ate was all really great Burgers were cooked well fries were delicious beer was coldAll of that being said I was annoyed that they play really good music but its so loud that its difficult to carry on a conversation across the table

Author: Jarret H.
Content: This place is consistent Every time we go we try a different burger and a different set of friesholyguacaioli burger was awesome and you have to either get the sweet potato or gravy fries  Great beer selection and prices are well setno pretentious 16 burgers here

Author: Phillip T.
Content: Went here for lunch with my family I ordered the Patty Melt or the number 9 We also tried out the truffle fries and the sweet potato friesAll the burgers were pretty decent Both of the fries came with their own sauce and both of the fries were good as well although it was a bit dry for me My brother didnt like his and said it was too greasy for him However my biggest gripe was the size of the burgers All of the burgers cost 9 and for a 9 dollar burger they were pretty small If you dont mind the quantity then thats all right but for someone like me who likes getting more bang for his buck it was offsetting for me However they are fillingLoud music and dimmed lights accurately depicts the environment I dont really like loud music but if thats your thing then go for itThere is also a full bar but I didnt try any of alcohol this time

Author: Tom K.
Content: Awesome burgers Creative selections and perfectly cooked Loved the sweet potato fries too And the service was exceptionalAsk for Kelly Shes a sweetheart And if you like beers they offer a huge selection of artisanal beers which the staff know a lot about Had the Lagunitas PILS from California Great taste but not as cold as I would have liked

Author: Sherlock A.
Content: Very courteous and friendly staff  The burgers are done right Loved the breaded deep fried pickles  Good variety of drinks from beer wine and custom mix drinks Cant wait to come back Had a good time

Author: Anna H.
Content: I love this place Burgers are great and its  even better that theyre grassfed I love the bison option which I highly recommend that Good selection of craft beers The sweet potato fries are great I wouldnt get the larger portion for just 2 people next time though Too big Overall great place

Author: Mike T.
Content: Four stars for the food two stars for the noise level which makes any conversation absolutely impossible So the result is three stars When we got in it was a bit difficult to understand who we had to talk to to get a table But although it was a Saturday night and it was pretty packed we got a table for three in 35 minutes Very good The burgers are DELICIOUS and they are not as heavy as the menu description might have you think We also had French fries with truffle cream also delicious and sweet potato fries not so good Good selection of beers and a few good cocktails we had the Geneva one which was all right   Would I go there again Not sure the noise was really impossible And to top it off they even put very loud music They need to do something about this if not they wont have any more of my business

Author: ML T.
Content: Dined here on Saturday 1114  The BF and I were greeted by a very friendly hostess who took our name and said the wait would be about 20 minutes  We went to the bar and ordered drinks notably the Madame Genevas Rhubarb DelightI highly recommend it and I dont even enjoy Gin  The bartender Drew was also very friendly and knowledgable about the drinks and liquors  We were seated after about ten minutes  We ordered the 1 11 Lamb Sweet Potato Fries Mac n Cheese 1 Chocolate Chip Ice Cream Sandwich and Dutch Chocolate Shake  Everything was VERY good  My lamb burger was one of the most delicious and yummy things I have had in a long time  The Mac n Cheese wasnt my favorite not very creamy but that didnt stop me from devouring the entire thing  The desserts were very tasty as well  We went back to the bar after dinner and continued to chat with various staff memebers everyone is so nice and friendly here  We will definitely be back SOON

Author: Jenna M.
Content: This place is right around the corner from where I live so sometimes its nice to go on Sunday night when its not too crowded and its convienent It looks like a night club from the outside and the seating set up is odd to me which I still havent figured out We usually just sit at the bar and talk to the friendly bartenders They have a nice beer selection  its not filled with all those shitty beers that are all the same Ive only tried one kind of burger and it was tasty although Im not sure why they have burgers listed on their menu that are coming soonwhat a tease The macaroni is terrible but the fries are good

Author: Denise E.
Content: One word can really describe DMK average The fries are good and yes the mac and cheese is yummy but DMK does call itselfs a burger bar so how are the burgers The answer my friends is average If they are trying to compete with bruger joints like Kumas Korner they they have missed their mark about a mile and a half Service was fine the atmostphere was also nice and the food just ok If you are in the area and need somewhere to eat the place is fine I just would not go out of my way for DMK

Author: Angela P.
Content: Im definitely a fan of DMK  Food  Burger  Fantastic  Really juicy great flavors  Not the largest sized burger Ive had but I much prefer quality over quantity  They dont allow substitutions of items on the burgers but mine was so good I would trust them to try any combinationTruffle fries  YOUMUSTHAVETHEM  Soooo good  I wish I had ordered more and taken them home  I also cant wait to try the sweet potato fries  The prices were reasonable for the burgers  fries but I thought it was a bit ridiculous to not have free refills of fountain sodas  I also am not a big fan of the large community table  I called a few weeks ago for a carry out order more truffle fries of course but they said they didnt have it going yet  Ill be excited when they get it going since this will be a great dinner option for me on busy days  Overall the food is really good  I look forward to trying some of the other options

Author: Megan G.
Content: Ive been to DMK twice now since its opened and both times got a turkey burger The burger was great the best part of it is the bun Its the perfect amount of bread The fries are also pretty good although the cheese on the cheese fries was not what you would expect I like my cheese baked on the fries this was more like a cheese sauce The beer on tap is great Very different I like it because it forces me to try new beer instead of falling back on my usual plain light They have a great bottle selection as well The bartender will even let you taste the beers on tapLastly the staff here is amazing Both times the server was extremely nice and attentive Even when it is super busy they are great

Author: Kellyn W.
Content: Im a gal who loves to put an onion ring on a burger so the fact that the 2 came with chilirubbed onion straws was a major selling point for me I like my burgers to be medium  exactly the way that DMK prepared them  but beware that you cant specify how welldone youd like it to be cooked Portion size was perfect although plate size was oddly small and my roommate and I shared small orders of the fried pickles  okra sweet potato fries and parmesan truffle fries The fried pickles were by far the standout side dish  the sweet potato fries were standard fare and the parmesan truffle fries left a little something to be desired Its good to note that they do have a few solid vegetarian burger options though the fries are prepared in beef fat Not my favorite burger place in the city but Id definitely go back

Author: David P.
Content: DMK offers a wide range of gourmet burgers and fries reasonably priced too  The space is long and narrow creating that iconic loud bar noise throughout the restaurant which kinda makes a fun atmosphere  In addition to the variety of burgers they have a large beer selection too just stay away from the cocktails they are on the smaller side and a little over pricedI get the 5 8 which consists of a burger with prosciutto fontina pesto red bell peppers and salt  vinegar chips  To pair with that I get the parmesan and truffle oil fries 2 which are to die for  My buddy gets the 14 which is a salmon burger with ginger scallions asian slaw and a curry sauce  I will definitely be getting it next timeAside from the loud shouts of the sports loving male Lakeview crowd this place is fantastic  Ive gone three times and every time I have to get the same burger and fries  Perfect for a group of friends or a significant  just dont expect an intimate dinner have fun

Author: Kate G.
Content: This place is AMAZING My dad found this place and took the whole family there and Im really glad he did Im a very picky eater and when it comes to burgers I usually just go for the classic with regular toppings When I saw the unique menu I was a bit nervous My family agreed to each order a different burger so we could taste them all so I picked the number 3 knowing I wouldnt have to eat it if I didnt like it This burger had pastrami and sauerkraut on it This is something I never would have ordered on my ownLong story short after taking the first bite I guarded that thing with my life It was possibly one of the best burgers I had EVER I didnt want to share it anymore It was delicious We also had cheese fries and fried pickles as appetizers and both were very good I cant wait to go back to this place I highly recommend it to anyoneeven picky eaters like me

Author: Jeremy S.
Content: Since I support grass fed beef I gave this place a try  Its a sleek loungelike type of bar  The place was surprisingly busy for a late afternoon lunch on a weekday  It must be a cool place for young professionals to have a beer with lunch  I wasnt impressed with the beer selection but I like my beer cheap  They had a decent selection of micro brews but since they didnt have Busch I had a cokeFOOD They have lots of unique gourmet burgers but I ordered a plain old cheeseburger  It was yummy  Didnt taste too different than corn fed beef but the i guess the juices were not as thick  The toasted bun was what really made it though  It makes my top 3 burgers of all time and it better because it was 8 bucks before the fries

Author: Chris M.
Content: This place was awesome First time trying it on a whim canceled reservations at a restaurant downtown to come here and we were not disappointed We started out with deviled egg appetizers which were outstanding My wife has the expresso shake and she said it was the best shake she had ever hadand she has had a few She had the salmon burger and I had the 1 and we ordered both the Parmesan fries and sweet potato fries and both had great taste I would highly recommend this especially for lunch where it wasnt crowded but there were plenty of people having a great time

Author: Eric G.
Content: I had a nice meal at DMK this past Sunday Aside from the mouthwatering burger the best part about my experience was not having to wait for a seat I went with the number one All the flavors played together nicely As I looked over my shoulder to catch the score from the Bears game I noticed the chalk board by the bar saying that the burger special was a Bison Burger It was too late to change my order but I want to try that if it is available the next time I return It sounded delicious

Author: Brendan M.
Content: I was running errands in the area and remembered driving by this place  I had to check it out  Walking in I noticed the nice modern design and was greeted pleasantly by the staff  Although I did not have any alcoholic beverages on this lunch trip I was very impressed with their beer selectionThe bartender was extremely friendly and helpful and recommended I grab the 1 with their sweet potato fries  I have eaten many great burgers in Chicago and DMK is one of them  Great all around experienceI will be back for more

Author: Fiz H.
Content: DMK you are overall a great burger place with amazing sweet potato fries and good mac n cheeseyour meat is also really good and your cheese i loved the lamb burger as wellBUT some people love spicy shit on their burgers and you are greatly lacking in this category your green peppery sauce or whatever was super bland and kind of disgusting MY ONLY COMPLAINT IS THAT YOU GOTTA GET SOME JALAPENOS ON THEM BURGERS that would make my burger perfect

Author: Brandon L.
Content: AMAZING food Im not much of a burger guy but this place is the truth Any thing that you can dream of going on a burger they do it with the most amazing combinations you could think ofAlso they have several different style fries to choose fromThe service is great Ive been there multiple times with different servers and each one knows the food and drink menu so well

Author: Michael P.
Content: 2010 the year of the Burger Bar in Chicago To be completely honest my first experience at DMK burger was not a positive one I hated it actually I went when it first opened and it was a mob scene to get in After over an hour wait for a table we had ordered a variety of burgers and pretty much all the fries and sides available Nothing seemed worth the trouble it was to get seatedAfter many conversations with other people and my consistent bitching to their praises I decided to give DMK another shot I couldnt be happier that I did I tend to go elsewhere after I have a bad experience in a restaurant Theres over 10000 places to eat in the city of Chicago and I work too hard to throw my money away in any of them I dont know if the food and service improved after time or the fact that the longest youll wait to get a table is now 15 minutes since the hype died down but DMK has been a great goto place for a burger and a beer after work or on the weekend for lunchWith a pretty good variety of different burgers and fries you can go back many many times before youve had everything on the menu But my biggest pleasure at DMK is their special shakes Not quite sure when it started but as of last October when they started pushing a special October pumpkin shake Ive tried to get in there at least once a month for whatever shake is being served The pumpkin shake is one of the best I EVER had Packed full of pumpkin flavor and topped with pumpkin seeds it was like pumpkin pie in a glass I only wish it were available year round I must have gone in 5 or 6 times for that shake in October and just when I thought I had the best shake ever made they introduced the Gingerbread cookie dough shake in December Im pretty sure there was crack in it cuz I went back time and time again until New Years Eve I cant wait to see what 2011 bringsThe food is great the service is friendly and its not too bad on the wallet either Now that the trendy crowd has moved onto whatevers next in burger places DMK is a great place for a burger and a beer

Author: T.R. M.
Content: I like this placeWe were looking for a place to have a late lunch that was cozy with comfort food and was outside of our own hood  We needed a change from our usual spots and I remembered our waitress at one of our other local spots telling us that her roommate worked at DMK Burger Bar aaaand she mentioned that they had sweet potato fries too  this enticed me I suggested it to the hubs and he quickly agreedIt was nice bc we could watch the Bears game and it wasnt too loud or too crowded  so we could actually enjoy lunchWe started off with a wedge salad to share AWESOME bacon   but next time Im gonna ask to go easy on the dressingThen I ordered a 2 and he ordered a 4  with a small sweet pot fries to splitthen he added Mac and cheese 1 at the last minute  I am not sure if I am happy that he ordered the Mac n cheese or upset with him because it was DELICIOUS  but with each bite I was envisioning every extra lunge and crunch I had to do with my trainer the next day to work off my moment of weaknessThe burger satisfied my need for comfort food blue cheese and crispy onions yummo  He loved the mix of toppings on his  especially the fried egg and hot peppers  The fries were great too  We were stuffed and had to box up more than half of the mac n cheese  It was a nice side with our dinner the next night  and still just as delicious as beforeI had a 3 Floyds beer a nod to our last name and my hubbys hometown    Our ONLY request  please add some nonalcoholic beers to the list  With such an extensive beer list cant be too hard to add 1 or 2  Even non drinkers enjoy a burger and a Bears game oh well  hubs had to settle for a diet coke other than that   4 thumbs up

Author: Joe G.
Content: This place had very tasty burgers  I really liked the burgers and the sides  Next time I go I want to try the drink list  As it was I was about to hit the road to drive for a few hours so I chose not to drink  Anyways here are the basicsFood We had the Mac  Cheese second option with bacon and onions  It was very tasty and was great to share between 4 people  Id definitely recommend it  We also shared the Parmesan Truffled Fries  Also delicious  The dipping sauce with those was amazing  Of the regular burgers I had the 2 a burger topped with blue cheese and crispy onions  amazing and would go back just to eat it again and my wife had the 1 a burger with bacon and BBQ sauce again she thought it was amazing and Id probably try that one next time  The couple we were with had the Sunday specials  He liked his the nonburger option but she thought her turkey burger had too many spices going on a distracted her from the flavors of the other parts of the meal  This was the only complaint anyone had about the foodAmbiance I loved the space  It was very well done and felt appropriate for the food we were eating and definitely made us feel like this was the experience they wanted to haveAnyways Ill definitely go back for more

Author: Ricky B.
Content: This burger place is amazing  Most all burgers are 8 and they are speciality at that  I had the 1 burger  Bacon cheddar cheese and caramelized onions with BBQ sauce  The customer service was impeccable and the host staff visited our table several times  There are 56 different kinds of fries there and it was hard to choose from I finally chose after much debate between two kinds  I chose the Parmesan fries with truffle sauce  When then food was delivered the wait staff included a free side of the other fries i was choosing from  cheddar cheese fries and scallions  The service is amazing and the food is effin awesome  Even better is that everyday they take some of their portions of proceeds and donate it to local charities  That just screams awesome to meAwesome job DMK Burger Bar

Author: John R.
Content: I think the atmosphere is kinda lame But that totally depends on the person It is kind of clubbar feel which I think is lame for a burger joint But whateverMy burger was good and the fries were pretty tasty Would I rather have this place than the Counter I think the Counter takes the edge

Author: Joshua H.
Content: DMK is a good spot for a burger  Two things keeping it from being 5 star 1 Price for quantity  2 AtmosphereServiceKeep in mind that 3 stars is a good rating  The burgers are good but nothing that will blow your mind  Fries are also good  Ice cream cookies are a pretty good way to wrap up dinner  It is hard to beat a place like Kumas Corner as a burger joint  I would compare DMK to The Counter but a bit more louder literally it is loud in thereI always feel like they try to rush you from your table once you finish your last bite  I get it   The place is small and they are busyIn short I think it is worth a try but isnt a place I die to go back to

Author: Sarah G.
Content: Im shocked this place only has 35 stars but its okay by me because if it keeps this place from getting too popular and keeps me waiting no more than 10 minutes for my table I dont careBEST BURGERSKumas is great but Im sorry Im putoff by the hugeness of the burger I can never finish mine and when I do I regret it My mouth isnt big enoughAt DMK its all done just right The patties are thin but not ridiculously so I say its just right because I can actually fit the thing in my mouth The fries are to DIE for hand cut dontcha know tooIve had almost every burger on the menu and I have NEVER been disappointed with the very rare exception of their breakfast burger turns out I dont like egg on a burgerBut the service is always speedy no matter how busy it is and every server Ive ever had has been friendly accommodating and allaround awesome The bill by the end is always reasonable and I love their beer listHow can you NOT love this place Ive been there AT LEAST 10 times and Ill keep coming back

Author: Chris B.
Content: Great burgers here loved them but not quite the best in town I love the many options they give you for making burgers and they have grass fed beef look it up its better for you than corn fedAtmosphere was different I dont know if it was hipster or trendy but seemed to be one of those kinds of places We sat at the bar lunch on a Saturday and ordered there The bartenders were nice always attentive

Author: Dan A.
Content: 5 stars for food 35 each for value and atmosphereI recently moved to Chicago 6weeks ago and decided to try DMK after a friend recommended it Ive now been back three additional times Twice in one weekend while my girlfriend was visiting I took her here for a burger on a Friday night and she loved it so much that when I offered to take her out for a nice dinner on Saturday she instead demanded that we go back to DMK ironically see you tomorrow appears at the bottom of the receiptFlavorful gourmetish grassfed burgers an aboveaverage beer list and speedy friendly serviceUnderstandably busy on the weekends so keep that in mind We waited 2030min each night Also not the best burger joint for for a date Its remarkably loud due to the hard wallsdecor and minimal space between tables

Author: Kelly M.
Content: I would live here if they let me  First off cutely decorated kind of minimalist but they get giant kudos from me for their logo a burger designed inside the Chicago flag it warms my heart  Secondly the staff is always superpolite always smiling and happy to serve you and just generally nice people  The bartender once gave us deviled eggs on the house while we were waiting at the bar for another friend to show up to be seated  Doesnt hurt that the bartender is nice eye candy Moving on to most important part the food  I have been to this place so many times yet can still spend 30 minutes or more just staring at the menu trying to choose just one option  These burgers are unlike anything else  They are not the giant badassmamajamas from Kumas that practically require you to unhinge your jaw to take a bite out of but nor are they your typical pub burger  Theyre all really creative with different flavors and toppings youre unlikely to see anywhere else my favorite is a bison burger topped with goat cheese and blueberry BBQ sauce Yeah blueberry BBQ sauce  amazing  Unadventurous people who think burgers should only be topped with cheese lettuce pickles onions mustard and ketchup should stick with going to Wendys because youd be wasting these nice peoples time  The burgers are a bit on the smaller size which means for me totally realistic to actually finish them unlike other burger places  All the meat is grassfed beef which makes a world of difference  Im not sure what type of bun they use I usually prefer a pretzel bun but theyre quite tasty and add the right amount of texture  Lastly the fries OMG the fries  I dream about their parmesan fries paired with truffle mayo  Truffle is like crack it will be the best thing youve ever tasted  The sweet potato fries  with lemon tabasco aioli are another favorite  Im not a huge ice cream fan but Ive heard from many sources that their ice cream shakes are amazing as well  Their beer list is pretty expansive as well and includes all of my local favorites like HalfAcre Two Brothers and Goose IslandId recommend coming here on a weeknight and the earlier the better  Its pretty popular and can have a really long wait time later in the evening and especially on weekends  Well worth the wait though

Author: J V.
Content: DMK tries too hard to be Kumas  Yes the ingredients used in their burgers are very fresh and I like that they serve milkshakes  but the weird community tables especially if you sit next to the rudest pickiest dramatic couple like we did makes the experience incredibly uncomfortableWe ended up at DMK on Halloween because Kumas Corner was closed  Like I said the food is very fresh tasting but a lot of the burgers are very very similar to Kumas corner but not in a good way  In a worse way  If  a restaurant is going to try to oneup one of the best burger places in the city  it needs to be 3 or 4 times better than what we had  The burgers are sandwich size and the meal in general ends up feeling like an expensive snack not a meal  I had an espresso milk shake  It was decent  I did not like the onion fries that we ordered  There is a decent beer list tooWe had 4 different servers and the server that was officially our server never actually brought us anything which was really confusing  We also sat at this large community table  The couple next to us was dramatic and rude  It was uncomfortable for us to have to listen to and witness their theatrics about the food being bad not having the condiments on the side in specific containers they requested the server bringing them a huge ice cream cookie sandwich for free and the couple complained about that too arguing about what kind of tip  they should leave etc   I dont really understand these type of seating arrangements unless you sit at a bar  I give major props to the servers that helped this couple because the servers handled this difficult couple with a lot of professionalism   Side rant  No matter how bad the service or food is I never throw a fit and also overtip by at least 25  No matter what  I have been a server and I know what it is like to deal with people who literally want everything for free and will be unhappy with everything no matter what  I will probably not be going back to DMK because I dont think the food is worth it and I dont want to sit at a community table with divas again  The ice cream cookie sandwich looked really good though

Author: Vivian T.
Content: I like to consider myself something of a veggie burger aficionado and HANDS DOWN DMK has one of the best veggie burgers Ive ever had Easily It was juicy and flavorful with texture and the right combination of ingredients  Also one of my other favorite things in the world is SWEET POTATO FRIES  Nothing makes me happier DMKs were good and comes with a lemon tabasco dipping sauce  My friend and I also shared the parmesean fries with a TRUFFLE cream sauce  I dont need to say more truffle Yes pleaseGreat burger choices great side choices great french fries choices  Atmosphere is clean and simple nothing fancy or that cool or hip but it works I guess If you like good food then go If youre looking for a fun atmosphere might not be it

Author: Beth W.
Content: Definitely my favorite burger spot in Chicago The last 2 times Ive been my husband and I split the 1 and 2 burgers because theyre just so good we cant choose I hear the lamb as well as the veggie burgers are delicious and need to try them I just get there and my mouth starts watering for the first two Also the parmesan truffle fries will blow your mind Love the sweet potato fries too If youre with a group get a few different kinds and share Husband loves all of the beer selections  and I love the Sweet Tea Revisited cocktail Great place to meet up with friends They dont take reservations and its usually pretty busy  but be patient Most of the time you can stand by the bar and grab a drink snag a stool when one opens up and then you can go ahead and order The bartenders are great at making sure youre taken care of if you want to eat dinner Otherwise enjoy the company of your friends over a drink or two and wait for your table Only complaint is that the music is pretty loud so you usually feel like youre yelling to have conversations And no Im not an old lady

Author: Reginice C.
Content: Grass fed beefI had a turkey burger melt and the fries with the truffle sauceYummm It tasted oh so goodIt was not a 5star experience because the waitress we had was never there and did not check on us we had to hunt somebody down

Author: Q M.
Content: 1 Gumballhead on tap  yaes2 The Holy GuacAioli burger IS that good Get it Unless youre not for spicy because it kind of is2b The 1 Burger with the BBQ sauce and bacon was tasty Compared to the Holy Guac it was merely tasty but I bet it was pretty good if I werent comparing it to a delicious burger with chorizo and guac on it Really you cant top that 3 Others have mentioned issues with the size of the burger and the service a My burger was a satisfying size I didnt have to unbotton my pants after I ate which is probably a good thing b Our service was just fine

Author: Dave S.
Content: DMK gets four stars for the good service and great burgers made from grassfed beef  Its not a perfect restaurant thoughFirst the tables are WAY too close together  That plus the fact that the back wall is literally completely blank means that the person unlucky enough to not be sitting in the booth seat has nowhere to look other than directly at the person sitting across from them which could make for a pretty awkward experience if youre on a bad first date or something luckily we didnt have that problemSecond the lights are really really dim  Combine that with the fact that the menus are printed on brown paper and you get a menu that is comically difficult to read  I was practically crosseyed by the time I figured out what I wanted to orderLastly the salt and pepper fries were waaaay overcooked  I like crispy fries but these were just plain burntAs I said though the burgers are fantastic so I can definitely see myself going back especially if they turn up the lights and buy a few posters to put on the wall

Author: Stephanie M.
Content: Went on Sunday night at ten oclock and the place was PACKED Service was great I explored the menu a little more than I usually would this time for whatever reason We started with the deviled eggs which I wont be getting from here again but I was curious I ordered the 4 burger we each got an order of fries my friend got the truffle fries and I the blue cheese bacon fries we ordered the mac and cheese 2 between us and we each got the cinnamon toast crunch milkshake to take away I love this food I love these owners These two concepts of Fish Bar and DMK are both just how I believe neighborhood restaurants should be  So fabulous

Author: Jacqueline O.
Content: so disappointed in their burgers  While their fries were great but with Burger in their name I expected better burgers  Love the options but the patty was lacking  Could not order it rare or medium rarethey only cook it one wayMusic was much too loud

Author: Natrina C.
Content: AWESOME burgers Did I say AWESOME Yep just that awesome I ordered the 1 on my first visit burger with aged cheddar bacon onions I eliminated the onions and BBQ sauce on a perfect potato bun I ordered a turkey burger on another visit Both times I added half order of sweet potato fries and half order of parmesan Can you say foodgasm With all of the traveling I do my palate has enjoyed some really great burgers Well over a year later this is the burger that I think about and compare all others to Five stars indeed

Author: K W.
Content: This were featured on Food Network and the burgers looked amazing My friends and I ate dinner here and I didnt think the burgers were all that good Ive definitely had better burgers

Author: Will S.
Content: Excellent service good taps and a great bottle selection I had the days 15 which nailed it on flavor but visually left something to be desired Fries were a bit thin and left me wanting more but the onion straws were on point delicate light crisp I imagine weekend and prime night waits are lengthy like the majority of reviews here say but sit at the bar on a weeknight and youll be rewarded handsomely for your offpeak visit

Author: Denise S.
Content: This place has the best burgers in the city The burger menu is creative great selection of fries and there is a wonderful selection of beers Try the fried pickles and okra  great appetizer

Author: Kerry H.
Content: Im really surprised at the abundance of subpar reviews I think the burgers here are fantastic My only qualm with it was the noise level The music was really loud good selection of tunes but just too loud for my late lunch taste Aside from that the food was terriffic and the service was great Our server was very knowledgable and friendly Also very quick and efficient My husband had the bison burger with pickled onions goat cheese and a blueberry BBQ sauce I was going to order it too but was not really feelin the idea of a blueberry bbq i was so wrong That burger knocked it out of the park Flavors like crazy The meat was so juicy I ordered the grass fed beef burger with bacon balsamic onions and cheddar amazing The bun was really nice not a pretzel bun and not a brioche more like a soft ciabatta but could have been a little more substantial it got  soggy pretty quickly but even a slightly soggy bun couldnt detract from the overwhelming awesomeness of these burgers We also got an order of the hand cut fries with wisconsin cheddar and scallions so good Still able to be crispy under what felt like a quart of homemade cheese sauce and sliced scallions I do have to say yes it is a higher priced burger than i would normally get but here youre not paying for quantity youre paying for quality The grass fed beef has such an amazing clean flavor and it definitely gets enhanced not covered by its toppings Overall great experience at DMK we will be back

Author: Billie R.
Content: Loved loved loved it I could have eaten my weight in fries with Parmesan and Truffle Cream The mac n cheese with carmalized onions and bacon was superb and my burger holy moly I got the burger with Pastramie and Gruyere cheese I usually have food envy and my friends burger looked good but I couldnt be happier with mine Also had the deviled eggs they were okay but mac and cheese came at the same time so I couldnt really give them much of my attention Cant wait to try the Holy Gaucaioli burger next

Author: David G.
Content: I gave this place a second chance after a very mediocre first visit and DMK deliveredService 5 starsThe primary reason this place is receiving 4 starts instead of 3 is the service It was OUTSTANDING Read my previous reviews my biggest complaint about Chicago restaurants is the typical garbage service DMK completely bucked the trend Granted it was an off peak time period Monday night but it genuinely felt like the staff was grateful for your business I know a shocker in this city During our dining experience the service was attentive generous accommodating and helpful I honest to God cant believe I am saying this but 5 stars for the serviceFood 3 stars The fries are ridiculously good best part of the meal hands down I typically dont enjoy sweet potato fries but these changed my mind The dipping sauce that accompanies them is fantastic The onion strings were also a surprise Very thin crispy and tasty The burgers are average It is almost like the burgers need more seasoning or something Even with bacon a fried egg and green chilis my burger was still rather bland If you are a normal size dude get a double 3 extra or you wont be full The bun is not a pretzel bun but is an excellent change of pace from it There are better burgers in the city without a doubt especially given the priceDrinks Be aware they serve their soft drinks in a can No refills As for the beer I didnt have any but the rest of my party seemed pleased with the list Bottom line Excellent service slightly above average food but will not become a regular place for me

Author: Sam M.
Content: Best burgers Ive had so far in Chicago and an awesome atmosphere Great location and good staff  Nothing bad to say about this place but get here early on a Friday or Saturday  Having a beer while waiting for a table isnt the worst thing in the world though  If youre coming to Chicago go DMK Burger Bar

Author: Joel M.
Content: This place gets really busy on the weekend so definitely keep that in mind Quite a few of us went here for a friends birthday and the burgers were great and the beer selection was very interesting as well  Id definitely go back again

Author: Mike D.
Content: This place was highly anticipated and I think Michael Kornick got it right I went here for lunch the second day it was open and right from the start I was greeted by Kornick himself The menu is well crafted and I had a hard time deciding which burger to choose but I went with 2 a burger with chili onion strings blue cheese and chipotle ketchup My girlfriend got the turkey burger and we got the cheddar fries and parmesan truffle fries My burger was cooked to perfection and each ingredient blended well The buns especially were a nice touch as they are toasted and perfectly sized for the burger The turkey burger was good as well but they really shine with their beef As for the friesif you are familiar with the truffle fries at MK these are very similar and amazing I was not as impressed with the cheddar fries which were very reminiscent of Weiner Circle cheese fries With at least 5 different fries to choose from it leaves numerous options for mixing and matching  Another thing DMK does well is drinks They carry Boylans sodas as well as a few they make themselves I tried the cherry and blood orange of which the blood orange really stood out The beer list is also very appealing with some really good local craft brews and the cocktails sounded quite intoxicating I will say the wait staff was not the most attentive and service was quite slow but hopefully that will improve the longer they are open I will definitely come back to DMK again and will make a point to try dessert as their shakes and ice cream sandwiches looked devilishly good At 1015 for a gourmet burger and fries its not too expensive at all and you will leave feeling satisfied

Author: KO B.
Content: I live right around the corner and finally got around to trying the Burger Bar today  Really interesting place  Its on the brink of being a really awesome place  Great atmosphere  There were a lot of tables but we werent jammed in despite the place being completely full  It was very loud but I like it that way  You wouldnt want to go there for a quiet mealThe menu was very big but doesnt have many food options  Lots and lots of beer which is good  Cocktails and wine too  They have a cocktail called Chase the Green Fairy which features absinthe which is coolAs for the food very good  My girlfriend and I ordered a shake and a homemade cherry soda  Id like to see them call it pop since we are in Chicago but thats a small detail  The shake was great the pop was very bland  They had a couple other flavors but I wont bother again  We started with an order of fried okra and pickles  Came with a dill ranch dipping sauce  I loved these my girlfriend wasnt impressed though  We also each got an order of friends  This is what shined most  The fries were fresh cut and very tasty  I had the WI cheddar fries and my girlfriend has the sweet potato fries  Each was a very good size but they should be since the burgers dont come with any sides  If I were coming here for a few drinks I could order just the friesWe ordered number 1 which was a bacon onion bbq burger with cheddar  I asked for it medium since I was sharing  I was told they only cook them one way and its medium plus  I didnt argue but next time when its my burger I will push to have it done medium rare  You cant tell people you are a burger joint and then not cook it the way they want it done  Im sure they will bend on this before longThats pretty hypercritical for a 4 star review I know but it got 4 stars because I will definitely be going back  They are trying to be trending a cool and they have done a good job  Its a cool place that is lots of fun

Author: Kate L.
Content: Yummy yummy yummy  The bubs stumbled upon this place late last week amp we stopped by for lunch this afternoon  The burgers were tasty  I had the standard 8 lettuce tomato onion pickles amp mayo  Truffle fries were well truffle fries at every new spot that pops up in the city but delicious nonetheless  We ended the meal with an ice cream sandwich  The individual components were good but the cookies were too hard for us to be able to get both cookie amp ice cream in one bite   A few thoughts1 The music is loud  We went during lunch when it was busy but not packed and still had a hard time hearing each other 2 Our waitress was friendly knowledgable and attentiveand completely ignored personal space boundaries  Im not exaggerating when I say that she touched me during every single visit to the table  Its one thing if youre my best friend or my grandma but having a woman rub my back during lunch is juststrangeKeep your hands to yourself and your music at a reasonable volume and were in business

Author: Christopher E.
Content: DMK was a lot of fun and had very good burgers Absolutely try it out We started out with the fried pickles and okra They were crispy not too oily and crunchy Nice job I had the 1 burger which is red onions and BBQ sauce Really great burger The style of this burger is a very thin patty which was fine by me because you can eat the entire burger without feeling too full after unlike other recently opened burger places The flavor was great bun was excellent Dont miss the cheese fries All in all this place is a great time with very good burgers in the thinpatty stiyle Well done Try it out and have a great time

Author: Melissa W.
Content: And I had such high hopesService Poor  The bartender whom we visited to get through the 30 minute wait did his job well with a very nononsense attitude  As in no smile no hello no enjoyjust  what do you want and heres your tab  The waitress was on the border of rude and arrogant  Had little time to discuss the menu at all and couldnt spare a moment to check back on us throughout the entire meal as in no water refills no 2nd round of drinks  It wasnt busy enough to justify this type of poor service  And when asked to REMOVE an item from a burger her canned response was No Substitutions  The food took 35 minutes to come up  which to me is way too long when they only have 30 other customers and nothing can be modified on the menu at allFood If you are going to call yourself a burger bar then you had better bring it w the burgers They didnt  The burgers are cooked to one temp only medium which turns out to be well unfortunately  The patties are pretty thin w little seasoning  The buns are overwhelmingly bready  The toppings are lack luster and uninspired  Been there done that and had it a million times better  I would venture to say that the burgers at Red Robbin are more lovingly crafted  On the other hand the side dishes were fantastic  Fried okra  awesome  Cheese fries  awesome  It is the side dishes and the drinks that took this from a one star to a two star placeValue Poor  For what it is this place is over priced  I would not recommend and will not return

Author: Tim R.
Content: I would rate this a BB burger  I had the 2 with fried onion strings and blue cheese  For a thin patty style burger I thought is was well cooked you do not order temp but it was not over cooked  The parmtrufle fries were awesome  I also tried my friends sweet potato fries and they were great as wellService was a solid BMy only issue was the fact that all burgers do not come with lettuce tomato and onion  When my burger came with no lettuce or tomato I did not want to wait so just ate as is  Also no mustard or ketchup on the table  Final WTF  We ordered the chocolate chip cookie ice cream sandwich B but how do you screw this one up and a couple people ordered coffee but they do not have any hot beverages  What  Get a coffee machine DMK  Also had the fried okra and pickles which were very goodOverall good burger and fries but I did not love the a la carte menu including 175 can of coke

Author: Andy S.
Content: I went here for dinner with a couple friends on a whim as none of us had been there before and they were looking for burgers We went on a Friday night around 9 and got seated immediately It was however extremely loud inside and difficult to hear each other or the serverOn its own merit the meal was good the burger was a bit thin for my taste I prefer a thicker juicier cut these are flattish though flavorful and the fries were quite good 5 varieties are available However I feel compelled to compare it to other burger focused restaurants and on that front I think it falls short Both Kumas and Bad Apple have a better burger thicker more flavor offer a pretzel roll my favorite kind of bread for a burger and have a much larger selection of beer in brewery as well as type

Author: Ash K.
Content: Fantastic from start to finish Loved every minute of it From the freshly baked bun to the well cooked burger and the truffle parm fries I went here on a Sunday night and my party of 4 was seated right away Started with the Orange soda Also made inhouse and ordered the Lamb burger Others on the table ordered the 2 Burger was moist and very tasty it went by too fast Next time I am going to add a patty just so I can be full The girls however were stuffed with jus the single pattyMy lamb burger was moist and exactly how a lamb sandwich should taste with Taziki and lots of olive oil I also tried their regular burger and it was just as tasty Next time I am going to order a burger and add an extra patty They dont have refills here plus that much orange soda cant be good for ya  so i opted for Diet coke Overall I wouldnt compare this to Five Guys burger as this is a higher quality burger and definitely one of my favorites I have yet to try Kuma as the long wait times turn me off Some suggestions would be  to keep a Ketchup bottle on every table   increase the qty of table fries   lets customers add more toppings with little or no upcharge  free refillsPeace and love

Author: Darragh B.
Content: Great place Stopped in last night with our 2yearold Ended up sitting at the bar and were glad we did Food came fast Service was great They even brought the little one out a cupcakeBurgers were pretty amazing Got 2 different kinds of fries and the onion strings We liked everything Beer selection gave me a headachenot last night but this morningWell definitely go back

Author: Becca K.
Content: Very much enjoyed itI split a 1  4 with a friend also got two sets of fries Wisconsin cheddar  scallions  Parmesan  truffle cream Both burgers were really juicy but not too heavy  which I prefer and probably has to do with the fact that their beef is grass fed Theyre a lot smaller than youd expect but still very filling The buns are really soft Yay Id go back to try the other burgers for sure You can also add on a fried egg or chili or etc for a little bit more  which is nice Theyre also coming out with a breakfast burger starting the 8th of January I def wanna see how that plays out

Author: Celeste C.
Content: I was underwhelmed to say the least  If I wanted a mediocre burger that was somehow soggy and flavorless I would have stayed home and made my own burger  But I didnt  I went to DMK  And then I regretted it  The wait was long the music was way too loud to even hold a conversation over and the food was mostly overpriced but mediocre  Except I give props for the cheese fries  Unfortunately  its gonna take more than cheese fries to win me over  I think at one point during dinner I legitimately pouted  Like a child  You want a burger you go to The Counter

Author: Sj S.
Content: DMKyum  Ive been there five times since it opened so I feel comfortable reviewing Good a  Food delicious and reasonably priced  Burgers are WAY more interesting than a typical burger joint  My favorites 4 and 9  The ability to add a fried egg to any burger for 1  YES PLEASE THE SWEET POTATO FRIES ARE SO GOOD  So crispy and sweetsalty So are the Wisconsin cheese fries  Parmesan and truffle arefine  Highly recommend the onion and bacon maccheese  The ice cream sandwichamazingId go there just for that  b  Drink selection  Every beer you could want  Good cocktails tooc  Nice friendly funny staff  Ive never been unhappy with service  Bada  Very very crowded and they dont take reservations  If youre hungry this isnt a good lastminute place to go because you will have to wait  The place is pretty small so it can feel cramped b  Loud music  loud talkers  screaming across the table  Definitely not a place for large groups

Author: Diana C.
Content: My inlaws took me here for an early lunch and though I was concerned by the description I had the breakfast burger with turkey sausage poached egg potatoes and maple aioli  I was concerned about Maple syrup  mayo but it turned out just to be maple syrup  Its suppose to come with bacon but I ordered mine withoutIt was so delicious  I personally love the sweet and salty combo so this breakfast burger was amazing  The fries and onion strings were good as wellI was a little annoyed they dont serve coffee since I didnt really want a milk shake or a beer with breakfast  I dont mind the no substitutions policy though there were a few burgers that looked good except for the blue cheese  I dont like stinky cheeses

Author: kay m.
Content: Patty melt was wonderful not too big just enough Order with a side of sweet potato fries Great beer selection Our server was helpful and made great recommendations for us We left happy and satisfied It was actually refreshing not to feel stuffed not to feel like we just ate a side of beef and had to be rolled out the door  Great burgersAtmosphere a bit loud for my liking and dining neighbors a bit to close  A short wait but worth it Looking forward to my next burger

Author: Rahul G.
Content: This place was fantastic  Maybe 5 of the burgers looked amazing and I could only pick one  I got the triple DMK because I was feeling zealous and it was fantastic  My server was awesome and friendly  They have a HUGE selection of beer and a full bar  They were playing lion king on their big screens for most of my dinner and who doesnt love lion king  So that was a huge plusThe burger itself was phenominal  We got these breaded pickles of some sort  fantastic  Just ask a server about them and Im sure they will know what you are talking about  I fully recommend this place and plan on returning time and time again

Author: George A.
Content: A friend and I went for the first time last night We were really hungry and wanted something quick Considering it is not a fast food place we decided to try it out anyway I was surprised at how soon we got our food The burger and fries were great But what I was really impressed with was the service Everyone was incredibly nice and welcoming We sat at the bar and both bartenders were always checking in with us As we sat there a waitress who was waiting on drinks for her table asked how we were doing We were kinda taken back because at most establishments no one cares about you if youre not tipping them During our meal another waitress brought us extra condiments and didnt seem bothered by it Staff at other places would seem annoyed if someone from another section would dare stop them for something Overall the food was good not the best but I would definitely come back for the service alone Although one thing I would suggest turn down the music Its a bit too loud

Author: Ashley D.
Content: I went to the DMK in Oakbrook todayI walked in and was immediately confused I was expecting over the counter service instead we got terrible table service All of the servers looked like they just rolled out of bed and threw on some hipster outfit for work Ive never been to a restaurant or any business for that matter where there wasnt SOME type of professional uniform There were girls in jeans and a guess top to guys in black pants and a button down They all had tattoos that were in plain view and blinded you should probably be covered up at work I am pretty sure the 4 families that were in there regretted bringing their children there for lunch Never been in a restaurant where all of the female servers walk around with their hair flowing all over the place Probably the reason why I found one in my patty melt As I soaked in the gloomy confusing decor I started to look at the menu You pay 8 for just the burger reasonable only because they claim it was grass fed beef But the fries I paid 4 for like 15 fries that had parmesan and parsley on them FANCY Oh and they came out 8 minutes after our burgers did The food was good but nothing special and definitely not worth 12 The restaurant resembles an underground train station or trendy retail space with some clubby looking booths and spooky lamp shades Between the blaring music and all of the servers hanging out in their street clothes it was hard for me to imagine this restaurant lasting longer than a year in Oakbrook Especially with Labriola across the street

Author: Renne H.
Content: Ate there this weekend and while the food was great the service was lacking  I joined my party late and when the server noticed I was an addition she did come over and asked if I needed a menu or a drink and I said yes and that Id have a glass of water  She cam back wi a highball glass of warm tap water  I looked on either side of me and people had pint glasses of ice water and I looked at my friends and we started laughing  I ordered the Mac and cheese 2 which was great and then I asked the server for a tall glass of ice water and she gave me a how dare you kind of look  Its not like I asked her to fly to France and get me Evian from the tapLike I said the food was good but the service and this server were subpar

Author: Ken Z.
Content: GREAT burger I had a double patty cheddar balsamic onion bacon  bbq Very juicy Full of flavor One of the best burgers Ive ever tasted Sweet potato fries were good Though you can get those anywhere Place had a cool vibe friendly bartenders and fun drink menu But really its mostly about the burger Just damn tasty

Author: Amanda M.
Content: Prefer this place over Kumas Much tastier and unique flavors Their assortment of fries are also delicious

Author: Christine M.
Content: I went for dinner Saturday night  This is my 3rd time so I decided to write a review  I really enjoy the burgers  The service is good and friendly  My problem and why I am giving only 3 stars is the ambience  It was hard to read the menu because it was too dark and the server could not hear our order because the music was blaring  Too night clubby

Author: Ellie R.
Content: Delicious Amazing So worth it This is one of my favorite places to visit when I have something to celebrate and want to commemorate with a tasty burger  Im a gross creature of habit and Ive only ever eaten the Holy GuacAioli burger but it is DELICIOUS and the perfect mixture of burger and pseudo Mexican food that I love  The sweet potato fries are also delicious

Author: Joanna P.
Content: This place is justokay Theres nothing terrible about it Ive just had better mac burgers and fries in Chicago see Fattys and VillainsPROS Very good peanut butter milkshakes Nice beer selection Portion control if youre watching your weight all their burgers are 5 oz Everything is organic Servers are nice but a little spaceyCONS Burgers and fries come separately In other words if you want burgers and fries expect to pay 15 for your meal alone Underwhelmingtired concept this place is the light version of KumasKumas Too You have the same tattooed waiterswaitresses same punkheavy metal feel same types of burger combos same ungodly long wait yada yada yada Wisconsin Cheese Fries  disgusting Theres something gross about the sauce that I just cant put my finger on It justdoesnt taste very good I was also hoping for shredded cheese instead of cheese sauce but thats my own problem The burgers were dry and too small for the buns Maybe Ive gotten used to other burger joints that serve burgers the size of my head but each burger Ive gotten from DMK has thrown me back to those old BK commercials with the old lady who yells WHERES THE BEEF It could also be compared to what girls experience after they move on from a guy whos really well endowed to a guy whoisnt Uh Oh Mac and Cheese no 2 the sauce was grainy the bacon was overcooked and there were onions at the bottom of my mac and cheese This may be a flavor preference but the whole combination of onions  yellow cheese sauce  gross And bacon How dare you OVERCOOK baconMy friends love this place but I think Im going to stick with what works for me Will I come back here again Yes but only for a beer or a milkshake

Author: Andrew W.
Content: DMK and Kumas Corner are probably the two best burgers Ive had in Chicago The biggest difference is portion size and levels of messiness Kumas will give you a beastly burger that you have to jam down to take bites of DMK is much more simple a more reasonable size and more simple combinations for the most part The Bison Burger with Blueberry BBQ sauce is the best burger Ive had at DMK Diners Drive Ins and Dives brought me here and pretty much ever Lakeview resident knows DMK Place is a no brainer if youre craving a good burger

Author: Kevin K.
Content: Some of the best burgers on the north side  and all of them taste great They have a huge beer list with some great choices

Author: Anna W.
Content: I have been to DMK several times and each experience is better than the last If you can handle the wait and a relatively crowded space it is definitely worth it They have a great beer selection both taps and bottles and honestly the best burger I have ever had My favorite is the lamb burger with feta I think its the 11  I studied abroad in Greece and it always takes me back to the nearly 100 gyros I had there You also have to get an order of sweet potato fries  they have some kind of aioli dip that is amazing The food is one thing but the service is probably the best I have experienced in Chicago Nothing is worse than having a server that seems to be bothered by your presence or on the opposite side wont leave you alone Every waiter or waitress I have had there has been friendly and accommodating but not in a fake way The hostesses are equally great On one occasion our party had to wait an hour and the hostess gave each person in our party a card to get a free beer We werent even upset about the wait but both she and our waitress were sincerely apologetic and made the effort to ensure the rest of our experience was great If you havent been here yet you HAVE to go It is a place I will go again and again and not get tired of it It has the relaxed and friendly atmosphere of a burger joint but the food and service of fine dining

Author: Magen M.
Content: okay so im updating this review because of a policy that I wasnt aware of when i previously dined I guess it didnt really apply then so it wasnt brought up But they WILL NOT substitute ingredients They dont really even have a regular old cheese burger there Theyre all specific with BBQ sauce or blue cheese or some other pairing that some may like but Im a plain cheeseburger type girl i find it downright rude that they wont put cheddar cheese instead of blue cheese on my burger i mean not everyone likes blue cheese its extremely unaccommodating if im paying 10 for a burger i want it the way i want it Im really a stickler for customer service coming from a family that owned two businesses growing up pharmacyold fashioned gift shop and drug store and a diner and this is a real downer I probably wont go back due to this policy

Author: Susan K.
Content: I went to DMK for the first time this past Friday evening with 3 friends Theres a spot at the bar where youre literally AT the bar but are still sitting across from each other as if at a table  Very cool seating arrangement for our lucky partyThe bartender Drew heard us say we hadnt been there before  After we ordered some beers a waitress brought over chilirubbed onion strings and told us it was compliments of the bartender  Shortly after the same bartender poured shots for everyone sitting at the bar again on the house  At the end of our evening we were handed 4 cards each good for 1 free drink at DMK  Pretty coolDrew was probably the nicest bartender I have ever had  His customer service skills were clearly amazing when talking to our group he looked each of us in the eye as he spoke and I will definitely be heading back there soon

Author: Johnny T.
Content: DMK why do you make me sad If you glance down below this update youll see that I was a fan from nearly two years ago While DMK had its detractors I wasnt one of them I spoke well of them and implored people to give them another chance in the face of bad service and shrunken portions It looks like the joke was on meI came here with a large birthday party Prior to coming my party called ahead days in advance outlined the number of people needs and expectations Knowing that DMK doesnt take reservations at all really not a fan of this trend I knew it would be a crap shoot I also expected however that the management would speak openly and honestly about realistic wait times with that number of people in their experience and whether or not the restaurant could realistically handle that kind of crush If so cool If not no worries They could handle it Wait time would be approx 3045 min provided our party arrive at the set timeGetting a bunch of redecated folks to arrive anywhere en masse on time is nothing short of a Christmas miracle but wonder of wonders it happened We arrived on time told the hostess we were here and bellied up to the bar to get some drinks I settled on a sweet tea cocktail that was disappointingly weak Adding insult to injury I was overcharged for it before I addressed the matter with the bartender She forgot Mhm I guess she also forgot how to add any liquor to it as well Things were not starting off well Our party was big and a few other large parties wandered in as well The place was uncomfortably crowded and hot What ever could rectify this situation Oh right Reservations Anyhoo 50 minutes passed and I went to get the hostess to check on our table She was going to look into it 15 more minutes passed Still looking After ten more minutes she informed me that part of the section she was to place us at had four folks sitting there Theyd already paid and finished but they were having a conversation Really On a busy Saturday night after satisfying the bill and finishing the meal its a good idea to keep a large party waiting for a half hour longer than expected 1 hr 15 min wait so far so people can take up real estate and not turn over to new paying customersHuh I wanted to leave but I was there for a birthday and that wasnt my call Fifty minutes later thats right over two hours of waiting at DMK after calling ahead days in advance and discussing needs and expectations we were sat My appetite was gone We received an order of onion strings and pickles for our troubles That sounds nice before you take into account the size our of party Not once did the management ever come up to us to apologize or explain the situation despite us asking for them Not once Unacceptable On the way to the rest room to wash my hands I nearly slipped and busted my bodacious butt Neither here nor there but it happened and added to my frustration My 4 turkey tasted like a Bob Evans sausage patty and my draft beer was served in a stemless wine glass rather than a pint glass Huh I got a wine poursized beer for draft prices Ugh Whatever at this point I was done Id been done for a while hours actually and literally but I was definitely done nowWith as much money as we threw down at DMK I didnt feel accommodated or taken care of at all In fact I felt unappreciated and unwanted My money was taken full price yall but no consideration was given The night was frustrating but moreover it was disappointing Happy birthday indeed

Author: Caroline M.
Content: Forget having cakecupcakesother trendy things at my wedding  I want to serve peanut butter shakes from DMK

Author: Dane K.
Content: Im totally on the fence of give it another shot and way too much attitude to go back with DMK  Ill probably give it another shot but overall the first experience here had so many undesirables the second visit had better be greatFoodPotentially great but their menu is weird  There were two burgers on the menu that said coming soon  Dont tell me what I cant order  At first I was confused if the name was what they were trying to decide but when I asked they said no they were still working on those burgers  Either way youre reprinting the menu stop teasing meYou cant substitute and the ability to make your own burger just does not exist  So if you want something other than the combinations theyve chosen youre SOL  You cant even add bacon or something simpleYou cant order your burger cooked how you want  They cook everything medium plus which to me sounds like a way to coverup for a potentially too busy kitchen   More problematically IMO the burger I got was too well done  Its grass fed beef but might as well have been the ammonia soaked crap everywhere else serves  This stuff had no flavor because it was just too far cooked  My dining partners was even more so well done at least mine had 1 or 2 morsels where it was slightly pink but overall it was grey matter  I cook grass fed beef almost weekly and if I had made the same burger at home I probably wouldve hoped I had cooked it two minutes less  Dont open a fancy high end burger bar and then not allow customers to order it medium or medium rare Especially if youre using higher end beef its a wasteThey have an extensive beer list but their only cider option is Crispin Not a huge fan They were out of their house red zinfandel  They have an extensive beer list a few wine options and a few cocktail optionsThe burgers were OK again they had not a ton of flavor the 2 condiments were decent  I appreciate that they make their own ketchupWe ordered a side of fried pickles and okra  It was really delicious perhaps the best thing we had  We also shared cheese  scallion fries for 1 and they were like pub cheese fries basically  Not overly gourmet but goodAtmosphereIt was packed on Saturday afternoon for a late lunch There was a 15 minute wait or so  Michael Kormick himself was handling the listThe attitude level of the place is a notch or two too high  The music is so loud it gave me a headache in the 15 minutes we were waiting for a table  The sound system is obviously overdesigned with speakers literally every 2 along the ceiling perimeter  So of course if the music in one area is too loud its too loud everywhere  The place was packed and people were probably having to scream to be heard which made it even worse  During some songs the music was soft and perfect but some others it was so loud I couldnt hear anything unless I stuck my head halfway across the table  The napkins they use were bar towels but apparently not washed enough I left and literally looked like it had snowed all over me and my faceI was covered in lintThe service was pretty good She was really busy and things werent super fast at times but it wasnt her fault at all  She did however ask us how our food was before my dining partner had even touched his burger then never came back  When she finally brought the check I just handed her my card not wanting to wait any longer She brought back my credit card authorization but threw the itemized receipt out kind of annoyingThey left a comment card w our check which we filled out  Michael Kormick picked it up as we were leaving  Hopefully things improve a lot next timeAt 1013 for a grass fed burgerfries depending on which fries you choose it is a pretty good value even notwithstanding the cooking mishaps  Ill give it another shot but I think next time I think Ill wait for a calmer afternoon weekday not 2pm on a Saturday

Author: Lauren P.
Content: dined here on a chilly thursday night around 930  no waiting we ordered appetizer deviled eggs sigh nothing special about these eggs i could have made them myself kinda disappointing but kudos for having them on the menumain entrees there were three of us 2 6 mac n cheese 1 salt and pepper fries sweet potato fries parmesan truffle fries the real stars of the meal were the fries with salt and pepper leading the pack i appreciate that dmk makes all of its own dips and ketchup but the sweet potato dip was just off it tasted mostly like sour cream not the best compliment to the fries in my opinion the mac was chock full of bread crumbs and dry as a bone where was the ooey gooey cheese thats what mac n cheese is about now if you have the word burger in your name in my opinion you should be hitting them out of the ballpark dmk burgers are more like pop up flies first they dont ask you how you want your burger cooked what my boyfriend got lucky  his came out perfectly cooked nice and pink mine was well done yuck the pattys pretty thin so i think itd be easy to do i also didnt care for the bun which made up for the majority of the burger that being said id suggest getting a double i ordered the 2 because of the amish blue cheese that was supposed to be on it turns out there wasnt much to be found except for a small dab in the middle i was really hoping to be wowed instead the burgers came off as very lack luster also the coming soon burgers on the menu are a waste i dont want to see it if i cant order it dessert chocolate cookie  coffee ice cream sandwich chocolate chip cookie  vanilla bean ice cream sandwich the chocolate chip cookie tasted like there was cinnamon in it which was a turn off the ice cream was good overall the sandwich was pretty messy and hard to eat since the cookies werent soft ice cream shot out the sides every bitei really wanted to love this place i did but i ended up coming away with an ehh feeling i dont know if ill visit again they did have a great beer selection so i could see myself coming back for beers and fries prices were pretty reasonable too but in all honesty duffys burgers absolutely kill this place something tells me mk doesnt careside note the music went from blaring passion pit to smooth jazz while we ate weird

Author: Frank L.
Content: Burgers were delicious and unexpectedly fast for a Saturday Night Service was friendly Drinks were great and they had a limited edition baklava milkshake that will haunt my dreams Will definitely be back

Author: Paul C.
Content: Do yourself a favor  Visit this place in 3 months and see if they dont have the kinks worked out  I found the bar itself unpleasant as it didnt seem to know if it wanted to be a hipster restaurant or a casual burger bar   Sports on flat screens with the sound off so I can listen to flavor of the month indie tunes  Pick one or the other guys  I hate the indecision  The burgers were nothing special  No option on how its cooked  Quite assembly line  The buns were the clear highlight  Theyve the perfect amount of bread to meat ratio and dont fall apart in your hand  Unfortunately nothing between the buns was worth it  I hope this place improves as it shows promise  But right now its no fun to be at and the food is not worth the visit

Author: dave s.
Content: A lot of people were telling me about this place so i finally made it over there tonight and I have to say it is NOT great It is trying SO HARD to be The Counter which is amazing but just isnt I got the 1 burger and my wife got the veggie burger and we also ordered seasoned fries and sweet potato fries 1 burger was small and the bun and onions were too burnt The Veggie burger was just average I have had better at almost every place i have ordered one Fries were good but it is hard to mess those up and like the burgers I have had betterDont waste your time

Author: Athena A.
Content: The bacon cheese burger  the vegetarian burger were amazing The wait was a little longer than we were told  our waitress was not on point that night but the burgers were fab

Author: Emily W.
Content: Blue cheese  bacon fries are the only thing that stood out about this place Our server was slow and took forever to come back and take our order and to check how our food was after we received it My friend and I both ordered the 4 burger and were not impressed It was spicy and needed some sort of sauce on it By the time we finally got the attention of our server our food was cold and we ended up sending it back I might try this place again but honestly the ambiance of the restaurant along with the service was just not my cup of tea

Author: Casey M.
Content: A Roasted Hatch Green Chile Burger Fried Okra  Pickles Margaritas and Micheladas all served up around 11pm on a Sunday night Yes DMK Burger Bar Your burgers and service were a great beginning to a great Sunday nightOn a late Sunday evening some coworkers and I had a hankering for some good burgers But what burger joint is open late on a Sunday night DMK is and is open everyday until 12am for us late night burger cravers This burger bar is dimly lit with a clean and modern façade The interior is fresh with a great creative feel far beyond any traditional burger joint The beer menu is extensive and the burger menu looks simple but with everything from a bison burger to a homemade veggie and grain burger it is sure to please every palate Upon being seated promptly in a giant party table in the middle of the dinning room we quickly ordered our drinks with the courteous and cute server We ordered margaritas and some Goose Island Sofia served in interesting stemless beer glasses I guess without the stem our hands will slightly warm the beer to release some of the beers nuances The margaritas were great With a great mix of El Jimador Triple Sec citrus and Lagunitas Pilsner Pilsner you heard me right all round this great margaritaWe all ordered burgers as well I ordered the Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack Smoked Bacon Burger and the Fried Okra  Dill Pickles served with Herbed Ranch The burger was cooked perfectly with slightly piquant smoky chiles jack cheese smoked bacon all topped with an over easy fried egg Deliciousness All this goodness was served between a dinky bun What gives I understand the burger and accoutrement are really the pièce de résistance but I feel the bun is lacking The Fried Okra and Dill Pickle were really great Crispy and well seasoned chicken fried pieces of pickle and okra served with a great ranch dipping sauce There were a lot more pickles than okra but that was fine with me I love pickles I finished the meal with the Gringo Michelada PBR fresh lime spiced tomato juice with salt rim All served a la carte so you get to mix each ingredient at your leisureThe overall meal and service was really great Although it was nearly closing time I felt we were all treated with utmost respect and care The burgers were great the drinks were very satisfying and quite frankly I see myself going back to DMK Burger quite soon

Author: Lindsay B.
Content: Awesome food I had the salmon teryaki burger OMG SO GOOD My boryfiend had this burger with the blueberry barbecue sauce also delcious Most amazing sweet potatoe fries Typical popular Chicago restaurant experiencedark close to people seating modern feel but pretty laid back attire The service was very fast and quick to serve us Their was a full bar with quite the beer list Apparenlty during the day I have heard it turns into a little bit of a hypster jointSo I have heard All in all I tell people to go here al the time

Author: Eugene H.
Content: wouldnt come here for industry night unless youd like to be questioned about being in the industry have your pay stub ready if you do not have a business card food is meh wouldnt make a trip over to have it again for sure way overhyped

Author: Brent G.
Content: Went to lunch here with a group of colleagues recently and really enjoyed it  Very nice combinations of ingredients for each burger variety plus tasty sides and salads  I had a salmon burger because Im in a no meat phase and it was scrumptious  I really appreciate being able to mix and match patty types with the different burger combinations  The fired okra onion strings and sweet potato fries were all excellent The waitress was funny and the service was prompt so good all the way around  I will be back and try to provide more details

Author: Courtney W.
Content: I go here about once per week It is usually crowded unless you go during the week around 5 or 530 The service is excellent The bar is first come first serve and the bartenders are friendly and generous The food normally comes out super fast which is nice I always start out with a blood orange soda which is excellent and house made Then I order the number three burger which has pastrami and saurkraut on it Excellent the best burger I have ever eaten I have had dessert there including their excellent shakes and ice cream sandwiches Nothing bad to say about this place

Author: Stephanie B.
Content: The wait was kind of long We went here Saturday afternoon and I think we waited something like an hour to be seated According to my codiners the burgers were good one had bison one had the regular The fries were really good I couldnt partake due to not liking meats but I trust their wordThe veggie burger was good but Im not sure if it was 9 good It had a nice texture and the toppings were actually a GREAT pairing The bun was a bit lackluster and Im not so keen on the no substitutions rule  Im also not sure why this place has waiters and waitresses Seems like it might go faster if you could order at the counter No matter I wont bash the owners for creating jobs

Author: s r.
