Content: Hyped up Nice bar Overcooked burgers Dont treat grass fed beef like a mcdonalds patty They dont offer you a selection of meat temperature Guy said something about chef driven or something I cant see why that apparently makes overcooking them ok

Author: Alfred T.
Content: Just had dinner at DMK the newly opened burger bar by well known chef Michael Kornick of MKs  We live in the neighborhood and thought wed give it a tryThe room is warm and comfortable with exposed brick nice lighting and good music We were seated right away it was early in the evening and the place did begin to fill up by the time we left The first thing we noticed is that although very friendly the our wait person seemed a bit naive We ordered a Northshore vodka martini dry with a twist They came out in highball glasses and were dirty We sent them back and out came two more that were properly mixed but maybe contained a shot and a half of vodka the same meager amount now in a vshaped unstemmed glass  The cost 11 a piece  Now Ive lived in this neighborhood for a few years and most establishments around here serve a decent sized martini for 11  We felt ripped off  I think the manager came over and was apologetic and brought out 2 more We were not charged for them because we complained but others my not have such luck To be fair the beer selection was extensiveOn to the food For a starter the fried pickles and okra We got maybe eight pickles and 2 pieces of okra The flavor was good with a good dipping sauce and crispy crust We both ordered the burger with green chili and a fried egg The meat is grass fed and was tasty but the patty was probably 6 oz at best  We ordered the parmesan fries with truffle cream dipping sauce  The sauce was great but the fries were limpNow I understand that this is a newly opened restaurant and there are usually a few bugs to work out but Michael Kornick is a pro and I guess we expected morePS this place is also way to hetero My partner and I began to feel like we were sticking out  How but a few gay boys in the wait staff mix  Maybe MK is shooting for a certain population For our money we can have a great martini and burger with fries at Jacks on Halsted straight or gay

Author: Chrissy P.
Content: Im about to divulge something that makes me feel slightly gross about myselfIve consumed every burger on the DMK menu Every One They are all delicious You cant go wrong this is a spot that all my out of towners demand to return to time and time again when visiting Chicago given the variety of food bevys and incredible atmosphere I do wish they would bring back the original number 5 you know what Im talking about MK but am just as happy to consume the 6 3 Ron Santo and 9 burgers in that order of preference with a side of sweet potato fries Save room for the ice cream sandwiches andor shakes you wont be sorry

Author: Shannon K.
Content: DMK Burger Bar is the real deal I have lived in Chicago less than a month and I am already familiar with Michael Kornicks reputation in the food industry I havent been to any of his other restaurants but based on DMK I certainly plan to The space is great not overstated but sleek and hip Its a place I would hang out just to drink their fine beer selection I sat at the bar and I like a bartender who is informative and knowledgeable Im interested in local brews and I asked Matt about them and he walked me through their beer selection and told me about a lot of the breweries I love that kind of thing Well done Matt He even gave me a couple sample tastes And a card to get a free draft on my next visit Now thats how customer service should be done I went to DMK on National Cheeseburger Day forreals I figured what better day than NCD to check out a new to me burger joint I love lamb burgers and I love Greek gyros so when I saw the lamb burger with grassfed Lamb sheeps milk feta olive tapenade Greek salad and tzatziki I was sold Wow the bun was exceptional it was soft and warm and thankfully not huge The burger was juicy cooked perfectly and so fresh tasting The Greek condiments were outstanding and flavorful a little less feta though it can be overpowering I also ordered the sweet potato fries with lemon Tabasco aioli  shut the front door  thats a great combo Again it was a small normal person sized order I appreciate this quality over quantity Dont get me wrong you will be full after a burger and fries here its just not that ridiculous size Americans have wrongfully become accustomed to in recent years Good start to my Chicago burger experience I will be back to try out the great brews there are so many and other burgers Cant wait

Author: Sandra G.
Content: Wow just the type of burger Ive been wanting Burgers are YUM Sweet potato fries are yummy And the gringo michelada was good The only drawback in my opinion was that the bun seemed kinda wimpy But by no means will that stop me from returning I will be back They also have an awesome pumpkin beer right now

Author: Rob L.
Content: Ohhhh gosh darn it and dag nab itIt was not the best of days for me when I came here Sulky about life a little and needed a little pick me up Luckily I had three friends that were able to join me for that pick me up I had been wanting to try this place um hello burgers fries and malts um yum and everyone in the group was good to go and try this place out Sweet Day is looking a little better alreadyI saunter in first to arrive which meant first to get a table The place at 1pm was pretty hopping The tables were full the patrons were munching away no one with a nasty face on sounds promising The girls serving if there are any male servers here I apologize I just didnt see any were very friendly and upbeat Not one with a smile  on their face They said a few minutes for my table of four While I waited one member of my party showed up and a minute later we were sat As we chatted and waited for the others I scanned the menu As others have said I see no point to tease me with unknown burgers Teasing me in to coming back Hmmm you are setting the bar high doing it that way The burgers better be phenom if you are teasing me with combos that I cant get already When the rest of the foursome showed up we chatted some more before we got down to business The menu besides the unknown burgers is pretty straight forward You choice of burger you can sub for turkey or veggie I did turkey for mine also you can add a fried egg plenty of choice for sides from mac and cheese fries to saladsI went southwestern on mine with cheese and chilies and slightly healthy with turkey I got a large order of the fries with Parmesan and truffle dipping sauce I really like some of the combos they have for their fires and mac and cheese If I had more room perhaps I would have asked if those around me wanted to share and got a side In the end I liked my turkey burger but wasnt super excited about it It was good not too dry but it didnt blow my mind I feel like they need to take the extra step and push the limits a little more The bun was good soft and homemade feel but there is that little extra kick I think it could use The fries were really good with the truffle dipping sauce they were hard to resist They also come on these small plates barely bigger than the burger itself Why I dont know I still ask this question to this very day I know you are getting just the burger but its nice to have just a little extra room I do like the ala cart system and how you can separate everything burgers here fries or mac and cheese which ever and its not all on the same plate I did notice strangely that they never asked how the burger wanted to be cooked for the beef burgers my friends ordered Strange For a place so highly prized on their burgers and how well they separate everything I would think they would also want to make sure they customer got everything they wanted just right In the end I wouldnt fuss about coming here again The service was great up beat friendly and helpful The sight of the place was interesting blending dark woodsy feel with a modern twists here and there and over by the bar The prices are fine They have a good selection of items for sides more than I can choose for one sitting but really if I was craving a burger I dont know if I would be running back to this place for it Considering there are so many places in the city with a good burger I dont know if I would rank this one high on the list It wasnt bad but certainly not my top pick

Author: Elaine C.
Content: If you aint hurd you better axe somebody

Author: David R.
Content: Tasty burgers great beer selection nice sides and friendly service   Started with the deviled eggs yes better than moms and then moved on to the 2 burger with chipole onion strings and blue cheese  The burger was cooked and seasoned perfectly and the crunchy rings gave it great texture  Service was great and the beer recommendations were terrific   My only complaint was the slaw which had way too much mayo  Looking forward to working my way down the menu at DMK over the new year

Author: Samantha H.
Content: I went at a very down time which is why I likely had a better experience than many  I also hate the no reservation trend but my friends just moved in around the corner so we decided to walk over after a Bears game  Yes it was about 330 so completely off time  Thus we were sat immediately but even at this off time within 20 minutes the place was full  Given this I likely would not go here during a peak time  That being said my experience was quite enjoyable  We were sat right away  The server was actually pretty attentive nothing spectacular  Now I know this is a burger place but it is an upscale spot and red wine and white wine as the only choices is rather annoying  We were with another couple one of which got the patty melt which she gets there all the time and loved  Her husband got the special  Because it was close to Thanksgiving they had a Thanksgiving leftover burger where the proceeds went to feed homeless  I got the 8 and my husband the 1  What I loved was the size of the burger  You can actually get a whole burger and not feel like you gained 14 pounds  The burgers themselves were solid not the best Ive ever had but definitely above average  The standout and reason for 4 stars are the truffle fries  These were the best truffle fries Ive ever had where the truffle flavor actually came out quite nicely whereas many places that market truffle fries end up with fries that taste welllike fries  The sauce that comes with that and the sweet potato fries also were solid  Overall would go back but not during peak period

Author: Samuel M.
Content: Update Went back to DMK tonight for a friends birthday dinner The hostess was horrendous My friend put our name on the list at 7 tonight for a party of four and then left for awhile before returning The hostess was fine with this and indicated no problem I was there at 720 sipped a beer no less than 15 feet in front of the hostess and heard no name get called When my friend came back with the rest of our party 735 we checked in with the hostess who informed us that DMK has a policy of not seating incomplete parties and had called our name to no reply which is a crock because I was standing there the entire time and heard nothing As a result she put our name ON THE BOTTOM OF THE LIST after we checked in this second time rather than as is customary for a party that is incomplete when called at any other place that doesnt seat incomplete parties putting us at the next 4top available after the rest of our guests arrived We had to wait around half an hour extra due to these shenanigans Theyre crowded so I understand suboptimal hosting They still make the best fries in Chicago if only to accompany slightly aboveaverage hamburgers and Ill definitely be back for them Having said that I feel that I would be doing the Yelp universe a disservice if I did not report tonights debacle

Author: Eames E.
Content: the bathroom here has mirrors that give u a good view of your lower bod which is sweet bc u can watch urself piss probably the most integral part of any meal imho

Author: Gina F.
Content: Went for lunch today our 2nd visit and everything was great  My husband had the burger with the chilirubbed onion strings  chipotle ketchup  I had the crispy portabella and both were great  We also had salt  pepper fries sweet potato fries and deviled eggs Everything was very wellprepared  I also reommend the rhubarb cocktail tho I subbed vodka for gin  The service was pleasant and attentive

Author: Annie N.
Content: Its really late at night yet I cant sleep Im laying awake partially cause of the coffee I drank late but partially because I cant stop thinking about the luscious burger I got couple days ago at DMKIve been well aware of the normal long wait at DMK I live bout five minutes away So Ive been trying to avoid mentioning it to my friends in case they go nuts and drag me here I mean how good can a burger get But then this one friend of mine came visit from Boston and I hadnt seen her in more than 2 years yes we are really friends so I gave in and took her here more so she was uber excited when she found out I live really near by  turned out DMK is famous even to a Bostonian But luckily we went during lunch so the wait was not an issueI ordered a burger with brie and portabella mushroom 6 while my friends got the turkey burger 10 and 3 with Gruyere and sauerkraut Their burgers dont come with fries and some dont even come with lettuce and tomatoes so we ordered a plate of sweet potatoes fries and Iceberg Wedge to share The food came out momentarily At first look I was slightly disappointed with my burger It looked rather empty  the brie and mushroom were both on the skimpy side but I guess thats normally how they do it And then I took a bite and Ooooh Emmm Geee I died That thing was perhaps one of the best things Ive ever eaten The meat was well seasoned tender and juicy enough Their buns are not too crisp not too stale The cheese and mushroom were just perfect Everything blended together sooooo well I mean how good can a burger be right NO  NOT right A burger at DMK can seriously destroy your hope to give up meat it can temp your boyfriend to not be a gentlemen and compete with you for the left over it can cause you to tear up when he win it can cause insomnia and in my case all of the above happened The fries and the lettuce were both phenomenon as well I actually prefer sweet potatoes fries at the Counter they have skinnier fries but I was for sure not against them here Service was great and if you can go for lunch to avoid the long wait Ill probably run into you there because Ive determined to come back and try every single burger on their menu 3 times

Author: Rah Rah C.
Content: After eating the most disgusting microwave Thanksgiving meal ever I thought I am going to treat myself to a good juicy burger on Black Friday  Went alone and sat at the bar  The music was a bit too loud and the lights a bit too bright had to ask them to turn down the spotlight before I began sweating but the staff were very friendly and the place was clean  I ordered the No 8 beef burger  Gruyere cheese Iceberg Lettuce Tomato Raw Onion Bread  Butter Pickles Mayo and chipotle ketchup  Also ordered the white truffle fries and a Boylans cane cola  Food was warm presented well  and savory  I will definitely return

Author: Lissette A.
Content: Im reading these reviews and Im thinking these people dont know a good burger I understand that the appeal of DMK in this Lincoln Park neighborhood is going to bring out a type of crowd but trust me dont bother with this place  Youre paying for a burger 8 and then on top of that fries And they dont even give you enough friesand then you have to deal with the over priced drinks The burgers are a jokeWheres the Beef You get more bun this burger Real Chicagoans wont go to this place Its crowded because all of the Lincoln Park trixies are there with there Volkswagen driving boyfriends who all originated from the burbs And the waitresses were wearing sequinsumm reminder this is suppose to be a burger place Bottom line Dont bother with this place and save your money

Author: Jennifer H.
Content: I have to say Im less than impressed  Ive been wanting to come here for a while since Ive heard good things about this place  My step dad is working on our house and saw this place on a food network show and really wanted to come so we cameIm a big four square user and checked in to be pleasantly surprised they had a free small fry with first check in  I was quickly unimpressed when my free small fry was 4 fries on my burger plate  Thank good I ordered other sidesWe also ordered the Parmesan truffle fries small order which was a tiny order of fries as well and was missing the truffle  In addition we ordered the pickle chips and fried okra which was just OKNext came our burgers which I was surprised how small they were and I found them to be OK  Nothing special theres actually another bar close by that has outstanding burgers same high quality that are much bigger and for the same priceIf looking for a burger place skip here and try another in the neighborhood service food and price is way better

Author: Allen B.
Content: Nice place overall however I guess Ive just had better burgers in my life Id go there again but probably just for a drink

Author: Desi C.
Content: This place was awesome The service was out of this world We sat at the bar and our bartender was Matt Kennedy He was fantastic and made our first experience fantastic From his thorough knowledge of the menu to the complimentary desert AND drink cards to use next time you couldnt ask for a better serverbartender We will definitely be coming back The food was great and the shakes were AWESOME See you again real soon

Author: Midori C.
Content: Love this place The staff is great and very friendly The fries and burgers are delicious Parking around the area is not idealwould love to see valet there

Author: Tom T.
Content: Fantastic burgers  I lived around the corner for a number of years and do miss the Green Hatch burger  Also Salmon burger was a nice change  Im getting hungry just thinking about the food  Though the burgers could be a little bigger

Author: Charles C.
Content: Delicious burgers and fries Try the sweet potato tots and the 4 Usually has a wait

Author: i.am.a A.
Content: Fun place for a casual burger Good for a lazy weekend afternoon postdrinking night meal Go here and have the fries Some good looking servers too

Author: Laila C.
Content: truffle truffle truffle fries I wish I could buy a big jar of that truffle mayobut that would also mean I wish I could gain 3 more chinsThe chipotle ketchup that came with the salt  pepper fries were also banginThe burgers weregoodbut nothing Id hip hip hooray over The beef might be grass fed but it was thin and overcooked since they dont let you pick how you like your meat I had the 4 with green chile bacon and fried egg They skimped little on the bacon but the green chile added a slight bit of heat and the creamy runny egg countered it very well Tried a bite of everyone elses burger The lamb was ok but I dont really like greek flavors on a burger The prosciutto and salt  pepper chips was crunchy and delicious 2 was also tasty but seemed like it was lacking some more depthOverall DMK is goodbut there are plenty of other burger joints Id pick over it

Author: Carolyn L.
Content: I finally got to check out DMK with my good friend the other night and Im kicking myself for not getting a milkshake But no worries I live pretty close and I plan on going back soon So I tried the burger with marinated portobello mushroom blue brie griddled scallion and dijonnaise And of course because it was an option I got a fried egg on top I just cant say no when that option is thrown in front of me We both had a couple of 3 Floyds Gumballhead White Ale which was delicious But like I said I will be getting a milkshake the next time And Ill walk home just to make up for the extra calories Oh and we split the truffle fries They were a bit on the toosalty side but delicious nonetheless

Author: Kristine N.
Content: Came here after a Bulls game one night and the burgers were typical nothing extraordinary but we ended up leaving with a 110 bill Fries are good though but thats not enough for me to come back

Author: John L.
Content: Id lean towards giving 3 stars since my burger was just kind of average tasting to me but my wife proclaimed that hers was the best burger in Chicago shed ever had So Im a bit confused  Well go with 4 stars The sea salt fries were excellent and theyve got a great beer menu Overall a pretty good experience though Couple of things of note that were a little aggravating but certainly not annoying enough to keep me from coming back The music was very loud for some reason Not barlevel loud but just loud enough to make it kind of difficult to have a conversation There was only one toilet in the mens room which meant that I had to wait in line for a while Our server although extremely pleasant and helpful didnt write down the order while taking it which while that might impress some it usually also means that something will be forgotten The forgotten item just happened to be my beer which I didnt get until I was able to grab her attention half way through my burger She apologized and promptly went and got the beer In her defense though she appeared to be the only server working the room and I thought that she did a hell of a job managing that because the place was somewhat busy DMK will do if youre just looking for a decent burger and a beer and a nice atmosphere The music should be turned down just a tad bit though

Author: BB C.
Content: A typical burger jointDMK is not just another burger joint because it has its own creation of burgers I love the burger and the service

Author: MR W.
Content: Love this place I live down the street so Im partial to my local spots but this place consistently delivers quality If you are lucky enough to get Matt at the bar he is great Knows his beer and explains all the tastes well  Staff like that make people want to come back All around good experiences

Author: Nycole H.
Content: Pretty good I got a 1 burger without the onions To me it was a regular well tasting burger nothing really stood out The sweet potato fries were good but Ive had better Everything seemed pretty subpar The service was actually great the girl was very nice It was lunch so pretty empty She recommended a Backyard BBQ drink which was actually good but for 9 it looked like a shot glass I guess I just found my love when it comes to burgers and drinks at another bar and itll be hard to live up to the Fifty50

Author: Zack R.
Content: I like the atmosphere of this place and the food is good but they dont like when you deviate from the menu I havent found a combo of fries that I really like a lot yet and the burgers are a little small compared to other burger joints that they are competing with I have no specific complaints that would knock it down to a 2 or a 1 star though and I have never disliked a meal here I was hoping it would be better when I heard DMK was moving in though However if a friend of mine suggests DMK I never argue so I keep giving them chances for that 4th star

Author: Tabitha G.
Content: I dont understand this place  did someone really sit down and say Burger places are all the rage lets do something different  lets make a place where you CANT get what you want on your burger Ridiculous The burger was the same as you can get at any one of a numerous places that have grass fed beef  and they actually let you put what you want on it It was also incredibly loud and I am not talking about the music   I could not hear someone 12 inches away from my face So great place to take someone on a date if you dont want to actually listen to them talk The only redeeming thing about this place is the buns They are to die for The most amazing burger bun Ive ever had in my life Unfortunately since I would never go back here I will have to relegate myself to bun dreams only

Author: Zachary W.
Content: My favorite neighborhood burger bar in Chicago  Unique and delicious burgers with a good selection of beers

Author: Ira L.
Content: We tried to go to Kumas last night and just couldnt stomach the line when we arrived  DMK was offered up as an alternate since we were already up North  Last night was my first time at DMK  The burger was excellent  The staff was really friendly and quick  The sides were tasty and I didnt have to wait to get a table at 7pm on a Monday  My only negative was that they served their Coca Cola in a can so drink refills cost  Bars usually give free soda refills

Author: Mr. C.
Content: One word SMUG I go here thinking its just your run of the mill burger joint but instead it turns out to be the most pretentious burger joint I have ever been to in my life Your telling me I cannot add a single slice of cheddar cheese to a burger because it would risk its carefully constructed culinary integrity Its a effing burger for heavens sake I can assure you this was not even close to being the holy grail of burgers rather I got a overcooked dinky under seasoned beef patty with tasteless crunchy onions and a wad of ketchup and your telling me I cant add cheese to it What has this world come toAlas they so unwillingly bring me a slice of cheese which they refused to melt on my burger but offered non the less on a cold plate Never again

Author: Katherine M.
Content: The sides are very good and my burger was excellent My other dining companions were underwhelmed but they did not have beef or bison The beefbison bragging by this establishment was deserved BUT the actual showcased food items are only part of a restaurant experienceSo the food gets a 4 but management gets a 2 so the overall rating is 3Ive been to 4 dozen of barsservingburger cuisine in Chicago maybe I should rate all of them when I get around to it I am rating this one since this is about the best potential for a great longstanding place of any I have been to but This establishment is in need of a couple changes to enhance the dining experience so it doesnt become just another bar that serves burgersit will if it doesnt make some improvements 1 This establishment is not a nightclubthe volume of the sound system was painfulit may have been the settings just for that night but I could not have a conversation at the very broad tables without shouting If my ears are going to be blown I better be seeing Metallica in their prime2 Waitstaff need to check on tables The guy delivering the food was checking more than waitstaff You do need to stop by sometimes Dude delivering food younger fella was conscientous If he hadnt been there would have been a very tiny tip 3 Bar service SLOW Need another bartender or have current tenders Talk Less with patrons I should not have to wait 810 min for a drink Crazy times FridaySaturday is always busierput more staff onI would like to go again soon and try another burgerit will be my last time if I get another clearly inexperienced waitresswaitdude and my eardrums are blown out

Author: Ziyan C.
Content: I have had the pumpkin pie milkshake and now I can die a happy woman

Author: Rebecca H.
Content: Great burgers and beer selection I have gone back multiple times

Author: Nick K.
Content: We went here for lunch and I think I have found the BEST burger in Chicago Wow was this delicious The truffle fries were phenomenal as wellThey also have specialty milkshakes available On the day I visited they had a baklava shake and I figured I would give it a shot It was GREAT Had a big chunk of baklava right in the middle of itService was fantastic and timely as well Very helpful in deciding what to orderDEFINITELY coming back

Author: Robin C.
Content: This place is amazing  Some of the best burgers I have had in the city ever  I love the fried pickles  okra  All of the different sides are awesomeThe beer selection here is pretty great as well  It covers the spectrum of what you would want  Whenever I have come here all of my friends always find something they likeThe last time I was here I was here with some friends just celebrating after a long week at work and the manager Michael Short came over and just checked on us  He bought us a round of shots as well  This guy is awesome  I recommend this place to anyone for a good burger to watch a game to catch a beer and to experience good service

Author: Zach T.
Content: One Sentence reviewDMK is Kumas for the Lincoln Park Set  By comparison its not nearly as good as Kumas but I love the spirit of this place the quality of the menu and that which makes it upIf I could go with Yelp here I would 35 stars as of this writingService is excellent  Hostess and Waitstaff no waiting at 630 on a Wednesday  The beer list is likewise excellent representative of a good palate  I had a Half acreThe Burger reason for being thereThe burger is small for an 8 burger  I heard many complaints about not being able to have your burger cooked to order most particularly from the TOC review by Heather Shouse but I will say that my relatively thin patty was still cooked medium showing some tasty pink  However it may be telling that theres not one plain burger or even just cheeseburger on the menu  You can certainly order them that way but the numbered choices are all dressed up  I ordered the 1 with bacon cheese bbq sauce and onions  As such I could not taste the meat hardly at all Grassfed Shmassfed  Does it taste good  One of my dining companions took the bun off to get rid of the BBQ sauce  It was good but there was way too much of it  Overall the flavor was good  By comparison again a Kumas burger is a synergystic experience where you can taste all the parts and their superior sum Fries were separate  4 for a tablesized order and 2 for individual  I ordered the plain not knowing the tastes of my fellow diners and found them unremarkable  Id love to try several of their dressed friesThe space is clean and trendy  Very much like the Bristol or Revolution brewing  Thoughtful decoration and lighting  With a touch of Epic Burgers design thrown in  Ill likely only go back if someone Im with wants to try itIn sum its tasty and innovative  Its a trendy space  Its pricey for what you get  Ill stick with my onesentence review

Author: Carter G.
Content: Had lunch here today with my mom The burgers were good and the price was right at 8 for any burger on their menu My mom was a big fan of the buns We had the deviled eggs for an app which were good along with the onion rings I would pass on rings as they were very thin with not a lot to them They make their own soda there which was good I had the blood orange soda The reason I gave this place three instead of four stars was bc they do not allow substitutions on the burgers I wanted to get their 2 but I didnt want blue cheese They told me that each burger is the chefs creation and you could not substitute ALL I WANTED was CHEDDAR and I would of been happy I ended up with the 5 burger which had some Italian cheese prosciutto and peppers on it It was good We also had the garlic fries and sweet potato fries They were both good but note they are not included with the burger If youre in the mood for a little bit higher end of a place where the prices on the burgers are fair check this place out Just be careful as they get you to pad the bill with all the extras which is probably brilliant on their part

Author: Ryan G. S.
Content: My first visit to DMK started off on the right foot with an outstanding wedge salad Then it got even better when the fries arrived with an unexpected complementary dish of macandcheese a kitchen error in our favor Unfortunately I was not as impressed when my burger arrived a 1 which has BBQ sauce on it I must have been so caught up in the euphoria of the wedge salad and the other delicious things that I forgot my  rule never order burgers with BBQ sauce It overpowered the other flavors and I was sad But I cannot wait to go back and try a different burger And order another wedge salad and more truffle andor sweet potato fries

Author: Jeremy G.
Content: Best grass fed burger in Chicago hands down Reasonable prices Fries with bacon and bleu cheeseridiculosity I only with they had a location in Andersonville  Oh and around Halloween  Thanksgiving the pumpkin pie milk shake is a must Grass fed is the only way to go Love the DMK please stay

Author: Ang R.
Content: Loud  So Loud  But worth braving every once in a while for the really tasty burgers and sides  One of the better fresher burgers in Chicago for sure  And the bun  The bun is what really puts this burger over the edge its clearly made in house and the tastiness was almost too much to believe  Im a believer now in these buns  I had the basic burger with BBQ sauce and bacon and it was good but I think I might have to go more basic still next time because the burger is standalone good enough  My bf had 4 and he was blown away by how good the egg cheese and burger were  Hes had other egg burgers before but this is now his favoriteWe also ordered onion strings which were addictively awesome and especially awesome when dipped in the homemade herb ranch SO DELICIOUS the ranch  The salt and pepper fries were also good but the house ketchup was not my favorite  Id happily try other fries thoughOne last thinggo early because by 7 pm the place WAS JAMMING  I mean it would have been a wait I imagine  Small place big crowds

Author: Eric M.
Content: DMK may have toppled Boston Blackies as the best burger place in the city for me DMK does what a good restaurant should which is not worry about size but taste Sure the patties here arent 25 lbs but theyre juicy and topped with great flavors I enjoyed the burger with chili rubbed onion rings and blue cheese My wife had the green chili burger with a fried egg Both were outstanding The burgers arent all that kill here either The sweet potato fries are great and the parmesan fries with truffle butter are so rich a small serving is all youll need Im also in love with a place that has a beer list large enough to fill its own page on the menu Had a great time at this place thats a nice modern setting great staff and good prices Cant wait to try more and more

Author: Hope W.
Content: Yum  I love this place Great beers great food great atmosphere great service All around pretty fantastic Ive never ordered something I didnt like Just tried the veggie burger and its one of the best Ive ever had lots of veggies mixed w brown rice and formed into a patty The sweet potato fries are delicious and somehow not greasy at all Also appreciate their use of grass fed beef

Author: Coleman B.
Content: I love DMK and am not even a big fan of hamburgers  They have so many different types of burgers and meats that you can try something new every time you go  Everything is so inventive and tasty that I really cant recommend this place highly enough  I LOVE the parmasean fries with Truffle oil and the other options for fries and the beer selection is incredible  If youre going for just drinks its a great choice and they have bar bite size food in case you get hungry  However you can also go food dinner if thats the type of experience you want  Really this is one of my favorite places in the city and the prices are very reasonable for the product and experience  Go get it quick

Author: FoodLover Z.
Content: Fantastic burgers and vibrant environment My only complaint is that the homemade sodas need to be better

Author: Mike C.
Content: Been here a few times and enjoy it Cant say I crave it but it is a convenient meeting place with friends a business colleagues Beer selection is good although I wouldnt mind seeing a few more new selections of crafts on there Service has always been great whether from the bartender or servers Very friendly and attentive Ive had the regular burgers and the turkey burger Both are good doesnt blow me a way for me to say greatest ever but its solid The sweet potato fries are a great addition as is the Parmesan fries We usually get 23 small size fries and share

Author: Andrew S.
Content: We appreciate the prompt service delicious and creative burgers and the Wisconsin cheddar fries

Author: terry h.
Content: hello amazing  came in on a tuesday night and it was pretty busy but not crazy  the bar was full but you could probably have squeezed in if you tried and there were a few tables empty at 830ish  the options for drinks were definitely more than enough  I got the honeycrisp cider and it was amazingThe food was incredible  we started wthe fried okra and dill pickles and they were great  Im not a huge okra fan but I actually preferred it to the pickles  Then we got a on the house side of the onion strawas which were incredible  perfect amount of spice and deliciousness  I got the veggie burger which I would say is definitely in my top 5 all time favorite veggie burgers  The consistency is a little mushy but the flavor was great and it wasnt so mushy that it was hard to eat or anything  My friend got the lamb burger and said it was fantastic as well  We finished the night with an ice cream sandwich of chocolate cookies around espresso ice cream  perfect end to a great mealthe reason only 4 stars instead of 5 is because the fries arent vegetarian  They all sounded and looked amazing so I was sad I couldnt try any of them  When I told the waitress I was a vegetarian though she pointed out the vegetarian options for sides which was very nice  Id definitely go back and bring more people here

Author: Bryan G.
Content: There was nothing wrong with the food at DMK  My burger was cooked perfectly on a baby soft bun maybe a potato bun  It was topped with some grilled pastrami and a sweet remoulade  The burgers come a la carte but they gave me a side of their salt and pepper fries for happy hour  It was just enough food and not really that expensive for a quality burger  My issue lies with the service  My bartender was too preoccupied with training the new guy to notice my empty drink or remove my empty plate  The twenty dollar bill I laid next to the empty plate glass and crumpled napkin might have given her the impression that I was finished  Im not really sure  There was a slight attitude that came with the service as well like I was an inconvenience  Everyone has a bad day but other reviewers had a similar experience

Author: Chris S.
Content: Ive been a couple times Lamb burger Check Okay I got the lamb burger every time Its a really good burger and the truffle fries are a requirement I cannot emphasize this enough One thing just know before going that its crowded and kind of loud

Author: Frank V.
Content: Inexpensive amazing food great beer selection awesome servicetop notch This place needs more than 5 stars

Author: Josh K.
Content: I like the idea behind their burgers grass fed beef good flavor combinations but if youre going to be a great burger you have to cook a great burger and that it where DMK has dropped the ball in my experiences Not looking for my super quality grass fed beef to be cooked medium well or even well when Im not asking for those temps There are more than a couple great burgers places in Chicago but this is not one of them

Author: Sean F.
Content: DMK was a disappointment and I will probably never visit again First and foremost you cannot even select how you would like your burger cooked The burger was a decent sized however this may have been misleading because of the appetizer sized plate it can out on This place wont last there is too much competition for burgers in the city Go KUMAS

Author: Lindsey O.
Content: A tad bit overhyped  There was nothing magical about the burger It was an ok burger and pretty good fries We had a 1  aged cheddar smoked bacon charred balsamic red onion BBQ sauce and a 14 grass fed lambfeta olive tapenade Greek salad tzatziki and split sweet potato and truffle fries  Not the best not the worst  just an ok meal I think this restaurant is more geared for men to come in for a drink with their buddies They have a full beer and whiskey selection that I could see as appealing I like beer and whiskey but I was hoping for a mind blowing burger  Again  not so much

Author: Kerry S.
Content: After a recent visit to DMK we are in love Awesome salads burgers fries and beer The only thing not giving this a 5star was the incredibly loud music the while time we were there I understand the atmosphere but shouting conversation throughout a 2person meal was just not ideal Be sure to try this place we will be back

Author: Ashley S.
Content: Its worth all the hype Ill be back The burgers are amazing and service was great too Go here now

Author: Rita W.
Content: I see that a lot of yelpers have been comparing this place to Kumas  Now let me preface this reviewI have not been to KumasGASP I know I knowits definitely on my list but the rumors of long lines have deterred me thus far  I have been to the Counter though and DMK is definitely much better than the Counter  Even though the Counter is closer to me I would trek the extra mileage to go back to DMKTo be honest I wasnt expecting much especially when I read about how they cook every burger medium to medium well but I was pleasantly surprised  Our waitress Lauren was friendly and very helpful with describing the menu to us  I ordered the 9 which was the turkey burger with portebello and eggplant and blue cheese coleslaw  I dont like blue cheese so I ordered the slaw on the side  I tried the slaw hoping that maybe the blue cheese description would not be true but nope it was pretty blue cheesy  I give it credit though it wasnt overly cheesy or over mayoed and if I liked blue cheese I would have liked it  Anyways I was impressed with the burger its hard to make a turkey burger without drying it out or making a turkey with flavor but this turkey burger was both perfectly moist and seasoned  I could almost eat this burger without any ketchup at all and if you have ever seen me with ketchup you would understand that this is a pretty high compliment  I also really liked the burger bun most bun dont have the strength to stay with your burger and usually disinegrates while you eat it 5 Guys anyone but this one was nice and fluffy and definitely held its groundWe also shared a large order of the truffle fries with truffle mayoI could have used more truffle oil on the fries and the portion seemed smaller than I assumed a large order would be but it was probably better for my stomach that the portion was what it was  It came out piping hot with sprinkling of parmesan cheese and they were the perfect fry size not too big not too small and cooked perfectly crispy on the outside and a little mushy on the inside   We also order a side of the regular mac and cheese it was good but nothing specatular and we agreed that it was less cheesy than we thought it would have been  We also shared the chocolate chip cookie ice cream sandwich which was two pretty sizable thin chocolate chip cookies with vanilla ice cream sandwiched inbetween You cant really go wrong with that combination and it was a perfect way to end our delicious meal   If I am in the mood for a good burger and fries I would be back at DMK

Author: Lupe d.
Content: I was hoping to like DMK I really was  I was looking forward to this visit and since we were in the neighborhood decided to drop in for lunch  I maxed out the meter because I thought for sure it was going to take a while to cook these burgers  I had the 1 CheddarBaconBBQBalsamic glazed Onions and my BF had the 4 Green Chile Egg Jack cheese bacon  We ordered some Gravy Fries and Cheddar fries as sides  We were a little baffled at the triple burger listed on the menu and I asked my BF if he wanted to pay the extra  for a double  He said he didnt think he could handle a double  At this point I figured we would be waiting a loooong time within less than 10 minutes our orders arrived  no lie  When I looked at the size of of the patty I was really disappointed  and I am not a big meat eater but I guess my expectations were more on the Kumas side that the Burger King side especially when all the burgers were 8 not including sides  So I tried to move past that and dug in I will say that despite the thinness is that a word of the patty the taste of the overall burger was pretty good  now keep in mind that includes the cheese bacon sauce onions yummy bread i liked the bread soft and warmbut for the first time I wanted MORE meat because I didnt really taste the beef I tasted everything else  again I dont even really like red meat    My BF really liked his burger but also commented that he wished he had ordered the double  The fries were pretty good I liked the gravy fries more than the cheddar fries were they worth 4 eachI think the gravy fries werethe jury is still out on the cheddar friesI can see how throwing alcohol into the mix can make people think that these burgers are divine we were on the clock so no alcohol but I did like their icedteapretty tastySo why a 3 star  Our host and server were very nice and I always appreciate good service  Will we return  Probably not but I am glad that I tried DMKgood but not greatIMO

Author: Zach Y.
Content: Best most creative burgers I have ever had The atmosphere is awesome the drinks are unique and the wait staff usually gets me all hot and bothered  There sides are equally as good as the burgers Love the fries and onion strings

Author: Maddy K.
Content: As a vegetarian I was not pleased when we decided to eat here Lots of restaurants serve microwavable boca burgers and pass them off as homemade burgers but this place was the real deal It was probably the best veggie burger I have ever eaten The onion rings were good but I didnt care for the fries Usually I dont like onion rings so I was very impressed with these Everyone I was with enjoyed their meals especially the bison burgerThe only downside was that it took a long time to get our beverages and the waitress did not ever return to refill them I had to ask someone else to do it I definitely recommend DMK and I intend to return

Author: Christina G.
Content: This place is fun and plays the Bulls games right now if you care about that  The wait on Friday night for a table was 6075 minutes but we found seats at the communal table in about 15 and personally I like that anyway  The burgers are good but not amazingbut I do really like that they only have grassfed beef  Gotta grab bits of health where you can  They also have Gumball Head on tap one of my favorites  Sweet potato fries and mac n cheese are excellent

Author: Nitesh M.
Content: Love the burgers and the beers here Friendly staff is a plus  Recommended to all friends and colleagues  Take out of town guests here all the time

Author: Matthew H.
Content: Great burgers and addictive truffle fries plus a top notch beer selection IMO you cant get much better than enjoying great food and drinks while Talking Heads and Wilco play in the background Ill definitely be back

Author: Louise P.
Content: Amending my previous 3star review at my significant others request We dine here bimonthly the food is consistently delicious and the staff is swell Sorry for not initially giving you that 4th star that you so obviously deserve DMK

Author: Matthew H.
Content: Great food but WAAAAAAAAAAAAAY too loud Are you a shitty Wrigleyville bar or a restaurant

Author: Jonathan M.
Content: I want to give this place 4 stars but if that was the case I would see myself going back here sometime When I went here nothing bad happen the service was good the food didnt take to long and it wasnt bad I really liked the burger with pastrami and green chili on it and the fries were great I feel that the space felt a little cold but its an open concrete room Honestly I think the reason that DMK only gets three stars is because its just not Kumas Corner

Author: Lauren H.
Content: We came to this place because it was our last resort because we couldnt decide where to eat  The burgers were OK I wasnt so fascinated by it  It is different because they have different burgers with each having different topping on it  The parmesan truffle oil and sweet potato fries would be my reason for going back

Author: Jim C.
Content: We had a great  fast lunch here on a Saturday at 1pm  Burgers  fries were awesome  Well be back

Author: Ellen O.
Content: split the burger with pastrami  kraut with an order of the regular fries the burger was okbut tasted more like a pastrami sandwich that happened to have a small burger patty on the bottom the best part of the whole experience was the homemade bun the fries were fine i probably wont go back just because there are other burger places i like much better

Author: Em M.
Content: BEST PORTABELLA BURGER IVE EVER HAD IN MY ENTIRE LIFEI want to be here every night Their sides are amazingThe atmosphere is great but good luck getting a table The wait is worth it for the foodPrices are good tooIf you are a vegetarian this is a topnotch place to go as a group if there a mix of veggies and carnivores Youll all leave satisfied

Author: Amy L.
Content: With the plethora of burger places in chicago its kind of hard to stand out DMK definitely does that They have an awesome bar menu with lots of fun cocktails I always get the bison burger because its so good and I dont want to risk getting something that I dont like as much ha The sweet potato fries are amazing but not as a amazing as the fires with feta on them nom nom

Author: Samuel C.
Content: Way too much going on with these bugers I prefer the KISS strategy to burger creating Focus on quality ingredients not funky ingredients Management were unpleasant to say the least

Author: Colleen F.
Content: hmm I dont seem to agree with the other posters here  I had assumed from my experience and the decor that this place just managed to stay open thanks to college students  Dont get me wrong the food TASTED good  It just didnt live up to most of the burgers Ive had at other places  First of all the burger is small maybe a 14 pound  They look big when you first get them until you pick it up and realize that its about 70 bun  It really reminded me of a Stake and Shake Burger for those of you in the know  It seemed to be cooked on a flattop too which isnt my preference  The burgers are not cooked to temperature why this usually makes me think inferior meat and you are limited as far as building your own strange when they have all the ingredients   So for one burger with fries it ran us about 14 yikes  Despite the hefty price my husband and I ended up ordering another burger to split because we were still hungry  I did like the bun they put the burger on and I give them credit for having Crispin Cider  I also thought that the service was fast even though our server was extremely inattentive  I hate having to flag people down after ordering just to feel like youre bothering them

Author: Alex B.
Content: Great burgers fast service nice beer selection

Author: Chuck T.
Content: Come on its an fing mediocre burger Not enough meat a disappointing bun and a much weaker beer selection than the bartender bragged about The bartender was a highlight however he did a good job The space is generic and very bright Kumas is far more fun with a better burger and beer list Twisted Spoke has a better burger and beer list I will not return too Lincoln Parkey the restuarant lacks character

Author: Kris C.
Content: Can I just say They really know how to make a burger taste like butter So juicy and so flavorful every bite keeps making you want more and more of its delightful indulgence Add the fried pickles and you are set If you want a great burger experience come here

Author: Jonathan H.
Content: Heard great things about this place expecting a fantastic gourmet burger  The fact that they didnt cook a burger medium rare or understand why a burger would be cooked medium rare was a huge downer  The Wisconsin cheddar fries were passable at best the cheese tasted very powdered and processed  However the staff was very friendly they have a great beer selection but a great burger is what wouldve propelled this place into a higher rating

Author: Jessica G.
Content: Came to this location for lunch today  One star off for the noise level which is the same as in the Lombard location  too loud  The burgers are excellent and I liked the Ron Santo that I tried today  It had some pretty tasty giardinera on the burger and perhaps some other meat besides just the burger patty along with some rather delicious cheese  I also liked the shake  this one was chocolate and espresso combined and the server was kind enough to have it split into three glasses so I and my dining companions could share without having to swap cooties  Good service  maybe verging on aggressive but I guess at lunch even though the place wasnt packed they wanted to move people through  Our orders were taken in a timely fashion and drinks were brought out rather quickly as was the food  Same extensive beverage list as at the Lombard location  Very good stuff

Author: Khadijah K.
Content: Juicy burger YUMMY espresso shake Ive had better friesSUPER loud musicdef made us leave a lot sooner than we wanted

Author: Dancer  Dreamer T.
Content: Late Sunday afternoon wasnt terribly busy but steady Our waitress Kate was very sweet Promptly bussed and wipe down choice table for us to sit at Articulated the menu making sure we understood all our burger options Promptly brought over drinks decent drink selection  Loved the Lamb burger it rocks so does the brioche bun it comes on Finish with the ice cream sandwich it truly is delicious Cheers to DMK

Author: Maggie C.
Content: Love this place  Went before a show at the Vic and the waitress was superfriendly and great about getting us in and out  Great beer selection wished I could have stayed longer and tried some more  As for the food the mac and cheese was good and the 4 burger was absolutely delicious

Author: Cole L.
Content: Of course when you talk burgers in Chicago you have to talk about Kumas I think Kumas having the vanguard spot in Chicago is a sad testament to the quality of this citys burger scene I really enjoy DMK Ive been half a dozen times so far and have never had to wait The burgers are very good better than Kumas in my opinion The quality of DMKs meat far surpasses the much larger and much more plain burger at Kumas The ingredients are paired better of the four different burgers Ive tried Ived loved them all If you feel the patty is too small you can order a double burger which Ive done several times The decor is a spacious modern industrial that I happen to like A nice escape from the blaring sludge metal which I love but cant stand when its distorted and pummeling my ear drums at KumasDMK bills itself as a beer place as well which I think it falters at The beer list is OK Of course its better than an average burger joint but if beer is a part of your sale then you should try to impress anyone with anything over a cursory knowledge of beer Every draught Ive had there has tasted watery and underwhelming I figured it was my own fault for ordering Goose Island there twice What can I say I know their beer is awful outside of Matilda but I continually give my local brewer the benefit of the doubt The bottle list is completely what one would expect It is a spattering of local and the few large national craft brews that Chicagos absurd liquor laws actually allow So you will find your ubiquitous Allagash White Dogfish Head 60 minutes Lagunitas and Sierra Nevada Pale Ale Nothing interesting but different from most burger bars in that it doesnt run on miller chill and Budweiser golden wheat

Author: Mark Z.
Content: It should be called DMK fry bar  Their fries are better than their burgers  Sure the burgers are very creative but the fries steal the show in my opinion  Gotta have the truffle sauce  mmm mmmmExcellent selection of brews and other specialty drinks

Author: Eric G.
Content: Any restaurant that mentions Nelson Algren and Simone de Beauvoir in the mens room will win my heart but throw in some of the best gourmet burger and fries and an excellent beer selection and youve got a favoriteThe burgers here are numbered not by rank but to simplify the awesomeness presented How can you truly define these burgers except by the list of ingredients The burgers are cooked per the chefs design and served on a bun that understands it belongs to a group of ingredients and isnt the MAIN ingredient Ive eaten everything on the menu at different times and havent been disappointed once The sides are perfect mac  cheese fired okra deviled eggs  By far the fries are whats not to be missed the Parmesan Truffle Cream fries the Amish Blue and Smoked Bacon Wisconsin cheddar and scallion etc All recommended Desserts are excellent too the icecream sandwiches or the shakes are the perfect belly busting finish DMK also boasts an ample beer menu offering a good selection of craft brews by bottle and tapHighly recommended

Author: Heather C.
Content: Before I begin I just want to say that I do not enjoy writing a bad review on a business especially in this economy However I believe that it is just as unfair to have a bad dining experience and waste your hard earned money especially in this economy as well and I certainly feel like people should be made aware of the prosand cons to make an informed decision based on THEIR tastesAs a few reviewers on here mentioned DMK definitely gets an A for effort I wanted to love this place largely in part to their quality ingredients and grass fed meats as well as variety of choices for vegetarians turkey and lamb burger lovers However thats pretty much where the A grade stops The AtmosphereYes it was loud and crazy However that does not bother me as much I definitely do think that whoever planned the seating in that space should have allowed for more space between the tables In some areas of the restaurant you sit so close that its like going to a benihana when its just you and one other person sitting at an 8 top table This is something that can be annoying but if the food is good I will eat standing up if I have to LOLThe FoodNow this is where the problem comes in The burgers were extremely small thin watery greasy and I think that you should definitely be able to choose the temp that you would like your burger cooked Everyone is different so how can you not offer different temperatures to fit your customers needs Also would be nice if we were told this up front so that perhaps we could go with something else The burger was not tasty and very mushy as another reviewer mentioned The burger buns are huge Making the burger appear much bigger than it is but if you are looking for a half pound burger boy have you gone to the wrong place The side salad Almost Greek was very good however I nearly broke my molar biting down on the olives since they were not pitted Now that really pissed me off and also Who does that Oh and the guacamolegross and I cant confirm for certain but it almost tasted fake although it could just be seasoned badly and over processed in their blenderit was not authentic guac for sure Which isnt a bad thing because guac is not what they specialize in anyway Just wanted to give you a heads upThe ServiceThe service was not that greatbut with that being said they were very busy The server seemed annoyed at questions and did not check on us hardly at all In fact I dont recall even getting a drink refill onceThe ExperienceAll in all it was not a good dining experience It was over priced for what you get Service was less than stellar and seating was awkward at best The shakes and desserts looked yummy as did the fries however I cant confirm that and will never be able to because I dont plan to go back Hope this helps

Author: Michael N.
Content: It was my first time there and my girlfriend and I always wanted to try this place out  So we decided to bring 2 friends along so we can order more food to taste I got the Breakfast burger which is a special AMAZING Turkey burger with a fried egg hash brown and maple syrup My girlfriend had the number 2 which was the classic Grass feed beef patty Amish blue cheese crispy onion strings with spicy chipotle ketchupOne friend ordered the Mac and cheese number 2 which had Gruyere smoked bacon charred balsamic red onions Its enough for 2 to share if youre not having a burger Great for 4 people if you want to share for the table The Parmesan fries with Truffle cream is AMAZEBALL Sweet potato fries are always a favorite A large order of Fries are perfect to share for two Their homemade sodas are great too We ordered the Blood orange Atmosphere is friendly and clean and the Bathrooms as well Always a plus Oh and we cant forget the other guys order Ben went with his heart and ordered the DMK Burger Made it a double Let me tell you this Im not kidding when I tried this burger It felt like a Big Mac on drugs I loved it Id come here again and again

Author: S T.
Content: When Im craving a really good burger I go to DMK I am a big fan of a classic burger and DMKs 8 is the best I love butter pickles so that may make me love the burger even more The burgers here are juicy not greasy and flavorful My friends have had the 1 4  9 which they all enjoyedThe sweet potato fries and Mac  Cheese 2 are always ordered when I visit both of which are deliciousOn my most recent visit I had a pork shoulder chili It came topped with cheese and a side of tortilla chips It was a little on the spicy side for me but really tasty and I liked that it had hominy in itIt gets busy and noisy but its worth the wait

Author: Keri W.
Content: Great beer selection  Had to go after seeing the delish food on a show on the Food Network   The burgers and everything was good  I sort of expected more but wasnt disappointed  Ill be back

Author: Elina S.
Content: Finally made it out here and Im not going to compare it to Kumas because I havent been as Im not too fond of this whole 2 hour wait for a burger conceptmaybe someday We came to DMK at like 9pm on a Tuesday night and got in right away aka 0 minute wait time score We were a little overwhelmed at how loud it was but then again after a few drinks and were in the same pace as everyone else We ordered two bison burgers served with pickled onions blueberry bbq sauce and blue cheese After first bite I was like wow this is good It was very good but overall it wasnt my favorite burger that Ive ever had because the sauce was a tad too sweet for my taste and although I usually like the balance of sweet and salty I guess I dont love it on my burger and the goat cheese is not my favorite component on a burger However the bison was cooked perfectly and it was tender and juicy and everything right The winner of the evening were there amazing sweet potato fries and we had to get the large portion served with a lemon ailoli and they were absolutely delicious Perfectly crispy and the sauce was to die forI should have just asked for that sauce on my burger Overall the place is definitely worth trying but not my favorite burger ever However maybe Ill come back and get some more sides  We left full and happy although we didnt love the fact that online the menu says the bison is 10 but at the restaurant its 11 not a big deal but I think it should be updated

Author: Greg M.
Content: This place rules pretty hard Well at least the food does The crowd this place attracts has a little diversity with age however most of the people who enter this facility appear to be yuppies But this is a result of its location The decor is nice almost has a slight high end vibe going for it Their beer selection is excellent and so is their house made fountain soda However if you do decide to get this get the Blood Orange flavor I got the cherry and it was a little disappointing but my gf got the Blood Orange and it was delicious I ordered the Number 3 with a fried egg and it was absolutely delicious My gf ordered the number 1 also with an egg and it slayed If you love burgers definitely give this place a shot The atmosphere may not win you over but I can guarantee you the food will

Author: John G.
Content: I was so excited when I saw Black Butte porter on the menu Its my favorite beer and I have never had it outside of Oregon That alone put them on the road to five stars add in the food and the great server and you get to where we are today Ill be back

Author: Tommy O.
Content: Of the 3 burgers Ive tried here only 1 has been absolutely amazing the chorizo one forget the name The others have been good not great Decent beer selection worth a try but the place is a little overpricedoverrated especially given the line out the door every weekend

Author: Gretchen O.
Content: Possibly the best burger I will ever have in my life I recommend 5 The Bison Burger

Author: Char Y.
Content: The burger was ok but everything else was great We had the mushroom burger sweet potato fries Parmesan fries 1 mac and cheese and an ice cream sandwich  Everything was good except the burger it was just average I absolutely loved the ice cream sandwich thought cannot wait for cookie bar to be open

Author: Kris R.
Content: i know what youre thinking  no its not as good as Kumas it was more than deece though  my husband and i went there on a saturday night at 6p which we thought was geriatric time but not at DMKs  it was packed  the host said wed have a 15 minute wait though it turned out to be 25 minutes  no big we came in early for a reason no were not over 65  we had the mac  cheese 1 as an app which was phenomenal  i had the 2 burger sans the Amish blue cheese  they would not substitute it w cheddar  its annoying when restaurants say they cant sub anything because theyre busy  i also had the sweet potato fries  he had the 4 and the truffle fries  those truffle fries were AMAZING as well but whats not amazing when theres truffle is all up in it  we ended it w a choc shake and a cookie sammy  both were greatof course we didnt finish everything but sometimes we splurge when we try new places  got the mac  cheese wrapped up in a doggy bag and next day it was still amazingi would come back   maybe well hit it up at 4p next time

Author: Amy D.
Content: Two years ago when we came to Chicago we attempted to eat at Kumas Corner but left because of the 2 hr wait and the noise level didnt help either  When we decided to come back to Chicago we knew we wanted to go back instead we stumbled upon DMK and truly witnessed greatness  They are very much what Kumas was a few years back  They both were featured on DDDs they both serve a young hip foodie crowd  It seems from many reviews that i have read that DMK is Hot and Kumas is Not  We came for lunch and were surprised that we didnt have to wait  Upon being seated we knew ordered their featured flavoured milkshake which was toasted marshmallow We were going to split it ourselves but our server was nice enough to do that for us  The milkshake was out of bounds it tasted like a campfire and they include whole chunks of toasted marshmallow so good  For our burger it came with caramelized onions cheese bacon and BBQ sauce it was perfection  I ate at Holeman and Finchs last summer and they claim to have the best burger in the states but i guess food critics havent tried DMKs because this burger is the bomb  If i had to fault them on anything my bacon was too crisp and it kinda shattered upon being bitten into  We also had the fries with truffle aioli i love how they come with cracked pepper and parm grated a top them  They were crisp well seasoned and the aioli was top notchOverall DMK was the first restaurant we came to on our Chicago trip and it set the bar really high i cannot wait to come back

Author: Angela S.
Content: Im a huge fan of this place However Ive been here 3 times and I have yet to try anything other than the mac n cheese and the standard burger

Author: Jenna C.
Content: It wasnt that much of a step up from something I can make myself at home Also I dont like that it doesnt automatically come with fries  what kind of burger place doesnt include fries with their burgers Amateurs definitely NOT nearly as good as Kumas

Author: John F.
Content: Not impressed  Its a good burger compared to a fast food joint but as far as burger bars in Chicago  This doesnt even make the top 20  Burger was thin and crumbly and you have to order a side separately really  That burger is NOT worth 10 bucks by itself  However their mixed drinks are pretty good otherwise it would have gotten one star

Author: Adam M.
Content: I actually really enjoy the simplicity of the menu as it highlights the complexity of each burger  Plenty of great options and typically good service

Author: Aprill C.
Content: ive been dying to try this place out after watching an episode of DDD i came in for lunch today expecting the place to be packed but surprisingly i was able to snag a spot at the bar no prob my preferred spoti ordered a lagunitas IPA on draft the bison burger w goat cheese  blueberry bbq sauce  a large order of the parmesan truffle fires i got the large because many reviews on yelp complained that the portions were small oh boymy food arrived about 10 minutes later the fries were bone cold i told the bartender Drew and he quickly took them away After listening to him apologize profusely and reassuring me that he was going to take them off my bill i got into my burger the buntoburger ratio was perfect again lots of reviews complaining that they are way too small but not in my opinion and i eat a lot cant say that i could detect the blueberry in the sauce but it was tasty none the lessfinally fries 2 arrived hot crispy and HUGE they were delicious  as i am a truffle whore these completely hit the spot even with the truffle cream it was all i could do to eat 12 of the ordermy bill arrived and sure enough Drew not only comped the fries but gave me a card for a free draft beer next time i visit trust me Ill be cashing in on that free beer very soonexcellent food and superior customer service sit at the bar trust me

Author: Roy A.
Content: I thought whether I should give this 3 or 4 The burgers are good But the options are not too many as of now Also there are way too many nonbeef options Seriously 12 turkey options and maybe a veggie portobello is enough If I remember correctly there were 7 or so beef ones and 45 nonbeef They even had lamb Thats fine to have 45 nonbeef options if you have 20 or so beef varieties But when about 35 of the burgers are nonbeef I get upset Anyways I went with 4 stars because it certainly has the potential and the fry sides are quite good I really was a fan of that This place is obviously no Kumas and I dont know if theyre trying to be honestly even though they have a bunch of beer and burgers Its a different atmosphere than Kumas and one worth checking outespecially ifwhen the menu expandsOh I should mention that I asked the waitress if she was gonna ask me how I wanted it cooked and she said something about the patties are too small to have different temps so they are all medium well or something like that Also annoyed me I like it med rare or med at worst But Ill still give it 4 based on potential and this can clearly change as I visit it more often

Author: Laura L.
Content: I just cant say I loved this place  Was it good sure  Was it close to the train yup  Was the environment acceptable yup  I love it that it provides sustainable meat and microbrews  Its really great to see somewhere covering both  And green chile options that actually taste good are rare outside of the southwest It also had gravy fries which is always always a good sign to me  I had the Green Chile Burger Gravy Fries and a cocktail cant remember the nameThe food was good  The burger I would describe as a high quality McDonalds burger  It didnt really leave me full but it did taste good  The fries were great  The cocktail was undrinkable  It was like straight whiskey and Im a whiskey girl and only half of the glass full  I looked around to other tables their drinks were full  I dont know if they forgot the mixer or what but when I asked for soda in it because it was really strong it still came back only about  generously  23 full  I had to pour water in to make it drinkableand barely stillFor a burger fries and 1 drink I was mildly satisfied and it cost me 20 just for that  Everything was fine but for the reputation this place has and what I experienced it is wholeheartedly average

Author: Heidi S.
Content: One of the best burgers in Chicago  Super loud busy place

Author: Joanna B.
Content: DMK Burger Bar was all I hoped it would be and more After noticing a blurb about it in Bon Appetit magazine a guaranteed trusted source of food literature I asked my boyfriend to join me for a Sunday night dinner LET ME TELL YOU SONThe beer and wine lists were encyclopedic but our server was as sweet as pie and helped us mostly my indecisive bf decide I mentioned the fact that I was a line cook at a near by restaurant and she mentioned that we were lucky to have come on a Sunday because it was industry night Industry night Cool what does that mean I askedHalf off everything on the menu girl She answeredThen my brain started to really sizzleThe two of us ordered two sides two beers two burgers and a milk shake at the end The total shouldve been about 60 bucks and ended up being just over 30 with tax We could not have ASKED for a better deal It was mindblowing But seriously the FOODThe fries were good but not stellar on their own I work at a restaurant that serves really good handcut fries and I know how easy they are to make so I allow little room for error I am a fry elitist The sauces and seasonings were GREAT but I would like to try a salad or mac n cheese next time The burgers were not HUGE but they had integrity The meat was so flavorful all on its own SO BEEFY and just real Loved the burgers loved allllllllll the combinations of toppings and housemade condiments I want to try every single one One claimtofame is their grassfed natural beef and its for real The burger was not as FANCY as I was expecting but the taste was truly legitThe milkshake was SPOT ON We ordered a Vanilla malt and honestly it was just perfect SO good after a meal like that We could barely walk home per usual for us but we didnt even careThe beer list is ROCKIN I would really like to take a beery kind of friend with me next time I go so I could really enjoy it and try some awesome brews My advice Go with someone you love who works in the industry Chef server bartender etc on a Sunday night after 9pm which is actually a really cool time to go cuz its not crazybusy and ENJOY Get a few burgers and a few sides and share share share Thank you DMK You are so cool not gimmicky and delicious

Author: Audrey S.
Content: Very good burgers  Not thick but wide which is what I prefer  The fries were good but not the best Ive had  The bartender was really friendly and they make very good cocktails

Author: Miles M.
Content: You cant give this place more than three stars if youre a true burger lover As Anthony Bourdain put it Any place that refuses to sell you a burger under medium temperature is basically on the side of the terrorists

Author: Amy R.
Content: Burgers were delicious but nothing extraordinary Onion straws were a goopy greasy mess I enjoyed the fries I would rather a Kumas Lockdown or Rockit burger any day though Mac and cheese was good but the portion size wasnt worth the money

Author: Dan M.
Content: I think the ambiance is nice and of course location  But the burgers just arent that great   If I am going to a burger place then I should be able to order a burger to a temperature that I like medium  medium rarewell etc  DMK is selling burgers that I would get from a chain like steak and shake   So what is the point of going to burger place that doesnt feature the burger  Anyone can put various toppings on anything   I guess wheres the beef applies here

Author: Sarah C.
Content: Ordered The 4  Burger with Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack Smoked Bacon the Holy Guac Aoli Parmesan and Truffle Fries and Wisconsin cheese fries and shared it amongst friends I liked the 4 burger bc the beef tasted softer and the bread is quite soft but I still think Kumas or Bad Apples burgers are more juicy and the meat is much thicker Truffle fries were probably the best thing I ate there and the wisconsin cheese on the fries tasted like fake cheese

Author: Anthony E.
Content: My favorite burger place in Chicago Great food great beer and a great staff I have dreams about the parmesan truffle fries If you love burgers and live in Chicago this place is a must

Author: Sarah Beth B.
Content: When DMK first opened I was super excited to have a burger place to close to my house  especially when I started hearing awesome things about the sweet potato fries  but it took me until this weekend to finally try it  I was definitely pleased  The menu is pretty straightforward and youve gotta order exactly how the item is listed but thats probably for the best because the toppings all work really well together I ordered the number 2 blue cheese fried onions chipotle ketchup and it was awesome I would have liked a little more ketchup and I think I might ask for more next time  I also got the sweet potato fries which come with a lemon aoli which is delicious Im southern and I love mayo AND sweet potatoes so this was like heaven  I was with a girlfriend who got the number 1 with bacon and cheddar and bbq and the truffle fries She loved hers too but I thought the truffle fries tasted just like normal fries so I think I win My only complaint and it registers a full star off is how loud this place is We were fully yelling by the end of the meal Granted it was a saturday night but Ive eaten at plenty of bars on a Saturday and been just fine while this was  primarily a restaurant and just too loud  Ill be back for sure but probably on a weeknight

Author: John O.
Content: Once again BYOB comes through with a great Chicago food recommendation  Super tasty burger and fries complimented with a good selection of micro brews  The service was friendly and enthusiastic  I enjoyed the 2 burger and look forward to trying some of the other menu items

Author: Michael H.
