Content: Im gonna start with some ProsCons since this place has gotten like 225 review in 6 monthsUNHEARD OFPros1 Well Laid out Space dont judge it by the outside2 Good Beer ListWell laid out simple menu3 Quality IngredientsFlavorful FoodCons1 SKIMPY Portions2 Expensive3 Weird MusicNo paper towels in bathroomThat being said obviously this is not a Half Pound behemoth like Kumaswe all know that These burgers are like 13 pound grass fed beef creations of their chef Every product they use in the preparation is high quality I had the 4Hatch Green ChilesWhite CheddarSmoked BaconFried Egg It had GREAT flavor but I just felt like each condiment on the burger was Skimpy  PUT SOME ON THERE Had a few CHILES on the bottom some SMALL bacon pieces Come on just lay it on there I wanna taste the different flavors Then the fries Russet PotatoesWisconsin CheddarTONS OF SALTThey were great Quality Stuff but again maybe TEN Fries on the LITTLE plate These guys have it down to a science believe me you are paying like 1113 for a burger with fries PERIOD  What is this The Four Seasons Lets not even get into the Temperature thingCharlie Trotter couldnt cook this thing Medium RareOne more thing you have to Ask for everything I had no SaltPepper or Water Had to ask for Ketchup Guess what A Ramekin about 13 full Go Figure Beer selection Standard Craftsnothing out of the ordinarymidwest breweries Ill be back to try the other burgers for sure I just hate feeling like your get skimped at all angles

Author: Mehran F.
Content: burger 410onion rings 310 where were the onionsservice 810 polite attentive accommodating

Author: Eric S.
Content: People struggle with the fact that DMK doesnt let you choose the temperature of the hamburger I say Get over it In fact I really like it when competent chefs make executive decisions He thinks that mediumwell brings out the flavor of the beef best I prefer rare beef but I admire his stand You know what else I admire Beef fat french fries Pro tip split a burger with someone in order to reduce the chance of cardiac arrest That would be a heart attack with a smile

Author: Jennifer C.
Content: I dont know if Ill be back because they will not customize any burger to your liking For example I wanted the 2 but I dont like bleu cheese on my hamburgers so I wanted to substitute another cheese but I was informed that they do not substitute cheeses I ended up getting the 1 which was pretty good albeit kind of greasy my husband got the 2 which he enjoyed We were not asked how we would like the burgers to be cooked and neither of us thought about it at the time so our burgers were cooked rarer than we would have liked For sides we had the bleu cheese cole slaw and the parmesan and truffle fries The coleslaw was ok and the fries and especially the dip were good Its actually pretty good food but theres just as good burgers elsewhere who actually will make burgers to your specifications

Author: Kaman T.
Content: Ive been here a few times and I wasnt very impressed the first few times but I went there again today and they seem to have updated their menu a lil bit I tried the Salmon burger with ginger slaw and red thai curry and it was one of the best salmon burgers I have ever ate The salmon was MOIST and NOT dry at all Its not very thick but full of flavor You can taste the freshness of the fish Usually salmon burgers Ive tried before are dry thick and bland but DMKs is very unique The slaw and ginger has a tangy flavor that compliments the fish very well I also had the sweet potato fries with lemon tabasco aoili Delicious The fries were very crispy and the taste of the lemon tabasco aoili is delicious Ask for a side of their house ketchup too It goes very well with the fries as well The bun for the burgers are very well made Its light and fluffy so it doesnt override the taste of the meat itself Personally I hate it when I get a burger and i get a mouth full of dense bread and cant even taste the meatOne thing Im disappointed about is that i didnt see the Madagascar Vanilla Milkshake on the menu anymore That was definitely the BEST milkshake I have ever had and I dont even like milkshakes The service here isnt bad Its a young staff and the bar offers a pretty good selection of beer

Author: Heather M.
Content: I will say that Im not totally in love with the all burgers cooked medium thing I like a rare stillmooing burger  I didnt get it here That said the burgers were all tasty The one with the egg was good  probably definitely wouldve been better if it were rare The barbecue one also excellent Bacon mac and cheese is to die for and I really like the truffle fries even though I typically prefer thin fries They gave us a peanut butter shake on the house for dessert  I would go back just for that Mmmm

Author: Anne C.
Content: Ive been to DMK a few times and have not been disappointed yet  Im not a huge fan of beef so the option to swap a turkey burger in for any of their signature burgers is fantastic  Ive always gone with a pretty good sized group and we love to order a variety of their a la carte fries I especially like the sweet potato fries  On my last visit I went rogue and didnt even order a burger had a great wedge salad to share and AMAZING mac and cheese with bacon and balsamic onions  Delicious

Author: AV G.
Content: the place has 500 reviews  Whatever your current favorite burger place is  DMK will not replace it  Very nice place totally together on how they handle things Nothing specialeverything is goodDrinks are very expensivefood is at  market price but very small portions  Do NOT get the blue cheese friesDont bother unless you collect restaurantsPompei across the street is MUCH better

Author: Melissa M.
Content: Pretty good beef for their burgers  nothing too special in my opinion though Fried pickles were great though

Author: Cecil S.
Content: Really great burgers loved the 13 Portabello w turkey Lose one star for dirty silverware

Author: Kensey W.
Content: so ive been meaning to try this place for a while and im glad i finally made it the atmosphere is a typical bar and really loud and even on a wednesday night we still had to wait a few minutes for a tablethey have a lot of different burgers i ended up having the lamb which was pretty good but not as juicy as i usually like my burgers i did really like the tapenade and tzatziki though that was a delicious touch on a burger the bread is also soft and not so dense which i likebut the highlight of the meal were our sides the parmesan truffle oil fries were delicious they were hot and crispy with plenty of cheese sprinkled on top the mac and cheese guyere bacon and red onion was soo good it was hot and melty and gooey and delicious the only complaint id have about those two dishes would be that they were really really salty but i guess thats to be expected considering the type of foods they were the miracle was that they were even good as leftoversoh i also tried their vanillaginger soda it was disappointing and not that fizzy think a supersweet cream soda with a slice of ginger in it that brings me to a story that will be boring for you but im still grudging about i said to the person who brought us our food you dont do refills on the sodas do you and she said shed ask our server a few minutes later a glass of soda shows up at the table and i assume they do do refills but they dont i was charged for the soda which is fine because its only a few dollars but the part that makes me angry is that i would have gotten a beer if i was going to pay for my next drink not a mediocre soda id already tried that was mostly a glass of ice anyway so missing out on my beer i left grumpier than when i was eatingstill ill probably be back to try some other burgers you cant tell with a lamb burger how good a places real burger will be

Author: Irene G.
Content: Went to DMK on a weekday night  There wasnt a wait which I liked very much  However we were seated too close to other customers which to me is a turnoff because you almost feel like you have to keep conversations at a minimum  The place and overall ambience is casual  comfortable Servers were attentive and not overbearingOn to the reason why we came hereThe burgers here are awesomely good  I liked that it didnt completely fall apart immediately after the first bite   I ordered the number 4 Roasted Hatch Green Chile with Fried Egg and bacon and it was delicious  Any burger with a fried egg on it gets major points in my book  I was tempted to make it a double burger but thought better of it  The regular burger is actually filling enough  We also had the Mac  Cheese with Parmesan Crust which was very tastyI still prefer Kumas over DMK because I do love me some pretzel buns  Plus Kumas burger is bigger and the burger comes with fries  DMK burgers do not come with friesyou must order them separately

Author: Rob J.
Content: Love that you can basically make your own burger and the toppings seem endless eg fried eggperfection The choice of fries is nice too Wish you could make a reservation bc like Fish Bar next door it can get crowded fast But thats the only thing I would changeoh and sign up for their rewards card you get 1 point for each 1 spent

Author: Darren F.
Content: the place looks pretty small from the outside and surely it was small inside also this is my second attempt coming here the first time me and friends came here it was too busy and we didnt want to waitso yesterday i found the time to come back here with a friend and we got seated without any wait it was still very busy too the service was goodi ordered the the 1 which was aged cheddarsmoked bacon charred balsamic red onions with rufus teasgues bbq sauce and added a second patty for an additional 3 also ordered parmesan truffle cream fries to sharesadly i was kind of disappointed on how small the burger was the burger tasted good tho the meat patties tasted fresh and it was tender the buns was warm and soft i really like the bbq sauce they used on the burger the parmesan truffle cream fries was just ok Im a big fries fan and after reading all the reviews about their fries i just had to come try it myself but i was let down the fries itself was good tho i would prefer just dipping their fries in ketchup instead of spending the extra on parmesan cheese and dipping it in creamoverall i think DMK is just OK not bad and nothing to b wowed about  but for the price i do think the burger should be bigger

Author: Katie K.
Content: Man This place was great I loved the burger and the fries were good too  The waitress was really nice and bought our table a some fries thought that was nice  I had the number 1 it was quite divinely delicious  I enjoyed the bbq flavor mixed in with the balsamic onions  YUM  The fries were great too top of the notch  I am not sure how you could not love their burgers  They cook them medium and if you arent a fan of that all you have to do is ask them to cook it longer  Definitely on my shortlist for good burger joints

Author: Katie R.
Content: I just cant give this place 4 stars  I want to because my burger was amazing but the rest of it was disappointing  first ill complain about something not in my control which was the service  maybe we were on an off night but it took a good 20 minutes to pay the check and the table waiting next to us waited for even longer for a side of ketchupnow the things that are in my control but still sad to admit were contributing factors to my disappointment  alright here it goes im a picky eater and by that i mean a vegetarian  with that said i totally get that they dont even have to have veggie options but some things seem unfair  their veggie patty looked amazing but i just wanted to have slightly different toppings WHY are all veggie burgers made healthy  dammit us vegetarians want to be fat too which really meant adding BBQ sauce and red onion instead of pesto and eggplant  well thats a 2 extra charge  usually that sort of thing doesnt bug me but the menu is all one price 9 FYI so it doesnt make any sense at all to me  it costs extra to substitute something for something else that is the same exact price really  lastly and just a bummer but not affecting my rating the fries are cooked in beef fat  i totally understand and am so ever grateful that our waitress let me know  yes i loved mcdonalds fries when they were cooked in beef fat too so i get why its done  she offered some other fried foods that i just wasnt totally up for as they were fried in canola oil and i just wonder to myself if fries cant be fried in canola oil too  i honestly dont know which is why im not deducting for it but i wish it was possible  sighNOW  for the positive  my burger was awesome  my dining companion had the old fashioned regular burger and loved it  the bun was fantastic and as much as i love pretzel buns id opt for this one because you dont leave feeling like you are going to explode  it was slightly crispy and just so delish  the drink i had was good and i suspect the others are as well

Author: Randall K.
Content: Great outing  Took family 4 from teens to toddlers  Very nice  Just get there early in evening as the place was turning from restaurant to happening hotspot  Everyone loved their food  The service was OK but server seemed a little busy  Only the 6 year old didnt like the food  I would take everyone back  Great place for adult dinner if we want to mingle with a younger crowd  Hip place and easy on the wallet  Fed family of 6 for 12500  Some private tables and some shared tables  No reservations but did not wait

Author: Phillip K.
Content: 4 of us went to DMK on Saturday night after a comedy show  Id been hearing great things about DMK for a while that its a top tier burger joint in Chicago  I ordered the Holy Guacamole burger and my sister in law got the bbq burger  We split large Wisconsin Cheddar and scallion friesSo first off everything is ala carte so the burgers dont come w french fries  Not a complaint but worth noting as the 9 burger seems cheap until you realize that to add the 34 for small fries makes it not so cheapThe food  Honestly it was just okay  Very thin beef patties  The toppings definitely dominated the burger  I couldnt really taste the meat  I tried the bbq burger too and it was just so heavily sauced  The bacon was delicious but any signs of the burger in there were lost  The fries were okay but portioned pretty small  We bought a large for 5 and it just wasnt enough  The best part of the meal was my beerOverall Im glad I went but wouldnt ever go back  For people looking for a great burger but not the Kumas line Id suggest Bad Apple or Lockdown

Author: Aaron B.
Content: Being one serving of veggies a day shy from being a carnivore I take my meat consumption seriously and boy does this place deliver Everything is perfect its wide open floor space that somehow doesnt ever feel too cozy or too large the beer menu is not overwhelming but something I couldnt possibly digest after even a visit or two and the burgers and fries are sublime I would definitely go with the 3 burger sort of a burger done reubenstyle None of the ingredients over power any of the others and the potato bun doesnt melt under the weight of the burger which is a major pet peeve of mine The fries especially the salt and pepper and the sweet potato are about the closest to the ambrosia of Zeus that I will ever get but to go for a truly Olympian endeavor it is definitely in the fried okra and pickles its like a dance party on my fungiform papila Boom To top it all off their homemade sodas which are placed in the afterthought location at the bottom of the menu are also quite awesome especially the vanillaginger which is what the streams of the Big Rock Candy Mountain must taste like But with all good things there are some problems albeit only one I can think of If its a weekend or anything where youd expect people to be going out to dinner that night expect to wait a couple minutes This is not necessarily a total negative because its testament to the cuisine on hand but is definitely annoying Other than that the waitstaff is amazing and extremely helpful I recently took my little sister here on a school night in an attempt to win Brother of the Year but when things were looking to run a little late our waitress Kiley was more than helpful in helping us get our food and was extremely attentive If youre in Chicago for a night I would definitely direct you here for something that I consider one of the better restaurant experiences in the city

Author: L. D.
Content: Actual visit was 92211  Turkey Burger Parm Truffle Fries  I enjoyed the burger more than the fries  It was an AOK meal but I have no need to rush back

Author: Amy X.
Content: its winter and im trying to save some money on heat  solution  eat more burgers and fries  roommate and i decided to grab some food and bond over the universal social equalizer heavy fattening american food  however we also wanted to bond over sandra bullock so the decision was made to order togowe both order the 5 prosciutto fontina pesto red pepper sea salt and vinegar chips and share an order of parmesan truffle cream fries  a heads up dmk does not allow you to substitute ingredients  as a self recognized highmaintenance orderer this does not bode well  WHY cant i switch my fontina for blue brie  ill pay for it  ill even come back in the kitchen and do it myself  please i just want some pungent cheesebut no cigar  all in all the meal was meh  we werent asked how we would like our burgers so both of our patties were cooked well done  if you would like your burger a bit bloodier i would speak up as it doesnt seem like the default  salt and vinegar chips were storebought  truffle cream was good but honestly the deliciousness did not exceed what would be expected from the sum of the two parts  at the end roommate and i were more enthralled with the movie than the food  at least we had sandra bullock to ease the pain

Author: Katie R.
Content: Good prices and interesting combos Ive been a couple times now and have had a turkey and a lamb burger But beware Diet Coke lovers no refills here

Author: Cynthia E.
Content: Had very high hopes which were dashed The service was great friendly and efficient   The French Country Ale was crisp and slightly rich  The wasabi slaw was the bomb and the fried okra and pickles were among the best weve had  The burgers were disappointing and actually needed salt although everything else was perfectly seasoned  We had the lamb burger which would have been tasty but the feta which was terrific BTW overwhelmed the flavor of the lamb  The most disappointing though was the burger with Hatch chiles  Hatch chiles are hard to find in this neck o the woods as was evidenced by their scarcity on my burger which arrived dry and overcooked with an over cooked fried eggBOOhardly a Hatch chile in sight and the meat tasted of liver which is a dead giveaway that the meat was old  For 900  And a la carte at that  Give me Bop n Grill ANY day

Author: David L.
Content: Cant believe how great these burgers fries beer desert are Great experience everytime and Ive been here a lot I go

Author: Joshua N.
Content: Im really starting to fall in love with the insane beer list and the awesome burgers I think Ive had about 4 of the burgers so far So I have some work to do for sure Really like that unless there is a big game on they play a Chicago based movie Cool stuff

Author: Sean M.
Content: Eh it was ok Nice inside but food isnt that great Staff is slow too Wont be going backIll go to Kumas

Author: Sunil D.
Content: Two of the best burgers Ive had in town and yes Im a fan of their rockstar competitor on Belmont Before I get to the food the service was phenomenal We sat at the bar for our meal and literally had 34 people making sure we had everything we needed without being overbearing or intrusive Everyone was really friendly and it was one of those rare times that the service really elevated the meal experience for me especially for a place that brands itself as a Burger Bar The food was great from top to bottom I started with a Caesar salad which had the quality of something I would expect from MKs or another high end restaurant A whole romaine head with anchovies and a great dressing it was on par with the version at David Burkes Prime for literally 14 the price As for the two burgers half of each I cant choose a favorite The pastrami with sauerkraut and russian dressing basically a reuben on top of a burger was phenomenal As heavy and greasy as it sounds the burger 5 oz manages to be flavorful juicy and satisfying without being overbearing If I had to choose a favorite though the lamb burger would take the slight edge Basically its a gourmet upscale version of a gyro Lamb patty with tatziki sauce and a greek salad instead of the standard LTO The bun they used was unusual in a good way not your standard burger bun more like a fresh baked artisinal bread not sure if it is or not it was firm enough to keep the burger intact which is also aided by the thin patty and had a great texture  The fries parmesan with a truffle based dip were also a big hit To top everything off the beer selection was top notch one of the few places in town that have Dortmunder Gold on tapThe atmosphere was somewhat lacking and it was a little too dark for my liking but I was so heavily distracted by the quality of my meal I could have cared less

Author: anita m.
Content: My momma always taught me if I didnt have nice things to say to not say anything at all Luckily I dont have to worry for DMK For starters the menu is very straight forward  all burgers are 8 and fries are couple bucks additional but definitely worth the money If there is anything that I will go back to DMK for it would be the Parmesan Truffle cream fries Seriously those alone have the power to lull me back there As for my burger which is presumably what they are known for was a tad bit dry Must have been a bad day I assume I look forward to my next visit the turkey burger seems pretty safe

Author: Emily S.
Content: Ive been back to DMK several times and I have really loved everything Ive eaten  New favorites include the fried pickles and okra the salmon burger SO GOOD and the sweet potato fries with lemon aioli  Drinks are a touch on the pricey side but the rest of the menu is pretty reasonable  Snag seats at the bar for the best service

Author: James Michael S.
Content: Had the veggie burger based on reviews from the trib and it had all the right moves Went in on a Sunday night and it was packed I can definitely understand why

Author: Kevin M.
Content: I LOVE DMK Burgers are so good Every time Ive been there the waiter will give my table something for free Not sure if this happens to everyone though ha Great selection of beers too

Author: Ashley R.
Content: I took my boyfriend here for a mid week date and am very glad I did It was pretty packed for a Thursday night but we waited and grabbed drinks from the bar The bartender Matt grabbed us and gave us two seats at the bar He was super friendly knowledgeable and not over the top He gave us great suggestions and even bought us an appetizer He also brought out his favorite ketchup which was amazing and was genuinely caring We were very impressed overall The service is what will bring us back Matt was great and made our experience

Author: Stacie K.
Content: I dont like burgers  But DMK Burger Bar makes me like burgers

Author: Diana T.
Content: Overall I feel like my experience is pretty similar to other reviewers Burgers are decently good but def not awesome Fries are tasty Service is good Environment is okay But the drinks are way too expensive especially when you want soda But this place is still pretty packed so patrons must love it

Author: Brandon V.
Content: Overall had a pretty good experience here but first Ill address the things that could have made it better for me They dont take reservations and given that they have very limited seating space this led to our waiting over an hour for a table on Saturday evening The system they use for seating once you do arrive is pretty screwy  Just a girl walking around with a clipboard who takes your name and gives you a low estimate of how long your wait may be  There is no announcement of names when theres space for you and your name comes up  There is no vibrating lighted coaster that alerts you that its your turn either  The plan is to simply walk around every few minutes after your estimated wait time has passed try to find the hostess again and ask if you can sit down yet  Just weird and not customerfriendly at all Since there is limited space you are basically going to share a table with people you dont know once you are seated if you go on a busy night  Actually it may be a different table but there will be only be about 12 inches of space between it and the next one  This coupled with the noise level means this isnt a place to have a private intimate dinnerOtherwise food was very good  Probably one of the better burgers Ive had Service once we reached the table was more than adequate and I was surprised by how quickly the food came out after we orderedI might try this place again on a slow Tuesday afternoon and see if adding another star may be in order

Author: Scott H.
Content: A pretty damned good burger in a great neighborhood  My only complaint is that the toppings seem to somewhat overpower the actual burger  Fries are great  The beer list was extensive

Author: Sourma K.
Content: I had the Grassfed Lamb Sheeps Milk Feta Olive Tapenade Greek Salad Tzatziki and that will probably be the best lamb burger I will have in my life We also had the fried okra and pickles which was my first time trying and wasnt disappointed I cant wait to go back

Author: William R.
Content: Good veggie burger just wish the fries were not cooked in beef fat Great beer selection cool atmosphere

Author: Suana W.
Content: this place satisfied my burger craving and offered up an interesting selection of beers to boot i only tried one the two brothers coffee beer that was available only for one day but definitely want to come back to try the regular two brothers on tap and the milk stout how did anybody ever come up with the idea of putting milk in beerbut i digress i came here at 830PM on a wed evening with three coworkers and the wait was about 20 minutes not as horrible as i expected i got the burger with the green chile and egg while the others got the lamb burger and the guacamole aoili burger the lamb burger got rave reviews we also split a few fries for the table my favorite was the truffle parmesan id definitely go back to try the lamb burger and the other beers

Author: Marissa S.
Content: Yummy yummy yummy  Ive liked everything Ive tried here from the regular burgers to the turkey burgers  Fresh bakery buns and high quality toppings  The service can be a little spotty and its definitely too loud but we keep coming back for more

Author: Larry B.
Content: One of the best burger meals I have ever had Great bartenders a truly good lamb burger out of this world sweet potato fries and a draft IPA that was one of the best I ever tasted Will definitely return People should make the pilgrimage if they have not already been

Author: brian b.
Content: Yes we ate a lot of burgers in Chicago this trip Burgers at DMK were very good Buns were crazy fresh It definitely all works together and these guys have their act down pat The July special Toasted Marshmellow shake needs to a become a regular item  killer Very nice selection of brews but stock it up with more locals folks You got to get those wonderful brews from Ale Syndicate Wild Onion Revolution and 5 Rabbits going The Half Acre was nice Parmasean fries were good and complemented the burgers well Server had to be new because my order was wrong then we were charged for 3 burgers not 2 since he had to put in a new order for my correct burger and didnt catch it till we were on the subway Just as much my fault as his for not checking the bill  Id still be back Right off the Purple line

Author: Gregory L.
Content: Day 1  Walking into a dim lit chic 50s music burger bar was a little bit confusing to me at first Being welcomed by owners David morton and Chef Michael Kormick changed that within the minute  Their fleet of the fast paced hard working servers and bartenders are always at your service no matter how packed it isWith a bar owned by such a reputable pair the ingredients are no less than top quality  Their buns made specially for DMK and delivered fresh daily by Highland Baking Co  The meats cheeses beer wine condiments and produce are second to noneOk ok so enough fantasizing lets get down to business  I walk in with my brother sit down at the bar and order the big red wine  It is exactly that  A special blend of grapes selected by Michael Kormick  The even bigger is supposed to be available soon  It is comparable to a petite syrah and I hear very good things  Then we order burgers fries and a caeser romaine salad I chose the GrassFed Lamb burger with sheeps milk feta olive tapenade tomato  onion salad tzatziki  All the flavors of the classical greek gyro with a twist and eruption of flavor  I cant believe Im saying this but it paired perfectly with the wineMy brother ordered the Roasted Hatch Green Chile burger with fried farm egg sonoma jack cheese smoked bacon Along with a chocolate shake  The green chile and jack cheese gave off a nice pickled spicy kick and was then mellowed out by the smoky baconThe shake looked like it was prepared with their chocolate ice cream malt and chocolate syrup I didnt try it but my brother seemed to really enjoy itNow for the french fries  We ordered the truffle parmesan fries and the bacon bleu cheese fries  The truffle cream sauce is certainly a winner Not too tangy and overpowering with parm cant go wrong with them  The bacon and bleu cheese were a nice change  The bleu cheese has a mellow sharpness and was melted over the fries topped with bacon  I mean its bacon of course it was good  The fries are cut in the standard pomme frites shape with their skins left on They are seasoned plentifully with salt and pepper  Its the toppings that really make themDay 2  I live across the street and couldnt wait to go back  I went their for lunch this time  I ordered the big salad with chickenchoice of chicken or imported tuna the chunk style I believe the deviled eggs and my brother ordered the 1Aged Cheddar Smoked Bacon charred balsamic red onions rufus teagues bbq sauce Michael Kormicks favorite bbq sauce from a place near st louis The salad had mixed greens with fennel and artichoke hearts on it as well  Just enough to fill me up  The deviled eggs are the standard deviled eggs Good cheap nothing special  I preferred the prior burger choices over this selection  The onions just didnt have as much flavor from the balsamic as I was hoping it would  However the barbeque sauce is a great sweet thick sauce to compliment the bacon and cheddarThe one difference I did notice with these burgers is that the toppings are actually strategically placed on the bottom of the burger so that it hits your tongues taste buds accordingly  They are not too big and if you do want them bigger you can always order a double  I will definitely back to try the rest of their selection

Author: geri s.
Content: DMK welcome to Lakeview  I am so happy to have you in my neighborhood  I feel like you guys did everything right  The staff was very attentive and friendly  One of the  owners was on sight hosting  How awesome is that  The burger selection is amazing  The prices are more than reasonable Im obsessed with the truffle fries  I had them for lunch today and I am considering going back for dinner  I live within a block of Counter Burger and Select Cut and have to say that this place blows them away  5 well deserved stars

Author: Jaime E.
Content: excellent burger stellar buns just enough fries i had the burger with marinated portobello cambozola blue griddled scallions dijonnaise mc had the roasted hatch green chile fried farm egg jack cheese smoked bacon we each got our own portion of fries regular and truffle  i think it would have been more impressive if i got one of the fries with a fancy cheese but i thought they were fine plain  simplewent back not too long ago and got one of their malts thick the deep fried pickles  okra very nice and tried the veggie burger which was texturally interesting and appealing but didnt have your run of the mill black bean base and it seemed deep fried for an external crunch which was nice and not greasy as you may be picturing to beat crowds i probably would only go for an early lunch on the weekend i hate to wait even for really good burgers

Author: Lindsey W.
Content: While my fries were the most amazing thing Ive ever had I felt that my turkey burger was a bit plain Even after trying the beef burgers I felt that they left something to be desired Great bar setting just too crowded on a Saturday night if youre looking for a good dinner Expect long waits and shared tables

Author: Shannon M.
Content: So I was really craving a veggie burger and fries and so I texted veggie burger Chicago to Google and DMK Burger Bar great way to choose a place I know so The Boy and I headed over I should mention that it just happened to be the Saturday before St Patricks Day so it was crazy Therefore I wont gripe about the 30 minute wait that led to us eating at the bar instead of waiting even longer for an actual table But even though it was crazy it didnt take much effortcleavage to get the attention of the bartenders that Whirling Tiger drink on their menu is dangerous and the Lemonade was really good tooNow about the food I will admit that I wasnt expecting to enjoy my food all that much because I am generally weary of places that dont let me choose my food optionstoppings so I wasnt happy that I could only get the 12 I dont like portobello mushrooms so I really did have only one veggie option But OH MY GOD I will never doubt them again I had a foodgasm of epic proportions It was so good that a guy came up behind me to ask about my burger  and when The Boy went to the mens room later he ran into the same guy who said his wife ordered the same thing and loved it also It was made perfectly with the eggplant being an excellent complement to the texture of the burger and the black pepper and sea salt fries were just what I was looking for The Boy a meatatarian if there ever was one loved his burger also dont remember what was on it but I think it was the 1 but the cheese on his fries tasted funny I blame Wisconsin for that The only problem was that there wasnt more of it especially the fries  I ended up ordering some additional sweet potato fries and The Boy ordered some additional mac  cheese alsoOh and I should add that The Boy was really happy about the bill considering how well we ate and drank that nightSo thank you DMK Burger Bar for setting me straight and quelling my hardcore craving I am definitely a fan now

Author: Karen L.
Content: There has been a lot of hype about DMK so I was expecting a burger that rivals Kumas burgers but I did not think that was the case at allMaybe I wasnt in a burger mood but I thought the burger felt a little flat I actually had a hard time deciding what burger to get since there was something that I didnt like in each of the options which I know you could take out but then it just seemed like a burger that was too plain Ended up getting the burger with portabello mushroom and dijon The burger was just okay it was really salty for my tastes though Also ordered the salt and pepper fries with the truffle cream sauce The sauce was good but the fries were way overfried and way too salty They could have potential And I would also suggest them to have a plain garlic aioli sauce too I dont know what places are trying to go so fancy with lemon aioli because it is just not that good Try different herbs or something They do have a nice beer list and their blue cheeseiceberg lettuce was decent It is also very loud in there so hard to hold a conversation

Author: Gabe L.
Content: This is a pretty good spot the burger selection is very intriguing  For my first visit I went with the turkey burger with swiss tomato arugula and dijonaise  It was very tasty bun was a nice buttery brioche bun  My one gripe is that the patty was very thin probably 6 oz  Definitely smaller than youd expect from a place called a burger bar  I got a single order of the salt and pepper fries they were pretty standard but tasty  I will definitely be going back here Im excited to try some of the beef burger offerings

Author: Tiff H.
Content: I have to admitDMK is one of the few things that will get me to go to Lincoln Park nowadays Love is such a strong word and Im not sure if I want to commit myself to use it when it comes to my relationship with this place as of yetits too earlyIve been here twice nowand heres a breakdown of the highlightsand the lowlightsTurkey Burger 9 Amazing Not usually a fan of turkey burgers but the eggplant and the portobello combo with the blue cheese cole slaw was just heaven Yes Ive ordered it twiceThe truffle fries and parmesan fries are nothing specialin my humble opinionKitchen Caesar Salad I felt like Brutus when it came outmy companion and I literally sat there for about 5 minutes trying to figure out why on earth would someone serve a salad like that Basically all of your ingredients are served on top of uncut romaine lettuce slices It was pretty good once we figured out how to tackle itFried okra  pickles This isnt mamas southern stylethe entire vegetable is lightly friedno little ballshee It was delicioushowever I was sad we got more pickles than okraMeat in general Yes Ive tried my companions burgers Delicious Sogood Service Excellent all the time friendly and speedyAtmosphere The music is just so damn loudDrinks Id stick to the beers on draft My cocktails were either way to sweet or just not what I even remotely expectedPrice 23 beers  2 burgers  a couple of sides  20ish tip  50ishVerdict Honestly the 4th star is purely for the burgers and good service Ill be backbut only if I have a reason to come back into the LakeviewLP areaand hopefully that reason will be moving to my side of town soon Youll see me there again before summer is overmay as well get as much out of this fling while I can

Author: Fuffie G.
Content: I went back last week to try a real burger since I did not love my veggie burger last time We got there at 645 on a Tuesday If you dont care that your eating a little early thats the time to go No wait There were three of us in our party We all ordered a different burger I had the 1 Delicious The meat was so flavorful and the bacon they use was cooked perfectly We also ordered a side of Parmesan fries and cheese fries The Parmesan fries are definitely my favorite with the aioli dipping sauce I am not a big fan of cheddar fries but they too get a thumbs up I cannot wait to go again for another great burger My only complaint which I know is a complaint to many that have posted reviews is that the music is a little loud

Author: Dina L.
Content: Good food Not the best burger in Chicago Shakes a little too rich and thick for me Turkey burger has been my favorite so far and Ive been 3 times

Author: Liz P.
Content: This place was greatgourmet burgers for 8 Cant beat a deal like that I got the 2 with onion string crisps bleu cheese and chipotle ketchup and it was absolutely DELICIOUS Some friends and I shared their Parmesan fries with cream truffle sauce and as one of the group put it one could easily eat a whole plate of Parmesan truffle fries by them self So good A cold hard cider paired perfectly with my burger I cant wait to go back and try other burgers on their menu as well as their mac  cheese The only complaint I have is our server was pretty horrible at her jobbut otherwise the food more than made up for it

Author: amanda g.
Content: oooo yum i have to say that i think dmk is as close to kumas goodness as ive found and i didnt have to wait at all to eat its not quite as good but definitely close its also a completely different atmosphere very polished feeling but not pretentious great casual atmosphere i went there with max and a friend at about 730 last night we were seated immediatelywe had deviled eggs and the chop salad for apps for my meal i tried the lamb burger with feta wow just wow i am not usually a member of the clean plate club but i definitely finished my entire burger amazingi also tried maxs egg burger and it was great too we had the parm truffle fries too so good so bottom line if youre in the mood for a great gourmet burger and dont wanna wait 2 hours for kumas youll probably satisfy your craving with a delicious DMK burger

Author: vivian c.
Content: Im a sucker for grassfed beef and the truffle CREAM fries are identical to the bigger brother MKs  the greek burger is delish as is the burger with bacon  YUM  expect to wait up to an hour if you go for dinner weve gone in the late afternoon on the weekends and not had to wait forever

Author: Katie C.
Content: This place is awesome and cheap  I had the bison burger 10 with a side of sweet potato fries with tobasco aioli  It was killer

Author: Steve G.
Content: I went here for a midafternoon lunch with my infant daughter It was a very good experience as the servers were all very friendly personable and accommodating Very pleasant modern interior fun vibe etc The burgers are delicious made with grassfed beef The beer and cocktails list is solid and interesting I imagine it gets crowded in the evening so maybe go during the day for lunch or brunch Ill definitely be back

Author: Kerry M.
Content: So I had hopes for DMK but wasnt hugely impressed It was good but I probably wouldnt go out of my way to go back The restaurant was packed and my friend and I grabbed a couple seats at the bar where we stayed for the duration  There is a good beer selection but the food was just alright We ordered quite a few things to share and everything came out really greasy The service was good no problems there Overall it was a decent meal but its certainly not the best burger Ive ever had If youre in the neighborhood it might be a fun place to stop for dinner Just wouldnt go out of my way for it

Author: John T.
Content: So I got the 4 with a fried egg and thought that it was delicious My one and only complaint is that the egg itself was kind of burnt and tasted funny but the place was great  Everyone in there seemed to be happy and that is saying something in the Windy City I recommend that people get the Sweet Potato Fries because they were awesome  Great place to go and grab a burger and not break the bank

Author: Rick J.
Content: Ive eaten here 3 times so far and will keep coming back to work my way down the numbered list  Each meal was excellent in every way  I really like how DMK focuses on its quality not size and quantity of food  What may look like a modestsized burger for Chicagos gourmet burger restos will end up being perfectly just right juicy and satisfying  I promise  Love their chunky blue cheese or other cheese topped fries  Ive enjoyed their shakes mmmpeanutbutter as well as their solid beer selection  Nothing but kudos to the chef and the cool servers

Author: Kevin O.
Content: Do I even need to review this place  Probably not but I like it so much I will  Great burgers left hand milk stout on tap pretty girls wisconsin cheddar fries to die for  DMK is the BOMB

Author: Jason P.
Content: DMK delivers a solid burger with pretty amazing fries and ultimately thats what you can ask for  All these burger places tries to amp up the experience by providing unique burgers and fries weird combos and specialties throughout the restaurant but DMK doesnt try to act like that  They provide good meat great buns and probably some of the best fries Ive tasted

Author: Edward M.
Content: decided to take a hiatus from the prethanksgiving diet to stop by DMK the best things about this place are its drink list great beer selection service super friendly helpful and CUTE and atmosphere pretty hip without being intimidating or pretentious at all plus the portions are pretty big and the prices are very reasonable but i thought the food was good not great ordered the onion strips underseasoned a bit greasy huge plateful fried pickles and okra delicious 1 burger solid the truffle fries probably the best out of them all bacon blue cheese fries close second sweet potato fries good and another kind of fries i forgot except had cheese that ended up congealing and mac  cheese standard everything was pretty good but HEAVY burger without lettuce tomato etc a bunch of fried stuff generally im pretty good at meals without nonpotato vegetables but i had trouble getting through here maybe next time ill get one of the sodas blood orange intriguingso yeah a decent place i dont think ill be craving it anytime but i wouldnt mind coming back to try whatever else i didnt try just after thanksgiving though

Author: Jeremy T.
Content: After two visits DMK has shown they make the best burger in Chicago in my view They also feature a very strong and unique beer selection as well as cool atmosphere and friendly service On a side note the Truffle Fries are a must

Author: wesley w.
Content: Been here a few times for lunch and had no problem getting a table In fact had rock star parking But what else could I expectOne time sat at the bar and had nice chat with the bartender He tried to inform us why DMK overcooks all the meat Really Theres no choosing your tenderness Its all overdone The bartender mentioned the health reasons which is a bit far fetched if youre truly using top grass fed beef But the burger had an awesome home cooked flavor only cause my mom used to over cook everything too But a grass fed burger and tallow fries arent offered everywhere so we found our way back just yesterday Had better service sitting at a table with a waitress My wife ordered a sidecar and it arrived at the table almost full Seriously Use a smaller glass if you cant fill it up For 12 either use better liquor or fill it up My draft beer was tasty but again small glass Im just used to getting a pint off draft Oh for all I know it was a pint but in a little roller glass Maybe its one of the optical illusions Good fries Good eggs Stay clear of the sweet potatoe fries if you like that sort of thing theyre as bland as the decor at DMK

Author: Jon L.
Content: Go for the burgers Pay 8 dollars Leave happy  Nuff said

Author: Sarah F.
Content: They were great  Amazing  Delicious  Juicy  I loved everything about the burgers buns cheeses and toppings on these burgers  Just cant beat a homemade floured bun  I also appreciated all of the types of fries you could choose all with their own dipping sauces  This place has managed to produce the FIRST crispy sweet potato fry Ive ever eaten and the best  So crunch  delicious with the most addicting tobascolemo aioli  Also a nice cockail wine  beer list  I will be back  A LOT

Author: Phil T.
Content: DMK  Delicious meaty or Knot Burger Bar  Ok I had to make it work knot  not  Meaning if you want beef turkey or veg this place has it and I tried all of them were sooo good  5s are hard to give but when giving thought  All of the burgers were great the fries excellent wait staff and ambience were up there  I obviously went with the 12 veggie burger w the blue cheese and bacon fries  Yes I know that has meat but come on how can you turn that down plus I know other friends ordered the sweet potatoe friesmy 2nd choice so why not    Hands down they were the best fries out of the ones ordered sweet potatoe w lemon tabasco 2nd  and fries w parmesan truffle really good but 3rd  To me there is one item that makes the burger really stand out from anyone else dont worry Felipe will release the secret to everyone  Its the bun yoooooos   You can put anything in the middle of a fresh warm bun and it will make the sandwich like today meat turkey or veg whatever the item is it was truly enjoyable  I tried all 312  veg so much flavor sooooo tasty very fresh tasting 5  basically an italian burger very yummy and then 9  turkey burger w an egg  come on throw a fried egg on anything its going to be good  I can honestly say though every burger was top notch w flavor taste deliciousness no matter the meat  Even better each burger and order of fries was the perfect portion size  Attended here on a sat during smack dab in the middle of lunch and it was only a 510min wait  The only possible knock which didnt bother me that could to others for basically burger and fries it was like 15 including tip  Me myself would rather pay for the freshness and quality so if you want a 6 greasy 12 lb burger joint go somewhere else and ill come here happily

Author: Patrick C.
Content: I live very close to this place and think Im pretty damn lucky because of it Very good burgers sides and drink list I have no complaints at all Service is great Prices are reasonable I highly recommend their take on the big Mac called the big dmk

Author: K C.
Content: I like the 3  I like their ideal of House Lab Drinks sadly  I didnt like the taste  Its all good  Service was nice and quick  I would stick to H2O next time I come

Author: Igor Z.
Content: Friend about the sweet potatoe fries dipping sauce if cum tasted like that there would be a lot more gay guys Nuf said

Author: Michelle D.
Content: While there werent many beers on tap there were a lot of good botlted beers to choose from  Several burger mac  cheese and fries options  I had a burger with aged cheddar and smoked bacon  I split the onion straws and sea saltpepper fries  Great ambiance  Will definitely be back soon

Author: Fallon D.
Content: Went over to try this place bcause Im a gal who likes craft beer and burgers The beer selection is good but nothing particularly fantastic You can find these beers just about anywhere I frequent It is nice to not have to deal with Bud and Miller though Their cocktail menu is fantastic Well thought out and inventive without being pretentious The Rhubarb Delight was spectacular and I dont like gin but Hendricks is in a class of its own The Whirling Tiger was tasty and it made me giggle with their version of a Michelada PBRMEASAPWe went there when there were free fries and that made me pleased They were VERY good and the ketchup was great I just wished I had gotten the truffle fries The deviled eggs were ok mine are better but it was sad you only got three think of people sharingThe mac and cheese was boring bland and kind of gross Almost an afterthought to the menu They should add some smokey cheese corn green onion tomato and then it might be somethingOur burgers were pretty good The bread was soft and a nice complement to the burger The bison burger with pickled onion and blueberry bbq was quite tasty and something I would get again The lamb was pretty good on first bite but by the time I finished my half my taste buds were worn out It was just too much salt cheese tzaziki Just too much Glad we shared and I only had to eat half Not sure I could have eaten anymore Service was competant and nice I was wellpleased The thing I didnt like was how the place was designed Too industrial without having the space to do it Cold in temperature I hate community tables and these were not set up to give a diner enough room if all are occupied If I wanted to eavesdrop on random conversations Id sit at the bar This is a place Id make a point to bring a 3rd wheel just to get a table Also there were like 6 kids running around the place Not what I expected and just kind of weirded me out And I also wish they would cook their burgers medium rareOverall pretty decent but Id probably just want to get takeout and I dont think this food would do well with any time in togo containers The drink menu of this place rules

Author: Matt P.
Content: As far as burger bars go in Chicago  sure theres other places I like better  Thats not saying DMK is bad because its really good especially their patty melts and 6 varieties of fries not to mention their deviled eggs  But even better than their food is the staff especially Drew  that guy is awesome

Author: Rocky H.
Content: YeahIm sorry I went to Kumas Corner yesterday That place has you beat by the most ridiculous landslide even if your clientele is more my style Sorry More than happy to give you another whirl when I know you improve your burger by a lot

Author: Peter P.
Content: In short if you DONT want to wait for Kumas Corner and prefer a B burger experience without waiting too long go here  Its very clean ambience more like a corporate lunch hour area and a good date place  My beef with the joint is their burger meat doesnt taste that great  And their portion for their appetizers and such are way too small for my hard earned money  Is it palatable  Of course otherwise this place would have closed within a month  Is it as comparable as Kumas burger  NOBeer is decent enough though although too pricey in my opinion  I know I shouldnt compare this place to Kumas but honestly if youre trying to compete gourmet burgers Kumas set a benchmark as far as Im concerned  In fact Five Guys has better tasting burger for cheap than DMK

Author: Becky K.
Content: this rustic little joint is jus the kind of burger place i was lookin forlets start with the food firstits all grassfed beef which i cant REALLY taste the difference but hell its good i had the 1 burger they go by numbers not names which had an interesting BBQ sauce and juicy thick slices of baconthe bad too many onions and i love onionsi tried the 8 which was a regular cheeseburger pretty much and it was pretty good toosea salt and black pepper fries with house ketchupohemgee love love LOVE the house ketchup kudos DMKmac and cheese 2ohemgee x 2 i love love LOVE that they have gruyere cheese not a lot of places have it and its my most recent discovery of cheesesyuminside DMKlike i said before rustic and trendycould go casual or dressy but i figured if youre going for burgers and beers dress down and get dirtyfull bar which is ALWAYS nice with a cutie little bartender that was distracting me from observing the rest of the place X

Author: Pavan G.
Content: I had the Date burger which was a special of the day It was hands down one of the best burgers Ive ever had Ever It was not too big and the sweet potato fries were  a great compliment to my meal I liked that the fries were crunchy I order sweet potato fries quite often at different establishments and they are almost always soft and soggy but not here I will definitely be back here if I ever get another opportunity The beer selection is great too Love me some craft brews

Author: Steven M.
Content: Very good quality as well as interesting ingredients in the burgers I always have a great meal at this burger joint  Parmesan truffle fries are a must im glad it is dark in there because Id bet that I look real piggish scarfing them down

Author: Jaclyn C.
Content: If I were giving this place a review solely based on food it would be 45 however when I yelp I review everything Went last Saturday night with the husband and knew there would be a long wait we were told 15 hours Which was fine cause we were planning to have a few rounds at the bar beforehand After squeezing our way through the masses of other people waitingeating at the bar and getting the bartenders attention we finally ordered our drinks Why on earth would any place staff only two bartenders for the entire restaurantbar area especially this place which boasts a great beercocktail menu The rhubarb drink was amazing but I feel like you could spend 50 before you ever felt you were even drinking alcohol Unless you like mint and liquorice DO NOT get the mint julep it was horrible We got two rounds with a semi decent wait but the third round it took literally like 22 minutes to order Finally this a waitress turned bartender saw us and got us our beers quick Now onto the food Good thing is that everything comes out quick We started with fried pickleokra and 2 macaroni The friend stuff was really good and the okra seemed pickled The noodles in the mac were a little over done and needed some salt but we still ate it Onto the main event we ordered the blue cheesechipotle ketchup and the friend eggbacon burgers Both were good but I think the fried egg was more unique if it didnt have as many green chiles it would have been perfect The parmesan and truffle fried are to die for just like MKs Yes this is a ton of food for 2 people and we ate everything even saved room for an ice cream sandwich which is amazing Id definitely come back to try the still coming soon burgers I would have given a better review had they been better staffed If you are gonna make people wait to be seated and they are willing to buy drinks in the meantime put the staff needed so we can drink and spend money We could have had more drinks but oh well

Author: Andrew M.
Content: Food 8511 Better than most in Chicago Ive been there twice and ordered the barbecue burger the first time and the turkey eggplant burger the next Both were good thin patties Plenty of toppings as well as perfectly matched buns I would have to say the highlight is the mac and cheese and the sweet potato fries I finished both of these off in a hurrybarely giving my girlfriend the chance to score a bite I also tried the salt and pepper fries At first I thought they were hella spicy but as my girlfriend pointed out it wasnt the fries that were spicy it was the ketchup In order to quell what I thought were spicy fries I was smothering them in what I thought was standard ketchup Wow Im an idiot But anyways all in all the food was solid So solid that there was no room for dessert Not that I would have eaten them anyway For the record vanilla bean ice cream is NOT the same as regular vanilla It is much much worse   Drinks and Bartenders 911 The best thing about the drinks are the price Great beer selection and good cheap wine options Perfect for a nice weekday meal or even a good place to go on weekends with bigger groups Service 811 Everyone was very nice but that doesnt take away from the fact that they could have been more attentive I was having a spicy ketchup issue and water was being consumed at a faster than normal pace They were what seemed exceptionally slow at refilling it I dont even think  there was water on the table in first place But again they were very nice so you still get 811 because Im nice and you cant be mean to nice people And yup My scale goes all the way to 11 Thats one point betterone point more comprehensive than scales that go to 10 And Yelp Really A scale that goes to 5 Cmon

Author: Dan P.
Content: Definitely a place will be going back to The place was packed but turnover seemed to be quick and we didnt have to wait very long to get a table  in fact the bartender wasnt even done pouring my drink when the hostess came up to usher us to our table  The service is not exactly speedy but then again I have no issues with taking my time to enjoy dinner in good company  If your idea of service includes having Speedy Gonzales as your server come prepared with an extra dose of patience Or better yet get one of the excellent cocktails and relaxAs far as the food goes I thought the sides were excellent Mac  Cheese sweet potato fries and the burgers were satisfying  The burgers are normal sized so if you like gargantuan burgers go for the double meat and dont be left wondering where the meat went I guess I can understand how some reviewers were dissappointed by the burgers  by american standards they do lack size and blood however I like the feeling of being able to breathe without unbuttoning my pants after having a meal so it was perfect for meFinally I thought the drinks were pretty good  It would be nice if they went for the same concept fancy cocktails extensive beer list in a more loungy place with only a small selection of tapasstyled dishes

Author: Van D.
Content: Nothing stands out with this place  Different varieties of burgers but nothing unique about the ingredients  Burger pattie good but not great  Sweet potato fries were excellent though  Would rather go to the Counter which is just a few blocks down and you can pick your ingredients  This place is not even in the same league as a Kumas

Author: Allison C.
Content: Met 3 girlfriends at DMK on a Tuesday night and the place was jumping If we would have gotten there 10 minutes later we wouldnt have gotten seats This a burger joint upscale but still a burger joint dont expect a big wine list Expect a good selection of beer AND homemade sodas My preggo friend said her blood orange soda was yummy My 3 girlfriends had bacon cheeseburgers and I had a turkey  swiss burger and we could not stop raving about how good they were I am tempted to say it was the best dang turkey burger I have ever had We shared mac and cheese and truffle fries they were both scrumptious The sides were more than big enough to share My only regret was that we did not have enough room for dessert I have heard the ice cream cookie is the best The only reason this place doesnt get 5 stars is because I felt rushed to leave The bar area where we were offers communal seating and the people standing near the bar waiting for seats were eyeing us up Plus I am just not a big fan of communal seatingperiod I cant wait to take my hubby to DMK we will go early and request a table for two

Author: Diane S.
Content: I have eaten here twice now and enjoyed my burger both times However this place is not a greasy indulgent type of experience like Kumas or Five Guys The burgers are cooked a little more than Id personally like  you dont get the optionThe fries are very tasty too and you can split a small for only 3 I have had the sweet potato salt and pepper and the Wisconsin cheddar All were very goodI dont enjoy the seatingeveryone is very close together or at a communal table and its very loud in there Just not ideal in my opinion

Author: Lindsay D.
Content: Loved the beer and drink selection and of course most importantly their burger selection I ordered the vegiie burger no cheese and the flavors were awesome little spicy little crunchy Ill make this one sweet and to the point I want to try everything there AIll be back for more

Author: L R.
Content: Great burgers at a great price the service is aight  If you are lookin for an option to Kumas Corner check this place out

Author: Asha M.
Content: I dream about you often Since we have met over a month ago I cant stop thinking about your mouth watering flavor We need to get together soon

Author: Bridgette K.
Content: This will be the new Burger joint since Im scared to eat Kumas Corner after getting food poisoning The fries are by far thee best sweet potato fries I have ever ate The DMK margarita is very fresh and strong The decor is very trendy and modern But the seating is very close to each other and not a lot of room to move around I will be back for more

Author: Celtic B.
Content: I went back to DMK for another burger and I gotta say I was impressed  I had the Sonoran with a side of sweet potato fries and a Daisy Cutter  The burger was hot and juicy with a great proportion of burger to bun to toppings  The sweet potato fries were incredible Ive never had better and doubt you could do much to improve on them  And of course the beer list is most impressive  I cant wait to go back and try some more of the burgers

Author: Jesselyn E.
Content: Burgers were AMAZING great selection of local beers too

Author: Mike D.
Content: This is a review for Takeout  I had the Barbecue Burger and the ParmesanTruffle Cream friesBurger was cooked to order which is nice as most places give you medium as though it were well done even when I got home the burger was still warm and nicely cooked  The onions were fantastic well cooked but not mushy  The barbecue wasnt spectacular but it was tasty nonethelessThe fries were okay Im not overly excited about them  They were really heavy but the spices were good  I think I just wasnt a fan of the Parmesan or the truffle cream  Im definitely going to have to try this place again but I may not go back too soon

Author: Kim T.
Content: I admit it I have a slight obsession with grassfed beef burgers Did you say house ketchup and maccheese too Yes please And the dessert is tasty too What more could a girl want

Author: T J.
Content: This is probably the best burger Ive ever had I cant remember the name of it since its been about 2mos but it had a spicy ketchup and onion strings on it that had me smacking my lips Me and the BF also arent huge red meat eaters and rarely choose a burger joint to dine in fact we were trying to get a seat at the adjoining seafood place but the wait was atrocious so we picked DMK He had some type of burger with portabello mushroom added truffle and sweet potato fries a beer and a shake and we were in heaven Were still talking about the place Also had a very nice patient and attentive server who even put my leftover shake in a togo cup since my eyes were bigger than my stomach that nightWere planning to go back to the place every few months  Only complaint is parking in that area which of course they cant control

Author: Melissa S.
Content: Two things you should know about the food  Its simple really just burgers  But their burgers are very good and they have some unique delicious choices  I had a lamb burger with feta tsaziki etc yummm As far as drinks  they have lots of good beer choices  But my husband is one of those huge Miller Lite fans so its important to know if youre like him that they dont have itOverall  simple and delicious

Author: Eazmg C.
Content: Pretty legit burgers  Thinsteak burger style get the double if you are craving something thick  The truffle fries are outstanding and i always enjoy the variety of high quality canned beer 3 a pop from fat tire to Modus Hoperandi  Needless to say the draft selection is good

Author: Kathy K.
Content: Went here for lunch with a friend I got the patty melt and it was fantastic I highly recommend it My friend got a standard cheeseburger and it was tasty but a little small for the price They use high quality ingredients and the menu is diverse This isnt your traditional burger place but it is very tasty

Author: Joe L.
Content: Not a huge burger fan but I have to say the number 2 on the menu was one of the best burgers Ive ever had Good service too

Author: Layne S.
Content: Look at you you have a baby In a barWent early as this place is always packed  It was LOUD  I could scream across the table to my gf WHAT joking around and no one seemed to notice  We got seated at a small table next to a couple who seemingly couldnt get a babysitter  there was a baby attached to mom and a roaming tiny one next to us  No real issues there other than bad parenting observations  We both got the BBQ burger and both realized the toppings were too much  A plain cheeseburger would have been a better choice  The mac  cheese was delishus  The deviled eggs were ok  Ive been craving deviled eggs all summer and they hit that spot for sure so that was a relief  Service was pretty good yet the noise was bad  I never like noisy places to eat  Kumas plays metal and its an enjoyable experience other than waiting an hour to get in the door  meaning a place doesnt have to be loud to be good  It seemed like much of the clientele were trying really hard to be hip and all I wanted was  good burger  Will not be returning

Author: Nirali S.
Content: I went here for lunch on a Thursday and it was nice and quiet  I ordered the 1 aged cheddar bacon onions BBQ sauce and it was really tasty  My friend had got the 13 portobello arugula fontina cheese and he was a big fan of it  We also split the sweet potato fries and the Wisconsin cheddar fries both were pretty good  He ordered the blood orange soda which was good but just needed a tad bit of sugar  For dessert we had a mix of the shake which was chocolate and peanut butter it was super thick and awesome definitely hit the sweet tooth spot  I think this place lives up to the hype easily

Author: Faye S.
Content: Bison burger and fries were delish Server was not very attentive but service was decent The atmosphere was nice They have full bar with lots of mixed drink and beer on the menu The tables seem a lil too close but it is a burger place after all I would definitely go back to try other burgers soon

Author: Alexa H.
Content: Sweet potato fries  Go eat them  Best ever  Wait can get long it is extremely loud but the food is yummy and it comes out in an instant  Not my absolute favorite burger but the fries oh the fries  Good price  I might go back try a fancy soda and just eat french fries  But if youre in need of a burger the toppings are really well thought out

Author: Brynn M.
Content: The burger here was pretty good and the fries were delicious but it was REALLY crowded and loud Great place to go on occasion to meet up with friends but I thought it wasnt worth all the hype

Author: Jaye L.
Content: What can I say that hasnt been said already Yes it does get very busy and noisy Seating is limited at times and you generally are almost rubbing elbows with your neighbors but there is a reason for that  The burgers are worldclass Dont come here for a greasy blandburger with cheese Granted they have it but go elsewhere for that This is the place to let your guard down and try things you wouldnt normally think of Or better put let the chefs get creative and just put whatever is on your plate in your mouthit will be delicious From Lamb Burger to the Holy Guacaoly Burger it is all good  Even the ketchup is spicy and unique Beer selection is long and diverse If you live in the neighborhood pick up the DMK card so you can build points for free tshirts and stuff Just a groovy little place right off the El in Lakeview

Author: Jen D.
Content: I just LOVED the veggie burger  It was one of the best that I have ever hadand huge  I was able to bring that and my cheddar fries home for a second meal  But the absolute best part was the Shamrock Shake with mint ice cream and Lucky Charms  Really enjoyed my first time and cant wait to go back

Author: Tony G.
Content: Great burgers   The fries are ridiculous   Wisconsin cheddar truffle and sweet potatomore please

Author: Shonnie M.
Content: Amazing  I had the lamb burger and husband had the bison burger both were very good but he will be ordering the lamb burger when we go back  Its a little noisy but you are there for a burger not a romantic dinner  Go Oh and I had a GREAT milk stout beer  Sounded strange but so glad I tried it

Author: Andrew K.
Content: Sweet potatoes fries were amazing and I consider myself an expert in pizza burgers and of course fries  I liked the decor but I thought there wasnt that much space between tables  Burgers were good but when the fries are the best thing in the menu there are problems  Good once but wont be heading back anytime soon

Author: Frances A.
Content: Order the bison burger Bartender drew had great beer recommendations Truffle fries may be the best in the city  Add a shot to whichever wonderful shake you order for dessert

Author: Sorrell G.
Content: Well the food is good Depending on where you are in the city you might not want to drive over Staff are polite Be prepared to wait a long time on the weekends No parking Place is very loud you might want to get it to go if you dont drink alcohol

Author: Paul T.
Content: You gotta love a place that serves a great grassfed burger and super fries Really nice beer selection Very friendly and knowledgable staff I keep wanting to try a lot of their burgers but I cant resist the burger with ChiliRubbed Onion Strings Amish Blue Cheese and Spicy Chipotle Ketchup Great milk shakes

Author: Patrick C.
Content: Good burger Loved the grassfed meat aspect since Im fairly healthconscious Fries are separate which I kind of like since I dont feel like I have to eat everything on my plate Portions are slightly smaller than other places Ive been to but still worth a visit

Author: Kanae O.
Content: This place was a little underwhelming I went there on Saturday night at 7pmish and wait was 3035 min The line got even longer around the time when we were seated The ambiance is nice with dim light and you dont feel that its overcrowded even though a lot of people are waiting near the door However as some people mentioned in the review the music was loud and it was hard to enjoy the conversation About the burgers my boyfriend ordered 2 ChiliRubbed Onion Strings Amish Blue Spicy Chiptole Ketchup and I ordered 11 Grassfed Lamb Sheeps Milk Feta Olive Tapenade Greek Salad Tzatziki The ingredients sounded very good for all the burger options but what disappointed me when I actually tried was that the taste of nonmeat portion overwhelmed the meat flavor Both burgers had the same problem Particularly I didnt enjoy the sourness that greek salad and tzatziki had in my lamb burger  We also had Wisconsin Cheddar  Scallion fries as a side Again the name sounded intriguing but it didnt meet the expectation They were just soggy fries with melted cheese and scallion on top Maybe we should have ordered sweet potato fries instead of normal potato friesThey have a wide selection of beer if you are a beer drinker We didnt get any as we wanted to try one of their shakes Peanut butter shakes turned out to be pretty good The portion was good for two people to share

Author: Jonah B.
Content: The best burger in town when you leave youll feel full and satisfied but not the classic too full feeling you get after a normal burger At DMK the friendly servers and diverse menu will definitely leave your taste buds stomach and your wallet satisfied

Author: Luis O.
Content: While their burgers are good a good restaurant needs more than just good food We were there twice recently on  busy weekends and they were totally overwhelmed and unable to manage the flow of people The host was a mess  she was just way over her headvery incompetent and unable to give people a reasonable answer as to how long the wait was going to be Both times after waiting for more than an hour we were 3 and hearing other people complain we ended up going to another great burger place nearby  there are quite a few in our neighborhood Bad uncaring customer service slow table service   not coming back

Author: Stephanie D.
Content: I was visiting from out of town and seeking a good mid western burger place something that I could not find in the west coast Insert my visit to DMK the service was great they even gave us a free order of deviled eggs I ordered the 4 which was amazing it had bacon and green chile nom and the sweet potato fries were to die for Definitely will go back there whenever I get a chance

Author: Mark S.
Content: Good stuff  Burger 1 was great  SaltPepper fries were fantastic  Nice beer selection  Cupcakes were very good as well  Nice to see a place focus on quality and not quantity

Author: Ben W.
Content: Pros  Great location low dinner prices gourmet flavors for 8 a burger fantastic beer selection with some great inhouse commentary on the menu and the service has never let me down friendly and knowledgable serviceCons  Overpriced but tasty desserts45 stars deservedly  Its absolutely a biweekly visit for us

Author: Gina R.
Content: This place is by far one of the best iv ever had Its newer so I feel people dont know about it  GO they have a bakery who makes theyr buns specially And they r always fresh and it melts in ut mouth Yum 1 is SO good And the fries but if u get the Wisconsin cheddar ask for the cheese on side its allot this coming from a girl whos fridge is 90 cheese Enjoy I order carry out all the time thats HOW good it is And they have shakes vanilla chocolate tastes weird  but could of just been me 5 stars Not sure about he whole theology on 4 stars anywho enjoy

Author: Jennifer A.
Content: I have been to DMK burger bar twice and I highly enjoyed it both times The burgers are delicious thick and juicy with a lot of flavor I have ordered a regular burger as well as the bbq burger that comes with bacon and bbq sauce The fries are delicious we tried the parmesan truffle fries as well as the cheese fries I am not a huge fan of cheese fries but my boyfriend loved them The parmesan truffle fries were amazing The beer menu is also very interesting I tried a peach beer that I really liked and there were a lot of unique craft beers The service is excellent The only reason for not giving it 5 stars is that it is very loud in the restaurant It is difficult to have a conversation

Author: Sherri M.
Content: The food here is amazing I particularly like the number 1 and 5 burgers which are truly delicious Alyssa my hostess on friday was particularly helpful and charming In fact the service overall is commendable I would recommend it to anyone who enjoys a good burger and beer

Author: Alex T.
Content: Overall a good burger place  However not the best The burger is decent doesnt quite live up to hype  The mac and cheese is phenomenal may be the best I have ever had  The beer selection is also great  The service can be hit or miss I have had great servers and then had horrible  I live right next to this pace so I go more for convenience than the food  Dont get me wrong there is nothing wrong with the food just doesnt live up to the hype

Author: David E.
Content: Not many places wow me with simple food But DMK did as I randomly stumbled by it a few weeks ago The burgers are AMAZING Save the 2 hour wait at Kumas and try this place for a burger just as tasty Dont get me wrong Kumas lives up to the hype but if you want a better atmosphere and service then go to DMK you wont be disappointed

Author: Kate M.
Content: Our 12 person group arrived right after work on a Thursday and we got the big center wood table  We started off right by reviewing the awesome beer list and we each selected something new and fun  The beer list along with the wine and cocktail lists are inventive and fun but not overwhelming or too muddled  All of the selections were great and the server offered great recommendations based on what we likeddescribedNext came the items we shared  onion rings super thin and crispy parmtruffle fries need I say more but they do these justice sweet potato fries crispy perfection fried pickles and okra surprisingly delish my first time and THE DEVILED EGGS  The menu says need I say more regarding these little gems and that is exactly right  a great treat the best consistency and oh so tasty And the sauces that came with each of the above items were so great thoughtful and the perfect complement to each of the items  Well doneThen the burgers  For 8 the selection is awesome  The variety of toppings sauces and choices  I was left trying to decide between some amazing options but went with the 3 WOWIt was just enough of the other ingredients cheese sauerkraut and pastrami where they were perfectly tasty but did not overwhelm the actual burger  amazing considering this is where a lot of other burger places fail  The balance was perfect and the tangy salty and juicy burger and toppings were just perfection  Everyone at the table got different burgers and everyones reactions were the same  just awesomeAt the end the service became a little sporadic as the place started to get busier  which is to be expected on a Thursday night  But overall the ambiance was great lowkey and the music was a great mix  And considering that all of us have still been talking about our burgers and what we want to have nextI have a feeling we will be returning some time very sooncannot wait

Author: Landis F.
