Content: Everything was good  burgers I had the 4 truffle fries Mac 2  until I found hair in my Ice Cream Sandwich Gross

Author: Amanda D.
Content: I have to upgrade DMK to 4 stars simply because I have been there so much and I am never disappointed  My favorite is the 10 turkey burger with sweet potato fries  And a good beerwhich they have a pretty decent selection of

Author: Ron S.
Content: DMK has quality burgers and an awesome beer selection I suggest trying the truffle cream fries because theyre simply delicious I have heard great things about their mac  cheese too so dont be shy This place isnt cheap and the burgers they have arent the best but it is still definitely worth checking out

Author: Chang L.
Content: Ordered a crispy Portobello burger which was delicious though overpriced in my opinion The truffle fries were also pretty good Dim place with good ambience nice place to eat with friends later at night

Author: Sarah N.
Content: I thought this place was good It was crazy busy when I went here on a week night we ended up waiting an hour because we had a group of 8 Our waitress was nice enough to bring us free tater tots and sweet potatoes fries so that was nice  I wish you could substitute the veggie pattie on any of the burgers Im generally not a fan of portabella burgers  I thought the veggie burger was fine but slightly over priced The service was good and I know my meat eating friends enjoyed their meals

Author: Jake D.
Content: Barreled in and split a 1 and 2 BOTH just delicious Great beer hip ambiance Bomb burgers Cant beat it

Author: Will B.
Content: 8 beer  fries Best burger bar in Chicago

Author: Nancy Z.
Content: I really enjoy this place I have had the 1 which is pretty much a regular burger I have enjoyed the lamb burger and the big salad is amazing  I also think the bar has a great selection at fair pricing  The food is very good and the servers are impressive as they are always very nice  The place is always clean as well and I have never had to wait to be seated

Author: marc f.
Content: dmk burgers are thin patties  all cooked to the same temperature medium  medium rare  if you like your burgers thick juicy and BIG TIME rare like me this is not the place to get a burgerif i judge dmk by thin patty standards id have to say meh  sure its better than fast food chains it better be but maybe not as good as burger baron which is surprisingly good for a diner kind of place      i recommend lock down bar  grill  kumas too if youre cool with the wait and the scene

Author: Chris P.
Content: Good burgers good fries good onion straws good beer good servicewhat more can one want

Author: Sergio R.
Content: My wife and I were CRAVING a burger this past weekend and decided to try DMK first because of the name famed chef and this new buzz on burger bars  I have to say after eating Kumas and Lockdowns burgers these were far less superior in taste you couldnt even compare  Burgers were much thinner bit too salty and they can only cook to 1 temperature   I tried the double to get the REAL burger taste but didnt work  My wife got the single and felt cheated  For the price an product I truly prefer 5 Guys  On a positive notes I did love the onion strings and sweet potato fries plus great beer choices and I do appreciate the grass fed beef

Author: Shawn J.
Content: Just an average burger Nothing too fancy Super friendly staff decent beer and cocktail menu The burgers are grass fed which I think is their gimmick however I thought the beef was just okay and had no flavor I want to love it great concept and decent menu but for the same price I would probably go somewhere different Willing to give it another shot though

Author: Ane P.
Content: Loved the burgers The service was kind of slow but overall it was a good experience The fries were fantastic as well Will go back

Author: Dave B.
Content: Burgers fries food and service is all fantastic Their beer selection is also very good Id have given 6 stars if they brought back Dragons MilkFor the naysayers out there that truly want to pick their own ingredients nearly any bar in Chicago should suffice and be more than willing to fulfill your request

Author: Jason T.
Content: Add another entry on the always growing list of amazing Burger joints in Chicagoland  This place should be commended for their unique and experimental menu a lot of good twists thrown in to make these burgers stand out   The wide variety of French fry stylings were also impressive my girlfriend and I were sad we couldnt try more  The beer selection was also fantastic especially the drafts  The business should also be commended for trying to use local ingredients and for donating all proceeds from their milkshakes which was so rich and delicious by the way to a rotating charity   Oh did I mention the burgers are almost all 8  Only reason I didnt 5 star this place is because of the long wait to be seated service after seating is quick and efficient though but who can blame all these people for wanting to eat here

Author: Alejandra G.
Content: Great Burgers and Fries The reason I love this place is because the burger size is just perfect not too big and not too small They are cooked perfectly I love the BIG DMK burger we usually split it because it can be a bit on the big side for just one person The Parmesan fires with truffle cream are to die for just like their 1 Mac N Cheese We had tried one of their special shakes and the best so far has been the Roasted Marshmallow Flavor One of my favorite burger places so far in chicago

Author: Steph L.
Content: Just as good as I was expecting  perhaps even better We went on a Thursday night around 7 and only waited 5 minutes I was expecting more of a wait so I was pleasantly surprised we were seated quickly The hardest part is choosing which burger to get The blue cheese fries we got on the side were delicious  a little heavy on the sauce for my liking but a halforder was more than enough for me and my date I will definitely be back to sample more of the menu

Author: Johnny G.
Content: Not the best burger place but one of the best You cant effectively rate any other burger restaurant without trying this The best fries Ive ever had and well proportioned burgers

Author: Willie B.
Content: Easily the most overrated overhyped burger place in Chicago A burger is about the patty and the bun and then the toppings DMK has got the toppings down Simply doesnt sniff Kumas not even in the same league Its nice to see people love DMKs vegan burgers but thats not a burger Thats just a mushroom on bread I do love DMKs fries Fun place with creative food but not a burger that you will remember

Author: Scott G.
Content: DMK is located right around the corner from my place and Ive been there a few times Each time I go I am never disappointed with the food or service The first time I went my friends and I received free shots of Jameson to welcome us to Chicago My favorite burgers are the Patty Melt and Bison Burger I recommend washing it down with a Gumball IPA and youre set

Author: Kevin B.
Content: Burgers were awesome everyone seemed to be very happy with their food the servers were great and they even brought out an extra beer for the table to share along with shot glasses for us to pour the beer into in order to divvy it up among 6 of us due to the fact that they were about 1 minute late with our mac and cheese dish which wasnt a big deal at all but clearly a nice gesture  I had the southwest burger or something and it was HOT but very good  Beer menu is good and the burgers are great

Author: Ginger L.
Content: OMG   AMAZING   Every time I come I get something different and Every time is the best time

Author: Cary M.
Content: I was really looking forward to eating at DMKs  We were greeted by a very friendly staff and sat right away  I was simply disappointed with the food and not really comfortable with the room  The burgers are quite small and just okay  We had 1 and 4 4 would have been so much better with a couple of strips of bacon and not just one lonely piece  The fries were good but again small pieces  The tables and chairs were also really small  Unfortunately the bill didnt end up being very small

Author: Robert E.
Content: Very good selection of high end burgers using a variety of different meats from beef to turkey to lamb and veggie too  Great beer selection  Service is okay and the space isnt that great but the burger and the beer are definitely going to be a weekly staple

Author: man i luv pizza p.
Content: Went here during lunch and surprisingly it was very busy  The space is kind of low key modern fairly comfortable except for this strange open space near the door  I ordered the classic burger and sweet potato fries  Burger was very good although the presentation of the food was burger and plate it did not look appetizing  The burger bun is a home made powdery one which wasnt too badOverall would i go back maybe if i was in the area but it was nothing special  BTW I love MK so it was slightly disappointing  However for two burgers and friens our bill was 22 which is unheard of  I would stick to The Counter for a better experience and tastier burger

Author: Mark H.
Content: I was there on a Wednesday night with some friends and I have to say Whats all the hype aboutThis is purely a burger joint so I am assuming the burgers are going to be amazing Nope  First my biggest beef with the place is the cooking  When I go to a nice steak house I order my steaks medium rare  My wife orders hers medium  I even have a friend who orders his filet well done why  Because thats how he likes it  Its nice to have a choice on how you want your meat cooked  Not here you get it how it comes barely pink  Now if thats how you like it then perfect but if you like it any other way your out of luckSecond its suppose to be an upscale burger joint wheres the upscale  There was nothing at all special about my burger i had the 1  It came with BBQ sauce cheddar cheese and saute onions onions were done perfectly though  So thats what was on my burger okay lets class it up a little bit with the bun Nope  Just a plain bun no bretzel no kaiser roll no nada just what appeared to be an unassuming bun  What gets me was they had 8 or 9 burgers to choose from okay thats a good selection but 2 of them were coming soon  Why are they even on the menu  Put something in there that someone can choose until the 2 new ones arrive  Im not trying to put anyone down but how hard is it to come up with 2 burger concoctions for only 3 weeks  My guess not hardOne touch I did like and that I got on  my burger was the choice of adding a fried egg which they clearly got from Kumas Corner best burger in the cityTwo things they did have right at this place was the fries and beer selection  I ordered the blue cheese and bacon fries as well as the Parmesan truffle fries  Both were excellent 2 days later I was still tasting the truffle aoili and it tasted great  The second thing that this place has done right was the beer selection  Some of the other reviews I have read said it wasnt that great  In my eyes it was pretty good  Could it have been better  Well yes everything can be better like this places burgers but the selection was goodOne last thing this is an upscale burger joint when you walk inside you can tell  The decor was nice the lighting was good and the wait staff was pleasantAll in all it wasnt bad but it didnt blow my mind either  Would I go again  No thats why I am off to Kumas Corner for the best burger in the city right now

Author: Nancy M.
Content: i liked this place a lot cool atmosphere friendly service great food awesome local beer selection the burgers are quite tasty  although i do think that its a little strange that they dont ask how youd like them cooked id heard they came well done but mine came out medium to medium rarei got a number four and it was delicious but there were a lot of greatlooking burgers on the menu ill definitely be back to try the nonbeef burgers  the lamb and veggie burgers are next on my listour group of five also shared the mac and cheese which i thought was kind of overrated and underseasoned at first but it had really grown on me by the end of the meal we also got two large orders of fries one order of the cheddar cheese fries and one order of the sweet potato fries both were delicious the cheese fries do seem to have more of a cheese sauce than melted shredded cheese but it was all goodthe only downside was that the place is really loud but everything else is really great keep up the good work dmk

Author: Dan M.
Content: The good  the burgers were awesome They had a large variety of burgers with some interesting toppings Im excited to go back and try more of them The onion strings were really good too And I kind of liked the environmentThe bad  The prices but I dont think I should hold them to the same standards of other places I get burgers from I mean its their specialty and they do a damn good job at it

Author: Jenna K.
Content: I love gourmettype burgers so actually I thought the prices were really reasonable  8 for any type burger way better than the prices for the Rockit famous 1921 burgers or even Kumas 1012 burgers  The burgers were good sized but not nauseatingly huge  I have that problem with Kumas though I do love their burgers I can never finish one without feeling like I never want to eat again  Heres what we got  I ordered the No 4 Roasted Hatch Green Chile Fried Farm Egg Sonoma Jack Cheese Smoked Bacon and my boyfriend ordered the No 10 GrassFed Lamb  Sheeps Milk Feta Olive Tapenade Tomato  Onion Salad Tzatziki and we split them so that we each ate half of each  I can say that both were delicious  I was expecting mine to be slightly spicier but I still loved what I ate  And the Lamb burger was awesomeOur friends ordered the No 1 Aged Cheddar Smoked Bacon Charred Balsamic Red Onions Rufus Teagues BBQ Sauce and the No 3 NY Pastrami Grand Cru Gruyere Cheese Sauerkraut Leroys Remoulade and they both loved and I mean LOVED theirs We all dug the fact that the beef is grassfed  And we all loved our fries which are a la carte  We got one order of the french fries with truffle cream and one order of sweet potato fries with tobasco cream to split between the four of usAll in all delicious  We cant wait to go backOh and other random logistics  They dont normally take reservations  We went there around 8pm on Valentines day however and they were doing reservations for just that day  We didnt have any reservations and were still able to get in after about 15 min wait  Also many of their tables are communal style seating  Im not the biggest fan of this however it seems to be a growing trend hello Publican Purple Pig Urban Belly etc  I usually find it to be awkward But the tables were spacious enough that it didnt bother me as much hereAnyway I would say that this is one of my favorite new places

Author: Larisa B.
Content: We came here after the Shamrock Shuffle this year trying to stay away from the huge March Madness crowds I had heard when they first opened the food and staff werent the best but had heard better since We both started with a bloody mary each  I like to think of myself as a connoisseur of them and these were good but not at the top of my list especially for 8 on a Sunday I got the 5 which comes w Prosciutto Fontina Pesto Red Pepper Sea Salt  Vinegar Chips which are actually on top of the burger and we shared the Amish Blue and bacon fries I dont have a bad thing to say about either The burger was cooked exactly how I wanted it and all of the fixings were great I want to try all of their french fry options If you like burgers this place is definitely one to try

Author: jessica m.
Content: ive wanted to try dmk burger bar since i first heard that it was in the works but everything ive read on here has mentioned that its not a good place for kids which makes it difficult for me to get out and enjoy  i decided to bite the bullet and call to see if they had high chairs available which is my strategy for deciding whether its a place that i can bring my kid to and also to kind of give the restaurant a heads up that a child will be entering their establishment  i was pleasantly surprised when i was told they indeed had high chairs and yes were very kid friendly  i packed up the babe hopped in the car and headed overi had burger 4  a grassfed beef patty with roasted green chiles smoked bacon sonoma jack cheese and a fried egg to top it all off  it was a like a little slice of heaven in my mouth the burger is a perfect size  not too massive a la kumas et al where you feel like crap after eating it and not too small where youre still hungry afterwards  it really was the perfect size  my little guy had their basic macaroni and cheese they had 4 different offerings which was so good that im glad he has a tiny stomach so that i can eat the leftovers for dinner tonight  the fried okra and pickles were also delicious  i washed everything down with their housemade blood orange sodawell definitely be back  i dont think id bring the little one during dinner hours but it was a great spot for lunch  im looking forward to working my way through the extensive beer and cocktail list and of course the rest of the burgers

Author: Angela Z.
Content: Im a burger lover and I have to say that thing that really sets the burgers apart at DMK from other places is the flavor quality of the meat  There really is something to that grassfed aspect that adds just a nice rich juicy flavor to the ground beef that I love  Its nice to eat a burger and to actually taste it and have it complimented and not overpowered by just a mess of toppings and a bunI got the basic burger here and I added an egg YUM  The bun is nice not too thick or thin  But I will say it falls apart a little too fast to support the ingredients  The fries here are good but I wouldnt fall all over myself for them  However the sauces they come with are quite tasty and different  Love the smokey ketchup too  Ive had no problems with service here either  The price for the burger is decent although I wish it included the fries as well  Overall a good place with a good product

Author: Dave C.
Content: It was thoroughly decent Nothing bad at all but not worth the hype Lets go bullet point style No wait for 2 on a Wednesday night at 7 but within 15 minutes there were tons of people waiting to sit down Service was fine no complaints there Drink menu was comprehensive Sweet potato fries were ridiculous If I go back Im ordering nothing but beer and sweet potato fries The Greek salad was good The mac and cheese was better but not outstanding The burgers were a disappointment For a place that calls itself a Burger Bar they really should be able to do better than this The toppings were tasty but overall they were complete mehLong story short not a bad place but I wont go back

Author: E D.
Content: Ive tried this place 3 times and the burgers just arent very good They are trying to be a gourmet burger place but its no better than average bar food Kirkwoods next door makes a better burger The Counter on Diversey or 5 Guys are way better

Author: Chris H.
Content: Happening place great staff amazing food  4 is my favorite with the turkey burger when there for brunch shakes will move you and sweet potato  parm truffle fries are a must

Author: Katherine M.
Content: Fantastic food The food came out quicker than it took to wait for a table House wine was pretty good too Very veggie friendly

Author: Matthew N.
Content: Ive only had one meal here so far I took my girlfriend on a date before she left for a 3 and a half week tripTo put it plain and simple the waitress was great and I think I had the 3 it has sauerkraut on it and I can not wait to have my way with that burger again SO GOOD

Author: Allison T.
Content: First off let me start off by saying Im a vegetarian so when my friends suggested we go to DMK Burger Bar for dinner one night I thought maybe they were starting not to like me very much anymore  But it turned out they had checked out the menu and there were lots of veggiefriendly options including a couple veggie sandwiches a whole section called cheese with things and several salads  So I was more than happy as were they given the creative list of what I would call meat with things that they had to choose from  All of the burgers were from grassfed beef and everything started at 8 unless you went with some sort of upgrade such as switching to bison making it a double or yes adding a fried egg  We started off by choosing from their extensive list of craft beers and found we had a lot of great options  Both of my friends ordered the patty melt and I had the veggie burger  We were also VERY excited to try all of their fries and ended up ordering way more than we needed  My veggie burger was great not a boring frozen patty like some places offer as their veggie option but just as creatively done as all the burgers on the menu so I didnt feel slighted in any way  My friends were happy with their choices and the fries were excellent  We left happy and full  The one complaint I really had was that it was superloud and really hard to hear a thing that anyone said but it was a packed Friday night so not a big deal I was excited to go back with my boyfriend and we did last night  This time I again ordered the veggie burger since it was so awesome the last time  I went to order the sweet potato fries because they were my favorite of all the fries we tried  Thats when the waitress asked me if I was a vegetarian or just trying to be healthy by ordering the veggie burger because the fries were fried in BEEF FAT  Ummm seriously  Even McDonalds gave that up in like the 70s but okay thats their perogative  I was quite bummed and had to order the onion straws which sort of sucked at least compared to their fries  Their onion straws ARE cooked in vegetable oil so what gives  Then I remembered how I ate the damn fries last time and there was no warning about the beef fat  Given how many vegetarians are in this town it wouldnt be hard to put a little description underneath the fries like hey sorry to disappoint you tremendously especially if youve eaten these fries before and loved them but they are fried in beef fat or something to that effect  Its not life and death but Im a vegetarian for many reasons and I wouldnt have eaten them if I would have known  Lesson learned I guess  Our waitress actually ended up giving us a free dessert just because she felt bad about it even though I wasnt exactly stomping my feet throwing a fit  So anyway vegetarians beware the next time I go there theyll probably say surprise the veggie burger is fried in beef fat tooThat issue aside the place is pretty cool and theres definitely something for everyone  The beer list is great they have a really creative menu and the staff is friendly and attentive

Author: Stephen P.
Content: Been there several times and everything I have had has been amazing  This past weekend I had  what i consider  the best thing i have ever eaten  It was a Breakfast burger  heaven on a bun  It was a turkey patty with Hash browns a fried egg bacon and a RIDICULOUS maple syrup aioli  This place is ridiculously insanely delicious

Author: Colleen K.
Content: DMK just gets better and better with time Perfect location right off the Wellington L stop  Super friendly staff that does their best even when its packed to get you fed and on your way I love their Turkey burgers as a 8 and their parmesean truffle fries are to die for I definetly cant eat here all the time or I would weigh 200 pounds but its a great place for a fun casual group dinner  Sometimes it can be a little overwhelming to get a drink and wait for a table but the bartenders are pretty good at noticing you and getting you served quickly Will definitely being going back

Author: Bobuzzi C.
Content: Are you a human Do you like food Do you love burgers and fries Then visit this place DMK serves up some of the best burgers and fries Their menu doesnt offer a ton of selection but what it does offer it makes very very well We had the classic bacon cheeseburger And their variety of fry choices and accompanying dips DO NOT disappoint Go there and enjoy Just leave yourself some time Its always busy and no reservations are taken

Author: Lauren C.
Content: I waited to write a review on this but it has come time I went once and loved it but it was my birthday so I thought maybe it was just a great mood Went another time and it was also fantastic but I was starving Went a third time and I began to dream about the burgers So I had to go again because of my dreams and they all came true Bison burger  awesome Blueberry sauce  who would have thoughtTurkey burger  awesomeThe big DMK  get it AwesomeThe one with green chilies and a fried egg  awesomeThe FRIES  AMAZINGJust go there Who cares if they are smug Their burgers are 8 so get over it and eat them

Author: Thomas K.
Content: One star since it was edible  Really below expectations   Horrid burgers small servings and no comparison to even some lower end burgers   Dont do it

Author: Laura C.
Content: Amazing The parmesan truffle fries were the best around  And the DMK Burger tastes like a Big Mac on steroids The wait was only a half hour on a Saturday afternoon and it was well worth the wait Parking can be a bit hard but if you drive around a bit youll find something I cant wait to go back and try other burgers at DMK

Author: Ana F.
Content: Great veggie burger After reading some previous reviews I feel it necessary to state that their fries are cooked in beef fat After the waitress pointed that out I ordered the chilirubbed onion strings which were also tasty The only reason Im giving four stars instead of five is because I was looking forward to the fries with Wisconsin cheddar and scallions and I could not have them

Author: Katy H.
Content: Yes yes yes My roommate stopped in after a show at the Biograph as I had been craving a good burger and really wanted to try DMK and boy I was not disappointed  My second visit was not as great but I didnt order the same thing and that made all the differenceSo far Ive ordered the 1 and the 2 The 1 was okay though Im not a huge cheddar fan The 2 was amazing This is one of my favorite burgers in Chicago hands down  You can really taste the difference in the meat as it is all grass fed beefIve also had the fries Both times they were just okay The truffle cream fries were my favorite but the fries were really just a conduit for the cream The Wisconsin Cheddar fries were very cheesyThey also have a pretty decent beer selection to accompany your meal The service is average Last time I asked repeatedly for water and never got any  I definitely think this place is worth the trip the burgers are great

Author: Erin H.
Content: I cannot wait to go back Atmosphere left something to be desired a little too sterile trendy for a burger joint but the service and food deliveredWe shared parm truffle and sweet potato fries both came with excellent dipping sauces and the server tossed in some free fried okra and dill pickles A smart move as I would go for the pickles and okra over the fried potatoes any day now Might as well have some green in there if youre indulging in fried food rightI ordered 6 Marinated portobello Blue Brie A combo I need to find out where to buy with griddled scalions dijonnaise and of course a beef patty The bun was perfectly toasted and held all the ingredients together nicely Ketchup wasnt necessary Did you hear that NO KETCHUP NECESSARY It was so delicious This from a girl who would put ketchup on cereal if it were socially acceptable I love that stuff Large variety of brews fast bar serviceThe chocolate chip cookie sandwich for dessert was delicious to share ways but didnt have any chocolate chips in it so that was strange

Author: Jim O.
Content: I dropped in with a friend after work  It had a trendy vibe pro or con depending on the mood  They had a fairly extensive beer list and a lot of good food options  I had the 3 pastramigruyere and we split an order of the Wisconsin cheddar fries and the Parmesan with truffle cream fries The burger was kind of thin consider a double if hungry but it was really tasty  I would definitely come back

Author: Patrick K.
Content: I saw this place on the Food Network Channel on  Diners Drives and Dives Also I pass this place everyday on the redline and I have always wanted to try it I had big expectations but it was just alright  There are better burgers in that neighborhoodThese gourmet burgers were very flavorful but were nothing spectacular I ordered a side of sweet potato fries and they were actually really good However they served a dipping hot sauce sauce that did not go well with the with the fries DMK a solid restaurant but I expected more

Author: Max S.
Content: A great twist on burgers and fries Really didnt have to wait long for a table and the bar selection is fantastic as well

Author: Paul S.
Content: Did I like it  Yes  Would I recommend it  Yes  Do I see myself going back anytime soon  Not really  I had decent expectations and they were met but there are a few other burgers in Chicago Id rate higher  FYI  The Lucky Charms in their Shamrock Shakes are such a good idea I cant believe Ive never come across it before

Author: Brian O.
Content: Great burger spot with an extensive beer list  Heard they might be opening a new location in Little Italy and cant wait Turkey burger and Parmesan fries are superb

Author: Ryan M.
Content: I have now been here twice the first time was better for some reason got the 1 both times with bbq sauce grilled onions and cheddar i do have to say tho the burger is super tasty hence the 4 stars but the fries add proibably one and a half stars to the score some of the best cheddar fries i have ever had the cheddar is similar to weiner circle but is on point all the time weiner circle would be better but more than half the time their cheddar is not being heated to acceptable temps and probably will get you sick refer to my weiner  ircle review that is in process

Author: Priya A.
Content: This place is absolutely awesome the burgers are amazing and the sides are amazing its a really great place with fabulous food

Author: Hatidza Z.
Content: Their veggie burger is so good Good consistency great taste I hate it when my burger falls apart so Im glad I had zero issues with my burger here Its sucks that their fries are not vegetarian but at least theyre nice enough to inform of this fact I will definitely be going back just not during the evening on a weekend because you can expect a long wait and I know that takes away from the good food experience for many

Author: Raphael D.
Content: First Ill state that Im a pretty serious foodie I do however appreciate a good to great burger Kumas corner Epic Burger In  Out burger This place however isnt nearly in the same league as those places I appreciate how juicy the burger was but after that its all downhill The fires didnt taste fresh cut to me though the bartender said they were After watching the DDD on this place perhaps I shouldve tried the bison or salmon burger and skipped the fries Ill head back to Epic before repeating

Author: Keisha S.
Content: Very good burgers

Author: Sollie F.
Content: DMK cooks all of its fries in BEEF FAT without labeling it on the menu  Only found out last night after eating there multiple times when my waitress told me as I ordered the portabello burger  Unacceptable especially for a place that serves veggie burgers

Author: Laura W.
Content: I want to start by saying that I do not give out 5 Star Ratings easily It takes a lot to impress me However my boyfriend and I found ourselves in Chicago after a drive from Milwaukee starving and soon to be late for a show With 20 minutes to grab a bite a man who is a bit picky and Chicago trafficparking I had high planned for the entire night to fall apart DMK Burger Bar saved the entire nightand I am not being dramaticEntering the burger bar I was a bit nervous since it looked quite busy Oh great itll be at least 25 minutes before we even get our food I whispered to my date But we were both very hungry and decided to hope it would all work out We sat at the bar and were greeted by a very knowledgeable and helpful bartender She picked out a cocktail for me which was The Summer Passage DELICIOUS and I told her we were in a hurry She smiled and took our order Me the turkey burger with tomato arugula etc Man a burger with a fried egg guacamole chorizo chipotle aioli and more I cannot remember the creative name  my apologies After we ordered it was less than a five minute wait before our burgers were staring us in the face How phenomenal And let me tell you No pun intended but HOLY COW were they delicious As I was happily working on my phenomenal turkey burger with a homemade bun I glanced at the signs around the bar reading Beer Sno Cone  WHAT I laughed and said out loud Babe Look A beer Sno cone How cool It was one small comment thats made while happily digesting my burger and thought nothing of it That is until I had a man delivering a beer sno cone on the house to my boyfriend and I Say what I was full of smiles Turns out one the thoughtful bartenders overheard my interest and curiosity and had one delivered to us So let me explain that for me to rate a restaurant with 5 stars it must be the whole package Great service phenomenal food and an exciting ambience And allow me to say that if there were more stars I would award them This place has EVERYTHING and even more Keep it up DMK Burger Bar I cannot wait until I am back in Chicago to visit again

Author: Marilyn P.
Content: I went there with a group today for lunch  the burgers were great the service was fast and friendly and the string onions and truffle fries also very tasty I hear that the place can get awfully crowded at times but it was very open for lunch and I would recommend highly

Author: Jake B.
Content: Walking into DMK I wasnt sure if I was eating burgers or sushi  The interior was way more posh than a burger joint should be  Regardless the burgers are very tasty  The hamburger meat itself is fantastic  However the soft buns are unappealing and a pretzel roll would be a much better compliment  They make their own ketchup and this is a good thing as the truffle cream leaves much to be desired  There is a draft beer selection that is lacking in quantity but high in quality and the service was much to be commended  Kumas Corner has set a high standard in Chicago and DMK just missed the bar

Author: Kent S.
Content: If Michael Kornick and David Morton are involved chances are that they will in theory come up with a pretty tasty burger  As the name implies it is a bar which serves burgers  They have a number of interesting beers and hard ciders on tap which all go well with the food  On a Saturday night at least it is a pretty busy scene and as they do not take reservations expect a wait for a table  We ended up waiting only about 20min or so  Compared with the wait at a place like Kumas not badNow to the important stuff  The Burgers  As you may have heard they offer many different incarnations of the burger including turkey lamb and portabello but we were there for the beef baby  My wife ordered the bacon cheddar burger which was delicious  The patty was cooked perfectly given its thickness  Medium well but still juicy  The balsamic glazed red onions gave the burger a wonderful flavor without overpowering the flavor of the beef  I had the green chile and egg burger which was also fantastic  The flavors of the egg and chiles   were a perfect complement to the burger as well  At least for the two we tried they paired the flavors of the toppings exceptionally well  This is what a gourmet burger should be unlike some places which just slap the work Kobe in front of the name and expect people to pay more for that  As for sides the sweet potato fries were very tasty although ours was a bit oversalted  The standard mac and cheese was excellent as well  The price is right and the service friendly  Definitely check it out

Author: Stacy D.
Content: Update  Have been able to go back a few times since the original visit  Great food great atmosphere  Very popular spot so be prepared to wait at key timesI walk by here everyday to get to the el and always think I need to stop and check this place out  So today I was craving a burger and thought Id stop by on my way home to pick up one for take out  I was sadly mistaken to think they had take out  They dont  I was told it might be a possibility at lunchtime when they were less busy but at 6 pm when I walked in they werent even close to busy  I like to support local neighborhood establishments but Im not sure Ill be back anytime soon  Ifwhen I do Ill update my review  My first impression isnt a great one though

Author: robert a.
Content: yummy burgers and incredible sweet potato fries I had the lamb burger I dont like beer but the selection seems vast  Ill definitely return

Author: A A.
Content: DMK Burger Bar is a decent place to grab a burger with friends  Pros I ordered the veggie burger and it was great  I also got the sweet potato fries which were out of this world The rest of the people I went with all ordered regular burgers and said the beef was very good Cons The wait is always longexpect to wait atleast a half hour on weeknights and over an hour on the wkendspersonally i dont think the burgers are worth that long of a wait they dont allow ANY substitutions  I was the only one who liked my burger because the other people i went with wanted to substitute the cheese in the 2 and werent allowed to and lo and behold when they got their burger what did they not like about itthe CHEESE i cant deal with places esp a burger place that doesnt allow any substitutionsits not like its some 5 star fine dining place so i dont get why theyre so anal about substitutions dont think ill go back unless they expand and the wait isnt as long also personally I prefer The Counter because the seating situation is much better and you get to build your own burger

Author: Mag W.
Content: Food  Reasonably priced at 8 for a burger and 5 fries with delicious toppings like Parmesan and truffle cream  I agree with the review below about the veggie burger  its fantasticDrinks  Great beer selection  The best part is that the bartenders arent beer snobs and theyll let you sample just about anything before you order it  Service  Quick and Friendly

Author: William G.
Content: Great atmosphere great food  They have a great beer list and some of the best truffle fries Ive ever had  Would def recommend the bison burger as well

Author: Lanny S.
Content: We were very disappointed in the burgers They were very thin and the toppings were sparse The fries were OK but just OK The value for what you get was poor The pictures on line of what theburgers look like had to be taken at another restaurantLanny

Author: B F.
Content: This tiny burger joint is definitely a hidden gem  My burger was cooked to preference and the toppings were fresh and tasty including the fried egg on top The beer list is decent  I cant wait to get back so I can try a different number on their list

Author: Corey G.
Content: I tried DMK for the first time last night It was great My friend got the peanut butter milkshake To die forthey I think make their peanut butter and it is really something to talk about I should have ordered one it was amazing I got the 4 green chile hatch and made it a turkey burger without the bacon It had a little kick and was totally satisfying Now there is a great debate amongst lovers of french fries like myself Some prefer real cheese others like fake cheddar DMKs cheddar and scallion fries are amazing Real cheddar cheese and the fries are so good cooked just right My party also got the truffle cream and parmesan fries also amazing I used some of the truffle sauce with my turkey burger All in all really great

Author: Mark C.
Content: Dont be afraid to upgrade it to a double the burger size is not overwhelming  Overall really tasty and the best burger bun I have ever had  Only downside is it is quite loud and difficult to converse even at a 2 top

Author: Stephanie S.
Content: The burgers are good they have a lot of options and the service is really quick  But the burgers are way too greasy

Author: Monkey M.
Content: DMK is relatively new in the Lakeview area  It has a great airy atmosphere inside with high ceilings plenty of seating and kept really clean  Choices include a list of specialty burgers which are numbered  You can also go with the plain old cheeseburger if youre not the adventure type  I have tried a select few and all have been great  If you feel like getting really unhealthy you can get a fried egg on any of them  I had never tried this before and wish I hadnt because it was delicious  The best though are their specialty fries with various dips  I really recommend the truffle fries which are unique and rock  Only downside that the burgers are a bit on the smaller side but given most burgers you get other places barely fit on the plate they likely represent a normal human serving size

Author: DeeDee B.
Content: Um Yea I dont like to write bad reviews for any place but this place was just a very very bad experience for me  DMK is probably the most over rated burger joint in the city of Chicago  It really could be a great place but I feel its being done all wrongThe interior is dark unwelcoming pretentious and not cute  The burgers are really bad  I mean REALLY BAD  5 oz patty on a dry ass crusty really disgusting bun  only cooked at medium which isnt true cuz our burgers were well done ugh and are 8 without fries  When I came here with my boyfriend we got 2 well done chewy burgers 2 fries and 2 glasses of water  Our tab was 3000  It was a Tuesday at 6pm the weekday specials are a free order of fries with your burgers between 5pm7pm  We didnt get the special because we didnt ask about it WTF Really  and NONE of the specials were offered to us by the server  I know that theyre trying to upsell but that just pisses off the customer  We left there disappointed and with painful stomach aches for the rest of the nightI will say that the fries are good the staff is very friendly and our server was very nice and attentive tooI really wanted to love this place I did  DMK could really be a cool joint but they just need to do a few things differently  I hate saying this but you could probably get a better burger at McDonalds for much cheaper and without a stomach ache  Well maybe a little stomach ache too lol

Author: Abby R.
Content: Good beer a great burger I had the burger with fried egg bacon and green chilies great fries bacon and blue cheese and great service Safia

Author: Allison B.
Content: LOVE this place 1 is very good and the truffle fries are delicious

Author: Brian T.
Content: Am I missing something here Yeah about half the burger meatThe first thing we noticed instantly was how obscenely loud the music was We looked around to see if there were any tables that werent underneath a speaker no chance They must have bought out best buy My boyfriend is deaf in one ear so we spent the entire meal without conversation What we did say to one another was mostly complaints about how loud it was and that was shoutedI ordered a diet coke 10 turkey burger and shared a plate of Mac n cheese When the CAN of diet coke arrived I knew all was going to go down hill from there I havent been to a burger joint that doesnt offer unlimited refills on soda Second the burger arrives on a small tea cup plate Okay so I thought the burger was going to be so outstanding that I wouldnt care that it was on such a small plate sans fries I lifted up the bun only to find myself thinking Wheres the beef well in my case turkey Thirdly I noticed that the burger was fried Maybe I havent realized that other burger places fry their burgers because the meat patty and buns were exceptionalnot so in this case Small burger big airy tasteless bun I will say one positive about the burgerit wasnt overly stuffed with toppings but the meat should have been a lot more substantialAlso positivethe MnC was passableIve had better but Ive also had much much worseI probably will stick to my favorite joints for burgers next time

Author: Kathryn C.
Content: I was very impressed with DMK  Burgers are a good size not small and not too huge and the fries are fantastic I really like the regular sea salt and pepper fries  The cheddar fries were not all that good because they use the liquid type of cheese rather than actual melted cheddar  Good portion size on the fries too  Quick service and decent prices  If you want to order food to go I suggest going there and waiting rather than calling it in  I tried to call it in once and it was so loud that a I had to scream into the phone so the lady could hear me and 2 my order was not corrrect  It is just too loud for them to hear you on the phone unless you call in very early when they are not busy yet

Author: Collier T.
Content: Best milkshakes everfabulous fries especially the parmesan truffle varietyand well of course the burgers are wonderful The restaurant has a great upbeat atmosphere low key modern chic with an equally energetic and fun wait staffI highly recommend for teenagers and adults

Author: A-train R.
Content: I finally made it 2 the DMK this week I ordered a Bison burger with a fried egg on it  and Wisconsin Cheddar fries My friend had an Original DMK with gravy fries At first i saw my burger and fries and thought  thats it I paid 9 for that then i took a bite from my Bison burger with the added yolk oozing out of it and it took me to another world It was SO good On some days burgers are just burgers unless they are huge then they seem much tastier but this one didnt need to be big to be good it was just damn good Then aside from the food the customer service really did me in There were at least 3 different people who asked if everything was cool but never annoying Also my friend had ordered his burger without onions but they gave him onions Just as he pulled the onions out of his burger our waitress saw and asked if he wanted another one He said it was totally fine hed just pull them out About 3 minutes later one of the servers came out with a side of gravy fries on the house Sometimes you go to a place that you feel really cares about customer servicesatisfaction They dont come around very often especially when they are taverns or burger joints DMK was everything I had heard about and more The only things i would say that may be a little negative about this place is that the portions are small which is something that you dont want if you go to a burger joint but it is well worth the money and also they have an option to double size the burger  The place was small and it was a little cozy but cozy like a place to hang out with friends not really like to take a chick out on a 1st date Also the drinks are a little expensive but they have a good selection of beers although they dont have cheap selections They are all 5 and up and nothing like a miller lite or budweiser to choose from

Author: Matt K.
Content: Burger bars are all the rage and DMK does it really well  Loud atmosphere so tough to hear yourself talk but thats all part of the vibe so be prepared  Went a little off the beaten path and had the salmon burger which had a lot of flavor but it just didnt do it for me and wouldnt recommend But the sweet potato fries were absolutely the best Ive ever had and highly recommend  The fried okra and pickles were also a great surprise and the crispy onions albeit greasy were really good too Great selection of beers and the burgers were solid although not crazy good like Umami in LA or elsewhere but you wont be disappointed

Author: Michelle T.
Content: I still think about this burger and its been months  Had the 4 egg green chiles bacon jack  french fries with the aged cheddar sauce and chives  Unbelievably amazing  The meat was wonderful and juicy and the potato bun was fluffy  And the egg goops out all over it was a mess  An incredibly delicious mess  The aged cheese sauce was also delicious and would have been the star at any other restaurant but the burger won out at this place

Author: Annika v.
Content: The best burgers in town hands down Dont miss the truffle fries If I could eat it everyday without gaining a million pounds I would

Author: gretchen b.
Content: We live in the area and have been meaning to get into DMK as I love me a good burger  Went on a Tuesday night around 745  it was pretty crowded  We waited about 15 minutes  Heres the thing  the place is LOUD  Like you have to speak up just to talk to the person across the table  That is the one major downfall  So I wouldnt take a date or a group  BUT  if youre up for it the food is worth it  Their beer list is great  not the boring norm  I enjoyed a 3 Floyds Gumballhead  Love it  We started out with the deviled eggs 2 for 3 little halves  They were tasty  very creamy  Yum  All the burgers are 8 a la carte with exception of some biggies  I went for 1  bacon BBQ balsamic red onions and cheddar  All burgers come pink in the middle  Perfect  My friend ordered the mac and cheese  Its a giant order and no way you could eat it all  soooo rich and creamy  We split a single order of the cheddar and scallion fries  They were quite awesome  Not sure what was so special but the cheese was glorious  It didnt get all clumpy  Soo goodAll in all a beer soda eggs burger mac cheese  side of fries came to 30  Great deal in my book  I really enjoyed DMK and would go backjust wish theyd turn down the volume a tiny bit

Author: Will M.
Content: Burgers were awesome  I had a number 4 which has an egg and green salsa on it  It was actually pretty spicy  which I like  My wife and I had an argument about the fries  I wanted just the plain ones with salt and pepper  she wanted gravy fries  So the waitress brought us the gravy fries onthehouse We looked on the bill and the line item said 400 for Love  It did take a while to get the bill at the end but since our waitress was so awesome Im gonna let it go this time  Oh forgot to mention the beer selection is great too

Author: Shari M.
Content: DMK is seriously the ultimately COOLEST place to be Just this afternoon i was in for a bite to eat with my friend Jonathan yes THAT hockey hunk and we were saying that DMK is not just a place to get amazing food I challenge anyone to find a better looking staff Bunch of hotties DMK is the totL package Best burgers are just the beginning Today I tasted the most creamy amazing avocado soup I am pescatarian so this is a major excitement for me Also making an amazing debut today was a burstingwithfreshness Gazpacho OMG I didnt think I liked Gazpacho until I had this heavenly masterpiece Seriously I could go on for days but lets talk about the shakes Milk shakesyou say Whats so special AGAIN I challenge anyone on the planet to make a better shake The shakes are super thick and so yummy The peanut butter shake is so out of this world but if you like coffee order the espresso It will blow your mind No really it will  BLOW YOUR MIND If you want the best beer hottest staff and amazing eats come to DMK I will be blogging from the bar downing the soup veggie burger and sweet potato fries Wait did i mention the beer is so awesome and originalTell them your friend Shari sent you Really not to be missed

Author: Michael H.
Content: OVERRATED  I had high hopes for this place given Michael Kourniks rep and the fivestar reviews on Yelp  But I can honestly say this place is so overrated  The beef might be grassfed but it is poor quality and so greasy you will burp it up hours later  The patties are pressed really thin think McDs quarter pounder and tasted like fried on a griddle  no special flavor at all  Trust me you can make better burgers at home on the grill  The fries were good but nothing unique who doesnt sell sweet potato fries or parmesan truffle fries these days  Oh and supergreasy  I really wanted to like this place and gave it the extra star because of its prompt and friendly service  But do yourself a favor  save 20 and skip this place

Author: H R.
Content: Visiting my brother last week who told me about the best burger place around  He had had only heard great things about this place and so we went  We left the restuarnt with him apologizing profusely for taking us here without first eating here first  Good things about the restaurant  fries and gravy you rarely see this anymore no wait the buns onion rings  good beer listBad things Hamburgers service and volumeI love grass fed beef and buy it at home from the local farmers market  It has great flavor and since i am in the red meat capital of the US I expected more basic knowledge  Grass fed beef is leaner than normal beef and thus needs to be cooked rare to medium rare to still be juicy  All 6 of our burgers were overcooked mediummedium well and dry as the sahara  The cheese covered barely half of my burger and i had maybe a  1 12 inch strip of bacon on it Our server couldnt have been ruder  We were talked down to told we could make no substitutions then when she brought 5 burgers for 6 people acted if one of us didnt order dinner  Oddly enough my 12 year old son loved it  Of course his favorite burger is the McDonalds quarter pounder

Author: Hillarie R.
Content: DMK you are all that is right in the burger bar world The blue cheese burger with onion crisps on top with a side of truffle oil fries one of my favorite burger meals in the city BF and I always come here for lunch when he is in town Great beer selection and nice waitresses I have never had that ice cream cookie sandwich thing that looks zomg so good mostly because I insist on eating a plate of mac  cheese meant for 2 but it will make it into my belly next visit Cant wait to try Fish Bar next door but putting them so close together is starting to give me whiplash

Author: k B.
Content: Great burgers and fries and beer  Atmosphere was good  Great selection of some different burgers  I had the bison burger which was great  Their buns are very fresh and soft  Loved that  Got there during happy hour so the fries salt  pepper were free with a burger  Topped it off with a nice cold Crispin on ice  Only weird thingall water came without iceA definite recommend

Author: Brian H.
Content: Great dining experience Food was fresh fast and priced right Great service with nice people Excellent dining experience  I will be back

Author: Claudia R.
Content: Yummy Loud Sometimes long wait  Worth it

Author: James B.
Content: Burgers served on freshmade buns and great extras like onion strings amish blue cheese housemade ketchup etc  Just cant go wrong with the burgers in this place And the fries and housemade ketchup are simply delicious We sat at the bar and were treated very well  The bartender told us about their current promotion to benefit a local charity  Very highquality applepie milkshake YUMMY Go here you wont be sorry

Author: Chris T.
Content: Amazing

Author: Jay G.
Content: We stopped in for a light lunch on Saturday afternoon  The decor is great  Love the vibe in the place  Service was a little slow but adequate  I ordered the fried pickles and okra for an appetizer  I love fried pickles and had never had fried okra  The breading is very good but its hard to tell between the pickles and the okra   The okra was fine but I was looking forward most to the pickles  I think there were one or two pickles in the whole order  The ranch that came with them was pretty standard ranch dip  My wife and I split a burger and fries  We had the number 2 onion strings bleu cheese ketchup and salt and pepper fries  The burger was excellent  The bun was excellent  The fries were very well done fresh cut fries but Ive had better  Neither of us were huge fans of the house ketchup  Overall very satisfying burger and fries  Reasonably priced as well

Author: Mike M.
Content: After having friends rave about DMK since I moved to the city I finally went yesterday during the Bears game  Got two seats at the bar and ordered right away  Ray was very friendly and overheard my friend and I talking about truffle fries we had somewhere previously so he gave us a free order when our meal came out  Later when my friend and I were talking about the beer we were drinking he gave us free samples of beers on tap  Turns out Ray runs the beer program at DMK  It was a great experience and a great meal  To top it off when we paid our bills he gave us free drink tickets for next time we are in  I will definitely be going back to DMK an 8 burger never tasted so good

Author: Lee T.
Content: Meh I could take it or leave it I only give this place 3 stars because our server gave us a card for a free beer on tapI had their 6 burger that had blue brie on it and damn was it a stinky cheese My fault my fault Other than that the burger was alright and the cheddar fries were overly salty Ambiance is nice and the wait staff was just whatever Not super friendly not completely obnoxious I really didnt think she cared about anything ever periodThis place could really up their everything or maybe I just had a bad experience I dont think Ill go back unless Im getting my free beer

Author: Hollie D.
Content: Amazing Love the atmosphere the music and the burgers

Author: Jennifer P.
Content: DMK Burger Bar is DEEEELISSSSSH Its exceptionally yummy and well worth the 45 minute wait My friend and I tried the Chicago favorite tonight for the first time after debating whether or not we wanted to wait almost and hour for a burger and fries Im glad we made the right decision and stayed DMK burger offers more than your traditional burger and fry experience This restaurant offers great food period My friend and I tried the HOLY GUACAOILI burger and it was pretty darn scrumptious My only qualm was the guacomole it is a bet bland similar to that of some concoction of an avocado and water blendweird Other than that everything was AHMAZING The maccheese is brought to the table pipping hot bubbling with gooey parmesean and cheddar cheese The mac  cheese is pretty filling large enough to share We also tried the sweet potato fries which were the best Ive ever had Theyre just right crispy on the outside soft on the inside Additionally the service was awesome Our server was very thorough in explaining the menu options to us She checked on us in a timely manner and made sure everything was going well I give her 2 thumbs upThe only reason why DMK Burger Bar in Lakeview does not get 5 stars is because of their wait DMK does not take reservations and they do not have the space to be super accommodating nor do they try to be The seating area is very congested and awkward

Author: Alisha O.
Content: Everything on their menu is fabulous  although 6 is my favorite burger  Some of my other favorites are their sweet potato fries espresso milk shakes and their fried okra and dill pickles  They have a great beer selection and kids always seem to be welcome  Their burgers are made from grass fed beef and their buns are the best Ive ever had  Very soft with a slightly crisp outer crust but somehow not crusty  Their burgers are always perfectly moist and the amount of toppings always balances the burger just right

Author: Meg M.
Content: Would love to be able to give 5 stars even 10 for the food wowBut if the food is so good what is with all the over the top rediculously  loud music Does DMK pay in advance for all of their employees impending hearing loss Best Veg buger Ive ever had and Ive eaten most of them Thought about bringing ear plugs next time I come but I probably wont be back I like to enjoy the conversation and company of those Im with and there is no way to do that over the noise Has anyone measured the decible level at DMKs

Author: Katie T.
Content: Went here on a double date The burgers are amazing I appreciate that they buy grass fed beef and theyre the perfect size to eat in one sitting I had the number 4 and loved it  They have an excellent beer and cocktail selection as well and the food came really quick considering how packed it was on a Saturday night The only issues I had were the noise extremely loud and our waiter wasnt around a whole lot I had to ask a couple of times to get a refill on my water Would definitely recommend But if you go on the weekend be aware that youll have to wait a while for a table

Author: Andrea W.
Content: This place is 5 stars all the way  The beer selection is awesome and the burgers and fries are even better  Weve tried pretty much everything on the menu and its all fantastic  If its not the best burger joint in town its pretty close  I dont see how anyone can be disappointed with this food

Author: R W.
Content: AMAZING BURGERS AMAZING FRIES I always order the 2 and sweet potato friesMy only complaint is that it gets so busy and you feel like you are sitting right on top of the people next to you

Author: Chad E.
Content: More like 45I refuse to rate a place until Ive been there a number of times and now I feel I can actually give a consistent rating to DMK Ive been there half a dozen times from late afternoon to late evening and with a party of two to six and every single goddamn time the folks at DMK have been amazing Sure sometimes there is a wait and yes burgers dont come out in four minutes and ohmyfuckinglord you cant order your burger to your desired doneness but I honestly dont care at all Their burgers are absolutely delicious without being overthetop and their fries are phenomenal I went after reading about them from Chicago Gluttons and they still have the best review of DMK Ive ever read

Author: Jared B.
Content: Honestly dont like this place You cant make your own burger and its expensive Fries are extra and also expensive The burgers you have to choose from are not my taste I go because other friends want to try it once they find out I live close to it but Ive never enjoyed it The only plus I have is that they serve Floyds Gumball Head Love that beer  Ive had better burgers at Kumas Corner or 5 guys

Author: Leah A.
Content: I am absolutely shocked by the positive reviews of this place I would never go back I took 3 teenage girls for burgers and my bill was 62 Yikes All the food was too salty the place was too dark the place was too noisy and I had to ask every time I wanted a water refillWhile the burgers tasted good they werent worth 62

Author: Daniel G.
Content: Great burgers great beers and very good fries  Word is out though so I would recommend going at a strange time after 9 or before 7  As an example 7PM on a Saturday is usually at least a 45 min wait

Author: Rob M.
Content: Love the foodthe wait not so much Has one of the BEST turkey burgers and bison burgers Ive ever had in my entire life

Author: Anna L.
Content: I am wholeheartedly on the gourmet burger bandwagon DMK knows how to make a darn good sandwichI would try any burger on the menu maybe I should make this a new goal The toppings are homemade unique and most importantly really yummy The best burger Ive had there had chilirubbed onion strings blue cheese and chipotle ketchup The burgers are a good size but not obscene Ive had truffle fries at a few places and the ones here are my favorite Fries arent included with your meal which is odd for a burger place Also they have an interesting beer selectionThe only kind of major complaint is that theres often a long wait to eat here and the bar doesnt accommodate too many people hanging around to wait for a table Also its really noisy

Author: Nimit P.
Content: The Holy GuacAioli Burger and the Chorizo Burger are my favorites Throw in the mac and cheese hand cut fries and anything from their rather generous beer selection and you have burger bliss on the north side Positives are the food service beer selection cozy vibe Negatives are generally long wait times especially on weekends restaurant is small good if you have table not so cool if its busy and sometimes the host can be a bit disorganized The Positives wildly outweigh the negatives at DMK which is become one of our favorite burger spots along with Burger bar on the north side

Author: Christopher C.
Content: Seat me at one of the dozen empty tables while I wait for friends I might even buy more beerThe burger was underwhelming  I love burgers but I dont think that putting it on a Ciabatta roll really counts for anything

Author: Tony S.
Content: I went to this place with my girlfriend on Friday bad idea and it was packed We waited about 30 min to get a table but I was cool with that because I had been there before and wanted to have my gf try it I love the food If you love burgers and fries this is the place to come Not much of a selection of wines but a great selection of beer Ill surely be going back

Author: Erica N.
Content: First and foremost the food here at DMK was pretty amazing my boyfriend got the 1 and we shared an order of the parmesan truffle fries and I ordered the Mac and Cheese 1 The mac and cheese was so good it was perfectly gooey with a really good crust on top and the large fries were plenty for 2 people to share The drinks werent bad either bloody mary was pretty spicy and i got the Strawberry Fields which I admit I wish it was a bigger drink for the 8 price tag but it was good none the lessThe food came out really quick and the waitstaff seemed to be pretty friendly and actually normal its kind of annoying to go into specialty restaurants like this and see big fake boobed girls wearing the lowest cut tshirts possible and dudes in tight muscle shirts For two meals order of fries and two drinks our tab was 40 bucks which I dont think is too shabby Id definitely recommend this place and we plan on going back

Author: Andrew L.
Content: For the second time in a week Ive eaten at a new burger bar and Im 2 for 2 with finding a great burger joint both home and away from home  After some reservations fell through at a certain famous Chicago eating establishment my wife and I were on a mission to find a new place to eat on a Saturday evening with little to no chance of an advanced reservation  Being that we were heading to a concert at The Vic we were pleased to realize that DMK a place wed been wanting to try anyway was located right down the street from the theater  We had about a 3040 minute wait at around 530PM so I can only imagine what the wait would be around 78  Once seated the service was great  Whenever I visit a place that has a great selection of craft beer I feel obligated to mention it and DMK definitely gets points for its terrific selection  As far as the burgers go they do not disappoint  I went with the number one basically a bacon cheddar burger with bbq sauce and onion sans onion and it was great  Perfectly juicy and great quality meat  I dont usually care for a lot of fixings on my burgers so I was happy I didnt have to tell them to hold the lettuce  tomato  such  My wife had a turkey burger which she also thought was great  The parmesan fries were very tasty as well  The only negative was that we were kind of looking forward to having a cookie ice cream sandwich as listed on their website so we were kind of disappointed to find out they no longer offer them  Otherwise well definitely be back

Author: Eldiva S.
Content: They still have it I heart this place they should franchise these out  come to FL please

Author: Happiness L.
Content: What a place  Hurry and try the Girl Scout Mint Cookie Milk shakeso yummy and only there until the end of the month   I ordered the delicious burger of the month topped with duck sausage cheese and onions soaked in something yummyjust forgot was it was   Blue Cheese and bacon fries are rich and okI will try something else next time   In addition to the yummy shake and burger the very best thing was the friendly staff  The girl at the door and Dan at the bar were so kind and attentive   The only recommendation is to offer more seating that is lower rather than higher   Lower tables are in the back just some people either have physical limitations where they can not get up so high or are uncomfortable at a higher level   Offering more lower tables would be beneficial    I am looking forward to coming out again with friends  I was very happy here

Author: Shin M.
Content: I got the Patty Melt Parmesean Fries and a Milkshake Yummy

Author: Alf O.
Content: Trendy ambiance but doesnt take itself to seriously  Good addition to the neighborhood  Food could be a little bit tastier  Best for an early 20s crowd

Author: Peggy G.
Content: DMK makes my favorite burgers in the city   My two favorite burgers are the 1 aged cheddar with bacon and BBQ sauce and the 2 ChiliRubbed Onion Strings Amish Blue Spicy Chiptole Ketchup  I come here just as much for the burgers as I do for the fries  I cant decide which one I love the most the parmesan truffle cream the sweet potato fries with lemon aioli or the blue cheese with smoked bacon fries  I recommend you go with friends and get all three  They have a great beer selection as well  I highly recommend you check it out

Author: Tom M.
Content: DMK is that special type of neighborhood hole in the wall with a subtle facade barley indicating what type of establishment lies inside  After a night of heavy drinking my Wrigleyville crew voted DMK as the best place to cure a hangover with burgers fries and more drinks naturally  Entering DMK you find yourself staring down the type of long retail slot you would see anywhere  Its populated with just enough tables and has one long bar on the side wall  The staff was excellent immediately bringing small glasses of steaming hot turkey chili to try something we were thankful for as it was a biting 25 degrees outside  Our server was helpful very friendly and got drinksfoodrefills out to us promptly  Overall the amenities and staff were excellent  The grub of course is what truly defines any eating establishment  DMK did not disappoint in the slightest  All burgers have multiple elements principally the bun patty and toppings  I got the 6 Chorizo Guacamole Sonoma Jack Chipotle Aioli Cilantro Onions 11  The meat was just the right taste size and flavor  The bread Im guessing they make in house was perfect for a burger  A soft spongy consistency with a niced baked crust that kept the sandwich from becoming a soggy mess like so many other burgers devolve into  The price point is high as 1100 doesnt include fries  DMK is not your everyday indulgence however and should best be saved when youre hosting out of towners or nursing a hangover  Its an indulgence a treat a meal to savor  Ill definitely be coming back to DMK theyve cooked up one Helluva concept

Author: Eric L.
Content: mac and cheese is the best thing here burgers are a 3 fries are a 3  burgers and fries are sooooo easy to do better than a 3 yet the crowds dont demand it so most kitchens dont do awesome toast my bun make my fries come out hot and crisp you know how to do it i undersatnd that its hard to do at volumescale maybe its just not economical to do it right

Author: Nikole H.
Content: Great burgers and onion strings  Sat at bar and service was amazing  Bartender Andrew went out of his way to make sure our first visit was amazing  Thanks

Author: Geoff M.
Content: Kumas for the nonskinny jean crowd with better fries and manageable decibel levels

Author: Jaimie S.
Content: wow  this was the WORST experience I have ever received from a new restaurant  I have been anticipating the opening of DMK for awhile now I live just a few steps away and anxious for a new restaurant to open in the neighborhood  However I will NOT be going back  EVER and we didnt even eatFirst off the owner Michael Kornick is extremely rude and didnt seem to want our business and didnt care when we left  Sadly I will not be visiting his other restaurant MK because of this reason  The atmosphere is very strange  is it a bar restaurant club  The set up doesnt hold very many tables and the bar is really small with an odd counter jetting off the end  I am not sure what the benefit of this is  You may have to eat with strangers because they have huge tables and will fill them up with 2 tops 4 tops etc until the table is filled  As I stated earlier we didnt end up eating because of the horrible treatment we received from the owner  Unfortunately I will never experience the food here  Save yourself a headache and go to The Corner just down the street on Diversey

Author: Robert B.
Content: Lamb burger with greek fixings mmm mmm good

Author: Brianna N.
Content: The huz and I stopped in here yesterday after working up a monstrous appetite post a morning of thrift shopping and bar hopping  We were ravenous  And when I hear the words Burger Bar I envision the wondrous concept at Mandalay Bay in Vegas  huge selction of meats breads accoutrements and friescreate your own dream burger concoction  While this isnt the concept at DMK the chefs have indeed created some remarkably simple and delicious flavor combinations  We shared an order of the parmesancrusted macncheese as an appetizer and it was piping hot and cheesy delicious  I had the 10 turkey burger with swiss arugula tomato and dijonaise and a small order of the sweet potato fries all washed down with an Alagash White  I thought the burger was perfection the fries tasty though its accompanying sauce strange and the beer impeccably cold but small could have sworn it was served in a stemless red wine glass  Alex N a sucker for anything with a fried egg and bacon ordered the 4 and the Wisconsin Cheddar and Scallion friesboth yummy though as Wisconsintes we were in agreement that their cheddar was questionable  Service was okay  The whole place seemed a little too cool for school  Nice beer selection and tasty food would probably bring me back next time Im in the area   Definitely worth a try

Author: Maya J.
Content: I will keep this review plain and simple  The burger was GOOD  The fried pickles and friends were GOOD  The service was EXCELLENT  I am a stickler for good service  I mean I absolutely abhor bad customer service  The place was packed for a rainy and cold Wednesday so we ended up sitting at the bar  The bartender who took care of us was awesome  Again I am a sucker for good service  I will be back

Author: Jeremy K.
Content: Great burgers Reasonably priced Good atmosphere

Author: nate m.
Content: Fantastic burgers slaw fries and frickles And equally fantastic service Recommend

Author: James W.
Content: The food and service were great There burgers and fries are delicious The atmosphere is cool unless loud music bothers you This place is my favorite burger spot in Chicago

Author: Amanda Z.
Content: Went back to DMK on Sat for early dinner around 530p with a big group  half kids half adults  I didnt expect this place to be so packed that early in the evening  However the hostesswaiters were more than happy to accommodate us and quickly so that was great  We had the 4 burger again cuz its just the best thing ever we couldnt resist but we also got the 12 veggie burger which was by far the BEST veggie burger i have EVER eaten  i couldnt believe how tasty it was  The only think i didnt care for too much were the Wisconsin cheddar fries  the cheese was too thick or something it just completely took over the flavor of the fries  The sweet potato fries were yet again sensational  The mac n cheese 1 was a hit with all the kids and pretty good to me too although nothing special Tried a fab hefeweizen at the recommendation of our waitress and loved it  They are always good about recommending beers when youre unfamiliar or indifferent  I will keep coming back to DMK and strongly recommend it to anyone for any occasion

Author: Lauren P.
Content: my favorite burgers in chicago particularly the 5 bison burger with blueberry bbq sauce goat cheese and pickled red onions the truffle fries and Wisconsin cheddar fries are a must there are also tons of delsih beers and sometime if your lucky enough you can get a drink card for a free beer next time your in

Author: Chanel W.
Content: Amazing service and great food  I sat at the bar and the bartender was very attentive and patient He explained the different beers in detail and helped me make a great selection I had the veggie burger and cheddar fries Yummy

Author: Lauren F.
Content: First off they use Grassfed beef which is the only kind I like to eat so points right there I got the 1 with bacon onions bbq sauce and cheese The bacon was well done onions cooked to perfection bbq sauce was not overwhelming and a tad bit if spice The burger was cooked about medium which is what I like but be aware they only cook it this way no special ordering No typical lettuce tomotoes onion on top and it didnt need it Only slight complaint was the bun was a bit soggy but I didnt hold it against them They make their own sodas we got the lime which was really good like a homemade sprite but better We shared 3 small orders of fries which between 2 people was more than enough Parm truffle was rich and yummy sweet potatoes were sweet  crispy and the cheese fries were good but Im not huge fan due to the soggy factor If that wasnt enough we split a chocolate peanut butter cupcake The frosting was so delish not too sweet and had good pb flavor You can tell all of the food is fresh and high qualitya little pricey for burgers and fries 17 per person but totally worth it

Author: Mrs. E.
Content: While the atmosphere was fun and sleek the burgers did not live up to the hype  The flavor combinations are interesting but the burgers themselves were too well done  The fries were good but not notable in any way

Author: Theresa D.
Content: Ive been wanting to check out this place since it opened and finally I did last night  The place was pretty busy and it was st pats weekend so Im not sure how normally busy it was but it was a Saturday night It was about 8pm when we got there and it was about a 30 minute wait for 2 people  We waited by the bar and looked at the decor pretty fancy for a burger bar  The drink menu was pretty great it looked like they had a thing for whisky bourbon rye etc  We waited for maybe 1015 minutes and 2 seats at the bar opened up we took them  I ordered a Crisin Honeycrisp Cider beer  Im weary of cider beers sometimes because they can be too sweet but this was one was delicious and served over ice  And it gave me a buzz fast with a 63 alcohol content  I ordered a turkey burger with swiss arugula and dijoinaise and we ordered the fries with parmesan and truffle cream  The burger melted in my mouth and followed by a fry dipped in truffle cream made my mouth and belly very happy  I really cant wait to check this place out again and try their ice cream sandwiches  Oh and the hostess and bartenders were very nice so good food great decor great service gets this place a 5 star rating from me

Author: k E.
Content: phenomenal sworn service

Author: Jonathan S.
Content: Went back on March 21st with a group of 4 and everything we had was great From the deep fried pickles to the fries to the burgers Service was perfect this timewe drank a lot and she kept us full

Author: Mark G.
