Content: When dining out I think its natural to ask yourself after the meal Was this meal and experience worth my time and money  The answer is no  Obviously everyone has different expectations and will respond differently to any given restaurant but when it comes to going out for a burger there needs to be something special or the value has to be so enticing to cause you to pay for something that you can easily do at home  With the backgrounds and resumes of the chef owner and his coowner I expected they would understand that basic idea and really give the reigning champions of special Chicago burgers  Kumas  a run for their money  Not even close  DMK offers you a 6oz burger for 8  You dont order by temp your burger comes out MW to W  Why My guess is that the pattys too thin for anything else  Options like fries are ala carte  Once you add a small order of fries at 2 you are looking at 10 for a burger  In summary dont waste your time and money going to DMK wondering if youre going to find another option for going out for a great burger  DMK is Five Brothers with higher prices and alcohol  I gave them two stars because Im not too cruel and Im trying to be realistic  Two stars is suppose to be meh Ive expierence better and that seems appropriate  I didnt walk out hating the meal  just didnt like it all that much  It was adequate service was fairly good but the ambiance was a bit ill lame music characterless space with a bunch of cookiecutter white people sitting around  sorry but I could be taken as one of those too sometimes  we could have been sitting in Naperville but maybe thats to be expected in LincolnParkLakeview

Author: Andrea E.
Content: I was really excited to try this place I was surprised how busy it was on a Tuesday night especially since the weather was so sucky One of my friends arrived before me so luckily I did not have to wait to long for a table I got the 3 a burger which has NY Pastrami Grand Cru Gruyere Cheese Sauerkraut and Leroys Remoulade It was very tasty I couldnt really taste the hamburger the pastrami overruled it but it was really good pastrami The burger Patties are thin but I thought the burger was filling We also ordered fries for the table 1 large order of the parm fries with truffle cream and 1 large order of the sweet potato fries cant remember the sauce Both dipping sauces were good but the fries were extremely salty Even my friends who like salt more than I do thought so The rest of the table got another 3 the green chili and bacon burger and the portabella mushroom burger Thumbs up on the green chili burger but my vegetarian friend was not impressed with the portabella burger It is deep fried so most of the time she just tasted grease and breading Just because its not meat doesnt mean you need to deep fry it I bet it would have been a better burger if they just grilled the mushroom The beer selection was good the whole table enjoyed there selections At 58 a bottle I dont think I would have more than 2 beers here Now the service it was pretty slow Waitress would disappear a lot and we had to ask for water I hate that Also I though the water had a weird metallic taste almost like they got it out from a hose outback We were debating having another beer here but the service was so slow we decided to go to another bar instead If service improved and they expanded their menu a bit I would be interested in returning but right now Id rather check out other burger places in the city then come back here

Author: Elizabeth V.
Content: Mediocre burgers at best  I was so hoping for better but didnt get it  The burgers are small not that well seasoned and the toppings are scant  Overall they were dry and we were both still hungry

Author: Kyle D.
Content: I just went to DMK for dinner a few nights ago and I would say it was alright  The menu had some pretty cool choices on it and my choice for the evening was a burger that the server described to me was a reuben on a burger  Although the burger was too small of a portion for 8 dollars it was quite nice  The burgers dont come with a side so I ordered the regular fries and the were cooked and seasoned great and were served with some pretty good house made ketchup  In addition to the fries I also ordered a macaroni and cheese gratin dish with onions  It was nicely cooked but it seemed as though whoever cooked it forgot to add any salt  It tasted completely unseasoned  For my drink I ordered a house made blood orange soda  I sent it back  It didnt really taste like orange soda or really anything else for that matter  It was very bland  I decided to  just stick with water  Overall it was ok but for a burger dinner most people probably dont expect to spend 20 before tip  I am one of those people  I dont think Ill be returning not because I didnt like it but because there are plenty of burger places that are better in Chicago and none of them require 20 bucks to grab some grub

Author: Johnnie F.
Content: Given the look of the website and burgers on same  I expected an experience food service on par with the top burger places in town  Forget it  I sit at the bar and the bartender gives me this look like Im bothering her for sitting at the bar yeah it was 1130  early  but shes the frickin bartender for Gods sake  when she tells me the burgers arent cooked to order  this automatically triggers a red flag  why  It means they are most likely frozen patties  The blue cheese sauce on the burger I had was literally no different than Kens Blue Cheese dressing out of a bottle  and I would have bet money that it in fact was  Fries were boring  every single thing about this place and the staff just spoke that they were more interested in yuckin it up about their Friday night rather than do their jobs well  OH and of COURSE when it came time for me to pay my tab the bartender broad was SUDDENLY all smiles and very nice to me  Jesus  Folks  there are better places to have burgers

Author: Philip P.
Content: DANG MAMA Parmesan truffle fries and a bison burger Yes please Pretty loud but atmosphere has a good vibe and the staff is attentive More than satisfied the bison burger craving we had

Author: John G.
Content: This place is solid  I have been here twice and the second time was definitely better than the first  Crowded but the wait isnt bad and you can grab one of the great craft beers they have on tap while you wait  Had a burger with sauerkraut NY pastrami and an excellent remoulade  My buddy and I shared some sweet potato fries which were solid Also the prices are very very reasonable

Author: David H.
Content: The food and service was great  I enjoyed their selection of items  It is very very very loud but I would go back

Author: Alan R.
Content: Not sure why I didnt give it 5 stars but the food and drinks are awesome Itd be nice if it was bigger but the food is worth waiting for

Author: Joe E.
Content: Every loves a good burger right  DMK is a burger bar that was opened by two great chefs of the city  This restaurant offers not only the grassfed beef burger but also some of the more exotic meats like lamb and bison  I have also heard it has one of the best if not the best veggie burgers in the city  Anyway  I found this restaurant to be more of a gourmet burger bar The toppings are unique organic or both  The price tends to be a little steeper than others with the portions being significantly smaller and the sides at an a la carte price  The atmosphere is definitely fun there is a huge communal bar and a bunch of smaller tables  It always seems very busy even on Tuesday nights there might be a long wait  Overall the burgers are delicious enough to make DMK the talk of the city for a while now but the price and portions are starting to scare people to the other burger joints in Chicago

Author: Donielle M.
Content: Went there last night for the Bears game  Beer was good  I had both of the Pale Ales on tap  Apps were good  We had the fried pickles  However I dont understand how you can be a place that specializes in burgers but only serve them one temperature  medium well  I couldnt eat mine because it was too well done  There explanation was that it was much more efficient to serve them that way  They had a lot of fancy toppings but I would have rather just had the burger the temperature I wanted it

Author: Saahir K.
Content: This place has the rare combination of great service relaxed atmosphere and amazing yet inexpensive food  They serve 8 gourmet burgers and 23 specialty fries with a great beer selection  Although Ive heard its often packed on weekends we didnt have a problem getting a table at 930pm on a Saturday  The waitresses were incredibly nice the atmosphere was fun with music and enthusiastic parties but not too loud or crowded to carry on a conversation  Id highly recommend this place to anyone looking for a great burger and a good time in Chicago

Author: Terry H.
Content: Well at last went to DMK last night for dinner Burgers were great and loved all the sides mac and cheese great  Wait staff was great  We are in our late 60s and do not love sitting on top of the people at the next table and also the noise level is horrible  We had our 20 year old grandson and his date and even they complained about the noise  Does the music have to be that loud

Author: Rach T.
Content: Love Watched Good Burger on tv this morning and had to have a cheeseburger I like the thin patty better than super big Mondo burgers  and their buns are great Only down side is the creamy coleslaw needed salt which is not on the table and they were too busy to flag someone and ask One more con no fountain popno refils

Author: Tom I.
Content: My buddy Drew works here and though I hate to tell him this DMK is a great place with awesome burgers The mac and cheese is ridiculously good and every burger Ive had here has been incredible Great meat quality many great burger choices and they have a decent beer selection My only advice get the fried egg on whatever burger you get makes it so much better Stop in and ask Drew if you can see his unicorn tattoo

Author: John D.
Content: Meh  Nice combinations and decent fries with dipping sauces but these burgers are for teenage girls  They are tiny  That is all I have to say about that

Author: Lisa C.
Content: Best burgers and fries  My favorites are deviled eggs burger with green chilies and truffle fries  They also offer a great variety of beers  There is always a long wait so be prepared  Its totally worth it though

Author: Amanda G.
Content: I just went here and I didnt like it at all The hostess was unorganized and we waited an extra 10 minutes while there were three empty tables one already bussed The waitress was fast but the burgers were thin bland and uninspired I expected more the burgers tasted like decent fast food burgers Id rather have gone to Five Guys The whole place was loud so much that I couldnt hear my companion Overall the whole experience was mediocre and not worth the trip

Author: Lyn B.
Content: I went with my husband for dinner and we sat at the bar  I loved the atmosphere here it was like a really nice bar and grill  Everything we ordered was good  The burgers themselves were outstanding as were the fries  Cant wait to go back

Author: jenni k.
Content: burger and atmosphere were subpar the food waitress didnt even ask how wed like our burgers done boyfriends burger came out pink in the middle but he likes his meat well done the bun oh the bun was really sad it was floppy and couldnt support the burger even though the burger was not big at all our burgers were just average if even that we had the winter greens salad to start and that was a decent salad the atmosphere super loud and so dark you couldnt read the menu tables are wide so if its just two of you you cant hear the other person from the other side of the table especially over the obnoxiously loud music the crowd there is super yuppie and lame

Author: SAW W.
Content: Alright so I am a all American burger lover DMK was recommended by my boss so I had to check it out My boyfriend and I went on a Sunday night and it wasnt crowded but it was full Our waitress was very nice and helpful The atmosphere was more of a sports bar but I was expecting a restaurantgrill environment They have flat screen televisions and a bar I got the regular burger and my boyfriend tried the bison burger We got a side of Parmesan fries The burger was juicy and flavorful however it was very thin Ive had thicker pancakes The bun was awesome It looked big but it was as soft as cake I had a bite of the bison burger and it was okay Im not a fan of the sweet sauce that comes on it The fries were good I love ketchup and they didnt have regular ketchup Their ketchup was spicythat was a negative for me They wont allow any substitutions to their burgers The table next to us was pretty upset about that Overall I would have to say the food was good but it definitely wasnt anything I would brag about Oh yeah prices were average

Author: Leah C.
Content: fried pickles and okrayou must order  you wont regret  promisei cant quite pinpoint what they are battered in  its not your typical onion ring or mozzarella stick coating  its almost pankobreadlike  whatever it is its GOOD and not greasy  oh yeah they serve burgers here too  i enjoyed my vegi burger  it was hearty and of the mushy type not meaty  it was topped with an eggplant slice which complimented it well and was a nice change from your usual tomato slice  husband got a burger with egg and bacon and had nothing bad to say about it  i struggled with the saucer that the burger was served on  it was not a plate but a saucer as in cup and saucer  not sure if they were going for the tapas feel but they really need to be more forgiving with the mess we are sure to makeid like to try the alleged fried green tomato burger that i see on this menu floating around chicagoistcom2009101…  it was not yet available on the actual menu when dining in but the menu did also read something to the extent of please no substitutions while we work out the kinks

Author: Triphena W.
Content: In a nutshell fantastic burgers magnificent french fries Friends and I visited DMK Burger Bar this weekend and everyone agreed this place was excellent The burgers are well conceived and well executed My favorites were the 1 burger with aged cheddar charred balsamic onions bacon and bbq sauce as well as the 4 burger with roasted green chile fried egg bacon and jack cheese I would order either of these again I like the buns DMK uses theyre soft but substantial far from your conventional tasteless spongy buns The burgers arent thick like Kumas Corner but I really enjoyed the crisp exterior achieved on these griddled patties One friend ordered their cheeseburger with an additional patty and was very happy but four of us thought our single patty burgers were nicely balanced between bun meat and toppings We shared 3 large orders of fries and demolished them The Wisconsin cheddar and scallion fries were delicious however the parmesan fries with truffle cream and sweet potato fries with lemon tobasco aioli were phenomenal These fries are probably my favorite fries next to Edzos Burger Shop truffle fries and garlic parsley fries and Longman  Eagles We also ordered the fried okra and fried pickles The batter fell off most of the pieces Skip Saturday afternoon the restaurant was packed and started taking names for seating around 1230pm Despite every table individual tables as well as communal tables being occupied the food came out within minutes of ordering Everyone from families with toddlers to couples to groups of friends were eating at DMK Burger Bar Easy street parking Highly recommend

Author: Deb M.
Content: Great food great service but the music is turned up so loud it is impossible to have any conversation at all with your lunch or dinnermate So go with someone who you dont want to talk to each other  at all Even when the place is not crowded they crank up the music so loud  you cannot converse with the person sitting right across the relatively small table from you When you ask them if they will turn down music slightly I think they actually turn up louder so that does not work

Author: Chuck W.
Content: Food was outstanding but atmosphere was horrible unless you like it loud It was so loud we could hardly hear each other talk

Author: Dan B.
Content: I have been eager to try this place since I first read about it and I was hoping to be blown away Needless to say I wasnt but I did have an enjoyable experience nonetheless The decor is modern and stylish without being over the top The service was fantastic and our waitress even offered a sample of the beer I was considering which is always a nice touch I had the lamb burger which was unique and a great combination of flavors I did think the patty was kinda small for 8 without fries but the beef burger my buddy had seemed bigger so maybe it was just the lamb We split the truffle cream fries and blue cheese bacon fries and both were stellar If I had to choose one condiment for the rest of my life it would be that truffle cream I find myself thinking about it and imagining that earthy creamy amazingness over and over again All in all this is a great addition to the neighborhood and I would definitely return

Author: Izabella d.
Content: this is a hard one folks  as a burger bar it does not shine but i had a great cesar salad amazing french fries and a delicious milk shake my main beef with the burger sorry cant help my love of puns is that the patties are on the small side when i imagine a great burger from a nonfast food joint im thinking thick juicy patty  and here you dont get that you can always order a double  but the 2 patties can never equal the greatness juiciness of one bigger patty we ordered the number 1 double and the greek lamb burger the toppings had nice flavor but it failed to compensate for the patty the parmesan truffle fries were great sweet potato were crispy and served with a citrusy mayo i would come back again  but in times of real burger cravings youll find me at Kumas

Author: andrew c.
Content: Parmesan fries with Truffle cream  Yes please  Walking into DMK Burger Bar the decor was telling me  to expect an aloof hostess to ignore me for 510 minutes then be bothered when I asked for a table for 2  It was quite the opposite I forgot this is not Los Angeles the staff was extremely friendly and we were sat right away  The menu has plenty of options for all different palates and dietary restrictions  Grass fed beef Bison Veggie Salmon Turkey all looked very tempting  As delicately as these burgers were crafted they are quick to make or suggest  substitutions But who am I to tempt fate  I went for the Signature burger no substitutions  Grassfed Beef Aged Cheddar smoked bacon balsamic glazed red onions and secret bbq sauce  My only complaint was the burger was on the smallish side  I could have easily eaten another one  The fries were handcut and masterfully paired with a sauce to compliment their toppings  A well paired IPA the name of which has left me made a great meal

Author: Sarah E.
Content: This was supposed to be a substitute for Kumas since the wait was too long but I had no idea that I would be so disappointed I get the whole 8 hamburger thing since the beef is grass fed etc but I didnt even get to order it medium rare When the hamburger came it was like a thin patty like McDonalds and came with butter pickles iceberg lettuce onions and 2 tomato slices The bun was very flimsy and easily fell apart This was sans ketchup and mustard so I had to wait like 5 minutes to get my condiments In addition to that I had to wait like 10 minutes to get a refill on my drink My boyfriend was not happy with be served a diet coke in a can and then us being charged like 180 If I lived close to this place or was visiting an ailing relative at Masonic I might consider going back but I wouldnt recommend this place to anyone and Im kind of pissed off that someone recommended this to me

Author: Lindsay A.
Content: Went to DMK Burger Bar around 6pm tonight with 5 people  We immediately got seated at sort of a small table for 5 people near the back of the restaurant and got to work looking at the menu  I was with 4 people from new mexico who were dually impressed that there was Roasted Hatch green chile on one of the burgers apparently this is some super authentic stuff  We ordered off the extensive beer menu then turned our sights on the excellent burgers that were zooming past our hungry eyes to nearby tables  I had seen a picture of the veggie burger in my tasting table email and knew I had to have it im a sucker eggplant and this burger has a big ole honkin slice of it right on top of the burger  Boyfriend was pretty miffed that at a BURGER joint they didnt ask him how he wanted his burger cooked and I mean come on that is pretty ridiculous  When he finally got his burger it was WELLLLLL well done im sure thats not how Michael Kornick or Sir David Morton had envisioned their burgers being served If I had ordered an actual burger I would have made sure to mention that i wanted it medium rare but I always do that anyway  The tastes on the Green Chile burger were excellent together very spicy and yummy if only that burger had been cooked right ho boy Ill give them a were two weeks old pass on that  Next time I go in Im deffffffinitely trying on one of the milkshakes which they mix to perfection on a super old milkshake machine  All in all it was a great experience well definitely go back as I imagine this place will keep getting better

Author: Nick C.
Content: My experience at DMK was a very good one I had planned on eating lunch at Kumas that day with my girlfriend and her two sisters but the girls were not ready on time and by the time we arrived at Kumas there was a solid 2 hour wait I brought up the idea of giving DMK a shot it had just opened so I figured there wouldnt be much of a wait not to mention it is only a 5 minute drive from Kuma so we gave it a shot We arrived at DMK and we were seated right away I cannot remember our waitresses name but she was awesome They had a great beer list which she knew inside and out I went with a Russian Imperial Stout that was very good We were trying to figure out which of the fries to order when I cam up with the only logical choice order every one of them and take advantage of the small and large portion sizes and we did All of the fries were very good but the best were either the cheese fries I cant believe it either I usually dont enjoy cheese fries or the sweet potato fries the best sauce was the truffle sauce by far The only fry I wouldnt order again were the blue cheese fries they are very very blue cheesy and a bit overwhelming I only had two or three and they were great but my palate couldnt handle any more than that Now onto the center of attention the burger I went with the classic burger but added a fried egg It was excellent and the bun held up well considering how juicy the burger was  The girls all order more exotic burgers and they all enjoyed them very much DMK is great burger place and I would definitely go back the atmosphere alone makes it worth the trip not to mention the great burgers and fries

Author: Chi N.
Content: seriously amazing are the mac and cheese and the espresso milk shake at DMK

Author: Chris C.
Content: Burgers were good but not great Beer list was very good Nice atmosphere very friendly servers music a bit too loud for conversation with a group

Author: Jen P.
Content: parmesan fries are a must  wait for a table was longso we ate at the bar  bartender was super nice made us a chocolate milkshake on the house    and they sponsor really cool community fundraising activities for different causes  will definitely go back

Author: Gary O.
Content: Ive been here twice now and both times the burger tthe 8 and the cracked sea salt fries were fantastic the food actually seemed better the second time around The waitress tells you that the burgers are served medium slightly pink in the middle When it comes to ground beef I want it cooke mediumwell at the very least dont like undercooked pink ground meat Both trips here I ordered my burged well done and they had no problem cooking it a little long I went on a Saturday night around 7pm so it was a little crowded and I had to wait about 20 minutes for a table but nothing unusual The service is good and the food is great Its probably the best burger Ive had in Chicago I cant compare it to Kumas Korner the place everyone says is the best burger in the world because I have tried to go there twice and didnt feel like waiting But this didnt stop me from writing a review of Kumas so please read that too My one complaint about DMK is that they commit one of my huge pet Peeves and that is serving CANS of Coke instead of a fountain Coke If I wanted to drink a can of Coke I would go to Jewel and buy a 12pack and drink it at home So DMK if youre reading your Yelp reviews PLEASE get a fountain soon Oh yeah they also have a good beer selection Well only six on tap but many different varities in the bottle Its one of the few places that serves Grand Teton Sweetgrass beer which I love Anyway good service a GREAT burger and good beer selection and right next to the Brown Line Wellington stop I will be returning there soon

Author: Nick C.
Content: good burger

Author: Anthony M.
Content: The burger was ok Nothing to rave about I love a good burger but these were just above average

Author: Patrick R.
Content: If I wrote the review right after I went there I would have given it a 4 But since then Ive had better Really its a 3 12 Their fry selection is awesome and their burgers are good  but there are definitely better out there If I lived near here Id be there all the time But its not worth making a trip for Not that Im one of those people that gives bad reviews because some place is far from me But there are places you go to multiple times because its great And there are places you go to multiple times because its good and convenient

Author: johnny b.
Content: good burger but stick to basics

Author: C C.
Content: Good one to try  Yes its trendy these days to make gourmet burgers so thats a little annoying but this restaurant is better than the greyness of the in crowd  Lots of options of burgers of course but also turkey salmon veggie and mushroom options as well as about five types of fries grilled cheeses macs and cheese salads shakes fried okra and other oddities which I appreciate the creative touches  I even had a rhubarb cocktail complete with a spoonful of rhubarb jam on the side I felt like I was in my Grams garden minus one star it was 11overpriced

Author: John R.
Content: Came here on a Friday night in February with a friend Waited about 90 minutes for a table and ended up leaving It wasnt even that busy  I have no problem with waiting Ive been to plenty of places that are more popular and more busy and not had to wait that long ie Chicago Pizza  Oven Grinder Piece The three hostesses looked lost

Author: D P.
Content: Great burger  Juicy with a variety of toppings   Loved the parmesan fries

Author: Brian R.
Content: This place is fine but frankly I dont understand the hype  Everything was good but there was nothing I am clamoring to get back for  Fried okra was ok cheese fries were ok onion rings were good mac and cheese was rather disappointing my burger was decent but not more than that  Try it to check it off your list but dont wait for too long and dont set expectations too high its a decent burger from a bar but not more than that

Author: R. S.
Content: Tonight was my second time eating at DMK Burger Our server was friendly and efficient and also beautiful but dont harass her slimeballs I had the 6 burger it has chorizo and guacamole so I was sold and we shared a side of fried okra and dill pickles I highly recommend the burger my favorite so far Everything was hot and fresh My only complaint is not enough breading on the pickles and okra I love the lightness of the breading but it was missing in several places The Wisconsin cheddar and scallion fries are so yummy and seem to be the most delicious looking of the fries from what I can tell The blueberry and lemon soda was tasty but not enough blueberry flavor The basil pineapple soda I had last time was unbeatable They have an extensive craft beer list and some interesting sodas Overall their food is delicious and thoughtful and the pricing is just right I love that you can get small orders of the fries or a larger order for sharing More places should do this Great service with a smile real ones not fake and annoying and it seems like the staff likes working there Great for a casual date before seeing a show at The Vic I shall return with more friends

Author: cathy c.
Content: Went back again last night had the lamb burger with tsatsiki feta and Greek salad  OMG perfect combo of flavors  And the sweet potato fries were terrific  Cant wait to continue to work my way through the menu

Author: Mikie B.
Content: Not sure this was worth the 45 minute wait The blood orange soda I had while waiting was awesome but as a lot of other people noted all burgers at this burger specialty restaurant come medium well The thin overcooked hamburger patties make DMK rival Steak and Shake and that prettywell ruined it for me

Author: Lizz Y.
Content: Good friendly service amazing parmesan truffle fries and great burgers turkey and beef what more do you need to know btw I like the burger with an egg and green chilies number 4 I think

Author: Tony G.
Content: Finally tried DMK a couple weeks ago and I wasnt disappointed  They have a great beer selection and many different burgers to choose from  I would recommend this spot to anyone looking for a great burger and a beer  I actually liked it so much we got takeout a week later  The number 2 is my fave

Author: Jen H.
Content: I have been wanting to try this place for a long time After finally making it here I was disappointed The burgers were okay but there are so many other burger places in the area The blue cheese fries were pretty good but in my opinion a sandwich should come with a side when you are already paying 8 Next tine I think Ill wait for Kumas

Author: marisa f.
Content: delicious burgers and unique fries  Deserves a great rating

Author: Mary M.
Content: DELICIOUS FOOD I tried every one of the fries over the few times I have been there and the parmesan truffle are my favorite  The guacamole burger is to die for if you like a little bit of spice  The problems with this place is that they do not take reservations and the lines can be very long especially on Friday or Saturday nights  They really could fix that by adding more tables but I guess that is not of their concern  Also we were sitting at the bar drinking while waiting for a table and the bartender politely asked us if we could move so that a couple could eat at the bar  That turned me off a bit  Overall the food is delicious and a musttry for anyone that likes burgers

Author: Mitchell S.
Content: great food awesome service always so so busy but love going here

Author: Rachel N.
Content: I still love DMK Soooo good  every single time I go in or order something togo

Author: genevieve c.
Content: Yum if I lived in chicago I would get so fat with this place around I loved the gaucaioli burger very different I think the chorizo is what makes it so fantastic I also had the portabello and blue brie burger which was also delicious I am not usually a huge burger fan when they put so much stuff on it you cant get it in your mouth but here the bread and topping ratio was just right The fries are also great my favorite was the sweet potato Then they also have a great list of draught beers and some amazing cocktails I didnt even think I liked gin anymore but am now a fan of the bubble gin and madame genevas rhubarb delight It always seems packed in here but I have always sat at the bar and found the bartenders to be very attentive even when it is crazy busy

Author: Anne A.
Content: The food was fine not fabulous However the restaurant was SO LOUD that I couldnt wait to get out of there I had to scream at the person across the table from me until my throat was sore So if you want to chat with someone you havent seen in a while this is NOT the place to go

Author: Brendan F.
Content: This is a really solid spot for such a new place The burgers were great even if they werent temped the sides not as much but ok Nice small production bar selection Im not sure what has yuppie couples bringing young kids and strollers to a bar but be warned this is not a child free zone

Author: Jen W.
Content: Went here on Tuesday night and really loved it  Great atmosphere  love the beer selection and the burgers were really creative and tasty  Price point is perfect too  Will definitely be back  and love that it is in Lincoln Park and not downtown

Author: laura e.
Content: Loved everything here  Big salad has really fresh ingredients beef and turkey burgers are delicious  Shakes are super rich and thick  I will be back for more soon

Author: Jason B.
Content: Great Tasting food Excellent Service Great Beer List all for an affordable price  One of my favorite places in the city

Author: Jeff C.
Content: I have now been to DMK Burger Bar twice  Im going to make a bold statement  This is the BEST burger I have ever had and it is the BEST burger place around  Their fries and the various combinations of toppings for them are absolutely outstanding  The mac n cheese they offer is equally amazing  To top that off they were playing the Beatles the entire time I was there the first time and more excellent music the next  I LOVE THIS PLACE Please do yourself a favor and check this place out  You will LOVE it too

Author: Nick C.
Content: Let me just start by saying I really really wanted to give this place 5 Stars The food at DMK is always great Every burger I have had has exceeded my expectations and the drinks are just as great The Martinis are dangerous in the fact that they are so smooth that you might end up drinking far more than you should have if you have to work the next day Food aside the reasoning for the 4 stars was purely based on the fact that when I was just in there recently unfortunately so was the General Manger From the minute we walked in and sat at the bar he was getting every server there in a tizzy Who stacked these cups  Read the drink recipes Make that again I hate being in an establishment where the micromanaging person in charge creates a bad environment Abrasive management aside the place is amazing even when being ruled by an iron fist Food and service A

Author: Alec T.
Content: This is my first review simply because my experience here was excellent regarding our waitress  I ordered the michelada which was good considering its not a Mexican restaurant  The other person I was with ordered a beer but she forgot to bring it we forgot to remind her about it until she reminded us when she brought the bill  She did not charge us and apologized profusely while giving us both 2 cards good for a free draft beer and let us have a dessert item on the house  It was incredibly kind of her  Oh and the burgers and fries are excellent too

Author: Hilary G.
Content: Went with 2 friends on a Sunday night We had to wait 10 minutes for a table We read the online reviews on here before we went and I have to report that the reveiws were correct it is a little loud in there The burgers were good but not amazing you know I mean Ive had some good burgers and these burgers were mediocre The ideas surrounding them like the toppings and flavors were excellent but the burgers themselvesso so I know I know these burgers are healthier like pasture fed or something of that sort But stillyou get what Im saying I used to live in this neighborhood right by Sheffield and Wellington and I think this place is a little pricey for its location I think you are paying for location not necessarily for food you know I mean Kirkwood is just a few store fronts down and thats a sports bar but they have good beer selection and good food I would sayslightly overpriced for what you yet but definitely okay for a sunday dinner

Author: Vernon P.
Content: Know this going in DMK is more of a upscale bar than a restaurant Lets just call it an upscale bar that happens to sell good food I got there expecting an experience like that of an upscale burger restaurant but instead found myself in the midst of a type of place I was trying not to go to It can be a family oriented establishment in the daytime When I got there it was just before sunset and there were a few families there at the tables enjoying a meal together I was hoping for a better restaurant experience as this place is billed firstly as a burger bar but dont be fooled this place is primarily a bar As for the burgers they were as advertised very tasty The place was packed and if the other reviews are any indication the place is always packed There are better places to get a burger in Chicago but if you are craving some good booze with some really good food then this place is kinda hard to beat

Author: Mike T.
Content: Marinated Portabella Blue Brie Griddled Scallions Dijonnaise with Parmesan Truffle Cream FriesMmmmmm and worth the wait

Author: d b.
Content: Great burgers and inventive french fry options The space was a little tight and I wouldnt go if you want a table without reservations  Its not a sports bar but it has tvs

Author: Fahad A.
Content: Heavenly The Beef patties look smell and taste heavenly

Author: Lulu L.
Content: This flexitarian will be back to get my 3rd burger of the year fairly soon Sorry Mr Cow but you are delicous  I had the plain old burger 8 and my husband got the 4 which ended up being a little too spicy  Truffle fries were ok and cheese fries were too rich Will probably try the sweet potato fries and salt n pepa fries next time

Author: Seth G.
Content: Burger was very good and was a good portion I was not too stuffed to move after eating it but that being said I thought 10 for a burger of that size and no fries is a bit much I had the Parmesan Truffle Cream Fries were also delcious Our waitress was attentive and went out of her way for us So the food and service was good but not for the price My other issue is the pretentiousness of the whole place I hated the atmosphere

Author: Dan K.
Content: The food was modern slightly unexpected fantastic and inexpensive The entire staff was friendly and helpful The 20 something hip professional crowd was delightful as well It is my new favorite restaurant

Author: LeAnn L.
Content: I went at a pretty quiet time and the service was very fast and the burgers were super delicious It is a bit pricey but stay away from extras and you can get out of there on a decent budget

Author: Christine K.
Content: DMK has really great burgers fries macaroni and cheese shakes and last but not least the cocktails  We all really liked everything we tried I think  I can only assume because everything was eaten actual conversation was difficult  Really do we need the music to be that loud in a hamburger bar  Went with my husband 18 year old son and 3 of my sons friends  ALL said it was too loud not hearing that the other people had already said the same thing

Author: Alisha A.
Content: Sides are decent and the toppings for the burger are good  The one area that leaves you wanting more is the actual burger  Its pretty small 6oz by restaurant standards especially if you are going out specifically for a burger  They only offer this one size and one particular way of ordering it  If they want to opt for this churn and burn style they shouldnt be touted as a burger bar  Unless they make these improvements and offer a few more things on the menu I dont see myself or others going there repeatedly  Really sorry to say this as I was so excited for a new hip restaurant in the area

Author: Jeff D.
Content: The blue cheese and bacon fries were amazing  Great beer list  My major complaint is the burger  fantastic creations but not cooked to order  Why waste such wonderful ideas on well done meat  I asked for my burger medium rare and the waitress informed me that all of the burgers are thinner and cooked the same  My burger was tasty but would have been 10x better if it was cooked to order  If I wanted a mediumwell to welldone burger Id go to Five Guys  I expected more from a MortonMK collaboration both amazing restaurants  Unless they change I will be going to The Counter and Rockit where I can get my burger medium rare

Author: Annie H.
Content: Delicious food and excellent service My friend and I loved our own burgers Mine was the hamburger with green chile a fried egg jack cheese and bacon and hers was the lamb burger with the olive tempenade and feta We shared an order of fries with parmesan and truffle butter delicous although we could have done with the smaller portion and been just as satisfied We both appreciated the extensive beer list whats better than a delicous burger with a refreshing beer As a former server I appreciated the attentive and friendly service without feeling as though she was hovering I will definitely go back there to try another burger and the sweet potato fries

Author: Katie L.
Content: My boyfriend and I went her on a weekday night around 830ish I walked into put our name down while he parked the car except I couldnt find a hostess So I walked to the back then back to the front then to the back then to the front again until finally I spotted someone with a clipboard and gave her my name A few min later spots opened up at the bar We sat down and decided to eat there except none of the bartenders acknowledged us So about 8 min later we decided to get up from the bar since we still hadnt been acknowledged Luckily a few min later our table was ready We ordered the 1 and 2 burger the truffle fries and some mac and cheese Everything was good but nothing was as good as I had expected or good enough to go back and risk being ignored again

Author: Carlucci R.
Content: We have been making our way around the city searching for the best burger and DMK has risen to the top of our list We loved this place Went on a Sunday around 3 and it was not too crowded Out waitress was very friendly and knew her stuff The patrons were also very friendly The best part was the food Outstanding burgers The bun alone is to die for but the combination of ingredients is unlike any other I have ever experienced I had burger 1 and would get it again Would like one right now actually And the friesmy eyes roll back just thinking about them Try the sweet potato and the truffle oil parm fries You wont be disappointed

Author: Joe K.
Content: please please trust me when i say thisthis place is NOT like kumasDMK is the opp of Kuma 1 burgers are the bomb they actually taste good      kumas its big ill give them that but its no where near as tasty as   DMKs    pick any burger they all taste great2 plenty choices of beers i suggest you avoid dragons milk even tho the name might tempt you to try it once tastes a bit like irish carbomb w a lot of jameson esp when its not as cold its ok just too strong of a beer for my taste 3 side dishes omg SO GOOD    try their mac and cheese w bacon and grilled onions    fries w blue cheese and bacon truffle friesif you go w a friend order the sides and share you wont regret iti only wish there was another location sometimes parking can be a pain but its def worth trying if you were not a fan of kumas and didnt buy into the hype give DMK a chanceavg tab for burger side and soda will run you a little less than 20 w tipi also suggest you go on a weekday wait will be around 15mins weekends mmm i wouldnt want to find outdont wait 2hrs to eat at kumas   EAT HERE insteadyou wont be dissapointed

Author: Meg K.
Content: The burgers were pretty good as were the deviled eggs appetizer They also have a good beer selection The thing its hard not to compare the DMK and Kumas and Kumas wins hands down For people in Lincoln ParkLakeview DMK is far superior than The Counter on Diversey so if you want to stay in the neighborhood go to DMK If you want to venture away from Lincoln ParkLakeview go to Kumas

Author: E G.
Content: Didnt realize until the burgers came that the server hadnt even asked how wed like them cooked  How is that possible  Of course they were totally well done and not how I and most people would like their burgers  Also the shape of my burger was appalling  It was very thin and in 2 separate small patties that didnt even begin to cover the bun I really couldnt believe it for a place that advertises itsself as a burger joint  On a positive note the fries and mac and cheese were very good but since you go for the burger it gets a low review

Author: Tom B.
Content: I went there early on a Thursday evening 630 and the place was half full I sat at the bar until the person I was there with met me Nice selection of beer Sat down and was promptly served Ordered the number 4  green chile fried egg bacon and pepper jack cheese The burger hit the spot Not too big not too small We also had the sweet potato fries  my favorite because of the spicy aioli that came with it We also tried the Wisconsin cheddar fries which were very good All in all good service good burger happy customer If this was here when I lived in the area Id probably go there once every 2 weeks

Author: Brandon K.
Content: ParmesanTruffle cream fries are delicious and DMK is worth going back to just for those  The burgers were ok but not special definitely better than fast food but not as good as say The Counter

Author: Jaz B.
Content: Delicious Burgers I am not too much of a red meat fan but an occasional burger is always delish I went with a couple of friends and will definitely go back  I had a turkey burger w smoked swiss tomato arugula and dijonnaise with a side of sweet potato fries It was so good very filling the meat was well seasoned and simply amazing  The fries were good that is if you like sweet potatos if not stick to their sea salt and black pepper fries which are delightful  I couldnt resist and had to take a bite of my friends burger she ordered the triple DMK burgerAMAZING Service was great very nice waitress I cannot remember our glasses ever being half empty  The only thing I did not like too much was that we had to sit at the bar since the wait was around 45 minutes to an hour  The place itself is not so big a bit loud be prepared to yell so the waitress can hear youbut the food is so worth it Parking wisetake the train or bring quarters for metered parking Four stars just because I was yelling to order and couldnt really carry on a conversation with my friends since it was so loud  Great burgers you wont be sorry

Author: Tony L.
Content: Great burgers and fries the truffle fries are amazing just like the ones at their higher end restaurant MK  They also have a great selection of beers  My only complaint would be that the music was way too loud I was barely able to hear the people sitting across from me  If your an older person or have a hearing issue your not going to be able to hear a thing  The decor is very simple  All in all though the burgers are great as are the fries and I would for sure go back

Author: Jen C.
Content: Went to DMK on a Sunday afternoon after viewing a football game at a nearby bar  The place was dead  we were surprised after hearing such good things from our friends about the foodbut we were not disappointed with the grub however the atmosphere was lacking  I had the 4 and my husband the 8 both phenomenal with chili rubbed onion straws yum and fries with wisconsin cheddar and scallions fine but would not get again  I am happy to read the other reviews on the website because it sounds like it get busier in the evenings but when we were there I couldnt help but thinking that the atmosphere was aweful and that DMK needed to choose between being a bar and a restaurant to survive  I will look forward to going back one evening for dinner when perhaps the crowd picks the atmosphere up a little bit  although may be then yearning for our slow Sunday afternoon when we could hear each other talk and didnt have to wait for a table   BTW the peanut butter shake is HEAVEN

Author: andrew s.
Content: I moved in around the corner and had read about this place a couple months ago so i decided i would try great beer selection good burgers but they were a thinner style which was not what i was suspecting fries were bomb Verdict they had me a beer and cheese That really all i left remembering

Author: melinda h.
Content: Dmk has the best burgers in chicago and awesome awesome fries especially the sweet potato  Can you just turn down the music  Please

Author: Mary Jo M.
Content: Yum Yum Yum  We went here on a Monday night and had no wait  Service was prompt and friendly  Great selection of craft beers from localregional breweries that you wont find at every place  We tried several of the fries and I had the turkey burger with a Crispin Hard Cider  The bun was amazing the burger was on the thinner side The Mac and Cheese wasnt fabulous but the shakes were  Great selection of classic 70s rock a bit loud but Ill be back

Author: MR. F.
Content: just ok

Author: Reva l.
Content: I really liked this place  It was busy for 530 which is good but seating was cramped since we needed a high chair  The milk shake was wonderful truffle parmesan fries were great burgers and mac and cheese were really good too  My husband was impressed with the beer menu but they didnt have wine  The server was very good with my son  I would go back

Author: Nyuu M.
Content: Great burgers Didnt expect it to be as good as it was The truffel fries and the sweet potato fries were amazing Place is a little small and not many tables but worth the wait

Author: Shayna W.
Content: 1 star off for eating there several times before someone tells me that the fries are cooked in beef fat so a word of warning to all you awesome vegetarians and vegans It would have been 5 because the portobello burger is so delicious that my coworkers are annoyed at how often I want to get lunch from here

Author: Jim M.
Content: Ive gone here a couple time and am a huge fan of their burgers and specialty fries so far The first time I had the BBQ burger and then just recently had the green chili burger with a fried egg and bacon Both were amazing The burger itself isnt thick but it goes well with the toppings and bun which also doesnt dominate the burger The fries were great Eating with friends weve tried them all The Parmesan fries in particular were my favorite The place is not well lit but its setup well and probably doubles as a bar at night We felt a bit rushed eating there since there were people waiting to get seated both time we were there Waitress just brought over the check after we finished eating and didnt ask if we were finished ordering and didnt offer another beer or refills of our water both empty Overall a great place to eat though

Author: loves f.
Content: Burgers are like crack for methis is the best burger I have had since I left LA  Juicy well seasoned DELICIOUS  I didnt want my experience to be over so I ate the second half of my burger slowly  I cant wait to go back there  This is the only place that can rival Juicy Burger  8oz Burger Bar in LA  Yes ive been to Kumas but this is more of my speed not really into to death metal music while I dine

Author: Dave K.
Content: TWO BROTHERS DOMAIN DUPAGE That alone is almost enough for a perfect review But ther burger was a little bit on the small side I got the Santo burger which was topped with Italian beef and mozzarella Delicious The ONLY reason they dont get 5 stars is because I like a big thick meaty burger and DMK wasnt

Author: K L.
Content: Loud and packed be prepared to wait  Great burgers  fries  Not for the health nut

Author: Julie B.
Content: Went here the other night after hearing great things  I thought it was okay nothing special  The bison burger was a little plain and the truffle fries arent cookedtossed in truffle oil they just come with a truffle aioli  My friend said the veggie burger was excellent but next time Im going back to Burger Bar at NorthClybourn which has amazing burgers  And the best truffle fries Ive had in Chi are at Big  LIttles

Author: R J.
Content: The burgers are OK  The fries are good  I expected higher quality and more quantity for the price  I prefer 5 Guys

Author: Steve L.
Content: The burgers were just ok for a burger bar Selection was so so as well There are too many good burger spots to go to wouldnt wait for a table here again

Author: Sean C.
Content: Love the sweet potato fries  Burgers are great  You can really tell the difference when you eat grass fed beef  The restaurant does get quite loud though  Usually have to get takeout because we have small children  Great spot

Author: Wyatt H.
Content: The food is phenomenal and the fries are incredible as well Even the items that sound questionable like the bison burger comes with pickled red onions goat cheese and blueberry bbq sauce are incredible Im convinced pretty much anything on the list is at least good i hear the veggie is fire All their specialty fries are tasty and they have some killer sweet potato fries The  beer selection is pretty good I wish they had more drafts but the quality of selection compensates for the lack of quantity The service here is absolutely wonderful and generous As a matter of a fact the reason why I got to try the bison burger was because I had expressed how interested yet hesitant I was about the meal I ended up ordering the 1 instead and she brought it out to us anyhow on the house That servers name was Austen and she was such a nice girl I also had another server recently named Kelly who noticed it was my birthday and gifted me a beer The service here is great and the food is right up there with the service This place serves up the best burgers in Lakeview Do not sleep on DMK youre missing out

Author: Jennifer B.
Content: The staff is great and the burgers are excellent  Great beer list and the mac and cheese is TO DIE FOR  Awesome place

Author: Alexander E.
Content: Easily one of the best Burgers in the city of Chicago I have tried many places and this was by far the best The burgers are huge and will fill you up I also had gotten the hand cut fries which were amazing The food is why I am giving this place 4 stars The only reason I did not give it 5 stars was because of the loud music which makes it had to have a conversation Other than that they have an extensive beer list and great service I recommend that everyone go here and try out their burgers You will not be disappointed

Author: Courtney B.
Content: I was seated right away even though it looked like there might be a wait They really cram people in I had about a 7 inch space to suck it in and slide in between two small tables to sit in the booth side of the tables that were all lined up next to each other So if youre looking for privacy forget it I heard every word of both conversations of the tables next to me But its quaint I liked how simple and straight forward the menu was  Each burger has a number  1  13 no substitutions Each one has different ingredients And each one is 8 Fries are extra but these arent just ordinary fries Were talking parmesan truffle fries sweet potato fries sea salt and pepper fries or bacon  blue cheese fries  You can order a small or a group order I thought a small would have been fine to split between 2 people The larger order will have you just waiting for a gripper I had a 13 which was a portabella burger meatless with arugula horseradish and marinated tomatoes It was light and lovely although I wish I had known the mushroom came fried I would have preferred to have it grilled but then theres that no substitutions rule posted on the menu Maybe after they get their feet wet theyll be able to handle someone asking for a change They have a nice beer selection as well The food came out quickly Our bill for 3 beers 2 burgers and 2 small fries was 48 So not cheap but not just ordinary burgers either Id like to try some of their other selections another time They had some coming soom items listed that had me curious and interested Very nice staff and comment cards to boot Good neighborhood addition

Author: michael b.
Content: tastier burgers than kumas with better service similar prices and more innovative menu

Author: Jill G.
Content: Went today for lunch and loved every bite  We got the 1 and 2  1 had carmelized onions bacon aged cheddar and BBQ and was amazing  2 had onion strings and amish blue  Both were so delicious that we could not decide which one we liked better  The burger was the perfect size  not too big but not small either  Buns were super tasty too  With our burgers we ordered the sweet potato fries and the truffle parmesan fries  They  brought us the salt  pepper fries on accident  but we didnt say anything bc those looked so good and I secretly wanted my husband to order those anyway  The fries were good but a little too salty for us and I have had better sweet potato fries  Not bad by any means but well try the other types of fries next time   We wanted to try dessert but were too full so next time well try to go in hungrier   Will definitely be back to this place  Staff was super friendly too  always a plus  We thought the value was great too  burgers were only 8 and small order of fries which is plenty was only 2 or 3

Author: Kathleen B.
Content: My husband and I had dinner here for the second time last night  Wed originally visited the week DMK first opened and we really enjoyed it then but our second visit was absolutely fantastic  My husband had 2 burger with fried onion strings blue cheese and spicy ketchup I had the 7 burger with grilled portabello mushrooms blue cheese and dijonaisse and we both ordered fries salads and drinks  Our total bill was only around 50  For a fanastic dinner for two with drinks that is a very reasonable price as wed spent 60 at the Mayan Palace the night before and the quality of food at DMK is much better  My husbands only small complaint was that he ordered the greek salad and while the menu indicated it would have olives the salad that was served to him had none  Id highly recommend a visit to this place if youre a burger fan and if youre trying to eat healthy they serve turkey burgers as well  While its a little loud and you might have to wait it will definitely be worth your time

Author: Dan L.
Content: DMK Burger Bar was excellent  Everything from the interior style music and environment to the wait staff and management to of course the delicious food  I tried a couple things last night and each one was well done  The onion strings were very peppery but in no way over powering  Those came with a simple tangy ketchup that complimented the pepper very well  The parmesan and and truffle cream fries were spectacular  The fries themselves were fried perfectly and you could truly enjoy the quality potatoes  The truffle cream that accompanied it was not too strong and was the right amount of punch  I definitely recommend burger 4  a beef burger with green chiles a fried egg jack cheese a smoked bacon  I wouldnt have changed one thing about the burger and I usually hate the buns that burger restaurants have  To finish the night I tried the vanilla bean milkshake which even though I was stuffed was too enjoyable to pass up  You could taste real vanilla and the milkshake itself was crafted to perfection  In addition to all of this DMK is a great spot for a beer as they have a truly great selection  Stop in a try the Scotch Ale that they have right now great for a wintery night  I cant wait to go back and I recommend it to everyone

Author: Ann B.
Content: I got there around 8 on a Friday night it was crowded and noisy The hostess said the wait would be 2025 minutes and she would find me when my table was ready I went to the far end of the bar ordered a beer and waited After about 30 min I went to check and she said there were still a few names ahead of my party of 2 Very good the place was thinning out should be any time I thought After about 20 addl minutes of waiting I went up again and gave her my name  Oh I sent my manager to find you and we thought you left Funny I didnt tell her I was leaving when I checked on my table just shortly prior to that  My name was crossed and they had moved on  She got the manager some 30 year old jackass who said he looked for me based on a visual description by the hostess I explained the situation to him how I had only moved from my spot at the end of the bar twice both to go to the hostess After a halfass apology he showed us a seat in the middle of a community table right between 2 larger groups I had noticed this spot about 30 min prior and told him so He said Ive already apologized 6 times you can either sit down here or leave and I can try to make this more pleasant he sure didnt sound pleasant or like he was trying to recover poor customer service I figured I couldnt give the place a bad review without trying the food The manager never came back to see how things were we got sent complimentary deviled eggs and onion straws a lovely 7 value  They were ok My BBQ burger was thin on a boring bun The fries were ok  Probably the best thing was the spicy onion strawsI wont be going back I recommend the counter on diversey instead
